@1694 = ~[ARAN] Great way to make me feel better, eh? Jan has an immunity to fear, on account o' he can't take th' time away from thinkin' which story he be about to relate to th' current situation.~
@1695 = ~[ARAN] Great way to make me feel better, eh? Besides, Imoen don't look so calm an' collected to me.~
@1696 = ~[ARAN] Great way to make me feel better, eh? HaerDalis has seen worse things than th' Underdark, I wager. I heard he had a role in a play in Westhoff called "Deep Desires And Passions". Th' reviews on that say he already lived through at least two o' th' nine planes o' hells.~
@1697 = ~[ARAN] Great way to make me feel better, eh? Edwin's overweenin' pride wouldn't let him admit he was scared, nohow. At least, not where I could hear it.~
@1698 = ~[ARAN] Great way to make me feel better, eh? Anomen is just too stupid to be scared. Besides, all that cleanin' his armor every five minutes kind o' distracts him from th' bigger picture.~
@1699 = ~[ARAN] Great way to make me feel better, eh? Cernd sees all this as a balancing act. Me, I prefer th' scales tipped in my direction, thank you very much.~
@1700 = ~[ARAN] Great way to make me feel better, eh? Yoshimo as done some scary things in his life, mayhap worse than I ever heard tell. Me, I am just hopin' this is a really bad dream spawned by eatin' too much curry.~
@1701 = ~[ARAN] I don't know why I started talkin' anyways. Look, don't mind me. I just need a change of pace. An' we need to GET TH' NINE HELLS OUT O' THIS BLIGHTED PLACE.~
@1702 = ~[ARAN] I wasn't blighted well keepin' tally, eh?~
@1703 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then.~
@1704 = ~[ARAN] Hey! Cyric's Buttocks, you traitorous wench... I'll not go wi' out a fight...~
@1705 = ~Whitehand Left for Waterdeep

I sent Aran Whitehand away permanently. He decided to head north to Waterdeep to pursue his own goals. I think that is for the best.~
@1706 = ~Whitehand Sent to the Gods

I destroyed Aran Whitehand. It is good to know that I have the power of life and death at my fingertips, and the will to use that power for my own ends.~
@1707 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands. Hopefully, he will find a good place to wait, and be there when I return.~
@1708 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, bothering the patrons of The Broken Sword. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1709 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, singing sea chanties and holding drinking contests in The Sea's Bounty. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1710 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, wandering around and getting into trouble at The Copper Coronet. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1711 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, staring at actresses in The Five Flagons. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1712 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, grimacing at the bills and sharpening his quill in my stronghold at the Five Flagons. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1713 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, eyeing the cook's larder at The Mithrest Inn. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1714 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, perusing the wares at the Imnesvale Inn in the Umar Hills. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1715 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, drinking swill at The Vulgar Monkey. Hopefully, he will be there when I return. Even more hopefully, he will have avoided behaving like the inn's namesake.~
@1716 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, listening to the bards at Vyatri's Pub in Trademeet. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1717 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, making smalltalk with the staff of The Den of the Seven Vales. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1718 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, gambling with anyone who will play at Calbor's Inn in the Bridge District. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1719 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, drinking the second-rate stock at The Crooked Crane. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1720 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, singing bawdy songs with the patrons of the only inn in Brynnlaw. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@1721 = ~[ARAN] I'll not go wi' out a fight! ~
@1722 = ~[ARAN] No, no, nothin' like that. I was just observin' is all. I did notice, though...~
@1723 = ~[ARAN] Sorry. Trade-speak. What do you want to know?~
@1724 = ~[PC] What is a 'sword', the way you used the word?~
@1725 = ~[PC] What is a 'knife', the way you used the word?~
@1726 = ~[PC] What is a 'stave', the way you used the word?~
@1727 = ~[PC] What is a 'wand' the way you used the word?~
@1728 = ~[PC] What is a 'pen', the way you used the word?~
@1729 = ~[PC] What is a 'fist', the way you used the word?~
@1730 = ~[PC] Well, what do you call Bards and entertainers? 'Harps'?~
@1731 = ~[PC] You know, I don't think I want to talk on and on about this. I'll figure it out as we go.~
@1732 = ~[PC] Got it. I have enough information to figure out what you are saying.~
@1733 = ~[ARAN] Well, I never did have no trouble before. 'Cept one time. I don't rightly hold with slavery. That one's a deal-breaker. Just thought I oughta let you know.~
@1734 = ~[PC] I didn't quite get all the terms you just used. I want to ask about... what was it? Pen? Sword, Knife? Something like that?~
@1735 = ~[PC] I prefer less talk and more action, Aran.~
@1736 = ~[PC] Do you always start conversations this way? I would think that you were more of the tall, dark, handsome, and silent type.~
@1737 = ~[PC] It is all right. A little trail talk is fine with me. We need to do something besides slaughter monsters, after all.~
@1738 = ~[ARAN] Th' whole trade talk thing changes a bit if you head south or north o' th 'Coast, but from Waterdeep to th' border o' Amn, most people use th' same basic terms.~
@1739 = ~[ARAN] I know I speak right strange. I write much better than I speak, though. Otherwise, there'd be naught in th' way o' work for me, eh?~
@1740 = ~[ARAN] O' course, there be crazier ways o' talkin' than this. I done heard two Rashemi merchants babble on for an hour, an' didn't understand more than one word.~
@1741 = ~[ARAN] I tried awhile back to get my speech cleaned up right proper. I even took lessons. But somehow, th' lessons... well, let's just say I had a right pretty teacher. My mind didn't stay on th' lessons long.~
@1742 = ~[ARAN] Now, listen to me, all babblin' like a drunken Luscan. Well, it passes th' time, they say.~
@1743 = ~[ARAN] O' course, if I be talkin' too much, you can always tell me to shut up, eh?~
@1744 = ~[ARAN] I wonder what they use for trade-speak in Moonshae. I did get some right strange looks when I was out there.~
@1745 = ~[ARAN] I spent a little time in Calimport, an' they got their own names for all of these things. I can't rightly pronounce any o' them, though, on account o' they sound more like garglin' sand than real talk.~
@1746 = ~[ARAN] Th' Flamin' Fist uses some o' this on account o' havin' so many local recruits. But mostly, they just use straight Common. You don't get too far yellin' "Staves Forward!" when most people have to ask what that means.~
@1747 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap there be easier ways o' sayin' this, but th' more I travel, th' more ways o' sayin' th same thing seem to show up.~
@1748 = ~[ARAN] There be lots o' wild things in Thieves Cant, but there be little overlap. Not that I'd know much about th' Cant, mind you.~
@1749 = ~[ARAN] I had me a mite bit o' trouble first time I got to th' Dale lands. They use a bit different trade-speak, an' some o' th' words we use are considered an insult. A word to th' wise... don't be callin' a Dale wizard a 'wand'. They get downright testy.~
@1750 = ~[ARAN] Sometimes I think all this would be a bit easier if everyone used th' same words for th' same things. But then again, a decent inn by th' docks in any given town might have a hundred languages among only fifty patrons, so it just goes to show how we like to make life complicated, eh?~
@1751 = ~[ARAN] You should hear some o' this talk among th' new hires. They start usin' it wi' everyone, to sow they are part o' th' team. O' course, that backfires a bit, usually. Marks 'em as green.~
@1752 = ~[ARAN] Now I don't say yea or nay to that, on account o' loose lips might get me in a mite bit o' trouble. No sense gettin' anyone upset, even accidentally.~
@1753 = ~[ARAN] Anythin' else you want to clear up? Gotta know the folks you are fightin' along side, to be safe.~
@1754 = ~[PC] Yes. I still don't quite get all the terms you just used. I want to ask about another one.~
@1755 = ~[PC] No, I think I have the basics. I think we need to move on.~
@1756 = ~[PC] It seems like you talk a lot.~
@1757 = ~[PC] We could get some things straight about what my being a Heartwarder of Sune means.~
@1758 = ~[ARAN] I thought that meant you might decide on some alternate sleepin' arrangements, mayhap get right friendly, eh?~
@1759 = ~[PC] (Sigh) Yes, yes... all of Sune's followers are very easy, just like every follower of Torm beats things with a mailed fist evenly on all sides, and all halflings steal... you have much to learn about Sune, Aran.~
@1760 = ~[PC] Well, good thing we can clear this up, then. Following Sune means I choose whom, when, where, and under what conditions. I do not pay for your services by sleeping with you.~
@1761 = ~[PC] Perhaps. If it pleases me, and pleases Sune. Until then, keep to your job, and keep your hands to yourself.~
@1762 = ~[PC] Ignorance like that will get you killed, sellsword.~
@1763 = ~[PC] Well good thing we can clear this up, then. Following Sune means I choose whom, when, where, and under what conditions. I do not pay for your services by sleeping with you.~
@1764 = ~[ARAN] Right, sorry about that. Rough trade, not much in th' way o' education on Sune here. I do rightly apologize.~
@1765 = ~[ARAN] Now, you know I be jokin'! I would have naught in th' way o' spellcraft if I really meant any o' it. Sune grants where beauty be appreciated, not where ignorance an' lust be appreciated. Shar's Spit, I'm no sensate.~
@1766 = ~[ARAN] Fighters, muscle, shield wall, th' whole physical group. What I do. Look for new things, meet 'em, an' usually kill 'em.~
@1767 = ~[PC] I understand. That is a colorful way of putting it.~
@1768 = ~[PC] Ah. The spear and gear carriers. I understand.~
@1769 = ~[PC] Ah. I prefer stealth and subtlety. But fighters can be important, at least as a distraction.~
@1770 = ~[PC] Ah. I prefer performance art of a less physical nature, myself.~
@1771 = ~[PC] Ah. I might just fit into that category myself.~
@1772 = ~[ARAN] Someone to look for traps an' scout ahead. You have to watch Knives, though. Most o' the ones I know are Guild, an' they won't steal from you while on the trail. But in town, a mark's a mark.~
@1773 = ~[PC] Ah. The sticky fingered kleptomaniacal maniacs who keep trying to steal my purse every time I get a drink. I call them bureaucrats.~
@1774 = ~[PC] Interesting observation.~
@1775 = ~[ARAN] Clerics, healers, do-gooders or sometimes do-badders that can back you up an' heal your wounds. I've known some right good ones in my time, for sure.~
@1776 = ~[PC] I understand.~
@1777 = ~[PC] Ah. I understand. Useful to have around, I agree.~
@1778 = ~[PC] I prefer not to have religious zealots around if I can help it. That is why healing potions were invented.~
@1779 = ~[ARAN] Spellslingers, casters, magicians, illusionists. The ones Swords have to protect first, last, an' foremost.~
@1780 = ~[PC] I understand. This is as awkward as Thieves Cant, or so I have heard... not that I know it myself, or anything.~
@1781 = ~[PC] I prefer to let them become arrow holders, myself. It keeps them from complaining and buying expensive spell components.~
@1782 = ~[PC] Very useful to have a few of those around, I agree.~
@1783 = ~[ARAN] Scribes, to write up the contracts, do the accounts, run the numbers, keep track o' things. I do that, too. Makes me useful, as I cover two positions on the Coster expeditions; three if you count wagon driver.~
@1784 = ~[PC] I have some experience with scribing, myself.~
@1785 = ~[PC] Hmmm. Perhaps I will talk to you later about scroll creation. You might be handy after all.~
@1786 = ~[PC] Oh. I have seen them before. Usually they stick to the backs of shops and avoid eye contact.~
@1787 = ~[PC] I never bothered with all that inky mess.~
@1788 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, a Fist is what you want when you be "punchin' to Calimport" . You know, travelin' to your next tradin' destination. You want to have all your bases covered, right, on account o' not knowin' what Faerun is goin' to throw at you, or what th' gods are goin' to send your way. So you get all set up wi' all your needs filled - Sword, Knife, Stave, Wand, an' Pen. You miss a finger, an' your Fist is likely as not to end up in a mite bit o' trouble.~
@1789 = ~[ARAN] We don't rightly call bards nothin'. We pray to the gods that there is one headed our way, an' ask politely if they will join us travellin'. Bard's a rare thing, brings in business, an' makes long travel bearable. I heard of some what hire on as Pen, but that don't work so well - they can write beautifully, but trade contract's not rightly meant to be pretty, just tight and tough to wriggle out of.~
@1790 = ~[ARAN] Profit always has cost, though... never knew a Bard what wasn't half Knife an' half Wand. An' when they move on, you got to look careful at the inventory, so as to chalk up what vanishes. But it be worth the price every single time. The power o' song seems to beat sword, pen, staff, wand, an' knife all together.~
@1791 = ~[PC] Well, that is nice to hear... I think.~
@1792 = ~[PC] You do know I am a bard, right?~
@1793 = ~[PC] I understand. Colorful turns of phrase.~
@1794 = ~[PC] Well, I call bards a waste of a good thief. They talk too much, drink too much, and always seem to be getting themselves and everyone around them into trouble.~
@1795 = ~[ARAN] Got it. I've a bit o' a habit o' ramblin' on an' on, you know. Sorry. Fills th' time, it does.~
@1796 = ~[PC] I still don't quite get all the terms you just used. I want to ask about one.~
@1797 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I do speak a mite bit strange, at times. What do you want to know?~
@1798 = ~[ARAN] Well, I like to break up the boredom a bit. But I'm no bard. An' just so's we are on the same page, <CHARNAME>, you are right good lookin', but I prefer the ladies.~
@1799 = ~[PC] Well, perhaps I can change your mind about that.~
@1800 = ~[PC] Fair enough. So the 'look but don't touch' rule applies.~
@1801 = ~[PC] You used some terms back there I didn't get. Some definitions? Because I really didn't understand you.~
@1802 = ~[PC] A pity. But then again, it really isn't a choice type of thing, is it. At least we can hit the bars together and not be poaching each other's territory.~
@1803 = ~[PC] You are a bit full of yourself, aren't you?~
@1804 = ~[PC] Watch it, sellsword - you made a big assumption there.~
@1805 = ~[ARAN] Most times, I keep to myself. And you are not so bad yourself, <CHARNAME>. Kinda easy on the eyes.~
@1806 = ~[PC] Let's keep the eyes on the road, and the hands away from me, boyo. Don't get ahead of yourself.~
@1807 = ~[PC] I'm flattered. I think.~
@1808 = ~[PC] You are no so bad yourself.~
@1809 = ~[PC] Keep it professional, Aran. I didn't hire you as eye-candy. And if that was an attempt at flirting, you are on dangerous ground.~
@1810 = ~[PC] Watch it, sellsword. I have killed men for saying less.~
@1811 = ~[ARAN] (Flushes burgundy) Aye, then. Didn't mean to be so forward. Shuttin' up.~
@1812 = ~[ARAN] Time to get movin' again, eh? Don't you be worryin'. I may talk a good bit, but I fight well enough to make up for it. I hope.~
@1813 = ~[ARAN] Well, now. Whether we are doin' well or naught but fallin' apart, there is always good reason to have a Shield Wall up front.~
@1814 = ~[PC] What is a shield wall?~
@1815 = ~[PC] I'm familiar with the concept. That's why I have you as a meat-shield.~
@1816 = ~[PC] We really do not have the coin to spare for things like that.~
@1817 = ~[PC] You might be right.~
@1818 = ~[PC] Are you sure you want more competition? I mean, all those extra swords about might make you less useful to me.~
@1819 = ~[PC] Are you sure you want more competition? I mean, all those extra choices... I might be tempted.~
@1820 = ~[ARAN] Aye, true enough. The whole concept works best on foes what swarm, like gibberlings, orcs, an' the like. But it does work just the same when the wall is strong, an' lucky... it sops up spells an' keeps th' archers an' spellcasters safe for their big attacks. But it be true that bein' on the wall's a mite dangerous.~
@1821 = ~[PC] I see no reason to spend more coin for living shields, but thank you for the input.~
@1822 = ~[PC] That 'shield wall' is a good idea, Aran. I'll see what I can do.~
@1823 = ~[PC] Dense, thick, slow, distracting, catches spells, first up to die... I have a 'shield wall'. Just make sure you know your place in combat, sellsword.~
@1824 = ~[PC] I suspect it works better with big mercenary companies in pitched battle. We don't have that kind of fighting here.~
@1825 = ~[PC] I have big strong you to protect me, Aran. You are enough.~
@1826 = ~[PC] When did I give you the idea I wanted more protection?~
@1827 = ~[ARAN] If I can't hold my own against the rest, <CHARNAME>, I don't deserve you nohow. But I am thinkin' how best to protect you, anyways. Shield walls work great for holdin' back the opposition.~
@1828 = ~[ARAN] If I can't hold my own against the rest, <CHARNAME>, I don't deserve th' space in th' party. I say bring 'em on, an' I'll take all comers.~
@1829 = ~[ARAN] Aye, <CHARNAME>, it does cause a man to think. An' evaluate, too. But that's naught here nor there, really. I'd be standin' on th' wall whether I was cleric or cook. But it can come in right handy to have a god watchin' your back, you know.~
@1830 = ~[PC] We are doing well enough. I don't think we need to continue this discussion.~
@1831 = ~[ARAN] I did see one time a Wall fail miserably, as an illusionist got workin' so the swords thought their friends was enemies. An' I did see one time where someone cast a spell what made most o' the Wall flee in terror. But then again, most o' the time, I've seen it work right smart against some pretty tough foes.~
@1832 = ~[PC] Any other weaknesses?~
@1833 = ~[PC] That is enough analysis.~
@1834 = ~[PC] Do you have lots of these stories?~
@1835 = ~[PC] I have had enough of your stories. Do the world a favor, and shut up.~
@1836 = ~[ARAN] Just a suggestion, you know. Tymora's Fickle Fingers, it'd be nice to have some more help, is all.~
@1837 = ~[ARAN] No, really? That was you? Well, go figure. I wanted to get in on a bit of action, and I had to pick you of all people.~
@1838 = ~[PC] That sounds a bit offensive. Me of all people?~
@1839 = ~[PC] The less said about the past, the brighter your future will be. And longer, too.~
@1840 = ~[PC] We did well by defeating Sarevok and his machinations. I am proud of what we accomplished.~
@1841 = ~[PC] I have had enough of this discussion. No more talking.~
@1842 = ~[PC] So, why did you decide to leave the Fist? It seems like it would be a good job.~
@1843 = ~[ARAN] Well now. Last I heard, the <CHARNAME> they were talkin' about had a smile what could melt the Spine o' the World. So it can't be you, nohow.~
@1844 = ~[PC] Hey, watch it, sellsword - that was me!~
@1845 = ~[PC] It is none of your business, anyways. Hey, you have not told me about deciding to leave the Fist. Why did you leave?~
@1846 = ~[ARAN] Well now. Last I heard, the <CHARNAME> they were talkin' about could lift a catapult in one hand, an' a house in the other. So it can't be you, nohow.~
@1847 = ~[PC] Defeating Sarevok and his machinations helped a lot of people. It was not all brute strength, you know.~
@1848 = ~[ARAN] Well now. Last I heard, the <CHARNAME> they were talkin' about could pick a fruitfly out o' the air an' tie his legs in a knot, while balancin' on one foot. So it can't be you, nohow.~
@1849 = ~[PC] Defeating Sarevok and his machinations helped a lot of people. It was not all speed and dexterous action, you know.~
@1850 = ~[ARAN] Well now. Last I heard, the <CHARNAME> they were talkin' about shrugged off dragonfire while drinkin' acid, with no ill effects. So it can't be you, nohow.~
@1851 = ~[PC] Defeating Sarevok and his machinations helped a lot of people. It was not all inner strength and toughness, you know.~
@1852 = ~[ARAN] Riiiiight. Couldn't have been you. You were never there. Mum's the word, an' all. Still, that stinks.~
@1853 = ~[PC] Watch it, Aran. What stinks?~
@1854 = ~[PC] <CHARNAME> is a common enough name.~
@1855 = ~[PC] Defeating Sarevok and his machinations was important. I am proud of what was accomplished.~
@1856 = ~[ARAN] Well now. Last I heard, the <CHARNAME> they were talkin' about could philosophize with Elminster while playing chess with a Red Wizard. So it can't be you, nohow.~
@1857 = ~[PC] We did well by defeating Sarevok and his machinations. It was partly luck, but being smart and careful made it possible to defeat him.~
@1858 = ~[ARAN] Well now. That is just the kind o' thing I heard the <CHARNAME> they were talkin' about might say. Wise beyond <PRO_HISHER> years. But you let me along this adventure, which don't speak so well o' your wisdom. So it can't be you, nohow.~
@1859 = ~[PC] Defeating Sarevok and his machinations helped a lot of people. It was not the most wise choice, standing against such powerful forces. It was simply necessary.~
@1860 = ~[ARAN] Point taken. Sorry. You don't like people to know how you operate, eh? Well, I suppose that's fair enough. But Mask's Left Hand, I had to pick you of all people.~
@1861 = ~[PC] Me of all people?~
@1862 = ~[ARAN] Hey, I was just teasin' ye. You did right effective work takin' those bastards down. It made it possible for the Fist an' Moonshae and all to field forces against the rest of those bandits. Selune's Fair Bottom, though, I had to pick you of all people to join up with.~
@1863 = ~[PC] Well, you asked to join up, if I remember correctly...~
@1864 = ~[ARAN] I heard a darker rumor, too, where that particular <CHARNAME> could pick a man's pocket from ten paces in broad daylight, an' there'd be a whole crowd what couldn't tell 'til after <PRO_HESHE> was two days gone.~
@1865 = ~[PC] Hey, watch it, sellsword - passing along those tales is bad for business!~
@1866 = ~[PC] Defeating Sarevok and his machinations helped a lot of people. You can't make an omelet without breaking eggs.~
@1867 = ~[ARAN] Hey, look, no offense, but fame is not always good for the folks followin', if you know what I mean. Every great general is built on a pile o' dead foot soldiers. And once rumors get rollin' the opposition starts to take notice. Fame an' fortune are great ideas, but they come with some heavy baggage. Heavier for the folks what back you up.~
@1868 = ~[PC] You don't know the half of it. Have I mentioned that I am the child of a god?~
@1869 = ~[PC] Hey, you signed on. What were you expecting, comfortable inns and dancing girls?~
@1870 = ~[PC] Don't worry. I take care of my friends, Aran.~
@1871 = ~[PC] Hey, we are a team, remember? We take care of each other.~
@1872 = ~[PC] I reward those who serve me as greatly as I punish my enemies. Any further questions?~
@1873 = ~[ARAN] If you say so. I just don't like not knowin' the odds. Makes me less useful an' all.~
@1874 = ~[PC] I'll tell you what you need to know, Whitehand. Until then, shut up and soldier.~
@1875 = ~[PC] Look, there are some things best kept very, very quiet. But off the record, that was me. Just don't mention it again.~
@1876 = ~[PC] The odds are high that you will prove useful, Aran. As long as you keep your rumors to yourself.~
@1877 = ~[PC] (sigh) Alright, Aran. Yes, it was me.~
@1878 = ~[ARAN] Ha! That's a good one! Or are you serious... hey, I never put any stock in *those* rumors. You really are a Child of Murder?~
@1879 = ~[PC] We godlings prefer the term 'Bhaalspawn', I believe.~
@1880 = ~[PC] No, I was just teasing you.~
@1881 = ~[PC] Yes. Father is a big guy, evil, lots of kids, murder, death, blood, the whole works. Do you want to meet him?~
@1882 = ~[PC] My father was Bhaal. We do not get along well.~
@1883 = ~[PC] Did you know that the word 'gullible' has four of the letter 'L'?~
@1884 = ~[ARAN] Well, now that you mention it, the occasional inn is right fine, but I wasn't expectin' it to be a regular occurrence. About that dancin' girls part, that depends... are you offerin' to dance?~
@1885 = ~[PC] Let's keep this professional, Aran.~
@1886 = ~[PC] You couldn't keep up with me, boyo. I wouldn't want to give you a heart attack, or anything.~
@1887 = ~[PC] You play a dangerous game, Whitehand. Did I somehow give you the idea that you could talk with me this way?~
@1888 = ~[PC] No.~
@1889 = ~[PC] Yes.~
@1890 = ~[PC] We Heartwarders appreciate things of beauty, Aran. Though your language is far from beautiful, I can see a time where Sune might decide you need special attention...~
@1891 = ~[ARAN] Well, now that you mention it, the occasional inn is right fine, but I wasn't expectin' it to be a regular occurrence. About that dancin' girls part... well, I suspect the whole fame thing works for me as for you. You let me know next time you go wenching, an' I'll be right happy to buy the first round.~
@1892 = ~[ARAN] Well, knock me over with Clangedden's Hammer. A Bhaalspawn. Well, that explains some things, I guess. I think I might be right glad I am on your side. If even half of the stories are half true, I wouldn't want to be against you, that's for sure.~
@1893 = ~[ARAN] Heh. You had me goin' for a minute there.~
@1894 = ~[ARAN] Hey, I'm sorry, there. Didn't mean no harm.~
@1895 = ~[ARAN] Well, err... I... Never mind, then. Got to go see a man about a horse, an' all.~
@1896 = ~[ARAN] Well, I guess that is the best that can be hoped for. I mean, I appreciate th' compliment, about friends, an' team, an' all. It makes it easier to do the job when you know your compatriots be watchin' your back.~
@1897 = ~[ARAN] Right then. I'll go sharpen somethin', or just poke about a bit. Make myself useful, an' all.~
@1898 = ~[ARAN] You be about as funny as a horde o' gibberlings tryin' to light a fire.~
@1899 = ~[ARAN] Now that I have naught in th' way o' toleration for. I may have a bit o' Trade-speak accent, an' mayhap those dwarven bastards what I fought wi' sprinkled some oddities in here an' there, but my writin' an' scribin' be top notch. Mayhap I will go on about my business, now, on account o' you keep findin' fault wi' me.~
@1900 = ~[ARAN] Aye, <CHARNAME>, sure enough. I talk a mite bit more than I should anyhow. Bad habit, I guess.~
@1901 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I need to start thinkin' more like an adventurer an' less like a mercenary, if I'm to be right helpful, <CHARNAME>. Old habits die hard, though. I just keep wishin' we had a few cavalry out on th' wings, an' mayhap a ballista or two creakin' along. Takin' on th' Realms be a dauntin' task.~
@1902 = ~[ARAN] Second, third, fourth, an' fifth ones. But then again, if I ever paid passin' attention to my thoughts, I would never have become a mercenary, eh?~
@1903 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Blighted Balls. Perhaps I should just write it all down an' hand it to you, eh?~
@1904 = ~[PC] Perhaps we should take this up another time, before both of our patience runs out.~
@1905 = ~[PC] Perhaps you should just shut up and soldier, soldier. I think the pain of learning new things is making your nose bleed.~
@1906 = ~[PC] Having second thoughts about all this?~
@1907 = ~[PC] That would be fine. Of course, then we would need to correct your writing.~
@1908 = ~[PC] Don't get all snippy just because I making fun of you. After all, isn't your primary job to entertain me?~
@1909 = ~[ARAN] Takin' a mage's power, especially one what can blow huge holes in th' Promenade, that sounds like one hells of a goal.~
@1910 = ~[ARAN] Well, gettin' a powerful mage what can blow huge holes in th' Promenade off your back be less o' a job for foot soldiers an' more for trained specialists, which be what we be, I guess.~
@1911 = ~[ARAN] Right, then... Perhaps I needs be...~
@1912 = ~[PC] 'Perhaps I need to...' ~
@1913 = ~[ARAN] When you be puttin' it that way, it almost sounds reasonable.~
@1914 = ~[ARAN] Chauntea's Golden Wheat, I get th' idea. Mayhap I needs be havin' some work on th' whole language thing.~
@1915 = ~[PC] 'Perhaps I need to work on my language skills'...~
@1916 = ~[PC] Look, all joking aside, I need to oppose Irenicus, and stop him from persecuting me.~
@1917 = ~[PC] To get back to your question, I need to oppose Irenicus, and gain his power.~
@1918 = ~[PC] I wouldn't change a thing. It is kind of cute, actually.~
@1919 = ~[PC] You had better work hard on that. I don't need you distracted when it comes time to strip Irenicus' dead body and steal his power.~
@1920 = ~[PC] This conversation is getting too personal. We should move on.~
@1921 = ~[ARAN] Oh, I get th' whole 'epic quest' thing, an' servin' th greater good. I just am used to doin' that wi' much more in th' way o' numbers an' support.~
@1922 = ~[ARAN] Now that sentiment I have heard an' seen durin' many a campaign. Good or evil, on th' side o' law or in th' throes o' chaos, it usually be about makin' sure th' winner wins both th' battle, an' makes sure th' opposition knows it won't rightly pay to keep up th' whole war.~
@1923 = ~[ARAN] It always does seem to come down to power, eh? A friendly card game, th' small bar fights, th' minor scuffles between guilds, or armies o' whole nations, it seems to be all about who gets th' last word.~
@1924 = ~[ARAN] Well, no one else be steppin' up to lend a hand. So I guess there be naught but you. Well, an' me, an' those who you get to help us.~
@1925 = ~[ARAN] Well, yes. It sure as Helm's Horny Hands beats sittin' around tryin' to make time wi' Erika, an' havin' old Orrin look for new ways to squeeze coin I don't have out o' my purse.~
@1926 = ~[ARAN] Bloody right on th' fear thing. A little fear sharpens th' sellsword. Coward? Hells no. I know th' kind o' fool you be talkin about... th' sellsword what cares more for sword-pay than for sword-play, so to speak. I have died more than a few time in service, an' expect I will again. Hurts more than bein' dipped in acid. Th' difference between a brave man an' a coward is th' brave one will crap his leggin's standin' his ground, while th' coward will do it runnin' away.~
@1927 = ~[ARAN] I can see that might pose a bit o' a problem. Time an' resources be tight. Mayhap a small group can do what a large one can't... but it sure would make things a mite more comfortable wi' a solid backup force for a flankin' maneuver, all th' same.~
@1928 = ~[ARAN] I be havin' first, second, third, an' twentieth thoughts. But then again, I tend not to do my thinkin' wi' my head.~
@1929 = ~[PC] At least not the one on your shoulders...~
@1930 = ~[PC] What else would you think with? Oh...~
@1931 = ~[PC] You are improving! Why, just yesterday, I said to myself, 'Self, Aran doesn't think at all, does he'?~
@1932 = ~[PC] You are selling yourself short. I think you hide your thinking, because you don't want a leadership role. It is probably more comfortable for you to follow rather than be responsible for the risks.~
@1933 = ~[PC] And on that note, can we stop this conversation? We are getting distracted from the tasks at hand.~
@1934 = ~[ARAN] You are gettin' to know me right well, eh?~
@1935 = ~[ARAN] Now, no call for insults, eh? I know most o' my own limitations.~
@1936 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap so. But whether it be true or not, I'll not be tellin'.~
@1937 = ~[ARAN] I be a sight happier havin' had this little talk, though.~
@1938 = ~[ARAN] I hold contracts right solid, I do. But I always be likin' to know why we fight. It gives me somethin' to believe in, you know?~
@1939 = ~[PC] Irenicus gives just about everyone enough reason. Those who wish to take his power, those who wish to shield others from his power, and those who seek to retain a balance of power... he seems like the kind of guy who doesn't make friends easily.~
@1940 = ~[PC] I want Irenicus to pay for what he has done. It can be in blood, in teeth, in broken bones, or just crisping in the middle of a dozen fireballs... but he has to pay.~
@1941 = ~[PC] We fight because we have to fight. There is both great good and great evil in the world, and we need to balance those forces.~
@1942 = ~[PC] We fight because we have to fight. There is great evil in the world, and those of us with power should protect those who cannot protect themselves.~
@1943 = ~[PC] It isn't about the fight, Aran. It is about taking power, and using that power to force my agenda. The fight is just a by-product of someone not realizing that they should be listening to me.~
@1944 = ~[PC] You do not need to believe in anything except your contract. I think, you kill. What more do you really need to know?~
@1945 = ~[ARAN] Hey! That be rightly... hells. You must be pullin' my leg clean off. I speak well enough.~
@1946 = ~[PC] Perhaps if you said 'My language skills are sufficient. I do not need your assistance.'...~
@1947 = ~[PC] You speak. In fact, you speak and speak. Then you speak, speak some more, and speak, and speak, and...~
@1948 = ~[PC] Look, asking questions like why am I here and what are my goals is really a waste of time.  I am here, and I can do some good for many, many people.~
@1949 = ~[PC] I am here. You are here. Together, we can accomplish lots of things.~
@1950 = ~[PC] It doesn't really matter. Actions are what is important, not words. That's why this whole conversation is kind of pointless. If I have a task, I just do it, and try not to think about any long-term plans.~
@1951 = ~[ARAN] True enough. But we seem to be talkin' cross-purpose here.~
@1952 = ~[ARAN] Chasin' your soul will be one hells of a blighted tough thing to do, you know. My usual fare be more in th' way o' chasin' down a few missin' coins, or mayhap some inventory what be taken on th' five-finger discount. Or chasin' down an' akin' care o' makin' sure th' opposition has no body left for th' soul to inhabit. How are we goin' to chase somethin' so slippery?~
@1953 = ~[PC] Look, all of this is really my business, not yours.~
@1954 = ~[PC] We find Irenicus, we find my soul. Look, this is about doing what is right, and what is good. Opposing raw abuse of power is our real goal.~
@1955 = ~[PC] We find Irenicus, we find my soul. Irenicus has power, and he may be able to show me how to control my own.~
@1956 = ~[PC] Getting my soul back is just the start. If I am to truly wield power, those who oppose me need to know that the cost of doing so is not worth paying.~
@1957 = ~[PC] Wait a minute... you don't know how to corral enigmatic mages and force them to see the error of their ways? I thought you could just bind him up in paperwork and torture him with your improper grammatical constructs!~
@1958 = ~[PC] To tell you the truth, I am not sure. But all I can do is search for an answer, and prepare as best I can for that eventual confrontation.~
@1959 = ~[ARAN] Now, that sounds like a straightforward goal. Find th' bastard, beat th' garbage out o' him, an' get a good solid revenge.~
@1960 = ~[PC] Not quite. If I find him, I find my friend Imoen.~
@1961 = ~[PC] That works for me.~
@1962 = ~[PC] When you put it like that, it sounds so petty. This is about doing what is right, and what is good. Opposing raw abuse of power is our real goal.~
@1963 = ~[PC] Among other things. Irenicus has power, and he may be able to show me how to control my own.~
@1964 = ~[PC] Revenge is just the start. If I am to truly wield power, those who oppose me need to know that the cost of doing so is not worth paying.~
@1965 = ~[ARAN] I think we might get a decent contract wi' th' Mindgulph, then. Takin' on th' Cowlies be a right fine idea, if we be half drunk an' just wastin' hot air, but that bunch o' arcane bastards be a right powerful force. We may need a bit o' backup.~
@1966 = ~[PC] I thought you wanted a life of adventure and risk, far from the boredom and ennui of pub-crawling, caravan-guarding ways. Are you having second thoughts?~
@1967 = ~[PC] We have neither the resources nor the time to add a mercenary company to our roster.~
@1968 = ~[PC] Do I detect a little bit of fear? Are you a coward?~
@1969 = ~[PC] I was not thinking of taking on all of the Cowled wizards. Only the ones holding Imoen captive.~
@1970 = ~[PC] I guess it is only natural that having such worthy and powerful adversaries would cause you to have second thoughts.~
@1971 = ~[PC] I have had enough of your useless chatter. If you have to continually question my choices, do it with a pair of old socks stuffed in your mouth.~
@1972 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I ask this, then. What be your long term goals, now that you be here?~
@1973 = ~[PC] Rescuing Imoen is my first priority. I will think about my long term goals after that has been accomplished.~
@1974 = ~[PC] Irenicus. I want to see him smashed into the ground in front of me, pleading for his miserable life to end the torment. Turnabout is fair play.~
@1975 = ~[PC] Irenicus. He needs to be held accountable for his actions.~
@1976 = ~[PC] Step one, get my soul back. Step two... well, I will think about that when I have accomplished step one.~
@1977 = ~[PC] Step one, gather as much loot as I can find. Step two, find a bunch of very cute young women to help me celebrate spending said loot. Step three... I suppose I should go get my soul back, or something like that.~
@1978 = ~[PC] Step one, gather as much loot as I can find. Step two, find a bunch of very strong young men to help me celebrate spending said loot. Step three... I suppose I should go get my soul back, or something like that.~
@1979 = ~[PC] There are plenty of quests to do, and plenty of traveling before us.~
@1980 = ~[PC] Well, I thought that I might take up tutoring you in Common. Actually, I can't think of a better use of my time. With a great deal of patience, we might even get you to erase 'rightly' from your vocabulary.~
@1981 = ~[PC] It is difficult to formulate a master plan when so much keeps changing all the time. I do know that I need to gather as much strength as I can, because at some point or another I will have to face a very powerful adversary. I need to be ready.~
@1982 = ~[PC] Getting you to understand when your babbling is not welcome.~
@1983 = ~[PC] Shut up and soldier, soldier.~
@1984 = ~[ARAN] Now there be no reason not to discuss it. You must have some opinion on it, eh?~
@1985 = ~[ARAN] Right. True enough. Choose one, then, eh?~
@1986 = ~[PC] Disadvantages to being a Bhaalspawn? Many. Odd powers, nightmares, constant anxiety, depression, assassination attempts, limited love-life, constant uncomfortable travel...~
@1987 = ~[PC] Advantages to being a Bhaalspawn? Powers that appear out of nowhere, travel, excitement, adventure, treasure, a full test and use of my skills...~
@1988 = ~[PC] Why am I here? To meet you, of course. That could be seen as an advantage or a disadvantage.~
@1989 = ~[PC] Advantages like being able to shape and change events. Disadvantages like being forced into conflict without enough time to create a master plan.~
@1990 = ~[PC] I don't know which one to choose. I really don't think of things in the way you seem to.~
@1991 = ~[ARAN] Well, mayhap you have a point there, at that. So th' whole divine intervention theory might not hold so much water.~
@1992 = ~[ARAN] Well, I can just follow orders, I guess. Or, I could be a mite bit more useful to you, if I was to know what you be really after.~
@1993 = ~[ARAN] No, no... blighted hells, I was talkin' about th' bigger picture, eh? Strategy, not logistics. Mayhap I can ask a different way...~
@1994 = ~[ARAN] Tiamat's Twisted Tongue, that be th' largest load o' horse dung I ever did here! You waltzed right in an just... oh. You do be a kidder, eh? Heh. Well...~
@1995 = ~[ARAN] I guess I done heard that expressed. But to deny th' gods... it be a hard thing to have no belief. It sounds like you be more about th' here an' now than th' hereafter an' forever kind o' thoughts.~
@1996 = ~[ARAN] I...~
@1997 = ~[ARAN] ...~
@1998 = ~[ARAN] Well, stuff a tree up my arse. I don't have naught in th' way o' talk on that one. Not believin' in th' gods... it just don't seem right.~
@1999 = ~[PC] There may be right and wrong, but those are concepts we all create together. We don't need gods to have morals.~
@2000 = ~[PC] Oh, can't you tell when I am joking? Of course I believe in the gods. One of them became my father. Perhaps not the one I would have chosen, but then again, none of us get to choose our parentage.~
@2001 = ~[PC] Oh, can't you tell when I am joking? One of the most powerful, feared, and hated gods ever to exist became my father.~
@2002 = ~[PC] If I had wanted your opinion... wait. When would I ever want your opinion? This discussion is over.~
@2003 = ~[ARAN] Come, now, there be naught in Faerun what doesn't have some sort o' god's hand in, unless it be th' Faithless. You... you do believe in th' gods, right?~
@2004 = ~[PC] Of course I do. I may even become one some day.~
@2005 = ~[PC] I believe in them. I just can't believe that they let you get away with that foul mouth of yours.~
@2006 = ~[PC] I believe in them, if only because only a god could twist your language into the sorry state it finds itself.~
@2007 = ~[PC] Actually, I am Faithless. I think those powerful beings masquerading as gods are no different that you or I. There is no need to place faith in them.~
@2008 = ~[PC] My faith or lack thereof is none of your business. Get moving, and stop trying to discuss matters that might burn what little brain you have out of your body.~
@2009 = ~[ARAN] How about th' nice warm feelin' you get when you support an' identify wi' th' people what's watchin' your back?~
@2010 = ~[PC] When you put it that way, sure. But I would appreciate knowing what it is for.~
@2011 = ~[PC] You must be mistaking me for someone who cares. If you want something, prove it is necessary.~
@2012 = ~[PC] Nice try. No.~
@2013 = ~[PC] We need to conserve our coin. Is this something you really need, or is it something you want?~
@2014 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, I don't go askin' for naught I don't rightly need. Come on, <CHARNAME>, it won't be more than 200gp or so.~
@2015 = ~[PC] For 200gp, I expect to know exactly what you expect to do with the purchase.~
@2016 = ~[PC] I will give you 10gp and you can go chew your own twigs and make your own paper.~
@2017 = ~[PC] That is a good deal of money for paper. My scroll vellum costs about that.~
@2018 = ~[PC] What kind of paper costs so much coin?~
@2019 = ~[ARAN] Well, you might not know this, but all that scroll preparation, it takes strong materials an' strong concentration. In fact, I'm just about th' only one I know what can do it while travellin' in the first place. So, about that purchase...~
@2020 = ~[PC] I think we should invest in better equipment instead. A few words on some parchment will have little long term effect.~
@2021 = ~[PC] Scribing scrolls is useful, but not necessary. I think we need to save our coin.~
@2022 = ~[PC] Convince me it is worth it, Aran.~
@2023 = ~[PC] I understand. I will provide you the supplies as soon as I am able.~
@2024 = ~[PC] I guess I know where you fall on the 'pen versus sword' debate, then.~
@2025 = ~[ARAN] Exactly. I have enough trouble concentratin' on buildin' scrolls an' preparin' em for spells while we be on th' trail. I need right good supplies, I do. In fact, I'm just about th' only one I know what can do it in the first place. So, about that purchase...~
@2026 = ~[PC] Convince me it is worth it, Aran. Why should I spend good coin on single-use flimsy parchment, when there are magic weapons to invest in?~
@2027 = ~[ARAN] Just doin' my part, is all. Th' pen's a bit stronger than th' sword, an' I am makin' sure you have that power available to you, eh?~
@2028 = ~[PC] So you believe the pen is mightier than the sword?~
@2029 = ~[PC] Hey, that is a silly notion.~
@2030 = ~[PC] I did not expect philosophy debates from a sellsword, but go on...~
@2031 = ~[PC] I will get you those materials. But I am tired of talking right now. It is time to move on.~
@2032 = ~[PC] Swords, pens, magic, might... I know my own choices on their relative power.~
@2033 = ~[ARAN] Well, if you must know, I be scribin' a scroll. That takes a fair amount o' work. I can practice spar an' keep myself limber on th' rail, but I can't rightly work on scribin' while walkin', eh?~
@2034 = ~[PC] That seems like a waste of time to me.~
@2035 = ~[PC] Can you actually do that while we travel?~
@2036 = ~[ARAN] I have no problems wi' tellin' you. I be scribin' scrolls, the magical kind. That takes a fair amount o' work. I can practice spar an' keep myself limber on th' trail, but I can't rightly work on scribin' while walkin', eh?~
@2037 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, I know my own mind, but I be right interested in what you think.~
@2038 = ~[PC] I say the pen is a force greater than a million swords. One bounty notice in Candlekeep, and I end up changing the entire Sword Coast.~
@2039 = ~[PC] I say the sword is a force greater than a million pens. One bounty notice in Candlekeep just triggered off the inevitable. I would have ended up changing the entire Sword Coast even without Sarevok and all of his machinations.~
@2040 = ~[PC] I say the sword rules all. Try taking on a horde of orcs with an inkbottle, and see what happens. I prefer something blunt to bash heads, or something sharp to remove them completely.~
@2041 = ~[PC] I say the question is silly. It is not force that wins the day, and it is not power from writing or communication. It is planning, preparation, and education on how to apply what power you have, and having the force of arms to back it up.~
@2042 = ~[PC] I say the question is too tightly focused. It is the faith behind the sword, and the faith behind the words, written or spoken, that provides the true power.~
@2043 = ~[PC] I say that questions like these are best left to the sages, and that the best we can do is hope they come up with an answer we can live with.~
@2044 = ~[ARAN] See, this little feather I'm usin' here can do some pretty powerful things.~
@2045 = ~[PC] Would you like to see a few better uses for that feather?~
@2046 = ~[PC] Ah, trail talk about philosophy. The 'might versus write' debate. I think I would rather be boiled in oil or served raw to a pack of gibberlings.~
@2047 = ~[PC] You are smarter than you appear, Aran.~
@2048 = ~[PC] A feather. A sharpened feather, dipped in ink. Are you joking?~
@2049 = ~[PC] (Lean forward and cut Aran's quill in half.)~
@2050 = ~[ARAN] You know, I'd swear you were havin' me on, an'...~
@2051 = ~[ARAN] No. You wouldn't be makin' no joke like what I heard in my head. My mind goes right to th' sparkin' side o' life, it does. Anyways...~
@2052 = ~[ARAN] Start makin' suggestions like that, an' what's a lad to do but take you up on it? Only I got more than... err... hrmpf. What were I sayin'? Oh, yes..~
@2053 = ~[ARAN] Gettin' bored wi' me already, eh? Now, th' next thing you know, you will be makin' jokes about quills, an' dippin' in th' inkpot, an' all sorts o' talk what makes a lad blush crimson. Anyways...~
@2054 = ~[ARAN] I don't need naught in th' way o' bedroom instruction from you, m'boyo. This be about th' power o' symbolic representation an' transmission o' information, not some bedroom farce. That be for later, when I can get some red-haired green-eyed half-dryad woodnymph what wants to have her evil ways wi' my poor quill, eh? Anyways...~
@2055 = ~[ARAN] Sorry, point taken. I get a bit deep on th' trail. It be all that readin' an' tryin' to expand my mind.~
@2056 = ~[PC] Well, I am not one to stop someone from expanding their mind. I have my own beliefs.~
@2057 = ~[PC] Too much thoughtful conversation for me. I prefer to philosophize while drunk.~
@2058 = ~[PC] How about less of the expanding of your mind, and more of the expanding of our purse. Time to move on.~
@2059 = ~[PC] How can you possibly expand anything inside of that thick skull of yours? I would think it would squeeze out of those flapping ears you use to shade the sides of your head.~
@2060 = ~[ARAN] Aye, that's real funny, that is. A perfectly good quill ruined. You could have just said you didn't agree.~
@2061 = ~[PC] Philosophy is not my strong point. I would rather save this for a deep discussion in an inn.~
@2062 = ~[PC] Actually, that was funny, but I think I get your point. You are talking about power.~
@2063 = ~[PC] Look, I do not want to talk about this any more.~
@2064 = ~[PC] I thought the point was made well. Actions speak louder than words.~
@2065 = ~[PC] I would debate philosophy with you, but I am afraid I would be taking advantage of your feebleness of intellect.~
@2066 = ~[ARAN] I guess I can see th' 'might is all' argument. Short term, sword takes pen. You don't see me grubbin' about for quill an' parchment right afore combat, now, do you? But I don't rightly agree long term.~
@2067 = ~[PC] If you have a good bunch of swords or any weapon, wielded well, you can take what you want by force. Set yourself up a stronghold, raid, do what you want. So sword takes pen, and the game is finished.~
@2068 = ~[PC] Just for the sake of argument, pretend I have the most powerful charm spell written down, and I speak it... and it fails. That would seem to me to indicate that a sharp blade would win the day.~
@2069 = ~[PC] I have my own beliefs on this.~
@2070 = ~[PC] My head hurts.~
@2071 = ~[ARAN] Really, now. That sounds right simple. I'm no sage, but tell me this... why do we end up takin' orders an' rules from folks what's less powerful than we are?~
@2072 = ~[PC] They have more swords. They can call on more forces.~
@2073 = ~[PC] I think I know where you are heading. You are about to say that the trade contract is the basis of civilization, aren't you.~
@2074 = ~[PC] I do not think about such things. And I try not to pay much attention to rules, orders, and governments that fall outside of what I think is right.~
@2075 = ~[PC] I do not.~
@2076 = ~[PC] They have governments, laws... oh. OK, point taken. Written laws.~
@2077 = ~[ARAN] An' how do they do that?~
@2078 = ~[PC] They do not. Look, I get the whole civilization and magic and transfer of power thing. But I take what I want, when I want, and from whom I want. No piece of paper, scribed spell, or silly rule is going to stop me.~
@2079 = ~[PC] You are looking at the debate too narrowly, Aran. The words on the paper are not what provides the power.~
@2080 = ~[ARAN] You have to hold what you take, <PRO_GIRLBOY>, an' you can't be everywhere. So to do that you have laws, contracts, bounty notices, accounts receivable... Gond's Bladder, th' whole communicatin' long distance thing what sticks whole countries an' civilizations together, let's 'em trade. All paper, an silly little quills dipped in ink.~
@2081 = ~[PC] None of that fancy writing makes any difference if you don't back it up with force.~
@2082 = ~[PC] Point conceded. I would mention that all it takes to set civilization back a thousand years is one warrior with a torch, but I think the words would be lost on you. If I grabbed this weapon and put it at your throat, though, you might agree with me.~
@2083 = ~[PC] You have not convinced me. Nothing can resist force of arms. Even beliefs can be changed, or the believers destroyed.~
@2084 = ~[PC] Well, I have my own beliefs.~
@2085 = ~[ARAN] Aye, now that be a right fine idea. tell you what, you but me those supplies, an' I'll buy th' first two rounds, next inn we get to.~
@2086 = ~[ARAN] I say the pen's a force greater than a million swords. One bounty notice in Candlekeep, an' you change the entire Sword Coast politics, social order, an' ends up settlin' a battle most of my friends didn't walk away from whole. Which is a damned fine thing, 'cause we wasn't expectin' any of us to survive.~
@2087 = ~[ARAN] No, I never did get much in th' way o' attention. My sister be smart an' charismatic, my mother th' same, an' my father could charm gold out o' a customer in two shakes o' a lamb's tail. Me, I kill things. An' write about it. Sometimes even in that order.~
@2088 = ~[PC] Is that why you keep waylaying me with random commentary and distracting talk? You want to make up for being ignored as a child?~
@2089 = ~[PC] All that lack of attention to you has changed, you know. Now that you have joined my merry band of adventurers, you too have danger lurking in every corner, long sleepless nights, and the constant sensation that everyone is out to get us.~
@2090 = ~[PC] So, is your sister available for contract work? If she is better than you are, I could upgrade.~
@2091 = ~[PC] Being the center of attention is not always a good thing.~
@2092 = ~[PC] Pity. I was the center of attention, and look what it has done for me. You could have been this lucky.~
@2093 = ~[ARAN] From all th' stories told, you started out by topplin' th' Iron Throne. Now, that might have been enough for some, but here you be, gatherin' up th' likes o' me, an' chasin' around Faerun.~
@2094 = ~[ARAN] I'd say that meant you have a knack for commandin' interest by any an' all parties involved, eh?~
@2095 = ~[PC] Haven't we already discussed all of this? I was kidnapped.~
@2096 = ~[PC] The Iron Throne stood in my way. Irenicus stands in my way.~
@2097 = ~[PC] I think this is enough random chatter. Let's move on.~
@2098 = ~[PC] Irenicus attacked me.~
@2099 = ~[PC] I hate being tossed about like chattel and sent on fool's errands. I tried to avoid all of this, but it was forced on me.~
@2100 = ~[PC] I never wanted any attention. I would give anything to have this "knack" disappear.~
@2101 = ~[ARAN] That sounds like fun.~
@2102 = ~[PC] It gets better. Now that you have joined my merry band of adventurers, you too can have danger lurking in every corner, long sleepless nights, and the constant sensation that everyone is out to get us.~
@2103 = ~[PC] It is much less fun than it sounds.~
@2104 = ~[PC] I was being flippant. I hate the attention. I was never one to stand in the middle of the street shouting at the world.~
@2105 = ~[PC] Look, I just have to ask... do you ever shut up?~
@2106 = ~[PC] Fun for me, but not so much for you. After all, I may be the center of attention, but your job is to stand in the way of that attention and block it. Especially if it is firing arrows at me.~
@2107 = ~[ARAN] No luck there. She has her apprenticeship to complete. Besides, I'll do right fine by you all by my self, wi' out my scrawny little sister around to pester anyone.~
@2108 = ~[ARAN] Well, that be something' to write home about, at least. It could be worse, you know.~
@2109 = ~[PC] How could it be worse?~
@2110 = ~[PC] You could really mess things up and get me killed.~
@2111 = ~[PC] Worse, better... what does it matter? I do not want the attention. I would prefer to work behind the scenes.~
@2112 = ~[PC] I know. But somehow, all this attention is getting me is a lot more toruble, with a side order of trouble, heaped with trouble-sauce.~
@2113 = ~[PC] Worse for you, or worse for me?~
@2114 = ~[ARAN] I could have signed up wi' one o' your adversaries. An' so far, on th' whole, you look to be on th' winning' side.~
@2115 = ~[ARAN] But that be th' facts o' what happened, eh? I mean, facts be facts, but motivations be a deeper question. You may have had that happen, but you keep on wi' all this an' don't just quit.~
@2116 = ~[PC] What do you care about my motivation?~
@2117 = ~[PC] You served with the Flaming Fist. You should know that motivations are secondary considerations, and facts can be manipulated.~
@2118 = ~[PC] You served with the Flaming Fist. You should know that swords and arrows ignore motive and intent. They just kill you.~
@2119 = ~[PC] I tend not to ask the deeper questions. Having Gorion hide much of my childhood is a fact. Asking about why he did so might lead to answers I don't like.~
@2120 = ~[PC] Chaos, order, good, evil, fact, motivation. . . you seem to be delving well past idle chatter and into philosophical introspection. Are you studying at university?~
@2121 = ~[PC] My motivation... I never really thought that I could just stop. Settle down, ignore everything... I wonder why?~
@2122 = ~[PC] My motivation is simple. I will not rest until I rule everything.~
@2123 = ~[ARAN] But it happened, right? It be a fact, no matter what your motivation, nor what your feelin's be, for that matter. You didn't just say "That's that. I be done here", dust off your hands, an' walk away.~
@2124 = ~[ARAN] Strictly speakin', I don't have no right to care, now, do I? But whether I do or not, th' question be interestin' all th' same. Look...~
@2125 = ~[ARAN] Servin' wi' th' Flamin' Fist were simple enough in th' matter o' facts. There were a contract issued, a job to do, an' payday rolled around once a tenday or so. But why we joined up, an' why we kept in, that were a different matter entirely.~
@2126 = ~[PC] So for you, most of the motivation was the payday.~
@2127 = ~[PC] So for you, most of the motivation was the killing.~
@2128 = ~[PC] So for you, most of the motivation was keeping your sworn word.~
@2129 = ~[PC] So for you, most of the motivation was being part of something bigger than yourself.~
@2130 = ~[PC] So for you, most of the motivation was avoiding making emotional comittments. All those barmaids, wanting to settle down...~
@2131 = ~[PC] Easier to let others handle the big questions, while you wonder about what is for supper?~
@2132 = ~[PC] Why would I care about what motivated you then? I am more interested in what motivates you now.~
@2133 = ~[ARAN] I be that transparent, eh? Aye. It felt good to be part o' somethin' what made a difference, at least a little.~
@2134 = ~[PC] What if that difference turns out to be the wrong one, in your view?~
@2135 = ~[PC] None of us really make any meaningful difference. If you live long enough, everything around you changes.~
@2136 = ~[PC] Perhaps we will make a difference.~
@2137 = ~[PC] I don't want to make a difference. I want to find a nice quiet corner, and hide.~
@2138 = ~[PC] So, what motivates you now?~
@2139 = ~[ARAN] I suppose that were a part o' it, to tell th' honest truth. But I think it be more about bein' part o' somethin' bigger than mine own self.~
@2140 = ~[ARAN] I suppose that be a fair question. I did have choices on goin' to th' colonies, or guardin' caravans, an' here I be, adventurin' wi' you. I think it be more about bein' part o' somethin' bigger than mine own self.~
@2141 = ~[ARAN] Then when that day comes, I needs be seein' about undoin' whatever turned out wrong, eh?~
@2142 = ~[ARAN] Hells, no. Though th' last contract I had academic-like were transcribin' a set o' philosophical texts into Chondathan. Mayhap all that talking' about deep things had some effects on me, eh?~
@2143 = ~[ARAN] At least I will know I were a part o' somethin' what changed th' face o' Faerun, even if it be a small part an' a change forgotten in half an elven lifespan.~
@2144 = ~[ARAN] I know, I know... you don't rightly want th' kind o' attention you have been gettin' lately. But like it or hate it, ignore it or walk right up an' take it, it be there. Th' question be, what are you goin' to do wi' it?~
@2145 = ~[ARAN] Me neither. Callin' th' shots, leadin' out, that sort o' thing were never my strong points. Mayhap that be why I joined up wi' a regular mercenary company. They did most o' that for a lad.~
@2146 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap both, but probably more on my account, eh?~
@2147 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD>, what be next?~
@2148 = ~[PC] Speak that disrespectfully to me again, and you will find me more than a little angry.~
@2149 = ~[PC] We really do not have time for all this talk right now.~
@2150 = ~[PC] Are you asking what task is next, or are you asking what we should do about our current situation?~
@2151 = ~[PC] Such a deep analysis, Aran. Perhaps I should teach you some grammar after all.~
@2152 = ~[PC] Dinner. I think I have a recipe or two tucked away somewhere...~
@2153 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> spellweaver, what be next?~
@2154 = ~[PC] Speak that disrespectfully to me again, and you will find I have polymorphed you into a frog. Or perhaps just parts of you into a frog.~
@2155 = ~[PC] Such a deep analysis, Aran. Perhaps I should teach you some minor cantrips after all.~
@2156 = ~[PC] Dinner. I think I have a recipe or two tucked away somewhere... no, that's a scroll... no, that's old research... never mind me, go on. It may take a while to find them.~
@2157 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> stronghandin' enemy-whackin' weapons<PRO_MANWOMAN>, what's next?~
@2158 = ~[PC] Do you have a death wish? It sounded like you just spoke to me with disrespect.~
@2159 = ~[PC] Dinner at Haversons of Waterdeep, of course. Carrying all this weaponry, I would fit right in among the elite.~
@2160 = ~[PC] Well, what about a bet. I kill something, you cook it. You win if it tastes great, I win if it doesn't.~
@2161 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> liturgy-preachin' god-followin' wonder<PRO_GIRLBOY>, what's next?~
@2162 = ~[PC] I find your irreverence toward my faith disturbing, Aran. Perhaps you wish an early audience with my god?~
@2163 = ~[PC] Are you interested in what is next in the metaphysical sense, about our place on the Great Wheel?~
@2164 = ~[PC] The gods will provide. Well, actually, the gods will provide the opportunity. We provide action. Unfortunately, right now they are not providing the food.~
@2165 = ~[PC] I might have an idea or two. But perhaps dinner would be a good place to start.~
@2166 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> sticky-fingered quick-handed re-appropriator, what's next?~
@2167 = ~[PC] The last person who alluded to my interests with such disrespect had an accident.~
@2168 = ~[PC] Why, my hide-bound, slow-witted stableboy, I think the next item on the agenda is dinner.~
@2169 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> smooth talkin' music-spoutin' entertainer, what's next?~
@2170 = ~[PC] I am not sure that I enjoy your words and tone, Aran. Bards and Bardesses prefer to be known as such. The title 'entertainer' often carries connotations that are not favorable in polite company.~
@2171 = ~[PC] Well now, my rough-talking, weapon-swinging, slow-to-think friend, are you asking about what adventure we should tackle next, or is your stomach growling again?~
@2172 = ~[ARAN] That wasn't my stomach growlin', I swear - an' judging by th' smell, I think last night's dinner did some harm to one o' us.~
@2173 = ~[PC] Hey, keep downwind of me!~
@2174 = ~[PC] Didn't you cook last night?~
@2175 = ~[PC] Guilty as charged. Iron rations seem to disagree with me lately.~
@2176 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> Exemplar o' Strength, Tower o' Virtue, what's next?~
@2177 = ~[PC] I am not sure you are speaking to me appropriately, Aran. I think that I have earned the right to be treated with respect.~
@2178 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> back-to-the-basics naturalist, what's next?~
@2179 = ~[PC] Perhaps I have been treating you too kindly, and you have sought to re-balance our relationship with inappropriate disrespect?~
@2180 = ~[PC] I don't know. Let me confer with a game animal or two, and get back to you. Shall we bet that they would prefer you chose plant over animal for consumption?~
@2181 = ~[ARAN] So, m'<PRO_LADYLORD> hunter, what's next?~
@2182 = ~[PC] I am not accustomed to being spoken to with such disrespect. Guarding the wilds is a position I take seriously.~
@2183 = ~[PC] I think I have just the challenge for you. Zhentian owlbear!~
@2184 = ~[ARAN] No, nothin' so grand. Just what are we doin' about dinner.~
@2185 = ~[PC] You have got to be joking. You gave an analysis of our situation to help decide what to cook for dinner?~
@2186 = ~[PC] Actually, I was thinking of having some food, too. What do you suggest?~
@2187 = ~[PC] Actually, dinner is always a good subject for conversation.~
@2188 = ~[PC] Having heard that summary of our situation, I don't think I am feeling very hungry. But I suppose we have to eat.~
@2189 = ~[PC] I don't care. Prepare something, and I'll eat it.~
@2190 = ~[PC] I was thinking more about what might be on the menu after dinner.~
@2191 = ~[ARAN] Aye, you are a <PRO_MANWOMAN> of my own heart. I was just thinkin' about dinner myself.~
@2192 = ~[ARAN] What did you have in mind?~
@2193 = ~[PC] Perhaps some nice venison...~
@2194 = ~[PC] Oh, I 'll find something. A brace of hares, a bird, a vampire or two... who knows?~
@2195 = ~[PC] Actually, last time I bet with you, it turned out to be a big mistake. Why don't you give me some ideas.~
@2196 = ~[ARAN] Hold on, now - I heard they was poisonous.~
@2197 = ~[PC] A minor inconvenience. I wager you could still make it taste wonderful.~
@2198 = ~[PC] Why, yes, they are. There is a two out of five chance we would nick a poison sac during preparation, and not know it until we had finished our meal.~
@2199 = ~[PC] All rumors, vicious rumors. I think. They might not be poisonous at all.~
@2200 = ~[ARAN] You are playin' wi' me again, <CHARNAME>.~
@2201 = ~[PC] It was an accident. A minor inconvenience. He 'accidentally' fell out of a second story window. Twice. While tied to a chair. It was most distressing.~
@2202 = ~[PC] No, really. He had an accident. Some things you just don't tempt fate with, Aran, and one of those is talking about my work.~
@2203 = ~[PC] It was no accident. I stole his purse just after he had agreed to pay for a round of drinks for a group of Chondathan mercenary lads. I think he survived the beating.~
@2204 = ~[PC] Of course I was. But you probably should watch what you call me in public. It tends to make people suspicious.~
@2205 = ~[ARAN] Aye, point taken. No disrespect intended. It's just that I was thinkin' o' dinner.~
@2206 = ~[ARAN] You're pullin' my leg clean off my body, there.~
@2207 = ~[ARAN] Perhaps later, eh, on account o' my stomach be growlin' somethin' fierce. I was thinkin' more about plannin' for dinner.~
@2208 = ~[ARAN] We don't have much in th' way of sweets an' such, I think... wait a sec. You weren't talkin' about food, were you.~
@2209 = ~[PC] Yes, of course I was. I was talking about desert.~
@2210 = ~[PC] No, Aran. I was thinking more of burning off some extra energy.~
@2211 = ~[ARAN] I was kinda hopin'... no matter. I'll see what I have available for desert.~
@2212 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. You sure you want to wait until after dinner?~
@2213 = ~[PC] Yes. But you can think of ways to make my meal end very pleasurably.~
@2214 = ~[PC] No, I think I would rather not wait all that time.~
@2215 = ~[PC] Yes. But you can think of ways to make my meal end very pleasurably, especially if you can figure out how to get some time for the two of us to be alone.~
@2216 = ~[PC] No, I think I would rather not wait all that time. But there is the little problem of privacy...~
@2217 = ~[ARAN] I'll keep somethin' in mind what to sweeten your evenin', <CHARNAME>. Tell you what. Maybe we find some quiet place to prep th' meal, so to speak. I could use your help wi' the real plannin', though, on account o' me bein' distracted by the way your lips curve just so... an' your collarbone just so... *ahem*.~
@2218 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, oh mighty spellweaver? Start a fire wi' your fingers, or just create it out of thin air?~
@2219 = ~[PC] I am good at cleaning up. I usually have to clean up after you regularly anyway.~
@2220 = ~[PC] One simple Burning hands spell, and your coals will be ready. Or would you rather I use lightning? A fireball spell?~
@2221 = ~[PC] I shall drink Shadowdark ale and enjoy the fire while you serve me.~
@2222 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, strongarm - gatherin' firewood, or cleanin' up?~
@2223 = ~[PC] Of course I will help with cutting up the ingredients.~
@2224 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, oh Speaker o' the Gods - cleanin' up, or buildin' th' fire?~
@2225 = ~[PC] I think my contribution will be providing an audience for your work. After all, the true work of eating is done by the taster, is it not?~
@2226 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, oh agile one - cuttin' th' ingredients, or just disappearin' into the shadows the way you sometimes do?~
@2227 = ~[PC] I shall scout the area, I think. You cook, and I will keep one eye on you, and one on our surroundings.~
@2228 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, oh entert... I mean, oh Great Beguiler? Sing our supper to the right temperature?~
@2229 = ~[PC] I shall entertain you in grand style, while you prepare a feast for the ages. Of course, in less flowery phrases, that means you cook while I sit and practice.~
@2230 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, oh Great Light o' the World? Just don't do no extra layin' on o' hands - I don't like cookin' things alive.~
@2231 = ~[PC] I am good at cleaning up. A clean mind, a clean body, and... well, never mind. I am not sure you would completely understand.~
@2232 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, oh Protector of the Balance? An' if you start in about how tasty grubs an' twigs are, I'm not lettin' you near th' cookin' pots.~
@2233 = ~[ARAN] So how are you goin' to help, oh woodland warrior? Huntin' down supplies, or cuttin' up ingredients?~
@2234 = ~[ARAN] Hanali Celanil's Bouncing Bosom, I don't know when you be teasin' me, an' when you are not. But suit yourself.~
@2235 = ~[ARAN] Aye, that would be right kind o' you to help.~
@2236 = ~[ARAN] Why, no, not that I have seen. It's just interestin' to ask, is all. I have done a mite o' readin' myself. An' then there's always battle orders to scribe. Those teach a thing or two, sometimes by example, an' sometimes as one o' those "how to get everyone killed" examples.~
@2237 = ~[PC] You plan before a fight?~
@2238 = ~[PC] I do not find it easy to plan before combat.~
@2239 = ~[PC] So you have studied all of this?~
@2240 = ~[PC] I plan carefully, but even the best plan needs flexibility.~
@2241 = ~[PC] No plan survives contact with the enemy.~
@2242 = ~[ARAN] Well, to each <PRO_HISHER> own, I suppose. But me, I prefer some kind o' plan.~
@2243 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. I stand in as a shield, you do whatever it is you do, an' the opponent falls afore us. I'd like to think I was more'n a livin' shield, though.~
@2244 = ~[ARAN] I do a full check o' gear, an' then I lay down a quick set o' ideas in my head. I used to follow a real solid order, you know, back when I was just a sellsword. I'd check th' other fighters, an' guess their style. Then I'd go through th' priority order...~
@2245 = ~[ARAN] Block attacks on the magic types, Check. Protect the healers, Check. Follow th' most disciplined warrior's lead and orders, Check. Relax my arms, Check. Keep silent, Check. Kill things... Well, then I'd just wait for th' "check".~
@2246 = ~[PC] That sounds a little too predictable.~
@2247 = ~[ARAN] Bugger tactics, get in close, an' just whack th' bastards 'til they stop movin'.~
@2248 = ~[ARAN] Suit yourself. An' I had a good punchline, an' all. I talk a mite more'n I should, anyhow.~
@2249 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know. I can imagine a pretty big amount o' treasure.~
@2250 = ~[PC] Do you want me to accept your answer at face value and pretend that amuses me, or do you want me to explain why that makes you shallow and ugly?~
@2251 = ~[PC] I have no problems with you chasing fame and fortune, but I am not doing all this for such rewards.~
@2252 = ~[PC] Nothing compared to what I can imagine. Do not worry, Aran. When I rule the known world, I will make sure to name a small hamlet or village in your honor.~
@2253 = ~[PC] Somehow I think your idea of treasure and mine differ. Your definition might include fine parchment, young redheaded half-elven girls, massive storehouses of alcohol, and warm baths.~
@2254 = ~[ARAN] Well, it seems like you be pretty serious about all that. I just think you ought to check your target right careful, an' see what's behind it.~
@2255 = ~[PC] I do not understand. Why would I want to do that, when my focus should be centered on Irenicus?~
@2256 = ~[PC] Serious? If I were serious, I would have told you about three miles back that your codpiece is not tied correctly, and you have been showing off the family jewels to all and sundry.~
@2257 = ~[PC] You seem to be saying we should slow down, and wait for Irenicus, allowing him to prepare defenses and even send agents after us. That seems like you have a sincere wish for death.~
@2258 = ~[ARAN] Bollux. That be a right heavy load o' crap. You are a powerful individual, <CHARNAME>. You could drop this whole thing, an' head somewhere else. Perhaps even set yourself up a stronghold someplace nice. I could even get together some lads an' lasses what can fight right proper, an' we could carve out a safe refuge from th' world.~
@2259 = ~[PC] Using a sharp tongue with me does not mean you have a keen mind, Aran. What happens if you leave a powerful adversary unchallenged?~
@2260 = ~[PC] What a good idea! Aran, you are a genius. I have an even better idea. Why don't we go ask Irenicus if he would like to drop by for tea, and mend our differences over a nice set of sandwiches. Then he could reform and be on our side, and we could go knit sweaters for destitute halfling children in Neverwinter together!~
@2261 = ~[PC] That would be expedient, not right.~
@2262 = ~[PC] I know what I am doing. You should trust me, and stop talking about things you do not understand.~
@2263 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, that is a mite bit sharp! I was jokin', <CHARNAME>. To be right honest, danger attracts to you like bees to honey, eh? That be excitin'. Gives me a sense o' bein' part o' somethin' big.~
@2264 = ~[PC] At least you did not say 'attracts danger like flies to manure'.~
@2265 = ~[PC] I did not ask for this, but I intend to finish it.~
@2266 = ~[PC] I was joking, too. Although if you play your cards right, there could be some fame and fortune to be had. You could be the first person to have a stretch Calimport sewer named after you!~
@2267 = ~[PC] I may not know exactly what I am doing, but you should trust me.~
@2268 = ~[PC] Great. A sellsword with a death wish. Just what I wanted.~
@2269 = ~[ARAN] I was jokin', <CHARNAME>. To be right honest, danger attracts to you like bees to honey, eh? That be excitin'. Gives me a sense o' bein' part o' somethin' big.~
@2270 = ~[PC] Then you are a fool. The only things that count in this life are power, wealth, and freedom to do as one wishes. Fame comes when you have enough of the other two.~
@2271 = ~[ARAN] Well now, that be right kind o' you. I will be keepin' my eyes open for a village o' redheaded young lasses to retire to, an' you can name it after me. But to be fair, I was jokin', <CHARNAME>. Danger attracts to you like bees to honey, eh? That be excitin'. Gives me a sense o' bein' part o' somethin' big.~
@2272 = ~[PC] I did not ask for any of this, Aran. But I intend to finish it.~
@2273 = ~[ARAN] When you pick a target as nasty as that slippery bastard, you might get an edge up if you look at th' whole target, not just what you are aimin' at, an' try to get ahead o' his game. Chasin' him around so he can lead you where he wants you be poor strategy.~
@2274 = ~[PC] You have a point. But for now, I do not see any alternatives. We are forced to play his game under his rules.~
@2275 = ~[PC] You have a point. Do you have some specific suggestions?~
@2276 = ~[ARAN] An' you be bound an' determined to do what be right, come dragons or demons, eh? I figured as much. I think when you be pickin' a target as nasty as that slippery bastard, you might get an edge up if you look at th' whole target, not just what you are aimin' at, an' try to get ahead o' his game. Chasin' him around so he can lead you where he wants you be poor strategy.~
@2277 = ~[PC] You think?~
@2278 = ~[ARAN] I thought about it, but somethin' told me you might not see that as rightly funny, eh? When you pick a target as nasty as that slippery bastard, you might get an edge up if you look at th' whole target, not just what you are aimin' at, an' try to get ahead o' his game. Chasin' him around so he can lead you where he wants you be poor strategy.~
@2279 = ~[PC] Hey, I would find it funny. Just as long as I do not end up buried in manure, in over my head.~
@2280 = ~[PC] Good choice.~
@2281 = ~[ARAN] Funny. Right funny, there. You should look into gettin' a job tellin' jokes at th' Low Lantern. I bet you could make it work, if you stripped down to almost bare nekkid.~
@2282 = ~[ARAN] Last time I got myself into a game like that, me an' Grisa had to toss th' table over, an' fight our way out o' th' inn. We done almost made it, too. Good to be friends wi' a lass with orcish blood at times. If they had stuck to ten to one odds, no worries, but they got smart an' called in th' watch. Cost me over 300gp to clean up that mess.~
@2283 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Rambunctious Rump, <PRO_GIRLBOY>, I wish I did. I should have been studyin' strategy instead o' tactics. Next time we see a LoreKeeper, I think I will have a mite o' a word on what tomes to study. Tactics you can learn piecemeal, but strategy, that be a tougher game.~
@2284 = ~[ARAN] Grumbar's Clay Fist, <PRO_GIRLBOY>, you do have an odd way o' lookin' at things. I wish I saw things as clear as you do. I just keep runnin' into some problems in my own head. Some fool cleric or other said it was on account o' havin' somethin' called a 'conscience'. But you been callin' the plays well enough, an' I should shut up an' soldier.~
@2285 = ~[ARAN] Now, I didn't rightly say that, now, did I. I be after th' 'near death' experience, an' th' excitement, but I don't rightly want to move on to the next level. There be a big world out there, and I have seen only a small part o' it.~
@2286 = ~[ARAN] Now, that sounds right beautiful! Riches beyond my wildest ideas, all summed up right proper! What more could I want, eh?~
@2287 = ~[PC] You are incorrigible.~
@2288 = ~[PC] Mine would probably include getting you a speech tutor.~
@2289 = ~[PC] Gold, platinum, gems, magic items, and wealth... and you chose wine, women, and writing. Amazing.~
@2290 = ~[PC] It is a good thing you are so easy to please, Aran. It will keep you alive and useful to me, because we just do not want the same things.~
@2291 = ~[ARAN] I know you are faithful to your god, <CHARNAME>... but I figure a few words in the air won't hurt anythin'.~
@2292 = ~[PC] Don't you ever worry about the gods hearing your talk? Don't you ever expect help or advice or something to come of your call?~
@2293 = ~[PC] Haphazardly calling random gods is dangerous to your soul. If you do not call on one god, who will claim you from Kelemvor's judgment?~
@2294 = ~[PC] Without faith, you are nothing. Literally. As in abandoned from the Great Wheel. If you would like, we can pray together, and perhaps it will help you decide.~
@2295 = ~[PC] I didn't intend that to be a request. I don't want the attention drawn to us.~
@2296 = ~[ARAN] Helm is a tough god, <CHARNAME>... a fine soldierin' one at that. But there's times where he doesn't quite cover it. I figure a few words in the air won't hurt anythin'.~
@2297 = ~[PC] You should worry about the gods hearing your talk. Do you not expect help or advice or something to come of your call?~
@2298 = ~[PC] Haphazardly calling random gods is dangerous to your soul. If you do not call a just and fair god like Helm, who will claim you from Kelemvor's judgment?~
@2299 = ~[PC] Without faith, you are nothing. Literally. As in abandoned from the Great Wheel. If you would like, we can pray together, and perhaps Helm with bear you up on his shield.~
@2300 = ~[ARAN] Lathander is a gentle god, <CHARNAME>... a fine one for new beginnings. An' th' gods know I need some new beginnings. But there's times where he doesn't quite cover it. I figure a few words in the air won't hurt anythin'.~
@2301 = ~[PC] Haphazardly calling random gods is dangerous to your soul. If you do not call a gentle and strong god like Lathander, who will claim you from Kelemvor's judgment?~
@2302 = ~[PC] Without faith, you are nothing. Literally. As in abandoned from the Great Wheel. If you would like, we can pray together, and perhaps Lathander will grant you a new beginning.~
@2303 = ~[ARAN] Talos is a wild god, <CHARNAME>... one for power an' strength. Good to call on in battle. I figure a few words in the air won't hurt anythin'.~
@2304 = ~[PC] You are a fool to chatter on so. The gods will hear your talk.~
@2305 = ~[PC] Haphazardly calling random gods is dangerous to your soul. If you do not call a powerful god like Talos, no god will claim you from Kelemvor's judgment.~
@2306 = ~[PC] Without faith, you are nothing. Literally. As in abandoned from the Great Wheel. Pray to Talos with me, sellsword. Perhaps you will weather this storm we call 'life.'~
@2307 = ~[PC] I didn't intend that to be a request, sellsword. I don't want the attention drawn to us.~
@2308 = ~[ARAN] All you tree huggers do is talk about the balance and such. But you are good folks to watch a friend's back in battle that's for sure. I figure a few words in the air won't hurt the great balance, or whatever.~
@2309 = ~[PC] Tree hugger, eh? Thanks a lot. Don't you ever worry about the gods hearing your talk? Don't you ever expect help or advice or something to come of your call?~
@2310 = ~[PC] True balance requires choice, Aran. Haphazardly calling random gods is dangerous to your soul.~
@2311 = ~[PC] Without faith in Nature and her balance, you are nothing. Literally. As in abandoned from the Great Wheel. If you would like, we can meditate together, and perhaps you will find some peace.~
@2312 = ~[ARAN] Clerics get all th' attention, far as I can see. Plus, I favor Tymora the most. I figure she would like the gamble.~
@2313 = ~[ARAN] Look, I don't mean nothin'. No offense to you, but I favor Tymora the most, an' I figure she likes the gamble. She sends me down some powers, so she can't be that angry about it. It's a soldier's prerogative to swear, and I may take advantage a bit, but I don't mean you no harm. By the way, you ever considered followin' Tymora?~
@2314 = ~[PC] I might be interested. What does Tymora offer me?~
@2315 = ~[PC] Hey, that is getting a little personal. Do not try to sway my soul from its destined path, Aran.~
@2316 = ~[PC] I serve my chosen deity for now. My faith in myself will be enough, and perhaps someday I will become a god myself.~
@2317 = ~[PC] I am not sure if you are ready to hear about my faith.~
@2318 = ~[ARAN] Either you be jokin', or you be th' scariest <PRO_MANWOMAN> I ever did meet, <CHARNAME>. Messin' with those forces is like stickin' your head down a firedrake's throat an' ticklin' him.~
@2319 = ~[ARAN] Look, I don't mean nothin'. I have faith in the gods. No offense, but I favor Tymora the most, an' I figure she would like the gamble. It's a soldier's prerogative to swear, and I may take advantage a bit, but I don't mean you no harm. But I have to ask, why do you choose service your god? Seems like all they do is play with us mortals like toys.~
@2320 = ~[PC] I serve my chosen deity as I have always done. My faith grants me the ability to help others see the true path...~
@2321 = ~[PC] I serve my chosen deity as I have always done. My faith grants me discipline and control over myself.~
@2322 = ~[PC] I serve my chosen deity as I have always done. My faith grants me dominion over others and glories in my eventual rise to master of all.~
@2323 = ~[PC] I serve my chosen deity as I have always done. My faith grants me great power.~
@2324 = ~[PC] I serve my chosen deity for now. My faith in myself will be enough someday, and perhaps I will become a god.~
@2325 = ~[ARAN] You are playin' wi' me now, <CHARNAME>. Tymora might offer somethin', but she judges by actions. Right now, looks like you don't give decent odds on her investment. You'd have to clean up the way you are goin' and move more toward bright gold rather than deep shadow. But, if you ever do move in that direction, I'm right here to help out a bit.~
@2326 = ~[ARAN] Well, she can offer some decent odds on fair gambles, <CHARNAME>. IF you are really interested, then it might be a good move for you. She don't hold with extremes, except for takin' risks. You seem like th' sort to take a risk now an' then. Hey, you brought me along - that counts double!~
@2327 = ~[ARAN] Well now, Tymora does like a good bet, an' you have the 'good' part down, at least as far as your actions are speakin'. She don't hold with extremes, though, except for takin' risks. So, come talk sometime.~
@2328 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I did jump too quick now, didn't I. I guess I have a bit to learn about the whole preachin' thing. I didn't mean nothin'.~
@2329 = ~[ARAN] Tymora's Coin, and I thought *I* was the one with th' loose lacing.~
@2330 = ~[ARAN] Fair enough. There's always other times to speak on this kind o' thing.~
@2331 = ~[ARAN] Tymora's Coin, that is a fine idea. I like helpin' folks. Just I get the idea most clerics think that involves changin' gods.~
@2332 = ~[ARAN] Tymora's Coin, that is a strange proposition. I prefer to let things hang out a bit. More fun that way.~
@2333 = ~[ARAN] Tymora's Coin, you better be careful. Seems to me gods have a tendency to give folks power and just to see if they have the sense not to use it.~
@2334 = ~[ARAN] Besides, I am all done up. Give me a hand up, eh? We better get movin'.~
@2335 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap you be right. But would it be better for you?~
@2336 = ~[PC] Well... no. I may not enjoy the death and blood, but working through these challenges has changed me. Strengthened me.~
@2337 = ~[PC] I can feel the battles changing me, hardening me. And I do not think that is a positive change.~
@2338 = ~[PC] What, we get something from all this wandering about and poking sticks into dark places? I mean, something more than foot fungus?~
@2339 = ~[PC] Of course it would be better for me. Most of the creatures we face seem not to understand the regard in which I hold my own life!~
@2340 = ~[PC] Things are as they are. If I could change it, I would, but since I seem to be unable to escape the fights, I will use them to strengthen myself as best I can.~
@2341 = ~[PC] Look, battle is part of what we do. Like it, hate it, avoid it, dismiss it... just around the corner, the next one will be waiting.~
@2342 = ~[PC] I think that is none of your business.~
@2343 = ~[PC] I know we seem to be getting closer than just friendship... but I think that is really my own concern, not one for discussion.~
@2344 = ~[PC] I know we mean more to each other than just friends. But this is something that I need to decide for myself. You really can't help me talk it through like this.~
@2345 = ~[ARAN] Well, true enough. But th' effect be th' same... we be here, an' they, well... they have naught in th' way o' stoppin' you from accomplishin' what you want to accomplish. An' each battle leaves you a little stronger, I think.~
@2346 = ~[PC] That is true. I just wish it were because I have learned more about the world, and not twenty ways to kill something.~
@2347 = ~[PC] No. Each battle leaves me more convinced there has to be another way. But you are right. I am stronger.~
@2348 = ~[PC] Each battle leaves me one step closer to the real enemy, the bane of any campaign... foot fungus.~
@2349 = ~[PC] I wish they would have a greater appreciation for my body. I rather prefer it be left intact, and preferably unbruised.~
@2350 = ~[PC] I am a Heartwarder of Sune. She would not send me more than my heart could bear, even if it changes who I am.~
@2351 = ~[PC] I am a Feywarden of Correlon. The Seldarine do not fear change, they manage it. Even when it changes what they are, and what I am.~
@2352 = ~[PC] I am a Strifeleader of Cyric. Change is the greatest gift His followers can receive.~
@2353 = ~[PC] I am a Firewalker of Kossuth. Kossuth's fire changes everything, forging a new soul from the old.~
@2354 = ~[PC] I am a Painbearer of Ilmater. We do not think about our own suffering. If what we do saves others, then the changes needed to accomplish that task are acceptable.~
@2355 = ~[PC] I am a Lorekeeper of Oghma. Part of preserving knowledge is not to lock it away. It is to experience it, gather it, and save it to help inform the changes everyone faces. I am no different.~
@2356 = ~[PC] I am a Silverstar of Selune. Her light protects me and changes me each night, giving me the power to go on.~
@2357 = ~[PC] I am a Holy Strategist of the Red Knight. I must seek to win battles in the most efficient way, and to do that I need to experience the battles we fight, and try to understand the changes that I make to adapt to new conditions.~
@2358 = ~[PC] I am a Nightcloak of Shar. If She did not wish me to change, She would stop it.~
@2359 = ~[PC] I am a Battleguard of Tempus. As long as I draw breath, I can fight. And each fight will serve Tempus. For Him, I embrace change.~
@2360 = ~[PC] I am a Authlim of Iyachtu Xvim. We do not question His ways, on pain of hideous torture. If He did not want me to change, I would not.~
@2361 = ~[ARAN] I can see that right clear, I can. "Pardon me, mister evil undead thing o' horror wi' blood-drippin' fangs. Stand aside. This here be <CHARNAME>!"~
@2362 = ~[PC] I have definitely changed. When I was first starting out, I would have thought you were crazy, saying things like that. Now, things have definitely changed.~
@2363 = ~[PC] I wish I could find that funny. Unfortunately, the way things have changed, it is actually a possibility.~
@2364 = ~[PC] At least I got you to lighten up, and talk about something other than spoiled food, walking everywhere, and your current favorite topic - foot fungus.~
@2365 = ~[PC] Aran... I can feel the battles changing me, hardening me. And I do not think that is a positive change.~
@2366 = ~[PC] I may not enjoy the death and blood, but working through these challenges has changed me. Strengthened me.~
@2367 = ~[PC] I think we will avoid that tactic. They may decide that I am a worthy adversary. I prefer to remain in one piece, thank you very much.~
@2368 = ~[PC] Next time we meet an undead dragon, I will let you run right out there and try that tactic. I will even raise you, unless you are completely destroyed.~
@2369 = ~[ARAN] That be true enough. Well, actually, it be about findin' new an' excitin' foods an' drink, mayhap gatherin' a bit o' coin, an' all. But mostly, it be about killin' things.~
@2370 = ~[PC] I think we are rising to the challenges very well. And we are changing because of it.~
@2371 = ~[PC] Killing things is a means to an end. Unavoidable, and necessary. But yes, this much destruction does change a person.~
@2372 = ~[PC] What did you think we would be doing, wandering about adding to Volo's Guide to Faeruinian Foot Fungi?~
@2373 = ~[PC] I kill things before they kill me. Usually. Actually, always. But it does not stop them from trying.~
@2374 = ~[ARAN] Well, mayhap not. But there be adventurers what do more in th' way o' stealin', or conquerin', or mayhap bribin' their way through. We seem to be fallin' more on th' killin' side, so to speak.~
@2375 = ~[ARAN] Do you think th' changes... do you think they be for th' better?~
@2376 = ~[PC] I think I have become stronger, more capable. Yes, I think the changes are for the better.~
@2377 = ~[PC] No. There is a part of me that wishes I could roll back time and go back to Candlekeep. I would go into the back tower with my books, and never come out.~
@2378 = ~[PC] You seem to think so.~
@2379 = ~[PC] For better, for worse... does it really matter? Change is change.~
@2380 = ~[PC] I don't think I am qualified to make that determination. The gods alone know what I will achieve, and sometimes I am not sure they actually know, either.~
@2381 = ~[PC] We all change. If we do not, then we will not be ready for what comes next. Battle is part of what we do. Like it, hate it, avoid it, dismiss it... just around the corner, the next one will be waiting.~
@2382 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly agree. You have kept yourself upright an' movin' forward in spite o' everythin' that has been thrown on top o' you. Mayhap you needed a little hardenin', on account o' th' tasks fate seems right insistent on pushin' your way.~
@2383 = ~[PC] Thank you for the analysis, but I know what my limits are better than you do.~
@2384 = ~[PC] You have greatly over-estimated my powers.~
@2385 = ~[PC] That's me. The Fates throw a mountain or two my way, and I juggle them.~
@2386 = ~[PC] Perhaps you are right.~
@2387 = ~[PC] Agreeing with me or not has no relevance. I have to accept the changes, whether they are positive or negative.~
@2388 = ~[ARAN] Hells, if it were all about th' foot fungus, we could o' stayed in some inn down by th' docks in any major city an' done th' job right proper!~
@2389 = ~[PC] I know we are not a regular adventuring party. Most of what we do is not really by choice. But I think at least we are getting better at winning battles.~
@2390 = ~[PC] Any change is both positive and negative, Aran. Foot fungus and wholesale slaughter aside, if we do not change, we get run over by the world. It never stops. Not even when we wish it would slow down a little.~
@2391 = ~[PC] No, sorry... you would get us thrown out or put in jail too quickly. But to answer your original question, yes. I think that the changes are for the better.~
@2392 = ~[PC] Too many healers around. We would need to find some quiet little dungeon somewhere and leave all our supplies behind.~
@2393 = ~[PC] And on that note, I think we had better stop talking. So far, we have death and destruction for creatures not recognizing me, and foot fungus. If we go any farther, you are going to find some way of working food, religion, sex, and Waterdeep politics in here, too.~
@2394 = ~[ARAN] They do seem to have a right cavalier attitude when it comes to keepin' your skin intact. But each battle does give you more understandin', more power.~
@2395 = ~[PC] More power is good. All the power would be better.~
@2396 = ~[PC] I don't need more power. I need more sleep.~
@2397 = ~[PC] And yet I do not seem to have the power to get you to just walk with me, instead of starting an odd conversation...~
@2398 = ~[PC] I will trade the power and knowledge gained for a few moments of peace and reflection.~
@2399 = ~[PC] I understand what you are saying. I just wish that life were more about working together and less about senseless loss and destruction.~
@2400 = ~[PC] At least I get something out of each one. You just get more opportunities to exercise you vocabulary of oaths and swearwords. By the way, that last one... I think it was anatomically impossible without magical intervention..~
@2401 = ~[ARAN] Aye. You have a point there. Me, though... I find myself a bit more resistant to th' concept o' "inevitability" these days. There be a powerful large amount o' change I done seen in myself. Some good, some bad, some indifferent. It makes me wonder if just dealin' wi' battle all th' time really changes who we be, or if it just builds a core o' armor around who we be.~
@2402 = ~[PC] Battlefield philosophy? I learn something new about you each day.~
@2403 = ~[PC] Wasting time wondering if the experiences you have are going to make you a different person or if they are going to simply be a new set of tools that you can use is a waste of time. In the end, you are what you present to the outside world, no matter what goes on inside.~
@2404 = ~[PC] What is inside is what counts. Finding ways of killing our enemies has little to do with who you are as a person. It is just a set of skills that help you move through life.~
@2405 = ~[PC] I think you will find a balance. I may not. But then again, you are not me.~
@2406 = ~[PC] You resist the concept of inevitability because you want to think that you have freedom. But the gods are the ones with freedom. We just play around the edges.~
@2407 = ~[PC] You can let what you do define you, or you can choose what you do to accomplish your goals. Killing things does not change who you are. Thee is nothing inevitable about life, except that we all move on. And some liches have even put a semi-permanent stop to that.~
@2408 = ~[ARAN] Why, sure enough. I can see th' whole thing might have put you off thinkin' or talkin', so I be right happy you let me chatter on. Passes th' time, it does.~
@2409 = ~[ARAN] You do have an active imagination, eh? No matter. You successfully got me clean off topic an' now I forgot what we be talkin' about.~
@2410 = ~[ARAN] I'd best be gettin' on wi' what we are doin', anyways.~
@2411 = ~[ARAN] All the more reason to take a swing or two, when there be no enemies about, eh?~
@2412 = ~[PC] Well, if you insist, sure. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents.~
@2413 = ~[PC] I suppose it might be a good idea. I prefer to rely on magic, but when one is out of spells, brute force is sometimes necessary.~
@2414 = ~[PC] I guess it would be more fun than trying out a traditional duel between mages. All right, let's spar.~
@2415 = ~[PC] I do not think it would be a good idea, Aran.~
@2416 = ~[PC] No. Physical combat bores me, and I only put up with it when I have to.~
@2417 = ~[ARAN] Twin Swords style, Moonshae Axes, Calimshan Dual Scimitars, mayhap even simple quarterstaves if you like. You have to know your enemy an' what he uses, eh?~
@2418 = ~[PC] Well, if you insist, sure. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents. I have seen too many good fighters injured when using magical gear.~
@2419 = ~[PC] I suppose it might be a good idea. Even if I do not need the practice, it would make sure you can watch my back effectively.~
@2420 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fellow fighter remembering what really matters.~
@2421 = ~[PC] I do not think it would be a good idea, Aran. I am not sure your ego could handle the trouncing I would give you. It might be best not to spar.~
@2422 = ~[PC] I am not going to waste my time this way. You practice without me. I am getting enough of a workout just keeping up with our daily routine of find things, talk to them, and then kill them.~
@2423 = ~[ARAN] Big words, cleric <PRO_GIRLBOY>. Do you want to wager a prayer will be no help against my mighty skills?~
@2424 = ~[PC] Well, if you insist, sure. I will wager a trade bar or two. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents.~
@2425 = ~[PC] No coin, Aran. But perhaps you will wager some few moments of time to listen to me about my god's plan for you. Where shall we spar?~
@2426 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fellow cleric remembering that faith does not preclude keeping other skills active and useful in service to the gods.~
@2427 = ~[PC] I do not thing either a wager or a sparring session will help me accomplish my goals, Aran. Perhaps you should find another partner.~
@2428 = ~[PC] No, I am not interested in sparring.~
@2429 = ~[ARAN] Why you slippery little <PRO_SONDAUGHTER> o' a b... right. Give that bloody well back to me. Now, are we goin' to spar, or are you goin' to rob me blind?~
@2430 = ~[PC] Can't I do both?~
@2431 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fighter remembering what really matters to you meatshields... a good headbashing.~
@2432 = ~[PC] No thank you. You are just too slow, Aran. It would not be fair. And you seem to think that things should be fair.~
@2433 = ~[PC] No thank you to both. You do not have anything worth taking, and I do not find sparring very entertaining... or useful.~
@2434 = ~[ARAN] You done heard me sing a tavern song or two, so you know that would be no sparrin', just plain slaughter. On th' wits thing, I do not know if I could come up with enough to entertain you. But combat, I got me a knack for that.~
@2435 = ~[PC] Lead on, oh wielder of weapons and shield of strength. Your instruction shall provide merriment, and my merriment shall provide instruction.~
@2436 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fellow remembering his roots.~
@2437 = ~[PC] No, Aran, I would rather not spar now, or ever, for that matter. I think I have had enough physical combat with our daily routine of finding things, talking to them, and then killing them.~
@2438 = ~[PC] A wordsmith, songsmith, or poet needs no instruction in crude belligerence, Aran. I would not find it much fun. I think I would rather not.~
@2439 = ~[ARAN] See, there you go again, all noble an' correct. I needs be showin' you a bit about fightin' dirty, an' combattin' those what do not follow your paladiny ways.~
@2440 = ~[PC] Well, if you insist, it is always wise to study the ways of adversaries who refuse to act with chivalry. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents.~
@2441 = ~[PC] There is no need to stoop to that level, Aran. Come, we should spar, and I will show you that winning the fight within the bounds of chivalry is much more satisfying, and much more effective.~
@2442 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fellow paladin remembering the thrill of single combat.~
@2443 = ~[PC] I do not think sparring like that will help me, Aran. I need to maintain my focus. Besides, you might get hurt, or I might get hurt, and we have important goals to achieve together.~
@2444 = ~[PC] On second thought, Aran, I think sparring would be a bad idea. I would not enjoy sullying the true combat forms with unchivalrous garbage.~
@2445 = ~[ARAN] We might stick just to your fightin' side this time, eh? I know you blend magic wi' fightin', but there be times when it pays to focus on one or the other, instead o' doin' both.~
@2446 = ~[PC] I disagree, but if you want to stick to sparring on the physical level, I understand.~
@2447 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fellow remembering what really matters.~
@2448 = ~[PC] Without magic use, fighting is really not that much fun. Perhaps we should do something else, like play cards.~
@2449 = ~[PC] I am not sure I would learn anything new, Aran. Besides, I think I have had enough physical combat with our daily routine of finding things, talking to them, and then killing them.~
@2450 = ~[ARAN] So you say, <CHARNAME>, but I think you be spendin' more time prayin' an' not enough time preyin', if you catch my meanin'. It might do you good to get th' fighter side limbered up, so as to get that whole cleric side protected, eh?~
@2451 = ~[PC] My faith and my weaponry are interlinked, Aran. But perhaps I could help instruct you in both. Some people need to have the words of the gods drummed into their heads... literally.~
@2452 = ~[PC] My faith shields me well enough that I do not need to be spending all sorts of time sparring, Aran. Perhaps you should find another partner.~
@2453 = ~[ARAN] I would take that wager, exceptin' that be *my* purse you be wagerin', you slippery <PRO_SONDAUGHTER> o' a b... here, give me that. You needs be winnin' it fair an' square, not liftin' it off my belt all quiet-like.~
@2454 = ~[PC] If you what to be embarrassed by my quick dexterity and sharp skills, then so be it. I will spar with you.~
@2455 = ~[PC] I think you should find someone else to spar with. You are not going to be a challenge to my skills if you cannot detect a quick pickpocketing.~
@2456 = ~[ARAN] Aye, a triple threat is a tough set o' skills to keep sharp, eh? You keep th' light fingers an' the arcane spell chantin' in your back pocket on this one, an' we can concentrate just on the weapons skills.~
@2457 = ~[PC] I might be more interested in trading ideas on scribing scrolls, but perhaps you are right. A good spar would clear my head.~
@2458 = ~[PC] I think you may not be the right sparring partner for me, Aran. Perhaps you should find someone closer to your skill level.~
@2459 = ~[ARAN] If you think this here 'form' o' mine is goin' to get all beautiful while workin' up a sweat, well, you got some strange ideas on what be beautiful, eh? But we can give it a shot. I want to see you fight fair an' square, without all that nature<PRO_GIRLBOY> chantin' an' spellcraft.~
@2460 = ~[PC] It would be very enjoyable. I promise that if you lose, I shall balance it cleanly with my win, thus preserving the natural order of our relationship.~
@2461 = ~[PC] If you are going to insult my bond with nature, perhaps you should find a new partner. I did not suggest sparring. You did.~
@2462 = ~[ARAN] Rangers be all alike. They think that anyone can learn th' skill, an' the ranger speakin' claims to be able to track a fly travellin' between Calimport an' The Dale Lands, at night, blindfolded, an' stuffed in a sack o' grain.~
@2463 = ~[PC] Well, if you insist on sparring, sure. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents.~
@2464 = ~[PC] What, no swearing? Come on, Aran, you are slipping! We shall help you track your missing blasphemy by whacking you repeatedly, eliciting many and various oaths and grimaces!~
@2465 = ~[PC] I could say 'it takes one to know one', or 'speak for yourself, ranger', but it will be much more fun trouncing you in a sparring match!~
@2466 = ~[PC] Well, if you want to focus on the crude weaponsplay of the fighter, instead of he subtle and refined approach of the true woods<PRO_MANWOMAN>, perhaps you should find another sparring partner.~
@2467 = ~[ARAN] Mask's Malicious Smile, you done pickpocketed me an' magicked my dagger... perhaps we need to have a mite bit o' a lesson on what be mine, and what be yours! A sparrin' match is just th' ticket to teach you the error o' your ways.~
@2468 = ~[PC] I think I just taught you the lesson, Aran - what is mine is mine, and what you cannot hold on to is mine, and... oh, everything is mine anyways. But if it makes you feel better, I will have a spar with you.~
@2469 = ~[PC] Why would I need to work on those skills? My magic can protect me, and nothing withstands a well timed backstab from invisibility. Perhaps you should find another sparring partner.~
@2470 = ~[ARAN] I trust you be smart enough to know that spells run out, an' wise enough to know that th' gods help when they can, but sometimes it all comes down to what you can do with a big stick an' a firm grip. Try a spar wi' me, eh? It will help us both out.~
@2471 = ~[PC] It is against my better judgment, but if you think it will help, then I will spar with you.~
@2472 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see you remembering the distant past, before you began concentrating on what really matters.~
@2473 = ~[PC] I think my studies and my faith will serve me well enough. I do not see much point in sparring. Perhaps you should find someone else to spar with.~
@2474 = ~[ARAN] Bugger all... an' you done took my purse, too! That god o' yours, an' those fingers, they be headed for a pack o' trouble some day. See, what you need is a right smart sparrin' match to get some sense beat into you!~
@2475 = ~[PC] Well, if you insist on embarrassing yourself, sure. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents.~
@2476 = ~[PC] There is nothing that says a faithful follower with agility and style cannot teach a fighter how to fight. I would enjoy teaching you, Aran.~
@2477 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see you remembering what really matters is faith and focus. I suspect we will not set our respective gods at each other's throats with a friendly sparring match.~
@2478 = ~[PC] Why should I bother? I an pray for assistance, and then attack from a position of advantage. Go find a fighter who likes long drawn out engagements to spar with, Aran.~
@2479 = ~[ARAN] Well, your fightin' ways have been slowed down a mite on account o' all that work on stealth an' trackin', an' all that spellswork. This be th' perfect time to catch up a bit, eh?~
@2480 = ~[PC] I suspect that a good spar is more useful for you then it is for me, but I will indulge you.~
@2481 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fellow druid remembering that what really matters is Nature's balance.~
@2482 = ~[PC] You probably would be better served sparring with someone else, then. Go find someone willing to waste their time swatting at you with play weapons.~
@2483 = ~[ARAN] Just hold off on th' spell protections, eh? What with a Bless and an Iron Skin or two, you wouldn't rightly feel when I made a touch, an' that wouldn't be fair.~
@2484 = ~[PC] Do not worry. I will not put up the protective spells. I will even heal your head when I drub it, and boost your ego with a spell or two when you find yourself sprawled across the ground like a sack of grain.~
@2485 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fellow jack of all trades remembering that balance between our three disciplines really matters.~
@2486 = ~[PC] You might find it better to spar with someone else, Aran. Without my faith or magic engaged, combat is just a boring routine of thrust and counterthrust. No artistry involved.~
@2487 = ~[ARAN] See, you have been spendin' way too much time prayin', and then you go wanderin' off through the woods an' trees all stealthy-like. You need to get a leg up on good, old-fashioned physical combat, you do.~
@2488 = ~[PC] Perhaps you are right. Besides, teaching you to track is probably wasted; you would stop to write in that journal of yours and be completely lost. We can spar, if you like.~
@2489 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see you remembering your roots.~
@2490 = ~[PC] You might choose another sparring partner, then. My faith and my love of nature are not subjects for banter, Aran.~
@2491 = ~[ARAN] I'd be right happy if you would avoid that, yes. I know you ken to things right easy an' natural, but sometimes you run out o' focus, an' then you be needin' a way to keep yourself alive until you get a chance to get all bound up in your 'weave', or whatever it be you do to get that magic rollin'. Come spar, eh?~
@2492 = ~[PC] If you can teach me some defensive combinations, I would enjoy that. It might be useful.~
@2493 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study, along with your newly discovered powers with the weave. Stop playing coy. If it means that much to you, I agree.~
@2494 = ~[PC] I am really not very interested in physical combat, Aran. I have you to handle that for me. I concentrate on blowing things up and melting things, deciphering arcane materials, you know... important stuff. You should find someone else to spar with.~
@2495 = ~[PC] I think I have had enough physical combat with our daily routine of finding things, talking to them, and then killing them.~
@2496 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, none o' that monk stuff here. I know you can clobber a man barehanded, on account o' I seen you do it. You pick up a weapon, fair an' square, an' fight me <PRO_MANWOMAN> to man, th' way civilized folk do!~
@2497 = ~[PC] Well, if you insist. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents.~
@2498 = ~[PC] It will do no harm to indulge you, Aran. If it will help you find your center, then I shall assist you. Where shall we spar?~
@2499 = ~[PC] I thought that you had given up weaponry when you became a monk, Aran. But I guess it will do no harm to indulge in some memories for you.~
@2500 = ~[PC] My beliefs will not allow that sort of weapons practice even in mock combat, Aran. perhaps you should find someone else to take as a sparring partner.~
@2501 = ~[ARAN] Chauntea's Rosy Cheeks, where do you think be a safe an' protected place anywhere on th' face o' Toril? Here be just as good as anywhere when your adversaries include the pack o' powerful beings what like to mess wi' you. Come on, a spar won't hurt none. Well, it might just sting a mite bit.~
@2502 = ~[PC] If you insist, sure. But we should use practice weapons to make sure we don't have any accidents.~
@2503 = ~[PC] I think you will be eating those words for dinner, boyo. I will spar with you, and it is you who will be stinging.~
@2504 = ~[PC] And here I thought you had been distracted by all that ink and study. Good to see a fighter remembering what really matters.~
@2505 = ~[PC] I said it was not the right time or place. Perhaps you should find someone else to bother about this, Aran.~
@2506 = ~[ARAN] Right then. Let's be gettin'...~
@2507 = ~[ARAN] Oh, Corellon's Uncertain Chastity, this be a bad idea right now. We are makin' progress, an' here I go interruptin' again. Plus, all my sparrin' gear be packed at the bottom o' things, on account o' we need other things ready at hand more. Look, how about when we settle into camp for a rest? Next time we be outside someplace we can move about freely? Some evenin', when we be campin'.~
@2508 = ~[PC] That sounds fine to me.~
@2509 = ~[PC] You are not going to let this go until we spar, are you. Fine. Next time we set up camp outside in the evening, I will look for you.~
@2510 = ~[PC] No, thank you. I think it would be a waste of my time.~
@2511 = ~[PC] Are you sure that you want to spar, or do you have romance in mind?~
@2512 = ~[PC] Chicken. You are worse than Melicamp. At least he had an excuse.~
@2513 = ~[ARAN] Well, that puts a damper on things. How about the first time we settle into camp for a rest, we take this up again? We should make it outside, too, on account o' havin' enough space. Some evenin', when we be campin'. Come on, it might be a mite bit o' fun!~
@2514 = ~[PC] Chicken. You are delaying this because you do not want to lose to me. You are worse than Melicamp. At least he had an excuse.~
@2515 = ~[ARAN] Meli-who? I don't rightly know who you be talkin' about.~
@2516 = ~[PC] Short fellow, feathers, clucked a lot, stole some bracers... oh. Right. You weren't there. Never mind. Sure, I will find you for a sparring session.~
@2517 = ~[PC] Neither do I. I just liked the sound of the name. I think it was a pet chicken Imoen kept back at Candlekeep. I will find you some evening and spar, Aran.~
@2518 = ~[PC] Heh. Bwak bwawk cluck cluck... you just do not want to lose to me right here and now. I will wander out some evening and see what you can do, boyo.~
@2519 = ~[ARAN] Why, perish the thought. I'm a right golden good boy, I am. My mother done said so once, I think. O' course, she might have been yellin' somethin' else, but it be hard to hear clear-like when you are bouncin' along in a Coster wagon.~
@2520 = ~[ARAN] Well, I made the offer, eh? I guess that just has naught for interest for you. Fine by me. Mayhap someone else will give it a shot.~
@2521 = ~[ARAN] Whoa, there, big boy, watch th' mouth! Don't you be talkin' too big for your abilities, eh? I can hold my own, you know. No Candlekeep weepin' willow is goin' to beat a Whitehand in a sparrin' match!~
@2522 = ~[PC] Sure, sure... the famous Whitehands of the Great Dragon Army, chased by every random kobold and gibberling from here to Luskan. Are you going to talk or are you going to spar?~
@2523 = ~[PC] 'Weeping willow'? Come on, Aran, you have to come up with better trash talk than that. You are supposed to get me all off balance by insulting me.~
@2524 = ~[PC] I am talking well within my abilities, boyo. Put up swords or pay up. I have plans for that money.~
@2525 = ~[PC] You can hold your own, but you are talking to the Master of Disaster. This should be over quickly.~
@2526 = ~[PC] Hey, we are joking around, right? You are not getting the idea I do not appreciate your work...~
@2527 = ~[PC] War is never the answer.~
@2528 = ~[ARAN] Now there be a silly thought. There's not much what can't be adjusted wi' a suitable application o' a great big pile o' hurt, eh?~
@2529 = ~[PC] I'm serious, Aran. We should save our aggression for our enemies.~
@2530 = ~[PC] True enough. Well, show me what you have, oh you of the big mouth and small mind.~
@2531 = ~[PC] Spoken like a true sellsword, Aran. I would debate the point and duel wits with you, but I would have to find some for you to borrow, and that takes too much energy!~
@2532 = ~[PC] Hey, I thought we were going to use weapons, not practice talking. Am I correct?~
@2533 = ~[ARAN] Funny, boyo, real funny. I bet you practiced that in front o' a mirror.~
@2534 = ~[ARAN] I think th' aggression for th' enemies part be fine. But I was thinkin' it be smarter to practice in safety, together. On account o' it means it be more unlikely that one o' us needs a Raise Dead spell, or somethin'.~
@2535 = ~[ARAN] No, no... I was stretchin' out, is all. But I be interested in a spar on dexterity, on account o' bein' a mite tired from the past few days.~
@2536 = ~[ARAN] What do you think o' tryin' a fencin' match with foils?~
@2537 = ~[PC] Do you think I am frail and passive, unable to handle the big weapons? What am I, one of your bundles of dried, ink-covered sheepskin?~
@2538 = ~[PC] Name the weapon, and I am ready. If I do not know how to wield it, I will ask how.~
@2539 = ~[PC] It is your funeral. Show me you can fight.~
@2540 = ~[PC] It is your funeral. (Punch him hard in the gut.)~
@2541 = ~[PC] That sounds good to me. I do not do well with brute force weapons anyways. And I promise not to throw any spells your way.~
@2542 = ~[PC] I had my heart set on some good solid Moonshae Hammers and Axes, but a fencing match is fine. Good warriors can turn a rock or a piece of wood into a decent enough weapon.~
@2543 = ~[PC] Hey, if you want to set yourself up for an embarrassing loss, it is your funeral. You do remember I live by my agility, don't you?~
@2544 = ~[PC] Clerics usually work with blunt weapons, Aran, but a practice foil is blunt. You do not even have to spot me a touch or two in points.~
@2545 = ~[PC] Clerics usually work with blunt weapons, Aran, but a practice foil is blunt. I would not be true to my god if I did not insist that you spot me a touch or two in points.~
@2546 = ~[PC] Clerics usually work with blunt weapons, Aran, but a practice foil is blunt. It is a fair balance, with my lack of familiarity and your fatigue.~
@2547 = ~[PC] I am surprised, Aran.  Gentleman's weapons? I am impressed. A good spar to clear the head and focus the mind. Come, now, Aran, let us have a clean fight.~
@2548 = ~[PC] Gentleman's weapons? Good choice, befitting our calling. A good spar to clear the head and focus the mind. Come, now, Aran, let us have a clean fight.~
@2549 = ~[PC] Somehow I think it might be fun to try a good old-fashioned swordfight. I will try to avoid melting your blade, or setting your trousers on fire.~
@2550 = ~[PC] Hand to hand is more my forte, but perhaps this will be interesting. I will spar with you.~
@2551 = ~[PC] I should be asking to spar musically, or perhaps with poetry, Aran, but I am afraid I have heard your singing. I think you should stop talking and start fighting.~
@2552 = ~[ARAN] That you be. Hey, I be interested in a spar on dexterity, on account o' bein' a mite tired from the last few days. I got me an idea, an' since I don't rightly have many good ones, why not try this one.~
@2553 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then, that be fine. Do you want anythin' else?~
@2554 = ~[PC] Now what might I want when I am headed for my bedroll?~
@2555 = ~[PC] No, I am fine. Have a good night, Aran.~
@2556 = ~[PC] Well, there are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather. You should get right on that.~
@2557 = ~[PC] A smart young blond with loose morals and a short memory.~
@2558 = ~[ARAN] If I had been a cute young female, I would have known better than to show up here alone an' all unprotected, wi' th' likes o' you runnin' the show. But seein' as there be a severe shortage o' amorous dryads an' such around these parts, what say we do a little fencin'?~
@2559 = ~[PC] I just thought of you as a female, and the whole idea turns me off completely. I think I will just go to bed.~
@2560 = ~[PC] That sounds like a good idea.~
@2561 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly have th' practice equipment for Waterdeep Twin Swords style, just two straight practice foils for duellin' wi' out harm. Wi' a bit o' luck, we shall see who gets a few extra coins to toss around next inn we be stayin' at.~
@2562 = ~[ARAN] Lathander's Luminous Legs, <CHARNAME>, you need a mite bit o' sunshine poured into that addled pate o' yours, you do. An' I am just th' man to do it.~
@2563 = ~[PC] Talk is cheap, and my time is valuable. Throw me a foil.~
@2564 = ~[PC] Actually, I think it would be a good time to quit while I am ahead. I seem to have won the verbal sparring, so I am off to bed.~
@2565 = ~[PC] Shall we spar?~
@2566 = ~[PC] Hey, all trash-talk aside, are you going to teach me how to spar?~
@2567 = ~[PC] You say 'man', but I see 'boy who throws a ton of wind'. Show me what you have, caravan-boy...~
@2568 = ~[PC] Look, can we skip the whole sparring thing, and just talk?~
@2569 = ~[ARAN] Torm's Blighted Balls, do you be jokin'? I thought we be talkin' trash to each other, an' gettin' into th' spirit, is all. Where have you been, a monastery all your life?~
@2570 = ~[PC] Let's just say that I have spent most of my life being very, very serious.~
@2571 = ~[PC] Good. Toss me a weapon, and let's see how this all works out.~
@2572 = ~[PC] Yes. (Punch him hard in the gut.)~
@2573 = ~[PC] This is taking too long. I think I will head for bed.~
@2574 = ~[ARAN] Bugger that. If I wanted to insult you, I'd be sayin' you smell like th' inside o' a Luskan Cathouse, or look like one o' them Calimshan eunuchs. Bundle o' dried sheepskin, my arse.~
@2575 = ~[PC] Why, thank you, sir. And I would respond that your breath is as stunning as an otyugh, but luckily for the otyugh it has the benefit of some redeeming qualities...~
@2576 = ~[PC] You can save the feeble attempts at insults. Throw me a foil, and let's spar.~
@2577 = ~[PC] Aran, you have so much to learn about talking to your betters. Perhaps a sound thrashing will help.~
@2578 = ~[PC] Actually, could you show me how to hold a foil? I never really learned...~
@2579 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. Here, catch.~
@2580 = ~[PC] (Catch the rapier by the hilt and place it to your lips, saluting him.)~
@2581 = ~[PC] (Catch the rapier and extend it away and to your left, ready to fight.)~
@2582 = ~[PC] (Catch the rapier and instantly lunge forward with a direct thrust.)~
@2583 = ~[PC] (Clumsily catch the rapier and grip it like a club.)~
@2584 = ~[ARAN] What in th' nine hells was that?~
@2585 = ~[PC] Weakness. You let your guard down, Aran, and I was right there to take advantage. Are we going to spar?~
@2586 = ~[PC] Fun. Here, let me do it again...~
@2587 = ~[PC] A warning. I came here to fight, not talk.~
@2588 = ~[PC] A sucker-punch. Where have you been living all your life, a monastery? Throw me a foil.~
@2589 = ~[ARAN] Now, that I could get behind, or in front of. Or in bed with, if I could find one like that. I'll be keepin' my eyes open, eh?~
@2590 = ~[PC] Hey, on second thought, I am going back to an empty bedroll and another night of troubled sleep. Throw me a foil.~
@2591 = ~[PC] You do that. Have a good night, Aran.~
@2592 = ~[PC] No need, Aran. I think I can handle getting my own women. You concentrate on yourself. Have a good night.~
@2593 = ~[PC] No need, Aran. I already have someone I am interested in romantically.~
@2594 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then, same to you. I think I am goin' to go get some energy worked out o' my system, eh? I will see you back at camp.~
@2595 = ~[ARAN] A man never lived what has too many girlfriends, as long as he be careful to keep them separate. Wives, it might be that just one be too many, but girlfriends, that be a different story. I think I am goin' to go get some energy worked out o' my system, eh? I will see you back at camp.~
@2596 = ~[ARAN] Big talk, big talk! With a bit o' luck, we shall see who gets a few extra coins to toss around next inn we be stayin' at.~
@2597 = ~[ARAN] Not on your life... I'm done wi' getting my gut punched on account o' you gotta let off some steam. You got anythin' else you want me to do for you? Mayhap somethin' that don't rightly hurt so much?~
@2598 = ~[PC] Well, there are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather. You should go do that, instead.~
@2599 = ~[ARAN] A smart young blond with loose morals and a short memory?~
@2600 = ~[PC] Sign me up. Do you happen to have her in your pack?~
@2601 = ~[PC] I think I have all I can handle with women right now, thanks. Have a good night, Aran.~
@2602 = ~[PC] Sounds more like your type than mine. Have a good night.~
@2603 = ~[PC] Like you could get one to pay attention to you, let alone me. Dream on!~
@2604 = ~[PC] I am sure I can come up with one of those on my own, should I want one. You, on the other hand... perhaps not.~
@2605 = ~[ARAN] No, I don't rightly think I can pull a blond out o' my pack right now, smart, loose, or even female. No brunettes, redheads, or even one o' them sparkley-headed Gensai, neither. Mayhap next inn, if there be a good bit o' alcohol an' some dancin', but not right here an' right now!~
@2606 = ~[ARAN] I think I am goin' to go get some energy worked out o' my system, eh? I will see you back at camp.~
@2607 = ~[ARAN] Aye, sure. This can be a mite bit strange for someone who has naught for trainin', but th' basics is pretend you are facin' an armored opponent wi' a long sword. Slashin' won't be gettin' you anywhere. You need to look for opportunities to pierce wi' the point, see? Here, hold it like this... an' then try to stick me any place below th' neck.~
@2608 = ~[PC] Just like this? (swish the blade side to side, and then whip it across his left leg.)~
@2609 = ~[PC] Just like this? (lunge forward and push the tip of the foil toward his left shoulder.)~
@2610 = ~[PC] Just like this? (feint left, then drive the foil directly for his right eye.)~
@2611 = ~[PC] This is not really that interesting. I think I would rather not spar tonight, Aran. I am going to turn in.~
@2612 = ~[ARAN] Blighted bones, that hurt! But aye. Only you need to hold your wrist like this... an' turn your body in so as to give th' smallest target possible, or I'll be rammin' my blade where th' sun don't shine first time I get behind you.~
@2613 = ~[PC] That will do. I can take it from here - let's spar.~
@2614 = ~[PC] Look, I learned how to do this back in Candlekeep. You are a bit gullible, aren't you. Let's fence.~
@2615 = ~[ARAN] (Blades clash as Aran blocks the thrust.) Not unless you be expectin' one o' us to die tonight. This be friendly sparrin', not pop 'Aran's eyeball an' clip his brain'. Looks like you can handle yourself right fine. Do you be ready?~
@2616 = ~[PC] Look, I learned how to do this back in Candlekeep. Let's fence.~
@2617 = ~[PC] The eyeball might pop, but there is no brain in there to hurt. If you want all this fancy fighting, go do it yourself. I am more of the 'beat them senseless and then vivisect their parts for the necromancer' kind. Have as good a night as you can. I am headed for my bedroll.~
@2618 = ~[ARAN] Here, let's get goin', eh - en garde!~
@2619 = ~[PC] (Circle around to his left.)~
@2620 = ~[PC] (Feint right, then slash toward his legs.)~
@2621 = ~[PC] (Wait patiently, watching him closely.)~
@2622 = ~[PC] (Stand very still, motionless in the moonlight.)~
@2623 = ~[PC] (Thrust savagely at him.)~
@2624 = ~[ARAN] (A spark strikes as his blade parries. He thrusts quickly forward.)~
@2625 = ~[PC] (Guard closely, on the defensive, parrying each of his thrusts.)~
@2626 = ~[PC] (Step back quickly, then advance with a flurry of quick strokes.)~
@2627 = ~[PC] (Twist your wrist, deflecting his riposte and flicking your blade toward his throat.)~
@2628 = ~[PC] Your bootlace is coming untied...~
@2629 = ~[PC] Didn't we do this already? You have to learn to be more creative, Aran.~
@2630 = ~[PC] Had enough, oh feeble wielder of swords? I can thrust and parry all night, you know. It does not look like you have the stamina.~
@2631 = ~[PC] Come on, just a few more exchanges, and I will have thoroughly humiliated you...~
@2632 = ~[PC] Hey, I am not bad at this. But then again, I always thought that negotiation was the art of saying "let's talk!" till I can find a rock.~
@2633 = ~[PC] Slow, slow, slow - you are slower than honey running uphill on the Spine of the World.~
@2634 = ~[ARAN] (He falls back, his riposte clashing against your blade with jarring force.)~
@2635 = ~[PC] (Advance with a flurry of quick strokes, pushing hard to make him move back.)~
@2636 = ~[PC] (Deflect his riposte, moonlight flashing along the blade as it drives toward his throat.)~
@2637 = ~[ARAN] (His blade parries, but yours finds its mark... Aran falls back and his riposte hisses through the air past your ear.)~
@2638 = ~[ARAN] (Your blade finds its mark, and Aran falls back, wiping the sweat from his brow.)~
@2639 = ~[ARAN] (His blade parries quickly, and the point of his foil dances forward to tap your shoulder.)~
@2640 = ~[ARAN] (You feel the point of his foil tap quickly on your chest, then on your throat, his body overbalancing as he spins past you.)~
@2641 = ~[ARAN] A point to me, there. Not bad for a sellsword, eh? Just don't be usin' none o' those fancy powers o' yours to make up th' difference.~
@2642 = ~[ARAN] Ilmater's Blood, another point to me, there. I must be gettin' good, or somethin'.~
@2643 = ~[ARAN] That be three points to me, eh? I do believe I be schoolin' you proper, boyo.~
@2644 = ~[ARAN] A point to you, there. A lucky shot? Or do you be just gettin' warmed up?~
@2645 = ~[ARAN] Bane's Bones, another point to you. You be right close to winnin' this, I think. I had best be steppin' up my game.~
@2646 = ~[ARAN] A point to you, there. Sune's Sweet Caress, you done got me, I think.~
@2647 = ~[ARAN] (He backs away, whipping his foil through the night air, muttering something under his breath.)~
@2648 = ~[ARAN] (He backs away, whipping his foil through the night air.)~
@2649 = ~[ARAN] Aye, feels good to get a point. I like winnin'.~
@2650 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Cruel Laugh, I needs get myself movin'. I hate losin'.~
@2651 = ~[ARAN] All right, I be ready to roll again. Make it count, eh? No fun if there be no sweatin'.~
@2652 = ~[PC] En Garde...~
@2653 = ~[PC] (Step back, blade pointing directly at his eye, then advance with a flurry of quick strokes.)~
@2654 = ~[PC] (Feint suddenly, then cut upward, flicking your blade toward his throat.)~
@2655 = ~[PC] You have to learn to be more creative, Aran. You could have thrown something, or kicked, or something. You are making this too easy.~
@2656 = ~[PC] I have had enough of this. I call truce!~
@2657 = ~[ARAN] Mielikki's Quiver, that stings. I should o' checked on th' tips, on account o' I got a little scratch back there I didn't feel until now.~
@2658 = ~[PC] Excuses, excuses. En Garde...~
@2659 = ~[PC] (Step back, blade pointing low, then advance with a flurry of quick strokes.)~
@2660 = ~[ARAN] Well, we be gettin' some exercise, I do believe. Though you be pantin' somethin' fierce. I should never have cooked that turnip curry tonight... *phew*!~
@2661 = ~[PC] Hey, my breath is nothing compared to the gaseous cloud you have been laying. And here I thought you had to use spellcraft to make a place uninhabitable.~
@2662 = ~[PC] (Step back, blade pointing low, then advance with rapid, precise strokes.)~
@2663 = ~[PC] (Feint suddenly, then cut sideways, flicking your blade toward his throat.)~
@2664 = ~[ARAN] Do it be me, or do it be gettin' right hot around here?~
@2665 = ~[PC] I think it is you, Aran, feeling the pressure of my superior skills and better looks.~
@2666 = ~[PC] (Guard closely, on the defensive, watching for each of his motions and countering.)~
@2667 = ~[PC] Hey, I am not bad at this. But then again, I always thought that negotiation was the art of saying "let's talk!" until I can find a rock.~
@2668 = ~[ARAN] (His rapier dances forward, boring toward your shoulder.)~
@2669 = ~[PC] (Spin lightly, ducking under his whispering blade and coming up with a thrust from underneath.)~
@2670 = ~[PC] (Thrust savagely past his guard.)~
@2671 = ~[PC] (Parry, and lunge forward to the right.)~
@2672 = ~[PC] (Press forward as fast as you can, in a whirlwind of slashes.)~
@2673 = ~[ARAN] You can start fightin' any time you want, now, eh? Or are you holdin' back on account o' I'm so feeble?~
@2674 = ~[ARAN] Defense never won no swordfight. Battles, mayhap. Unless you be tryin' to tire me out...~
@2675 = ~[ARAN] Dancin' about like that will be gettin' you tired, eh? You goin' to take this serious, or do I have to do all th' work?~
@2676 = ~[ARAN] Nice dancin'. I think I done seen that footwork in th' Angry Turnip Public House.~
@2677 = ~[ARAN] Nice dancin' footwork, there. Not th' way to win, but it sure do look pretty for th' crowd...~
@2678 = ~[ARAN] (Blades spark in the cold light of the moon as you circle, the shadows dancing around you.)~
@2679 = ~[ARAN] (You circle under the stars, feinting occasionally, the harsh clash of metal skittering along metal an erratic music in your ears.)~
@2680 = ~[ARAN] (Aran steps back slightly, arms outstretched, opening his chest for an attack. His grin gleams bright as he bows to you, but his ruse is made apparent when he charges directly at you.)~
@2681 = ~[PC] (Advance to meet him, striking first toward his extended knee, then toward his shoulder.)~
@2682 = ~[PC] (Crouch quickly, thrusting up from underneath his blade.)~
@2683 = ~[PC] (Sidestep and slash hard at him.)~
@2684 = ~[PC] (Guard closely, on the defensive, deflecting both his blade and his charge.)~
@2685 = ~[PC] (Charge him, foil arcing to slash at his body.)~
@2686 = ~[ARAN] (His rapier dances forward, boring toward your chest.)~
@2687 = ~[PC] (Advance with a flurry of quick strokes, first toward his extended knee, then toward his shoulder.)~
@2688 = ~[PC] (Sidestep and slash hard at him, advancing with a flurry of quick strokes.)~
@2689 = ~[PC] (Deflecting his riposte, flicking your blade toward his throat.)~
@2690 = ~[PC] (Slam straight down toward his head with both hands, then quickly thrust toward his shoulder.)~
@2691 = ~[PC] (Duck under his whispering blade and lunge forward to the right.)~
@2692 = ~[ARAN] I'm not bloody well fallin' for that old trick, boyo...~
@2693 = ~[ARAN] Big talk from th' Bhaalspawn. You tryin' to spar, or kill me wi' your fetid breath?~
@2694 = ~[ARAN] I got testimony from a couple o' tavern wenches what beg to differ... on both counts!~
@2695 = ~[ARAN] I been in worse humiliations than this, eh? Just bein' seen wi' you might count as one!~
@2696 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a truth.~
@2697 = ~[ARAN] But th' ladies find me plenty sweet, eh? I was tryin' to play nice, an' not be remindin' you that you smell like a dungheap, an' swing like a gibberling.~
@2698 = ~[ARAN] Hey, wait a second, now... one, two, three points...  by my count, you just won, fair an' square.~
@2699 = ~[PC] Look, now that we have that out of our system, can we just talk?~
@2700 = ~[PC] You know, I am going to turn in. I need some sleep.~
@2701 = ~[PC] Another match?~
@2702 = ~[ARAN] Now, wait a moment, eh? one, two, three points... by my count I won, fair an' square.~
@2703 = ~[PC] I demand a rematch!~
@2704 = ~[ARAN] Aye. What be on your mind?~
@2705 = ~[PC] Oh, nothing much. You know, I need to sort out my own problems. Let's spar.~
@2706 = ~[PC] I do not understand women. Mostly, I do not understand <PLAYER2>.~
@2707 = ~[PC] I do not understand women. Mostly, I do not understand <PLAYER3>.~
@2708 = ~[PC] I do not understand women. Mostly, I do not understand <PLAYER4>.~
@2709 = ~[PC] I do not understand women. Mostly, I do not understand <PLAYER5>.~
@2710 = ~[PC] I do not understand women. Mostly, I do not understand <PLAYER6>.~
@2711 = ~[PC] Why are you doing all this following me around, anyways? I would think you would have struck off on your own by now.~
@2712 = ~[PC] Never mind. I think I would rather not spar tonight, Aran, verbally or physically. I am going to turn in.~
@2713 = ~[PC] Oh, nothing much. You know, I need to sort out my own problems.~
@2714 = ~[PC] I don't know. You know, I am going to turn in. I need some sleep.~
@2715 = ~[ARAN] Oh no you don't, laddie. I got my own woman troubles, an' you don't rightly want no advice from th' likes o' me.~
@2716 = ~[ARAN] Come on, you sorry bastard... enough wi' the chit-chat. We got places what to go, things what to see, an' creatures what to kill. An' a good night's sleep be just th' right way to get started.~
@2717 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know. But I back a friend, no matter what. Even if they don't always be actin' friendly themselves, eh? It just be th' way things are.~
@2718 = ~[ARAN] Come on, you sorry bastard... enough wi' the chit-chat. We done got places to go, things what to see, an' creatures what to kill. An' a good night's sleep be just th' right way to get started.~
@2719 = ~[ARAN] Oh no you don't, laddie. You will be naught but trouble for me if I don't get enough rest. I'm out, eh?~
@2720 = ~[ARAN] We got places what to go, things what to see, an' creatures what to kill. An' a good night's sleep be just th' right way to get started.~
@2721 = ~[ARAN] Right then.. what be th' problem? You gettin' tired?~
@2722 = ~[PC] I just needed a breath of fresh air. You are starting to send out a powerful stench. Come on, let's spar!~
@2723 = ~[PC] Just tired of your big mouth. Come on, let's spar!~
@2724 = ~[PC] I don't know. You know, I am going to turn in. I need some sleep. I am not having much fun doing this.~
@2725 = ~[ARAN] Mielikki's Quick temper, I done just.. just.. oh, hells. Fine. Go to bed. I be gettin' on wi' th' chores, like a blighted good little boy.~
@2726 = ~[PC] Good night, Aran.~
@2727 = ~[PC] Good to see you follow orders so well.~
@2728 = ~[PC] I was joking, Aran. Come on, we should head back to camp. Unless you feel like running a few miles, just to get ready for sleep?~
@2729 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, sometimes I do, sometimes no. But I don't think I'll be askin' you to do the same. That blouse looks right pretty, it does. Especially as I can see right through it in this moonlight.~
@2730 = ~[PC] (Quickly pull your jerkin closer around you.) Are you going to gawk, or are you going to fight?~
@2731 = ~[PC] (Cross over in front of him.) All part of my plan to distract you and win, of course.~
@2732 = ~[PC] (Loosen your blouse, allowing the silk to billow gently in the night breeze.) I simply need the freedom to move. A gentleman would not look so closely.~
@2733 = ~[PC] You are being silly again, Aran. Stop joking around. You can see very well that I am still in my armor.~
@2734 = ~[PC] (blush) Aran, I... I...~
@2735 = ~[ARAN] No, no... I was stretchin' out, is all. I don't rightly suppose I should ask you to match me, eh? Well, no matter...~
@2736 = ~[PC] Any decent mage will tell you that a good, well tailored robe is the first line of defense. I think you should stop talking and start sparring, Aran.~
@2737 = ~[PC] Warcries, distracting sounds, blabbering on about my beauty, all valid combat tactics, Aran. But really, aren't we both a little to seasoned for such distractions? Put your sword to use instead of your tongue.~
@2738 = ~[PC] In my profession, it is important to learn when to hide one's assets, and when to display them. Less talk and much more action, please.~
@2739 = ~[PC] I think you should stop talking and start fighting, Aran. Good intentions pale in comparison with actions.~
@2740 = ~[PC] I think you should stop talking and start fighting, Aran. The gods prefer actions over platitudes. Besides, you need to be taught your place.~
@2741 = ~[PC] I think you should stop talking and start fighting, Aran. I shall endeavor to show you the essence of spiritual focus, or at least give you a good drubbing.~
@2742 = ~[PC] A good spar to clear the head and focus the mind. Come, now, Aran. Let us have a clean fight.~
@2743 = ~[PC] I think I will keep my top on, thank you.~
@2744 = ~[PC] You could ask. But my answer would be no. Besides, that is a highly unromantic suggestion.~
@2745 = ~[PC] (Bare your torso, stripping to the waist to match him.)~
@2746 = ~[ARAN] That you be. An' in th' moonlight, I don't know what be prettier... you, or a full contract tight-bound.~
@2747 = ~[PC] Are you comparing me to a bundle of dried, ink-covered sheepskin?~
@2748 = ~[PC] Me. I am prettier. See? (Spin slowly, raising your arms).~
@2749 = ~[PC] Laugh all you want, monkey boy. I have come to show you your inadequacies!~
@2750 = ~[PC] Talk is cheap. Show me you can fight.~
@2751 = ~[PC] Talk is cheap. (Punch him hard in the gut.)~
@2752 = ~[PC] You do not seem to get the idea. I am interested in friendship, nothing more. Are we going to spar, or talk?~
@2753 = ~[PC] Yes. Sex. With you. Right here. Right now.~
@2754 = ~[PC] Well, there are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather.~
@2755 = ~[PC] I want... I... I do not know what I want.~
@2756 = ~[ARAN] Now, what could be more amorous than to be swordfightin' in th' moonlight? Where be your sense o' romance, o' foreplay, o' gettin' all hot an' bothered?~
@2757 = ~[PC] The whole idea turns me off completely. I think I will just go to bed.~
@2758 = ~[PC] No, I am fine with avoiding complications. Have a good night, Aran.~
@2759 = ~[PC] I guess that actions are louder than words. (Wrap your arms around him, kissing him, and slipping your hands someplace very warm.)~
@2760 = ~[PC] You have a point. But I think I am ready for that match, now.~
@2761 = ~[PC] I can think of many more romantic notions, Aran. Do you think fighting is the way into my heart?~
@2762 = ~[ARAN] I... I...~
@2763 = ~[PC] The great Whitehand, Pride of the Sword Coast, laid speechless by the sight of a partially naked woman. I think I will just go to bed.~
@2764 = ~[PC] Oh, my... I seem to have had a minor wardrobe malfunction. No matter... I will cover up again, just to be fair.~
@2765 = ~[PC] Look all you want - it will not change the fact that we are never sleeping together. I am interested in friendship, nothing more. Are we going to spar, or talk?~
@2766 = ~[PC] I do not know why I did that. (Cover yourself).~
@2767 = ~[PC] I can think of many more romantic notions than stripping in the moonlight, only to spoil it with weapons.~
@2768 = ~[ARAN] Look, I am not rightly sure how to try to romance you, <CHARNAME>. There be so many ways you are not quite th' normal... err... Helm's Beard, that came out wrong...~
@2769 = ~[PC] So you think calling me abnormal is the way to get me interested. Fascinating.~
@2770 = ~[PC] You do no have to try so hard, you know. You could just kiss me.~
@2771 = ~[PC] Aran, I keep telling you we are just friends. If you are here to spar, then let's spar. With foils, not with words, please.~
@2772 = ~[PC] You could try flowers, or chocolate, or just listening to me, you know.~
@2773 = ~[PC] I think I am ready for that sparring match, now.~
@2774 = ~[ARAN] Now then, I don't rightly have th' practice equipment for Waterdeep Twin Swords style, just starlight... err. Just *straight* practice foils for duellin' wi' out harm.~
@2775 = ~[PC] 'starlight'?~
@2776 = ~[PC] That will do just fine.~
@2777 = ~[PC] Cut the clumsy attempts at seduction, sellsword. Save it for your tavern slatterns.~
@2778 = ~[PC] Wait a minute. You have not finished all your chores. There are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather.~
@2779 = ~[PC] Too much talk, not enough action. You missed your opportunity, Aran. I am going to bed.~
@2780 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Delight, <CHARNAME>, I be right sorry. Here, have a jerkin to cover up. I didn't mean to upset you. You just can tear a man's heart right out wi' your beauty, is all.~
@2781 = ~[PC] I am not beautiful.~
@2782 = ~[PC] I know.~
@2783 = ~[PC] Are you going to teach me how to spar?~
@2784 = ~[PC] You say such strange things sometimes.~
@2785 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, that came out all wrong, that did! Though your skin be as beautiful as a blank sheet o' vellum, ready for new scribin'.~
@2786 = ~[PC] Why, thank you. And your compliments are as smooth as a crumpled dishrag.~
@2787 = ~[PC] You can save the feeble attempts at compliments. Throw me a foil, and let's spar.~
@2788 = ~[PC] My dearest Aran, you have so much to learn about women. Perhaps a sound thrashing will help.~
@2789 = ~[PC] You keep talking like I am interested in you. I am interested in friendship, nothing more. Are we going to spar, or talk?~
@2790 = ~[ARAN] I do believe you, there. No contest - you look right pretty, you do. An' there's somethin' about moonlight or starlight what sets you off right dangerously, it does.~
@2791 = ~[PC] That is quite poetic, Sir Aran. When did you begin studying courtship and chivalry?~
@2792 = ~[PC] Actually, Aran, I have never fenced before. Do you think you could teach me?~
@2793 = ~[ARAN] *gasp* What in th' nine hells was that for?~
@2794 = ~[PC] I do not know. You confuse me so much that sometimes, I just feel like I have to hit you or I will explode. Throw me a foil.~
@2795 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap a bit o' company?~
@2796 = ~[PC] No, no thank you. Look, this was a mistake. I am headed back to camp. Have a good night, Aran.~
@2797 = ~[PC] On second thought, I think I might need some energy worked off. Why don't we spar.~
@2798 = ~[PC] My, you just push your luck at every opportunity, don't you?~
@2799 = ~[PC] No, thank you. But I do think there are some things you can do for me. Let's see... there are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather.~
@2800 = ~[ARAN] Mielikki's Quick temper, I done just.. just.. oh, hells. Fine. Go to bed. I be gettin' on wi' th' chores, like a good little blighted boy. (Damn females, anyways. Th' bloody creatures never did have no sense, an' they are a right pain in th' left buttock, they are).~
@2801 = ~[PC] Did you say something?~
@2802 = ~[PC] (Damned males, anyways... they never clean up after themselves, and never have the good sense to kiss a girl goodnight when she is practically throwing herself at them).~
@2803 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I could do that. But flowers, they don't speak to your strength. They seem all scawy when compared to you, too. An' chocolate be nice, but it seems soft an' usual, which... oh, by th' nine blighted hells, I'm walkin' my feet right into my mouth, aren't I.~
@2804 = ~[PC] But I like chocolate. And I like flowers.~
@2805 = ~[PC] I do not think 'scawy' is a word.~
@2806 = ~[PC] I was joking, Aran. Flowers are a waste of time, and chocolate is overrated. I value actions and deeds over useless gestures.~
@2807 = ~[PC] Do not worry, Aran. You were born with both feet planted firmly in your mouth. I will simply have to teach you how to avoid that.~
@2808 = ~[PC] I get what you mean, Aran. But I think you will do better by just tossing me a foil and starting the practice. If I let you ramble on about me, soon I will be an unusual thorny flower with non-chocolate petals with a nice bottom. And you will be spending the next three tendays apologizing. We should just practice fighting!~
@2809 = ~[ARAN] Look, this is comin' out all confused-like. An' there's somethin' about moonlight or starlight what sets you off right dangerously, it does.~
@2810 = ~[PC] Well then, why not see exactly how dangerous I can be. Why don't we spar.~
@2811 = ~[ARAN] I'm not rightly sure I know what you mean. I take my time writin', but I figure if a lad is gettin' fancy in his speech, he is just hidin' behind a shield. Better to be up front an' honest, as th' lady in question will find out th' true man soon enough.~
@2812 = ~[PC] Well, I don't enjoy wasting my time with someone with that attitude. Clear the wax out of your ears, and listen to what I was hinting. I prefer sophisticated gentlemen. Good night.~
@2813 = ~[PC] This is getting a little personal. Look, just put up your sword and fight, OK?~
@2814 = ~[PC] I guess that actions are clearer than words. (Wrap your arms around him, kissing him, and tucking your hands someplace very warm.)~
@2815 = ~[PC] You know, Aran, I have never fenced before. Do you think you could teach me?~
@2816 = ~[ARAN] Good gods, woman, you are a study in contradictions, you are. You twist my words around right proper, an' now you talk about wantin' me?~
@2817 = ~[PC] I did not say I wanted you. Clear the wax out of your ears. Good night.~
@2818 = ~[PC] I think we both are a little confused, by now. Look, just put up your sword and fight, OK?~
@2819 = ~[ARAN] That I could, I guess. It be a might forward, but then again, mayhap you want me to be a bit overbearin', eh?~
@2820 = ~[PC] It spoils all the fun if you have to be coached. Just do what you know you want to do, Aran. Quickly, fiercely, and thoroughly.~
@2821 = ~[PC] Sorry, you missed your opportunity. Let's spar!~
@2822 = ~[PC] Well, we have established you are not aggressive enough in romance. Show me that at least you can fight.~
@2823 = ~[PC] What, are you some kind of weakling? (Punch him hard in the gut.)~
@2824 = ~[ARAN] Must be somethin' wrong wi' me. Sorry. Caught sight o' your eyes, an' got distracted. Won't happen again. Here, let's get goin', eh?~
@2825 = ~[ARAN] (Aran catches your chin quickly, turning your face to his) To me, you are right beautiful. Hanali Celanil an' Sune are but pale comparisons, <CHARNAME>.~
@2826 = ~[PC] (Kiss him.)~
@2827 = ~[PC] (Break away quickly.) Are we going to spar, or talk?~
@2828 = ~[PC] (Look him directly in the eyes.) Big words. But a real man would not talk. He would take what he wants.~
@2829 = ~[PC] (Look him directly in the eyes, and slam your fist into his gut.)~
@2830 = ~[PC] And you, sir, are nearly as cute as you think you are. Nearly.~
@2831 = ~[ARAN] Not on your life, girl... I'm done wi' getting my nose broke on account o' you gotta let off some steam. You got anythin' else you want me to do for you? Mayhap somethin' that don't rightly hurt so much?~
@2832 = ~[PC] Well, there are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather. You should go do that, instead. I doubt you could please me any other way.~
@2833 = ~[PC] But lovemaking is supposed to hurt a little, don't you think?~
@2834 = ~[PC] I came out here because you are a friend, Aran. And I need all of those I can get right now.~
@2835 = ~[ARAN] Funny thing is, <CHARNAME>, you got strange ways o' showin' it, but I do believe you.~
@2836 = ~[ARAN] Look, sometimes we be seein' different things in th' way o' how life is supposed to be, I guess. But whether I like your actions or no, an' whether you be god, bad, or indifferent, there be somethin' about you I like right fine.~
@2837 = ~[ARAN] You might use that against me later on, I wager, but hells... I done flipped your coin to Tymora early on, an' it came back heads. I'll call you friend long after you've forgotten I exist. Let's get you back to camp, an' get somethin' nice an' warm in your stomach.~
@2838 = ~[ARAN] Well, I do thank you, I think. Now, do you want to spar, or not, eh?~
@2839 = ~[PC] We spar.~
@2840 = ~[ARAN] No, naught. I was just mutterin' to myself.~
@2841 = ~[ARAN] I thought you might say that. Problem is, I don't rightly believin forcin' that sort o' thing.~
@2842 = ~[PC] You are so weak. I have exactly what I want - proof you do not have the strength to overpower me and take what you want. Have a nice night, Aran. And thank you for the practice session.~
@2843 = ~[PC] What if I was play-acting the whole resistance thing... (Draw one sharp fingernail lightly down his chest, following it with your gaze.)~
@2844 = ~[PC] I, on the other hand, have absolutely no compunction about taking exactly when I want, how I want it.~
@2845 = ~[PC] Well, enough fun. I think this enough sparring for one night, in any area. Have a good night, Aran.~
@2846 = ~[PC] (Begin unfastening your clothes.) If you need instruction, then I have sadly misjudged you, Aran. Do what comes naturally, of course.~
@2847 = ~[ARAN] I think you might be...~
@2848 = ~[PC] ...a little unsure of myself? Hardly. Just hold me, Aran. Make me feel alive. Just be a good friend and hold me.~
@2849 = ~[PC] ...a little confusing to you? I am confused, too. Look, let's just get a few rounds of swordfighting in, and be done with it.~
@2850 = ~[PC] This was a bad idea. I think I will just go to bed. Alone.~
@2851 = ~[PC] (Kiss him again and move deeper into his arms.)~
@2852 = ~[ARAN] Hey, What are you after, <CHARNAME>? You be not quite into th' sparrin', I think. Why did you come out here, anyways?~
@2853 = ~[PC] I... I do not know. I was bored, and wanted amusement?~
@2854 = ~[PC] I... I do not know. I thought I wanted to have someone want me, desire me. But now I really just feel like that will make things worse. I think I should go now.~
@2855 = ~[PC] I came here to be made love to, silly. So shut up and get to it!~
@2856 = ~[PC] (Kiss his neck and move deeper into his arms.)~
@2857 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. I think I am goin' to go get some energy worked out o' my system, eh? I will see you back at camp.~
@2858 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>, I can do that, I can. I can hold your hand right proper. An' I value your friendship above any treasure what's been thought of.~
@2859 = ~[ARAN] (You stand together for a time holding hands, watching the stars and the moonlight, before returning to camp.)~
@2860 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>, I can do that, I can. I can hold you right proper. An' I value your friendship above any treasure what's been thought of.~
@2861 = ~[ARAN] (You stand together for a time in the moonlight holding each other, before returning to camp.)~
@2862 = ~[ARAN] Did you say somethin', <CHARNAME>?~
@2863 = ~[PC] No, not a thing. Good night, Aran.~
@2864 = ~[PC] I said, 'damned males, anyways... they never clean up after themselves, and never have the good sense to kiss a girl goodnight when she is practically throwing herself at them'.~
@2865 = ~[PC] I said, 'If Aran does not kiss me right this minute, I will make his life a living hell for all eternity'.~
@2866 = ~[ARAN] That makes sense, but you be phrasin' that as a question. Are you sure there be no other ways I could entertain you?~
@2867 = ~[PC] Look, I am going about this all wrong. Just put up your sword and fight me, OK?~
@2868 = ~[PC] Yes, there are. but I am not in the mood tonight. I bet that will give you some interesting dreams...~
@2869 = ~[PC] You could hold my hand for a minute. I just need to feel like... I just need to feel supported.~
@2870 = ~[ARAN] Well, a man can have imagination, can't he? I was just hopin' to get you out of all that armor, is all.~
@2871 = ~[PC] (Unstrap your armor, dropping it where it falls, advancing toward him.) If you insist. We will see if your swordplay matches your bold words.~
@2872 = ~[PC] Less talk, boyo. Toss me a weapon, and let's see how this all works out.~
@2873 = ~[PC] Nice try. I shall retain my modesty, thank you. And stop flexing your chest like that, it is distracting.~
@2874 = ~[PC] Stop thinking with the wrong sword. I believe the phrase is 'en garde'?~
@2875 = ~[PC] Stop, please... you are embarrassing me...~
@2876 = ~[ARAN] Aye, it would be a pleasure to teach you. Here, hold it like this...~
@2877 = ~[PC] Just like this? (Move into his arms, awkwardly holding the foil at arms length.)~
@2878 = ~[PC] Just like this? (Move into his arms, nestling back into his chest.)~
@2879 = ~[PC] Just like this? (Nervously stand in front of him, holding the foil down.)~
@2880 = ~[PC] Just like this? (Smile sweetly at him, and punch him hard in the gut.)~
@2881 = ~[PC] HEY. Hands off, Aran. I am interested in friendship, nothing more. Are we going to spar, or are you going to keep making passes at me?~
@2882 = ~[ARAN] Aye. Only you need to hold your wrist like this... an' your waist, it be better here... sorry, didn't rightly mean to touch you there... now gentle-like, lean in like this...~
@2883 = ~[PC] (Rest your head back on his shoulder, falling into a slow dance of movements.)~
@2884 = ~[PC] It would be very nice, except your hands keep wandering. I am interested in friendship, nothing more. Are we going to spar, or talk?~
@2885 = ~[PC] (Rest your head back on his shoulder, nuzzling his neck.)~
@2886 = ~[ARAN] There you go. Nothin' to it. You dance right fine, an' duelin's just like dancin', only with a point, eh? I mean, a point system. I guess there be a point to dancin', too.~
@2887 = ~[PC] (Lean your head back onto his shoulder and offer your lips to him.)~
@2888 = ~[PC] Interesting approach, but I have had enough of it. But I do think there are some things you can do for me. Let's see... there are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather.~
@2889 = ~[ARAN] Well, no. You don't have no shield, so you want to get a good profile, an' make as small a target as possible.~
@2890 = ~[PC] Is that what you are staring at? My 'profile'?~
@2891 = ~[PC] I think I am ready to try this out.~
@2892 = ~[PC] Show me what you have, boyo. Is your blade as fast as your tongue?~
@2893 = ~[ARAN] That be my story, an' I'm stickin' to it. Here, try this. Knees slightly bent, side toward me, an' blade down toward my knee. This be a dancer's weapon, not for use on th' shield wall.~
@2894 = ~[PC] I tire of this. I want a different kind of thrust and parry. (Drop your foil and fling yourself hard into his arms.)~
@2895 = ~[PC] I am ready to fight. I do not need more instruction.~
@2896 = ~[PC] I have been playing with you, Aran. Hull taught me well, back in Candlekeep. I will try not to hurt you too badly.~
@2897 = ~[ARAN] Well now, if you be interested in that, I think that we be doin' th' wrong kind o' sparrin', eh? But let's stick to th' business at hand.~
@2898 = ~[PC] (Thrust savagely directly at his chest.)~
@2899 = ~[PC] (Kick hard toward his knee.)~
@2900 = ~[PC] (Barely catch the rapier, fumbling with it.) How do you work this thing, anyways?~
@2901 = ~[PC] (Clumsily catch the rapier, gouging your finger on part of the hilt.) Oh!~
@2902 = ~[ARAN] (His rapier dances forward, boring toward your left shoulder.)~
@2903 = ~[PC] (Twist your wrist, deflecting his blow and flicking your blade toward his throat.)~
@2904 = ~[PC] Is that a rabbit in your pocket, or are you just happy to see me?~
@2905 = ~[PC] So, do you give up? (Thrust savagely toward his right shoulder.)~
@2906 = ~[PC] Come on, you know you want to surrender to me... or do I want to surrender myself tp you? (Slash your foil toward his throat.)~
@2907 = ~[PC] I seem to be doing quite well. But your face is turning a little red, Aran (Thrust savagely toward his right shoulder.)~
@2908 = ~[PC] This fight feels like it has gone on for hours... (Twist quickly, ducking under his blade.)~
@2909 = ~[ARAN] (Soft moonlight falls across his face as he circles to the right, sword's point toward you.)~
@2910 = ~[PC] (Thrust savagely toward his left knee.)~
@2911 = ~[PC] I thought that you were a fighter, Aran. What is the matter, are you afraid I am too delicate a flower to fight?~
@2912 = ~[PC] I do not know about this, Aran. You look... you... I want to...~
@2913 = ~[PC] (Feint left, but duck quickly under his guard and slap him solidly across the face.)~
@2914 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, do you need some instruction? I thought we was sparrin', not passin' th' time. Not that you don't make th' perfect picture, I must admit.~
@2915 = ~[PC] (Thrust savagely toward his right shoulder.)~
@2916 = ~[PC] The perfect picture of your demise, you mean?~
@2917 = ~[ARAN] (A spark strikes as his counterstroke sends your sword's point off to the left.)~
@2918 = ~[PC] (Duck past him, slamming the pommel of the foil against the back of his head as you pass.)~
@2919 = ~[PC] (Close quickly, ducking inside of his swinging arc and slamming your fist into his ribs.)~
@2920 = ~[PC] (Parry each of his thrusts, circling, seeking a gap in his defenses.)~
@2921 = ~[ARAN] Now, m' lady sword-swinger, that would have been a point to me. Not bad for a sellsword, eh? Just don't be usin' none o' those fancy powers o' yours to make up th' difference.~
@2922 = ~[ARAN] A point to you, there, if we had been keepin' score. A lucky shot? Or do you be just gettin' warmed up?~
@2923 = ~[PC] Oh, ouch! I just cut myself.~
@2924 = ~[PC] I have had enough of this. The only swordplay I want right now has nothing to do with foils. (Throw your foil on the ground in front of him.)~
@2925 = ~[ARAN] Now, where were we... oh, we were gettin' you all hot an' bothered...~
@2926 = ~[PC] Come on, you know you want to surrender to me... (Slash your foil toward his throat.)~
@2927 = ~[PC] Hey, is that a rabbit in your pocket, or are you just happy to see me?~
@2928 = ~[ARAN] Well, we be gettin' some exercise, I do believe. Though you be pantin' somethin' fierce. It does right nice things to your profile, from what I be seein'...~
@2929 = ~[PC] Enjoy the show while you can. It will make my revenge far sweeter!~
@2930 = ~[PC] (Kick hard toward his groin, following up with a stab toward his heart.)~
@2931 = ~[PC] Is that all you have? (kick hard toward his knee.)~
@2932 = ~[PC] Wait a second... hold on, I have to do something... (adjust your clothing to show off your leg to mid-thigh, and then instantly launch an attack when he is distracted.)~
@2933 = ~[PC] I think it is you, Aran, feeling the pressure of my superior skills. Either that, or the way I move is just a little too distracting for you...~
@2934 = ~[ARAN] (He dances back, then counters, rapier hissing in low and straight.)~
@2935 = ~[PC] (Drop your rapier and tuck yourself into a ball, flinging yourself hard into his arms as he desperately windmills trying to avoid piercing you.)~
@2936 = ~[PC] (Twist away quickly, then advance with a flurry of quick strokes.)~
@2937 = ~[PC] (Deflect his foil, flicking your blade toward his throat.)~
@2938 = ~[ARAN] I'm not bloody well fallin' for that old trick, but I'd like to see some other things untied, eh?~
@2939 = ~[ARAN] (Hard muscle blocks your path, and the riposte stabs toward your right side.)~
@2940 = ~[PC] Enough! I do not want to do this any more.~
@2941 = ~[ARAN] (Soft moonlight falls across his face as he circles you, sword's point extended.)~
@2942 = ~[ARAN] (The point of his blade whistles close past your guard, seeking your left inner thigh.)~
@2943 = ~[PC] (Step inside of his thrust, then dance out of the way, circling around to his left.)~
@2944 = ~[PC] Stop. I do not want to spar. I want you.~
@2945 = ~[ARAN] Hah. Now do you be talkin' swordplay, or playin' wi' words? Not that it rightly matters - I can tire you out either way you intended, you know.~
@2946 = ~[PC] Promises, promises... (Kick hard toward his knee.)~
@2947 = ~[PC] Yes, yes... you said that before.~
@2948 = ~[PC] (Drop your rapier and fling yourself hard into his arms.)~
@2949 = ~[PC] Hang you and your paternalistic crap! (Send a spinning kick toward his head.)~
@2950 = ~[ARAN] (He falls back, blade countering blade, teeth bared savagely in the moonlight.)~
@2951 = ~[ARAN] Well, we be sparrin'... no score, just for th' practice. It ends when you say it ends, or when one o' us calls quarter.~
@2952 = ~[ARAN] (Blades clash, sparks bright in the shadows.)~
@2953 = ~[ARAN] (Blades clash, ringing in your ears.)~
@2954 = ~[ARAN] Aye, you are gettin' th' hang o' this, eh?~
@2955 = ~[PC] Oh, I am getting the hang of this. But I heard that you have troubles... you are not so well hung as you claim? (Lunge forward to pink his right shoulder.)~
@2956 = ~[PC] I... I am not so sure... (Guard closely, on the defensive, parrying each of his thrusts.)~
@2957 = ~[PC] No, not at all. But you seem to be having troubles winning, yourself. (Drop your rapier and fling yourself hard into his arms.)~
@2958 = ~[PC] Child's play. A fitting moniker, seeing as I am sparring with you. (Spin lightly, then check yourself and lunge forward, foil tip to the right leg.)~
@2959 = ~[PC] Stop for a bit. Truce!~
@2960 = ~[ARAN] You know, I do believe there be nothin' prettier than a lass what be sweatin' so fierce.~
@2961 = ~[PC] We 'lasses' do not sweat. We glow. We 'Mist'. (Send a spinning kick toward his head.)~
@2962 = ~[PC] That is nice to hear. You look pretty, too. Tired yet? (Lunge forward to pink his right shoulder.)~
@2963 = ~[PC] I can think of prettier things... like figuring out what your next line of attack will be... (Guard closely, on the defensive, parrying each of his thrusts.)~
@2964 = ~[PC] Nice picture. Pity you stink like a mule when you sweat. (Fling yourself hard into his arms, attempting to knock him down.)~
@2965 = ~[PC] Didn't your mother ever teach you to keep your mouth closed when you need to concentrate? (Spin lightly, then check yourself and lunge forward, foil tip to the right leg.)~
@2966 = ~[ARAN] I do believe you blighted well nicked me!~
@2967 = ~[PC] Quick, shall we call a healer for your little boo boo? (Send a spinning kick toward his head.)~
@2968 = ~[PC] I'm so terribly sorry. That was the point, right? (Lunge forward to pink his right shoulder.)~
@2969 = ~[PC] I'm sorry... do you want to stop? (Guard closely, on the defensive, parrying each of his thrusts.)~
@2970 = ~[PC] Oh, Aran! (Drop your rapier and fling yourself hard into his arms.)~
@2971 = ~[PC] Well, when you play with me, you play with fire. Or ice. Or lightning. In fact, you could cut to the chase and just say you are running with scissors. (Spin lightly, then check yourself and lunge forward, foil tip to the right leg.)~
@2972 = ~[ARAN] Celanil's Sweet Lips, let me see... are you hurt?~
@2973 = ~[PC] HAH! (as he moves forward dropping his guard, place the tip of your foil at the base of his throat.)~
@2974 = ~[PC] It is just a little cut. But I think you should kiss it better.~
@2975 = ~[PC] It is nothing. Besides, you have a scratch or two, too. But I think I have had enough for one night. Have a good rest, Aran.~
@2976 = ~[PC] There will be blood tonight! (Advance with a ferocious whirlwind of quick strokes.)~
@2977 = ~[ARAN] (Aran staggers, surprised, arms enfolding you.)~
@2978 = ~[ARAN] What in Bane's... <CHARNAME>?~
@2979 = ~[PC] (*whisper*) I do not want to spar. I just want you.~
@2980 = ~[PC] HAH! (Spin out of his arms, duck down, grab the foil, and flick it toward Aran's throat.)~
@2981 = ~[PC] I call truce!~
@2982 = ~[PC] I think I just got cut...~
@2983 = ~[PC] I am tired. Tired of everything. Look, Aran, just hold me. As a friend? Just hold me.~
@2984 = ~[ARAN] Bane's Blood, did I hurt you? Here, let me see that...~
@2985 = ~[PC] (Punch him hard in the gut.)~
@2986 = ~[PC] Ow! You just broke one of my nails. I spent a long time getting them just the right length. And that is not easy while adventuring!~
@2987 = ~[PC] That hurt. Perhaps giving you a sound thrashing will help ease the pain.~
@2988 = ~[PC] Look, obviously I am not that proficient with this weapon. Perhaps you would teach me how to hold it?~
@2989 = ~[ARAN] Well, I'm right sorry, I am. I didn't mean to hurt you none. Is there somethin' I can do to make up for it?~
@2990 = ~[PC] Kiss it better. (Hold your hand out to him imperiously.)~
@2991 = ~[PC] Well, there are still some cooking pots you have not cleaned, and there is firewood to gather. I don't want to do any silly old sparring anyways. I'm going to bed.~
@2992 = ~[PC] No, no... a minor annoyance. Prepare to be defeated.~
@2993 = ~[PC] I think I have had enough excitement. I call this a draw. We will have to do this again sometime.~
@2994 = ~[ARAN] (He gently takes you hand, and kisses each fingertip.)~
@2995 = ~[ARAN] Is that better?~
@2996 = ~[PC] Perhaps. But it hurts a little higher up.~
@2997 = ~[PC] No, no... it is fine now. A minor annoyance. Prepare to be defeated.~
@2998 = ~[PC] I bet you do that to everyone's fingers.~
@2999 = ~[PC] Yes, it is fine. Let's spar now!~
@3000 = ~[ARAN] (He gently kisses the inside of your palm and carefully kisses each wrist.)~
@3001 = ~[PC] Perhaps. But it now aches a little lower down...~
@3002 = ~[ARAN] (He gently kisses his way up to your mouth, leaning in and savoring your lips.)~
@3003 = ~[PC] Yes, it is fine. But I think I want you to teach me how to hold this thing.~
@3004 = ~[ARAN] Aye, now you be after sparrin' o' a different kind, I see. For that, I'd have to get rid o' some o' these obstacles...~
@3005 = ~[PC] (Open the front of your clothing carefully, avoiding eye contact.)~
@3006 = ~[PC] (Tear your clothing from your shoulders, baring yourself in the moonlight.)~
@3007 = ~[PC] I will not yield to you. But I will take what I want from you, right this moment.~
@3008 = ~[PC] But I think I am ready for more fencing, now. We shall see if you can concentrate on the task at hand.~
@3009 = ~[ARAN] (One strong hand reaches out to grab your shoulder as his foil batters yours down.)~
@3010 = ~[PC] Ah ah ah... no touchie-feely the girl, now... (Counter quickly, and slice inward toward his side.)~
@3011 = ~[PC] So, what were you thinking of fixing for dinner tomorrow? Aran-ke-bobs? Because I almost skewered you there.~
@3012 = ~[PC] This is... a good bit... harder than it... looks.~
@3013 = ~[ARAN] (He springs forward, blade countering blade, pushing you back.)~
@3014 = ~[PC] (Duck down quickly and slam yourself hard against his legs, attempting to knock him off his feet.)~
@3015 = ~[PC] (Twist frantically to avoid his blade, moving back.)~
@3016 = ~[ARAN] (The clash of steel rings as his counterstroke sends your sword's point off to the right.)~
@3017 = ~[PC] (Send a spinning kick toward his head.)~
@3018 = ~[PC] (Lunge forward to pink his right shoulder.)~
@3019 = ~[PC] (Spin lightly, then check yourself and lunge forward, foil tip to the right leg.)~
@3020 = ~[ARAN] No rabbit, but now I know where you are lookin', I can use that to my advantage...~
@3021 = ~[PC] (Slash toward his head.)~
@3022 = ~[PC] Oh, Aran - why look when I can feel! (Drop your rapier and fling yourself hard into his arms.)~
@3023 = ~[PC] Just be careful. I am not sure we want the makings of rabbit stew.  (Spin lightly, then check yourself and lunge forward, foil tip to the right leg.)~
@3024 = ~[ARAN] Right, we can take a break. What are you after, anyways, <CHARNAME>? You be not quite into th' sparrin', I think. Why did you come out here?~
@3025 = ~[PC] I just needed a moment to regroup. (Flick your foil point toward his throat.)~
@3026 = ~[ARAN] OUCH! Ilmater's Sufferin', that bloody well hurt! What in th' nine hells do you be after, <CHARNAME>?~
@3027 = ~[PC] I am taking advantage of your weakness. You let your guard down, Aran, and I was right there to take advantage. Are we going to spar? I think you need to be taught more.~
@3028 = ~[PC] I do not know. But back away, and let's get fighting again.~
@3029 = ~[ARAN] Well, if you want to play that way... (His arm catches you solidly across the chest, knocking you over.)~
@3030 = ~[PC] Well, now that I am down here, do you want to come and join me?~
@3031 = ~[PC] (Roll over onto your back and stretch, beginning to daintily removing anything that would hide your body from his eyes). You win. Come and take your spoils of war.~
@3032 = ~[PC] Oooohh... just the way I like them. Rough, stupid, and easily provoked... (sweep his legs, slamming him to the ground.)~
@3033 = ~[PC] Ouch! Gods, Aran, I was only joking.~
@3034 = ~[ARAN] I do believe you blighted well tricked me! That hurt, it did. What do you want, anyways? It don't rightly look like you want to spar.~
@3035 = ~[PC] Well, when you play with me, you play with fire. Or ice. Or lightning. In fact, you could cut to the chase and just say you are running with scissors.~
@3036 = ~[PC] *whisper* I do not want to spar. I just want you.~
@3037 = ~[ARAN] (Aran staggers, surprised, slamming to the ground next to you.)~
@3038 = ~[PC] HAH! (Spin out of his arms, roll, grab the foil, and point it at Aran.)~
@3039 = ~[ARAN] True enough. Well, you done got me here. Mayhap I can make th' most o' my opportunity...~
@3040 = ~[ARAN] (With a sudden twist he is on top of you, crushing you, his arms holding yours hard above your head.) Surrender, or do I take my winnin's right now?~
@3041 = ~[PC] Get off me, idiot. Game over. If you value your life, that is.~
@3042 = ~[PC] I... (roll over, pinning him) ...will do exactly... (bury your face in his neck) ... as I please.~
@3043 = ~[PC] Take what you will.~
@3044 = ~[ARAN] (He rolls away, coming to his knees before you.)~
@3045 = ~[ARAN] I surrender.  An' what will you do wi' th spoils, <CHARNAME>?~
@3046 = ~[PC] Absolutely nothing. I have exactly what I want. Have a nice night, Aran. And thank you for the practice session.~
@3047 = ~[PC] I was thinking of an armistice. (Roll over and kneel with him, drawing one sharp fingernail lightly down his chest, following it with your gaze.)~
@3048 = ~[PC] I... (roll up, grab the back of his head and tug him back down to you fiercely) ...will do exactly... (bury your face in his neck) ...as I please.~
@3049 = ~[PC] Practice a completely different form of combat.~
@3050 = ~[ARAN] Hey, if you keep goin' on like that, there will be a mite bit o' different kind o' sparrin' goin' on tonight...~
@3051 = ~[PC] And the light dawns... gods, man, I am literally sprawled at your feet, here for the taking. Are you slow, or do you need instruction?~
@3052 = ~[PC] Well, we do not want to have any of that, now, do we. This is boring anyways. Look, let's just get a few rounds of swordfighting in, and be done with it. But I might leave some of these clothes off... it could provide a good distraction.~
@3053 = ~[PC] On second thought, the whole idea turns me off completely. I think I will just go to bed.~
@3054 = ~[PC] That is not fair! You can't touch a lady there! You are tickling me! (Swat at Aran with your hands.)~
@3055 = ~[ARAN] All be fair in love an' war - an' what we got goin' on now counts as both, in my book! Come on, there, get up an' fight, eh?~
@3056 = ~[PC] The only love I have for you is the love of watching you lose, big boy. Hold on while I get up, and then let's see if you can survive.~
@3057 = ~[PC] Well in that case, expect no quarter from me! En garde. I will make you wish you had settled for a tickle-fight!~
@3058 = ~[PC] Look, do not get the wrong idea. I just want to be friends. But I would not mind sampling a few benefits... but if you want to fight, then we will spar.~
@3059 = ~[PC] You are no fun at all. But you will be, when you take me seriously. I mean that. Take me. Seriously.~
@3060 = ~[ARAN] I do take you right serious... oh. Oh. You mean... well, now, it would be rude o' me not to oblige. If you wouldn't mind liftin' those delicious hips o' yours up a little, we could get some o' these silly clothes out o' your way...~
@3061 = ~[ARAN] As opposed to just your fingers, or as opposed to me kissin' somethin' else?~
@3062 = ~[PC] Spare me the talk of your many boisterous adventurers, Aran. They are all probably made up, anyways.~
@3063 = ~[PC] Enough talk, just teach me to spar.~
@3064 = ~[PC] Put your blade up, and we will see who can fight, who can talk, and who can do both at the same time.~
@3065 = ~[ARAN] I do tell some tall tales. But for you, there be nothin' but truth. I have had my share o' lovers, but you are in a class by yourself.~
@3066 = ~[PC] So I am stupid, held out with need of a personal tutor?~
@3067 = ~[PC] I do not care about the truth. I want you.~
@3068 = ~[PC] I do not want the truth, and I most certainly do not want you.~
@3069 = ~[PC] Gods, Aran, all this talk, talk, talk... you are confusing me so much. I think I need to go, now. Good night.~
@3070 = ~[PC] So you have had me? I was unaware of that. Was I an acceptable lover?~
@3071 = ~[PC] This conversation is over. Do not speak another word.~
@3072 = ~[ARAN] Now, I didn't mean...~
@3073 = ~[PC] You did not mean, or you did not think?~
@3074 = ~[PC] Surrender while you are behind, because I do not think you will get out of this one. Perhaps I will be merciful.~
@3075 = ~[PC] Oh, another thing you do with all the girls - stammer and stutter. So you have no spine at all, and any pretty face and sharp tongue can slay you in an instant?~
@3076 = ~[PC] Come on, Aran, if you want to keep up with me, keep up... did you mean to tell me I was stupid and a poor lover in need of special instruction only you could give me?~
@3077 = ~[PC] I think you have annoyed me enough for one night. Good night.~
@3078 = ~[PC] It hurts when you talk like that. I do not like all this fencing with words. I can play the game, but I hate it. If you like me, kiss me. If you do not, walk away now.~
@3079 = ~[ARAN] (White moonlight flashes along swiftly moving blades as they meet point and counterpoint, weaving their harsh music. Staccato clashes of metal upon metal, ostinato breaths becoming shorter and labored, no thought but the weave of body with body... until suddenly you find yourself locked chest to chest, leg to leg, straining against each other.)~
@3080 = ~[ARAN] Do you want to be beggin' quarter?~
@3081 = ~[PC] Not likely. Look down, Aran. I think you will find I have everything in hand...~
@3082 = ~[PC] Never!~
@3083 = ~[PC] I will not yield. But I will take what I want.~
@3084 = ~[PC] Do you?~
@3085 = ~[ARAN] Now, then, you be a mite winded, there - I can see right down your front, you know. You move right beautifully when you pant like that.~
@3086 = ~[PC] (Lean hard into him, kissing him ferociously.)~
@3087 = ~[PC] (Butt your head forward hard toward his nose.)~
@3088 = ~[PC] I yield to you, Aran. In every way.~
@3089 = ~[PC] I have you right where I want you. Surrender now, and I will be merciful.~
@3090 = ~[PC] I thought this was a friendly sparring practice.~
@3091 = ~[ARAN] I... hey, I... Sune's Sweet Skin, <CHARNAME>, do you be jokin' wi' me? You drive me to a frenzy, an' now I desire you more than any man ought. What do you want o' me?~
@3092 = ~[PC] What do you think, Aran? Am I teasing? (Slowly begin to disrobe.)~
@3093 = ~[PC] I... I do not know what I want. There are so many reasons that I cannot do this...~
@3094 = ~[PC] I... (grab the back of his head and tug back fiercely) ...will do exactly... (bury his face close to your heart) ... as I please.~
@3095 = ~[PC] Somehow, it always comes down to sex with you. I said I wanted to be friends, but you keep interpreting everything as an invitation to move into my bedroll. Let me spell it out for you - N O T  I N T E R E S T E D.~
@3096 = ~[ARAN] (He steps away, dropping his sword, falling to his knees before you.)~
@3097 = ~[PC] I was thinking of an armistice. (Kneel with him, drawing one gentle finger lightly down his chest, following it with your gaze.)~
@3098 = ~[PC] I... I think I will surrender in return...~
@3099 = ~[PC] Practice a completely different form of physical combat.~
@3100 = ~[PC] I know what I want to do. But I think it is too soon. I don't think I can.~
@3101 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>...~
@3102 = ~[ARAN] (His lips burn hot on your cheeks and mouth.)~
@3103 = ~[PC] Hold on. I need to clear my head. I cannot do this!~
@3104 = ~[PC] (Lean your head forward and fold both hands against his chest.)~
@3105 = ~[PC] You... you are scaring me, a little.~
