@3331 = ~[PC] I feel nothing. That would not change my approach to combat, whether I had my soul or not.~
@3332 = ~[PC] What have you have seen on the battlefield that might be similar to what I have gone through?~
@3333 = ~[ARAN] If I could steal th' answer, I would. I'm curious, as I have seen thieves what seem to lose heart, but not their soul. Havin' no soul. Is it a good thing, or a bad thing? I mean, it might come in handy. I seen some things on a battlefield what deaden your insides right proper. Might be a kind o' freedom, in combat, not havin' to worry about nothin'.~
@3334 = ~[ARAN] I am new to all this bardic stuff, anyways. I should have read more on th' subject, but there's not much in common song or story what's coverin' this particular topic. Havin' no soul. Is it a good thing, or a bad thing? I mean, it might come in handy. I seen some things on a battlefield what deaden your insides right proper. Might be a kind o' freedom, in combat, not havin' to worry about nothin'.~
@3335 = ~[ARAN] I've been prayin' for an answer, but I must not be high enough in my god's graces to get an answer what makes sense. Havin' no soul, that is. Do it be a good thing, or a bad thing? I mean, it might come in handy. I done seen some things on a battlefield what deaden your insides right proper. Might be a kind o' freedom, in combat, not havin' to worry about nothin'.~
@3336 = ~[ARAN] This 'havin' no soul', that is. Do it be a good thing, or a bad thing? I mean, it might come in handy. I done seen some things on a battlefield what deaden your insides right proper. Might be a kind o' freedom, in combat, not havin' to worry about nothin'.~
