@3509 = ~[PC] Do all your stories involve Kravich?~
@3510 = ~[PC] Heard it. You and Kravich found out the monks that you were guarding were actually cute young female thieves in hiding, and you helped them expand the definition of 'undercover work'. Try another one.~
@3511 = ~[PC] You keep telling the story, Aran. I am going to keep my eyes on our surroundings, so if it looks like I am not paying attention, you just keep talking.~
@3512 = ~[PC] No, wait... tell me a story about your family.~
@3513 = ~[PC] Hey, what was that? Over there, behind you, I thought I saw something moving... does anyone else smell sulphur?~
@3514 = ~[ARAN] I be bloody well serious on this one - listen to yourself. If you be screamin' rage an' fear inside, that be fine. I am watchin' your back, an' I will be there to help out. But if you be screamin' rage an' hate an' power, let me know, on account o' I want to be out o' target range when you decide to smash th' world into rivers o' blood.~
@3515 = ~[ARAN] Torm's Stalwart Fist, now you be talkin' th' right kind o' story! You keep on, an' I'll just listen. I just hope it be havin' a happy endin', like they be elves smitin' th' crap out o' a whole pile o' Drow bastards...~
@3516 = ~[ARAN] Torm's Tangled Banner, that lad be in for a mite bit o' hurt. An' it don't rightly make sense, neither. Did he take his broadsword, or was he all unarmed, eh? Or do it be one o' those symbolic stories... oh, hells, I'll be just shuttin' up an' listenin'. You go on.~
@3517 = ~[ARAN] Bloody hells, no! I want naught to do wi' horror or some mad wizard experimentin' on poor unsuspectin' souls wi' polymorph spells! Forget it. I'd rather just think up some stories myself, anyways. Let me see... so a handsome, modest sellsword meets this really cute lass...~
@3518 = ~[ARAN] Bloody hells, no! I want naught to do wi' horror or some cold knife bein' tossed about! Forget it. I'd rather just think up some stories myself, anyways. Let me see... so a handsome, modest sellsword meets this really cute lass...~
@3519 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I suppose we should be thinkin' deep thoughts, an' worryin' about what be next. But hells, <CHARNAME>, There be power in distractin' yourself, an' enjoyin' life. Come on, now, tell a story, eh? Just a little one, what be funny an' happy?~
@3520 = ~[PC] No. But you tell me one.~
@3521 = ~[PC] Forget it, Aran. We should get back to business, and focus on what needs to be done.~
@3522 = ~[PC] Perhaps another time. Right now, you should pay more attention to what you are doing. Or that your codpiece has come loose...~
@3523 = ~[PC] No, I do not have a story ready. But you could tell me a story about your family.~
@3524 = ~[PC] Perhaps this one will be amusing... 'The cold passed reluctantly from the earth, and the retiring fogs revealed an army stretched out on the hills, resting.'~
@3525 = ~[ARAN] Well, let me see. Some story what gets your mind off o' things. I know... how about a joke, instead. How do you be tellin' if a Shadow Thief be dead?~
@3526 = ~[PC] They crossed me?~
@3527 = ~[PC] I have no idea.~
@3528 = ~[PC] Don't we have spells for that sort of thing?~
@3529 = ~[PC] Well, first step on their wrists, then kick the weapon they were wielding away from them, then cut off their head...~
@3530 = ~[PC] What fool kills a Shadow Thief? Oh, you mean when there are no witnesses...~
@3531 = ~[PC] Hey, some of my best friends are Shadow Thieves.~
@3532 = ~[ARAN] Hold a piece o' gold out in front o' them an' see if they grab for it. O' course, you do have to be careful, on account o' there might be a slight twitch in their fingers even hours after death, eh?~
@3533 = ~[PC] Very funny. You can tell, by the fact that I am not laughing. Come on, Aran, liven things up a bit. Tell me a story.~
@3534 = ~[PC] Very funny. You can tell, by the fact that I am not laughing. Tell me a story.~
@3535 = ~[PC] Stick to your day job. At least there, you won't accidentally bore someone to death.~
@3536 = ~[ARAN] I like eggs.~
@3537 = ~[PC] Well, that was short and pointless. How about telling me a story?~
@3538 = ~[PC] Is that it??~
@3539 = ~[PC] You can do better than that. Tell me about your sister.~
@3540 = ~[PC] Judging by the smells that occasionally issue from your general direction, they seem to not like you...~
@3541 = ~[ARAN] I like eggs when they be scrambled, wi' a little rasher of bacon on th' side.~
@3542 = ~[PC] Well, that was short and pointless. How about telling me a real story?~
@3543 = ~[PC] Hey, Aran, I remember you telling a real story... can you tell it to me again?~
@3544 = ~[PC] Fine. I will tell you something true. You are wasting my time trying to be funny.~
@3545 = ~[PC] (sigh) It really is true. All you can think about is food.~
@3546 = ~[ARAN] Well, Elanil is doin' right fine, last I heard. She spends all her time doin' apprentice stuff in Waterdeep, cleanin' th' mask o' her patron, an' generally learnin' all that a mage ought to know. Not much to tell, right now. We have not been travellin' where I can get much in th' way o' letters goin' back an' forth. Why do you ask?~
@3547 = ~[PC] Just passing the time, really. I am not big on family stories, for obvious reasons.~
@3548 = ~[PC] No particular reason. I know she means a lot to you.~
@3549 = ~[PC] Is it a crime to ask about a pretty girl?~
@3550 = ~[PC] Is it a crime to ask about your sister?~
@3551 = ~[ARAN] Bloody hells. That might have been a bit embarrassin', or even a mite painful, eh? Go on, then. I'll be back in a second or two, once I got all my gear settled proper.~
@3552 = ~[ARAN] That be a downright exaggeration. Sometimes, I think about romancin', too.~
@3553 = ~[ARAN] Some people don't rightly have no sense o' humor. None at all.~
@3554 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. Got you to talk about somethin' unrelated to where we be right now, so mission accomplished. I' m goin' to go see what trouble I can stir up to make this place a mite bit more excitin'.~
@3555 = ~[ARAN] In your case, it might just be a capital offense!~
@3556 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing, <CHARNAME>. Now, me an' Kravich, we had been workin' our way north half a tenday wi' this pair o' monks, see. They kept to themselves, though we thought it was a mite bit odd that they did not seem to pray none, an' th' smaller one giggled a bit much for a monk, but then again we both had seen stranger things than laughin' monks on the Trade Way...~
@3557 = ~[PC] (Listen to the story intently.)~
@3558 = ~[PC] (Let the story fade into the background, listening to the friendly sound of his voice.)~
@3559 = ~[PC] (Pretend to listen, letting Aran ramble on until he finishes and moves off cheerfully.)~
@3560 = ~[ARAN] Taiamat's Tentacles, my tongue twisted twice, eh? Well, what about the time Kravich an' me, we went huntin' gibberlings wi' naught but a couple o' wooden spoons an' in our undergarments...~
@3561 = ~[PC] They do. All your stories seem to involve Kravich.~
@3562 = ~[PC] You know, all of your stories involve battles, chasing women, and drinking. I want to hear something else. Something completely different.~
@3563 = ~[PC] No, I don't want to hear you stumble through some tall tale. How about telling me a real story?~
@3564 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Lickable Lips, am I tellin' th' story, or are you goin' to bloody well interrupt every five buggerin' seconds?~
@3565 = ~[PC] You are telling it. Go on, I will not interrupt again. Is that better?~
@3566 = ~[PC] You look so cute when you go all red in the face like that.~
@3567 = ~[PC] Hmmmm. That depends on how much you pay me to keep listening. Or is expecting fair coin for wasting my time a crime?~
@3568 = ~[ARAN] No, no crime there. But you have a knack for changin' th' conversation. If that were to be made a crime, in your case, it might just be a capital offense!~
@3569 = ~[ARAN] WHERE! What be... Oh, funny, funny <PRO_GIRLBOY>. Shar's Blackened Bodice, you have a knack for changin' th' conversation. Right, then. I'll be keepin' my story to myself.~
@3570 = ~[ARAN] Well, there be naught in th' way o' grand stories locked away in my brain. Although there was one time when my father got trapped into a trade contract wi' some shady characters, an' he managed to turn th' tables on 'em.~
@3571 = ~[PC] How did he do that?~
@3572 = ~[ARAN] I meant it literal, eh? He had a payoff in Easthaven of a ring what animated objects. It only had one charge left, but it were enough to do th' job. We picked up a quick run off th' beaten path to a Cyric-blighted place called Dougan's Hole, not knowin' th' goods was suspect. We delivered th' goods fine, no questions asked, but th' shady characters wanted to walk leavin' no payment save some cold steel between th' ribs, so to speak.~
@3573 = ~[ARAN] Now, my father, he sizes things up right quick, an' he sends me out to gather th' coster an' get set while he keeps 'em entertained. He was a great talker, an' still is to this day. When th' boyos decided to come after him an' finish up quick, he had th' table hug 'em real tight, holdin' 'em in place, an' made a run for it.~
@3574 = ~[ARAN] It worked right fine, too, but o' course it meant that we were not likely to want to go back past Dougan's Hole any time after. We stuck to th' Eastway between Easthaven an' Bryn Shander when up in those icy blighted lands from then on.~
@3575 = ~[ARAN] We thought nothin' o' th' strangeness, but it were a mite hard to keep focused on th' tasks wi' all th' flirtin' goin' on. Then it happened that a band o' brigands jumped us right proper. Th' small one, she dropped th' charade right quick, an' it seemed like she spat funny little sharp objects from every part o' her body, while th' larger one seemed to fade away in front o' our eyes only to reappear holdin' a dagger in th' back o' one o' th' ones who jumped us.~
@3576 = ~[ARAN] Unfortunately, Kravich an' I were busy wi' four others, an' missed how it happened, but one o' th' 'monks' took a right solid thrust through th' right lung. By th' time we finished 'em off, she'd passed on. Her friend were right angry, but ready to move on, when Kravich steps up an' says anyone who can make steel dance like that deserves another bit o' time on this plane, eh?~
@3577 = ~[ARAN] So to make a long story short, we got to a temple an' brought her back. Both o' th' ladies was right appreciative, too. Now *that* were a fine tenday! The carousin', it cost us both dear, an' they left us naught in th' way o' gear or coin at th' end, but it were a fine, fine tenday.~
@3578 = ~[ARAN] Oh, funny, funny <PRO_MANWOMAN>. Shar's Blackened Bodice, you have a knack for changin' th' conversation. Right, then. I'll be keepin' my story to myself.~
@3579 = ~[ARAN] Torm's Tangled Banner, th' blasted wizards done forgot to refresh th' spells, an' everyone got exposed at once? It must o' been a bloodbath! Easy targetin' on all sides, eh? I'd be grabbin' any bit o' cover I could, on account o' a shield wall exposed like that be ripe for a fireball up the arse... oh, hells, I'll be just shuttin' up an' listenin'. You go on.~
@3580 = ~[ARAN] Need help?~
@3581 = ~[PC] Perhaps.~
@3582 = ~[ARAN] What can I do?~
@3583 = ~[ARAN] Lost me...~
@3584 = ~[PC] Not here.~
@3585 = ~[PC] Forget it.~
@3586 = ~[PC] Kiss me?~
@3587 = ~[PC] Got my back?~
@3588 = ~[PC] Later.~
@3589 = ~[PC] SHUT UP.~
@3590 = ~[PC] Screw you.~
@3591 = ~[ARAN] Understood.~
@3592 = ~[ARAN] Always.~
@3593 = ~[ARAN] Yes ma'am!~
@3594 = ~[ARAN] No thanks.~
@3595 = ~[ARAN] When an' where?~
@3596 = ~[ARAN] Bugger that. You bloody well know I'm not goin' nowhere if I get a say.~
@3597 = ~[ARAN] Sune's... You are right. We are facin' more than anyone should.~
@3598 = ~[ARAN] I have backed your play for a good time now, an' I think you know where I stand.~
@3599 = ~[ARAN] Unwinnable? My heart's unwinnable, but you have it solid an' for keeps. There ain't nothin' unwinnable. It's just a matter o' what you are willin' to pay.~
@3600 = ~[ARAN] Unwinnable? There ain't nothin' unwinnable. It's just a matter o' what you are willin' to pay.~
@3601 = ~[ARAN] Aye.~
@3602 = ~[ARAN] (His arms encircle you in a crushing grip, and your body is pressed deeply into his.)~
@3603 = ~[ARAN] (He pulls away suddenly, holding you at arms length, eyes ablaze with inner fire, his voice whispering huskily in your ears.)~
@3604 = ~[ARAN] There be somethin' wrong here. You look more than a mite fatigued. In fact, you look... Bane's Broken Bones, what in the blighted hells is wrong with you, girl? You be paler than most o' th' vellum I scrape.~ [c-aws098]
@3605 = ~[PC] I don't know, Aran. But I will be fine. I just feel a little dizzy.~
@3606 = ~[PC] I felt... I definitely felt ill. It was as if I was fading away a little.~
@3607 = ~[PC] Just leave me alone, Aran. I am fine!~
@3608 = ~[PC] Shut up, Aran.  Prop me up, and make it look like there is nothing wrong. Showing weakness is not acceptable.~
@3609 = ~[PC] You worry too much. We need to move along.~
@3610 = ~[ARAN] Right, you don't look all there, <CHARNAME>. Somethin' is hittin' you hard an' fast. Are you about to be sick?~
@3611 = ~[PC] No... I... need... to... control! Losing...~
@3612 = ~[PC] I am changing again! The Slayer! I am...~
@3613 = ~[PC] Run, if you value your life!~
@3614 = ~[ARAN] What in all th' gods names was that?~
@3615 = ~[PC] I think I am following my father's curse.~
@3616 = ~[PC] I think I am following my father's blessing.~
@3617 = ~[PC] I do not know precisely. But I intend to find out.~
@3618 = ~[ARAN] You don't rightly sound fine, <CHARNAME>. Selune herself would envy goin' that white. Actually, more Kelemvor, eh... on death's door. But I know, I'm to shut up an' soldier.~
@3619 = ~[ARAN] Hot soup, an' a good solid night o' sleep, that be my prescription. There's no shame in leanin' on me a bit, if you want to.~
@3620 = ~[ARAN] That sounds like one hell o' a hangover. But you have had naught to drink. Here, get a bit o' water an' jerky in you, an' let's get out o' this place. Loviatar's Lash, this place would get to anyone.~
@3621 = ~[ARAN] Bugger your image - get your blighted arse awake, <CHARNAME>. You are Bane's Own Blood, an' stronger than anythin' what opposes you, even aspects o' th' gods. Stand on your own two bloody feet, an' command me, girl, as is your right. An' th' first command better be to get you some hot soup an' a place to rest.~
@3622 = ~[ARAN] Your lips be movin' <CHARNAME>, but that's not rightly any language I know... hey... Lolth's Cruel Fingernails, you be growin' claws!~
@3623 = ~[ARAN] We need to find you a cure for that, an' right quick. I'm right fond o' you, <CHARNAME>, but I can't hold you down in that change wi' out bein' torn limb from limb.~
@3624 = ~[ARAN] Blessin'? Well, it be powerful. But your power has always been you, not somethin' else possessin' you. If you can control it, well, it will be a fearsome power, it will. But if you can't, it won't rightly be a pretty endin', eh?~
@3625 = ~[ARAN] That strap there looks a bit worse for th' wear. Here, let me...~
@3626 = ~[ARAN]...err... that were a mistake, I think. Now, how did that hand make itself so familiar?~ [c-aws099]
@3627 = ~[PC] No offense taken. Why would you think so?~
@3628 = ~[PC] I was about to ask you the same question.~
@3629 = ~[PC] No offense taken... after I box your ears. Touch me again without my permission, and I will do far worse.~
@3630 = ~[PC] Do not touch me. I need you to watch our surroundings, and stop watching me.~
@3631 = ~[PC] You flatter yourself, boyo.~
@3632 = ~[PC] Can we move along? Each time we get close to accomplishing something, some idiot begins interrupting my concentration on killing things...~
@3633 = ~[ARAN] Well, I wasn't rightly sure you were receptive, is all. An' I do believe I was a mite forward with my hands. You should box my ears but good. Sune knows I deserve it.  Or was you goin' to tell me that I have permission to be a scoundrel?~
@3634 = ~[PC] You have my permission, Aran. If you are man enough for the task.~
@3635 = ~[PC] Scoundrel. Aran, you surprise me. You actually know a word longer than 'aye'.~
@3636 = ~[PC] Again with the romance. Some men don't take a hint. Look, drop it, Aran. And touch me again and you will be very sorry.~
@3637 = ~[ARAN] Well, I didn't mean to, but I am naught in th' way o' sorry it happened. An' I notice you didn't box my ears when my hand kinda wandered off course.~
@3638 = ~[PC] Touch me again without my permission, and I will do far worse.~
@3639 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I do believe I was a mite forward. You should box 'em but good. Sune knows I deserve it.  Or was you goin' to tell me that I have permission to be a scoundrel?~
@3640 = ~[PC] Forward is good. But there is a time and place.~
@3641 = ~[PC] *whack*~
@3642 = ~[ARAN] Well, I do admit you are a sight to be watched, <CHARNAME>. But I can watch you an' keep lookout too.~
@3643 = ~[PC] You misunderstand me. If you think I am watching because you are attractive, you flatter yourself. I just can't trust you to keep your mind on the job.~
@3644 = ~[PC] I don't mind the glances, Aran. But there is a time and place.~
@3645 = ~[PC] Oh, Aran, my dearest love, come and we shall frolic freely among the stars, and be one together for all eternity...~
@3646 = ~[PC] I think I have had enough of both glances and talking. Keep your mouth shut and your eyes on the job.~
@3647 = ~[PC] No more talk. Just do the job at hand.~
@3648 = ~[PC] This conversation is over.~
@3649 = ~[ARAN] Aye, that's right. Make fun o' the poor lad what just was flirtin' with you. Go on wi' ye.~
@3650 = ~[PC] Well, stop with all the love stuff and let's just stick to business, shall we?~
@3651 = ~[PC] No, no, it's true. You are my destiny, Aran. That, or I am supposed to be the doing something about prophecies, or something.  We can't just leave all that to chance, can we?~
@3652 = ~[PC] What is sauce for the goose is sauce for the gander, Aran. You have been teasing me with all this looking and touching.~
@3653 = ~[PC] You have a good deal to learn about women, Aran.~
@3654 = ~[PC] I take what I can get. Hey, you never told me about deciding to leave the Fist. Why did you leave?~
@3655 = ~[ARAN] Well, not to flatter myself, exactly. I just believe in takin' some chances, is all.~
@3656 = ~[PC] Chance is fine when it comes to some things. But you are treading on dangerous ground here.~
@3657 = ~[PC] Chance is something to be avoided at all costs. There is an order to all things, Aran.~
@3658 = ~[PC] So you believe that taking your life into your hands and accosting me is worth the risk?~
@3659 = ~[PC] If you want a chance with me, you had better behave.~
@3660 = ~[PC] No chance here, Aran. I have my attentions placed elsewhere. Stop bothering me.~
@3661 = ~[ARAN] Oh, I be man enough. Just not sure where the rules an' regulations put us. Then again, I do believe in takin' chances.~
@3662 = ~[PC] Some things I leave to chance, Aran. But I like the odds better when the person is much better educated.~
@3663 = ~[ARAN] Oh, you know how to hurt a lad, you do. I didn't do all this scribin' blind. There be some words I can't pronounce, but I can even do a bit of Dwarven an' Luskan script. 'Scoundrel' has been used about me before, too. Sometimes for good, sometimes meanin' bad... an' always meanin' trouble.~
@3664 = ~[PC] Your mother must be so proud.~
@3665 = ~[PC] And you chose to use this extensive vocabulary on me because...~
@3666 = ~[PC] Good, bad, or indifferent, you are welcome to try sparring with me, Aran. But aren't you taking a big chance, here?~
@3667 = ~[PC] Somehow this conversation has gotten sidetracked. Keep your eyes and hands to yourself, sellsword. I won't give many second chances.~
@3668 = ~[PC] Somehow, that sounds very familiar. I seem to get the same kind of attention wherever I go. It hardly seems worth the gamble when everything I do ends up in a battle.~
@3669 = ~[ARAN] Now, I don't rightly believe that. There is naught but little time to spend on Faerun, an' it don't serve the time we have to play it so safe.~
@3670 = ~[ARAN] SUNE'S RUMP! That bloody well hurt!~
@3671 = ~[PC] Forward is good. But there is a time and place. Learn it, and yours.~
@3672 = ~[PC] Keep your eyes and hands to yourself, sellsword. I won't give many second chances.~
@3673 = ~[PC] Shall I kiss it and make it better, Aran?~
@3674 = ~[PC] I mean what I say. Stop flirting with me, or risk my wrath.~
@3675 = ~[PC] (Burst into tears and move away quickly, hiding your face and avoiding him.)~
@3676 = ~[ARAN] I already bloody well am sorry I brought anythin' up. You need to lighten up, <CHARNAME>, an' take some chances.~
@3677 = ~[ARAN] Selune's Sweet Breath, you be mockin' me! Well, now, can't say as I blame you. I did come on a bit strong.~
@3678 = ~[ARAN] Look, most times it is better to dive in, an' try, no matter what. An' if there be some problem, the folks you want to be around forgive you freely, an' the folks you want naught to do with try to extract some price. When Tymora lets fly a coin, I jump right in an' wager high. I take my chances every chance I get.~
@3679 = ~[ARAN] You just don't blighted stop, do you.~ [c-aws100]
@3680 = ~[PC] What are you talking about?~
@3681 = ~[PC] Why do I get the feeling you are about to start a discussion...~
@3682 = ~[PC] No, I don't stop. Can we talk while we walk?~
@3683 = ~[PC] I do not have time for discussion now.~
@3684 = ~[ARAN] I kind of like it, y'know. Admire it. There be some drawbacks what come up, though. I don't see anyone really capturin' your attention right now.~
@3685 = ~[PC] Enough talk. Let's move on.~
@3686 = ~[PC] If you are talking about this lifestyle, then you are right. I don't like to stay in one place long.~
@3687 = ~[PC] I capture all the attention I want, and more.~
@3688 = ~[PC] Just what kind of attention are you talking about, Aran?~
@3689 = ~[PC] I don't want romantic entanglements right now. I have a job to do.~
@3690 = ~[PC] My attention is pretty well captured, I think.~
@3691 = ~[ARAN] Well now, it be more than th' lifestyle.~
@3692 = ~[ARAN] Oh, didn't realize. You get too much attention from the menfolk?~
@3693 = ~[PC] Yes. Especially from sellswords who should have their minds on their job, not on my cleavage.~
@3694 = ~[PC] No. I get just the right amount of attention. All of it.~
@3695 = ~[PC] I think this conversation is over.~
@3696 = ~[PC] Well, I have noticed a few looks here and there. I even have a returned a few glances.~
@3697 = ~[PC] I have already fallen for someone, Aran, and it isn't you. Do you think we can just be friends?~
@3698 = ~[PC] I wouldn't mind a little more attention. At least from certain people.~
@3699 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I should be more straight wi' the talk. I'm talkin' about romance an' the single adventurer, so to speak. It's just that travellin' is fine, but a man wants more than an occasional frolic in a hayloft.~
@3700 = ~[PC] You must have a very different impression of 'men', Aran. I thought that is all they ever want.~
@3701 = ~[PC] So this is about romance. Look, Aran, I don't think we have anything to talk about here. You might make a good friend, but that is all.~
@3702 = ~[PC] Well, women adventurers are no different than men adventurers. It comes with the job.~
@3703 = ~[PC] Too much information from you, Aran...~
@3704 = ~[PC] I know exactly what you mean. I have not had much time to think about romance myself.~
@3705 = ~[ARAN] I do know what you're sayin'. Soldier, guard, adventurer, or travelin' merchant, the job's always first. But there be times when I think I might be ready for more, y'know?~
@3706 = ~[ARAN] You could have fooled me. You don't seem to be makin' eyes at no one in particular.~
@3707 = ~[PC] You just don't know what to look for, Aran. A lady doesn't advertise.~
@3708 = ~[PC] Sometimes men are so dense.~
@3709 = ~[PC] I think I have made my feelings pretty well known, Aran.~
@3710 = ~[PC] Why should I flirt with one, when there are so many to choose from?~
@3711 = ~[PC] This doesn't sound like you, Aran. Is there something on your mind?~
@3712 = ~[PC] It is none of your business, anyways. Hey, you never told me about deciding to leave the Fist. Why did you leave?~
@3713 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, I won't lie. Most times, given the choice between a frolic in a hayloft and anythin' else, well, that's no choice. That's a certainty. But after a few years down that road, when all the boy wears off an' a man looks around an' don't see no partner to share with, it wears kinda thin.~
@3714 = ~[ARAN] So you prefer no strings, an' quick action, an' no regrets?~
@3715 = ~[PC] Yes. Perfect.~
@3716 = ~[PC] Sometimes there are just needs to fulfill, and that is the way of things. There will be time later to settle down.~
@3717 = ~[PC] I was joking, Aran. Of course not.~
@3718 = ~[PC] I don't see much choice, given what life is sending my way.~
@3719 = ~[PC] Look, I may talk a good game, but the truth is I simply avoid romance like the plague. There are too many unknowns.~
@3720 = ~[ARAN] Pullin' my leg, eh? Well now, that's right funny. But I am bein' kinda serious.~
@3721 = ~[ARAN] I used to think the same m'self. But I don't know any more.~
@3722 = ~[ARAN] I may be gettin' older, but I haven't seen more than twenty five summers. I can hold my own in a bar, be it drink or song. An' I can do a mite better than that if there be fightin'. No, it might be that I just haven't found the right woman.~
@3723 = ~[ARAN] I know a mite about sacrifice, but there's got to be more to this pass 'round The Wheel. Tymora's Bright Coin, fortune favors the bold, an' so does she.~
@3724 = ~[ARAN] Oh, I think about it about every five seconds, an' make no mistake, it be pleasant thoughts! It is just I never did realize 'til now that there's a big difference between a roll in a bed an' a real romantic time. Or mayhap I just never took the time to look hard at what I was doin'.~
@3725 = ~[ARAN] The story of my life. I be hearin' you, <CHARNAME>. Don't quite understand, but I do hear the words.~
@3726 = ~[ARAN] That they can be. I've seen it m'self. The fool boy goes on blatherin' and blathering, completely ignorant o' the blushes, glances, an' even attempts at flirtin'. Either that, or they dive right in an' ignore the warnin' signs.~
@3727 = ~[ARAN] I been on th' road now nigh on eight years, by one count, an' my whole life by another. An' it is fun for awhile. But sometimes leavin' a pretty lass behind after a few weeks just feels all empty, somehow.~
@3728 = ~[PC] That sounds like you have a bit of a problem. Luckily, I don't share it.~
@3729 = ~[PC] Are you developing a conscience, just have not found the right woman, or are you just getting old?~
@3730 = ~[PC] There really is not much choice for an adventurer. The freedom to explore requires some sacrifices.~
@3731 = ~[PC] You need to embrace the moment, and enjoy life fully. Life is too short to be wasted on permanent arrangements.~
@3732 = ~[ARAN] As for me, I don't rightly know what I'm doin'. I can glance an' spark, an' get myself into lots o' trouble, but I can't never seem to find a good balance.~
@3733 = ~[PC] I thought that all men ever want is a good tumble with no strings attached.~
@3734 = ~[ARAN] Arvoreen's Silver Sword, you know how to cut a man down. Fine, I'll shut up up.~
@3735 = ~[ARAN] Kossuth's Fiery Kiss, you burned me bad, there. Shuttin' up an' soldierin'.~
@3736 = ~[ARAN] Talos' Tempestuous Temper, you be in a mood.~
@3737 = ~[ARAN] (blushes) Well, now, I didn't mean nothin'. An' it is right fine cleavage, too. But I get your point. Less talk, more walk. An' eyes front o' the formation.~
@3738 = ~[ARAN] All I know is, I'm lookin' out for a change. Next time I see some lass wi' that look in her eye, or some fine woman who can give as good as she gets, I'm gonna be ready. For what, I don't rightly know. But more than a tumble.~
@3739 = ~[ARAN] (Aran is walking close to you, silent except for the occasional slap of leather against metal from his gear. He appears lost in thought.)~
@3740 = ~[ARAN] (Suddenly, he pauses, hiking up his pack.)~
@3741 = ~[PC] (You stand beside him, eyeing him critically, cross your arms across your body, and send a stern glance his way.)~
@3742 = ~[PC] (You pause beside him but ignore him, carefully studying your left hand and fingernails.)~
@3743 = ~[PC] (You move beside him, stepping close to his left shoulder, and help him adjust the strap.)~
@3744 = ~[PC] (You walk on past him, flashing him a smile.)~
@3745 = ~[PC] (You walk on past him with an icy glare, ignoring him completely.)~
@3746 = ~[ARAN] (He quickly adjusts his gear, and falls back into line without a word. His gaze seems to be following your figure as it moves ahead, though.)~
@3747 = ~[ARAN] (Aran grins uncertainly at you, but does not make eye contact. He unbelts the pack, and sets it down. He twists this way and that, then flexes his back in a languid arc, showing long, lean, sharply defined muscles. He reaches up to rub the back of his neck.)~
@3748 = ~[PC] (You glance at him him, sigh, and begin studying your fingernails.)~
@3749 = ~[PC] (You step close to him, and run gentle hands under sections of his armor, attempting to ease the pressure on his neck and back.)~
@3750 = ~[PC] (You step close to him, gently brushing his hair back and running your fingers along his jawline.)~
@3751 = ~[PC] (You grab the pack and swing it toward him, pushing it into his chest.)~
@3752 = ~[PC] (You raise your eyebrows and point forward toward your destination.)~
@3753 = ~[ARAN] (Aran swings his pack down close to your feet, and begins stretching his back. His eyes seem to be locked on your fingertips.)~
@3754 = ~[PC] (You blow a gentle breath on your nails and then bring them close to your chest, polishing them lightly.)~
@3755 = ~[PC] (You stretch yourself, arching your back like a cat, and running both hands through the hair at the nape of your neck.)~
@3756 = ~[PC] (You frown at your fingernails, and bite at one corner of a cuticle.)~
@3757 = ~[PC] (You make a rude hand gesture in his direction, and walk away.)~
@3758 = ~[ARAN] (Aran coughs slightly, and a quiet smile creases his weatherbeaten face. He raises his eyes to yours.)~
@3759 = ~[PC] (You return his smile, and your eyes meet his.)~
@3760 = ~[PC] (You frown in his direction, and shake your head slightly, then nod for him to move on.)~
@3761 = ~[PC] (You turn your face from his, pretending to pay attention to your gear, but watch his face from beneath lowered eyelashes.)~
@3762 = ~[PC] (You cup his face gently with your palm.)~
@3763 = ~[ARAN] (He smiles brightly at you, and his eyes follow your form closely as you pass.)~
@3764 = ~[PC] (You turn and walk backward, facing him, and gesturing for him to follow along.)~
@3765 = ~[PC] (You purposely slow your stride and put a bit more sultriness into your walk.)~
@3766 = ~[PC] (You pretend to stumble, and reach an arm out toward him.)~
@3767 = ~[PC] (You lift your chin, sniff disdainfully, and continue past him.)~
@3768 = ~[PC] (You make a rude hand gesture in his direction, spit at his feet, and walk away.)~
@3769 = ~[ARAN] (Aran resets his pack on his back, and makes a show of stretching and flexing his arms.)~
@3770 = ~[PC] (You glance at him from under your eyelashes, and smile.)~
@3771 = ~[PC] (You sigh, and brush past him.)~
@3772 = ~[PC] (You point firmly toward your destination, and brush past him.)~
@3773 = ~[ARAN] (The muscles in his back and neck move under your touch, and he sighs. His shrug traps your hand for a moment, then releases it, and he turns to face you.)~
@3774 = ~[PC] (You slap his shoulder gently, and spin quickly and playfully away from him.)~
@3775 = ~[PC] (You brush the hair away from his eyes, letting your fingers play in his curls, finally sliding your palm down to cup his rough cheek.)~
@3776 = ~[PC] (You lean forward as if to kiss him, but as he leans forward you duck under his embrace and cross your arms, wagging one finger at him and gesturing for him to walk on ahead.)~
@3777 = ~[PC] (You cinch the armor with a fierce tug, firmly slap his rear, and walk on ahead of him.)~
@3778 = ~[ARAN] (His gaze holds yours for a time, and he moves closer to you, until there are but a few inches between your face and his. His smile becomes more intimate, and his fingers gently stroke your hair.)~
@3779 = ~[PC] (You slap his hand away, and spin quickly and playfully away from him.)~
@3780 = ~[PC] (You mirror his gestures, and play with a lock of his hair, finally sliding your palm down to cup his rough cheek.)~
@3781 = ~[PC] (You catch his hand, place it firmly on his belt, and walk on ahead of him.)~
@3782 = ~[ARAN] (He grabs your wrists as the pack slams into his chest, and smiles widely as his fingers trace along your wrists and fingers until he has regained control of it. With a smooth, supple motion he resets his pack, his arching back bringing you both very close together.)~
@3783 = ~[PC] (You lean suddenly into him, very, very close - but not touching.)~
@3784 = ~[PC] (You step back, and stick your tongue out at him.)~
@3785 = ~[PC] (You make a quick cutting gesture across your throat, and brush past him.)~
@3786 = ~[PC] (You make a rude hand gesture at him, and walk away.)~
@3787 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's eyebrows lift in mock surprise, and he flashes you a wide grin. He bows low at the waist, gesturing to you as if to nobility, and readjusts his gear with an exaggerated puffing of his chest. He gestures for you to lead on with an expansive sweep of his arm.)~
@3788 = ~[PC] (You grin in return, and your gesture indicates he should lead the way.)~
@3789 = ~[PC] (You smile, raise your nose in the air, sniff grandly, curtsy with exaggerated motions, and brush past him leading the way.)~
@3790 = ~[PC] (You send an exasperated glare his way, and motion for him to get moving.)~
@3791 = ~[PC] (You sniff disdainfully and walk on past him.)~
@3792 = ~[PC] (You glare at him, and gesture that he should lead the way.)~
@3793 = ~[ARAN] (His eyes follow the motion, and follow down your form, pausing at every appreciable place. Suddenly, his eyes sweep up to meet yours, and he blushes a dusky red.)~
@3794 = ~[PC] (You smile and loosen the front of your clothing slightly, brushing your hand through your hair.)~
@3795 = ~[PC] (You pretend to stumble, and throw your arm out toward him for 'support'.)~
@3796 = ~[PC] (You catch his collar and pull him firmly to face you, then make a show of brushing his hair back from his face and generally straightening him up.)~
@3797 = ~[PC] (You point at your bottom, make a kissing sound, and walk away.)~
@3798 = ~[ARAN] (A quick hand catches yours, and you feel the sudden warmth and softness of a kiss replacing the sandpapery grit of his close-shaven cheek.)~
@3799 = ~[PC] (You jerk your hand away quickly and frown at him, pointing for him to get moving again.)~
@3800 = ~[PC] (You turn your palm over in his hand, presenting your knuckles to him in a courtly manner.)~
@3801 = ~[PC] (You catch his other hand in yours, gently unfolding his fingers, and kiss his palm.)~
@3802 = ~[PC] (You slap him.)~
@3803 = ~[PC] (You wrest your had away and walk on past him with an icy glare, ignoring him completely.)~
@3804 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's eyes are tracing your every curve, and his grin widens. He works his shoulders under his pack, and quickens his pace.)~
@3805 = ~[PC] (You continue to walk backward, and watch his long, lean stride as he moves toward you.)~
@3806 = ~[PC] (You smile sweetly at him and turn away, letting the sway of your hips tell him all he needs to know about the direction you plan to travel.)~
@3807 = ~[PC] (You frown at him, place one finger across your lips to silence him, and blow him a kiss.)~
@3808 = ~[PC] (You turn back to the front, sure he is maintaining the pace.)~
@3809 = ~[PC] (You stop and motion for him to continue past you.)~
@3810 = ~[ARAN] (You cannot see him behind you, but you hear his footsteps catch and falter, and his muttered oath as he stumbles. Obviously, his attention has been captured.)~
@3811 = ~[PC] (You giggle quietly to yourself, and move on.)~
@3812 = ~[PC] (You smile to yourself, and move on.)~
@3813 = ~[PC] (You sigh, mutter something about men and their short attention spans and one-track minds, and move on.)~
@3814 = ~[PC] (You turn around again, continue to walk backward, and see if he has recovered himself.)~
@3815 = ~[PC] (You pat your bottom, make a kissing sound, and walk on.)~
@3816 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's eyes lock on yours as he lifts his pack and resettles it on his back. His smile is easy and promising, and his eyes have a hunger hidden in their depths.)~
@3817 = ~[ARAN] (He brushes past you with the smell of cured leather, strong soap, evergreen, and sweat. The view from the rear is just as trim and muscular as the view from the front, though he appears oblivious to your gaze.)~
@3818 = ~[PC] (You grab the back of his pack and tug gently.)~
@3819 = ~[PC] (You grab the back of his pack and haul back hard on it.)~
@3820 = ~[PC] (You run your gaze over broad shoulders and narrow waist, and begin to envision the sight without quite as many garments in the way.)~
@3821 = ~[PC] (You see a small corner of parchment sticking out of a pocket of his pack, and tuck it back in.)~
@3822 = ~[PC] (You see a small corner of parchment sticking out of a pocket of his pack, and gently pluck it out.)~
@3823 = ~[ARAN] (Aran meets your gaze until a blush begins spreading across his face, and he drops his eyes with a wry grin. He brushes past you with the smell of cured leather, strong soap, evergreen, and sweat.)~
@3824 = ~[PC] (You shake your head silently and move on.)~
@3825 = ~[PC] (You scowl at his receding form, but move on.)~
@3826 = ~[ARAN] (As you brush past him, you smell cured leather, strong soap, evergreen, and sweat. His step is quick behind you.)~
@3827 = ~[PC] (You turn and walk backward, facing him, and gesturing for him to follow along more rapidly.)~
@3828 = ~[ARAN] (His arm is firm as it cradles you around the waist, and his shoulder catches under your outstretched arm. Quite suddenly, you appear to be waltzing a courtly dance as you move together. He gently steadies you on your feet.)~
@3829 = ~[ARAN] (He pulls his hand away quickly, staring at you with surprise. You can feel his pulse pounding in his throat as your hand traces his outline lightly, and he steps away quickly, turning away slightly and readjusting his belt.)~
@3830 = ~[PC] (You smile, tilt your head to one side inquiringly, arch your eyebrows, and motion for him to continue in front of you.)~
@3831 = ~[PC] (You grin widely, glance downward at his 'adjustments', and motion for him to continue in front of you.)~
@3832 = ~[PC] (You smile demurely and look down at the ground, arching your neck and avoiding eye contact, and walk on ahead of him.)~
@3833 = ~[PC] (You grab his shoulder roughly, give him a quick shake, and stride in front of him.)~
@3834 = ~[ARAN] (Aran is blushing burgundy but has obviously recovered himself. His eyes match yours, and widen in sudden surprise as you catch a heel and have to twist your body around to avoid falling flat on your behind. His laughter is quick and friendly, and it is your turn to feel your face go warm.)~
@3835 = ~[ARAN] (His quick fingers mime catching the kiss and placing it in his pouch. He brushes past you with the smell of cured leather, strong soap, evergreen, and sweat.)~
@3836 = ~[ARAN] (Aran glances back at the slight tug, and grins at you as he moves on.)~
@3837 = ~[ARAN] (Aran glances back at the slight tug, but does not see that you have the parchment. He grins at you as he moves on.)~
@3838 = ~[ARAN] (Aran stumbles slightly, glances back over his shoulder - and stops suddenly directly in front of you.)~
@3839 = ~[PC] (You frantically attempt to stop, but your well known lack of dexterity proves itself again - with a solid *thump* you run into the back of his pack and are knocked off of your feet.)~
@3840 = ~[PC] (You frantically attempt to stop, and to your astonishment you actually succeed in avoiding him. Unfortunately, you fail to avoid a slippery spot, and find yourself tumbling onto the ground.)~
@3841 = ~[PC] (You narrowly avoid running into him, and brush against him hard as you continue on past him.)~
@3842 = ~[PC] (You frantically attempt to stop, but your dexterity fails you - with a solid *thump* you run into the back of his pack and are knocked off of your feet.)~
@3843 = ~[PC] (You slip past him with ease, and you continue on your way.)~
@3844 = ~[PC] (You slip past him with ease, but in spite of your normally very strong agility a slippery spot surprises you and you reach out to catch his arm.)~
@3845 = ~[PC] (Your usual nimble agility allows you to duck quickly past him, and you quicken your pace.)~
@3846 = ~[ARAN] (You can hear his gentle stifled cough of amusement behind you.)~
@3847 = ~[PC] (You sniff disdainfully and move on, ignoring him.)~
@3848 = ~[PC] (You make a rude hand gesture in his general direction, and walk on.)~
@3849 = ~[ARAN] (Aran frowns in concern as he rubs his elbow, peering anxiously at your chin to make sure there is no real damage done. His relief that only pride is bruised is mirrored in his grin.)~
@3850 = ~[ARAN] (His shoulder is steady under your grip, and his face threatens to split in half if his grin gets any wider. You steady yourself and continue on your way.)~
@3851 = ~[ARAN] (Aran grabs clumsily at you, but manages to catch your arm and haul you upright. His face threatens to split in half if his grin gets any wider. You steady yourself and continue on your way.)~
@3852 = ~[ARAN] (Aran stumbles heavily, and swings his arms wildly as he attempts to stabilize himself.)~
@3853 = ~[PC] (You frantically attempt to avoid the oncoming arm, but your well known lack of dexterity proves itself again - with a solid *thump* you get an elbow on the chin.)~
@3854 = ~[PC] (You frantically attempt to avoid the oncoming arm, and to your astonishment you actually succeed in avoiding it. Unfortunately, as you twist away, you fail to avoid a slippery spot and find yourself tumbling onto the ground.)~
@3855 = ~[PC] (You narrowly avoid his arm, and brush against him hard as you continue on past him.)~
@3856 = ~[PC] (You duck under the oncoming arm, but as you twist away, you fail to avoid a slippery spot and find yourself tumbling onto the ground.)~
@3857 = ~[ARAN] (Aran grabs his jaw, rubbing away the sting of the slap, and raises both eyebrows in surprise.)~
@3858 = ~[PC] (You grin a wide grin and motion for him to continue in front of you.)~
@3859 = ~[PC] (You raise your eyebrows, point at the pack, point at him, and point forward toward your destination.)~
@3860 = ~[ARAN] (Aran smiles easily and ignores your icy stare. He tugs a waterskin from his gear, and offers it to you.)~
@3861 = ~[PC] (You send him an even more icy glance and walk on past him.)~
@3862 = ~[PC] (You frown severely, shake your head at him, and gesture that he should lead the way.)~
@3863 = ~[PC] (You take his offer, and enjoy a long swig, your back arching as you lift the waterskin.)~
@3864 = ~[ARAN] I wouldn't ordinarily mix business wi' pleasure, but it might not hurt to poke about a bit. What's an interestin' girl like you do for fun, anyways?~ [c-aws101]
@3865 = ~[PC] Oh, many things. I like to sew, do bead work, craft little booties for my future children, sit in a rocking chair, and wait for my true prince to come and save me.~
@3866 = ~[PC] I like to play games with rude sellsword's emotions until they are driven insane with desire, and then dump them.~
@3867 = ~[PC] I find many things pleasurable. But I have not had any time to do much beyond survive, lately.~
@3868 = ~[PC] A quiet, warm, calm place, a good book, and something nice to drink.~
@3869 = ~[PC] Oh, you know, the usual. Wine, song, feasts, a little more wine...~
@3870 = ~[PC] I think that is my own business, not yours.~
@3871 = ~[ARAN] They do say sarcasm be th' spice o' romance. You laid that one on a bit thick, though, eh?~
@3872 = ~[PC] Why, whatever do you mean, oh comely prince? Are you here to save me, carry me off, make hordes of children, and live happily ever after?~
@3873 = ~[PC] Ask a silly question, get a sarcastic answer.~
@3874 = ~[PC] You do not take hints easily, do you?~
@3875 = ~[PC] Well, I guess I just thought that was too obvious a pick-up line.~
@3876 = ~[PC] If I were wearing a flower, Aran, it would be in the other ear. You are definitely barking up the wrong tree.~
@3877 = ~[ARAN] Oh, so you play th' courtin' game for fun, instead o' for profit.~
@3878 = ~[PC] If you mean do I enjoy flirting, absolutely. And if you mean am I hard to get into bed, extremely.~
@3879 = ~[PC] If you mean do I enjoy flirting, absolutely. And if you mean am I hard to get into bed, you haven't seen the looks I have been giving you.~
@3880 = ~[PC] Courting is a serious business, not a game. If I intend to find the right person to share my life, it demands care and consideration. Is that what you mean by 'profit'?~
@3881 = ~[PC] I think both sides of that coin are available. The game is both fun and serious.~
@3882 = ~[PC] I think you are being a little slow, Aran. I have already set my heart on someone, and it is not you.~
@3883 = ~[PC] The question and answer session is over. Move along, nothing to talk about here.~
@3884 = ~[ARAN] Fair enough. But have you ever thought o' lightenin' up a little, an' having some fun, tryin' th' courtin' game?~
@3885 = ~[PC] I have not given it much thought.~
@3886 = ~[PC] My idea of a really good time would be to have you stop speaking, and let me continue in silence.~
@3887 = ~[PC] So you think love is a game. Interesting.~
@3888 = ~[PC] I play games to win. I do not waste my time with what you call 'fun'.~
@3889 = ~[ARAN] That sounds right nice, it does. I like sittin' down in an older section o' a library, an' huntin' through as many illustrated manuscripts as time will allow me. Unfortunately, it sounds absolutely nothin' like what we are doin' here, trekkin' about an' fightin' over an' over again. But riddle me this - you ever think about sparkin'? Courtin'?~
@3890 = ~[PC] I think you are getting too personal. Get your mind back on the job, Aran.~
@3891 = ~[PC] I have courted, loved, and lost. That part of my life is over, at least for now.~
@3892 = ~[ARAN] That sounds right nice, it does. I like sittin' down in an older section o' a library, an' huntin' through as many illustrated manuscripts as time will allow me. Unfortunately, it sounds absolutely nothin' like what we are doin' here, trekkin' about an' fightin' over an' over again. An' you have an eye for a mite bit o' fun, on account o' we have had a flirt or two pass between us. But riddle me this - you ever think about sparkin' more serious-like? Courtin'?~
@3893 = ~[ARAN] That sounds right nice, it does. I like a good solid meal, both th' preparin' an' th' sharin'. There's few drinks I met I didn't like, too. Unfortunately, it sounds absolutely nothin' like what we are doin' here, trekkin' about an' fightin' over an' over again. But riddle me this - you ever think about sparkin'? Courtin'?~
@3894 = ~[ARAN] That sounds right nice, it does. I like a good solid meal, both th' preparin' an' th' sharin'. There's few drinks I met I didn't like, too. Unfortunately, it sounds absolutely nothin' like what we are doin' here, trekkin' about an' fightin' over an' over again. An' you have an eye for a mite bit o' fun, on account o' we have had a flirt or two pass between us. But riddle me this - you ever think about sparkin' more serious-like? Courtin'?~
@3895 = ~[ARAN] Now, <CHARNAME>, come on wi' ye. Just humor me, eh? A little harmless fun, that's all I'm askin'. What do you like to do, when you don't have no crowd o' monsters tryin' to dog your every step?~
@3896 = ~[PC] Apparently, your definition of 'monster dogging my step' is more restrictive than mine. For me, impertinent personal questions fall into 'dogging', and someone who cannot take a hint qualifies under 'monster'.~
@3897 = ~[PC] Life so far has left me little time or inclination for courting.~
@3898 = ~[PC] I like romance, Aran. Do you like courting?~
@3899 = ~[ARAN] I'm right sorry, I am. You ever feel like talkin' about it, I'm your man for listenin'. You are lucky, though.~
@3900 = ~[PC] Lucky is not the word I would chose.~
@3901 = ~[PC] You do not know how wrong you are. Cease talking while you are ahead, Aran. This is too painful to talk about.~
@3902 = ~[PC] Yes, I am lucky. I have found my soulmate, and nothing will keep us permanently separated. There is no room in my life for you, Aran.~
@3903 = ~[ARAN] I wasn't gettin' that serious, but since you brought it up, that sounds about right. The profit would be findin' someone what completes you, or makes life a bit more interestin' an' enjoyable.~
@3904 = ~[PC] I have courted, loved, and lost.~
@3905 = ~[PC] You will find someone someday, I am sure.~
@3906 = ~[PC] So, you think you might be a profitable outcome? Or are you just seeing if I am up for a good time?~
@3907 = ~[PC] Have you ever found that 'profit'?~
@3908 = ~[ARAN] I keep findin' lots o' possible winnin' hands, but there's always a mite o' a problem here or there what throws th' game. I guess I just haven't found th' right partner yet.~
@3909 = ~[PC] That sounds like a story, or stories. Come on, tell me a story, Aran.~
@3910 = ~[PC] I think I can help you with your problem. When you seem to be interested in a woman, I see you do lots of talking, but absolutely no action...~
@3911 = ~[ARAN] That's for another time, I suspect. I don't rightly think I am goin' to get you sparkin' wi' sad tales o' lost loves. You'd need a real accomplished bard for that.~
@3912 = ~[PC] I think is is just the right thing to spark my interest in you, Aran. I think you should tell me a story about your lost loves.~
@3913 = ~[PC] Perhaps, perhaps not... but somehow, I think if I actually expressed a serious interest in settling down with you, you might just run for the hills.~
@3914 = ~[PC] Well, if you are anything at all, 'accomplished bard' does not spring to mind. But you started this, so go on - tell me a story of your lost loves.~
@3915 = ~[ARAN] I have been pokin' about an' playin' th' game for a mite bit o' time now, an' it seems like each time there's lots o' glitter, but no real payoff. You got someone who could be part o' you. I never did find my special someone.~
@3916 = ~[PC] You do not want to.~
@3917 = ~[PC] By all means find her, and have her rip out your soul as she moves beyond your reach. Then you will grow empty inside, and be able to concentrate on the things that matter, like power, or riches.~
@3918 = ~[PC] Well do not look here for such 'luck', Aran.~
@3919 = ~[PC] Are you really a man of action, or do you just talk?~
@3920 = ~[ARAN] Aye, well, I do like th' game. I know there's a mite o' trouble to be had, even when the person in question is displayin' a flower behind her ear. I never quite get which ear for which likin', either, which leads to some discomfort when th' lady in question prefers ladies. But it be a grand game, wi' nice stakes, good payoff, an' once in awhile there be a chance for somethin' pretty special.~
@3921 = ~[PC] Aran, I don't know why you have not picked up on this before, but... I prefer women.~
@3922 = ~[PC] I don't think I am good at any of these 'games'. I don't know why anyone would want to play them with me.~
@3923 = ~[PC] I have no desire to put myself under the thumb of any man.~
@3924 = ~[PC] Well I do not like 'the game', as you call it. I expect people to treat me as more than a prize to be won.~
@3925 = ~[PC] I play about, and I play hard. The question is, can you survive the game?~
@3926 = ~[PC] If you are going to talk about romance, go have the conversation with someone else. I suspect you only want to annoy me.~
