@5491 = ~[ARAN] I do see your meanin'. An' feel it, too. Play it is, an' naught more, though by Sune's Hair I think you will get th' best o' this bargain, eh?~
@5492 = ~[ARAN] Gods. What now! This be teasin' me somethin' fierce... see, he be leapin' an' jumpin'.~
@5493 = ~[PC] Now we sit very, very still, and we see how long you can stay right where you are without moving or anything else.~
@5494 = ~[PC] Just enjoy the sensations. Don't do anything rash, or lose control. Just enjoy.~
@5495 = ~[PC] Now, we sneak away and we try this again, with as many variations as we can think of.~
@5496 = ~[PC] (Begin rocking harder, letting the sensations play about, reveling in the feel of him.)~
@5497 = ~[PC] I can't believe I just did this. I... look. Forget this ever happened. I'm serious. It never happened.~
@5498 = ~[ARAN] If you don't stop, I am goin' to fill you wi' everythin' I have. I won't be able t'... to stop.~
@5499 = ~[PC] (Stand up swiftly, hiding both of your activities, and leave the room.)~
@5500 = ~[PC] (Redouble your efforts, slamming the heels of both your hands onto the tabletop as you move on him.)~
@5501 = ~[PC] (Relax as your own waves begin to rise, your pleasure blinding and passionate.)~
@5502 = ~[PC] Who told you to stop?~
@5503 = ~[ARAN] (He grips the table with fingers of steel, his body rigid under yours. Short gasps sound in your ears as he pulses within you once, twice, thrice... and slowly his tension ebbs as his breath sighs past your ears.~
@5504 = ~[PC] Now that was fun, don't you think? And if you ever tell anyone we did this, you are a dead man. Understand?~
@5505 = ~[PC] (Lean back against him, patting his cheek gently and whisper...) This can be our little secret.~
@5506 = ~[PC] I... I don't know what came over me. This is all wrong! Can you keep it a secret? Please?~
@5507 = ~[PC] That was a new experience. I might want to do that again sometime. I take it you mightbe willing...~
@5508 = ~[ARAN] Now, I can hold out as long as you can. Mayhap more. I think it would be right fun to see how many little gasps I can bring out while you be concentratin' on scribin'. Wi' any luck, we both will win.~
@5509 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, this be a mite bit public, an' you seem to be interested in things o' a more personal nature.~
@5510 = ~[PC] No one can see anything, Aran. Just relax and help me concentrate on the task at hand.~
@5511 = ~[PC] I... hey. Friends can just cuddle, right? I mean... there is no harm in just working together. I mean, petting your leg like this is no more than petting a dog, right?~
@5512 = ~[PC] Hey. I do what I want, but you can't. I didn't say you could touch me like that. Cut it out. (Drive your fingernails sharply into the back of his hand.)~
@5513 = ~[PC] Sorry. I will stop.~
@5514 = ~[ARAN] I'd blighted well be able to concentrate better if your hand weren't so warm. Somehow, this be less than relaxin'.~
@5515 = ~[PC] Hey, friends can just cuddle, right? I mean... there is no harm in just working together. I mean, petting your leg like this is no more than petting a dog, right?~
@5516 = ~[PC] This is good. Well, this far is good, and no more.~
@5517 = ~[PC] I am having trouble concentrating, too. But this is nice.~
@5518 = ~[PC] You could kiss my neck. I wouldn't mind.~
@5519 = ~[PC] I don't want you relaxed. I want you to be confused, bewildered, off-balance, and firmly under my spell.~
@5520 = ~[ARAN] Friends do a mite bit more than that at times, too. But somehow I get th' feelin' this is leadin' down a path you have some doubts on. That be my cue to stop, eh?~
@5521 = ~[PC] Why are you running away from me? I just am not sure I know what I want.~
@5522 = ~[PC] You are such a coward. you could press the issue, and you might find I was interested in more than just sitting on your lap.~
@5523 = ~[PC] I didn't say you could leave.~
@5524 = ~[PC] You are right. You should stop. I should stop.~
@5525 = ~[PC] Are you still here? Sorry. I was distracted by that handsome young thing over there. Get out of here, quickly, and I might just be able to convince him I am free for the evening.~
@5526 = ~[ARAN] I think I just did. An' there... yep, I did it again. I can feel your pulse race a mite bit, too. Or am I wrong?~
@5527 = ~[PC] Shut up and kiss me.~
@5528 = ~[PC] Completely wrong. My pulse is not racing, and I am definitely not kissing your cheek right now. And the whole caressing your hands as they run along my body... not happening.~
@5529 = ~[PC] Actually, it is kind of just... icky. Stop.~
@5530 = ~[PC] The speeding up of my breath has more to do with me getting angry than excited. You are frustrating me, in so many ways. I think I have had enough of this.~
@5531 = ~[PC] Aran... do you want to go somewhere? Somewhere private?~
@5532 = ~[ARAN] Now it would be right rude if I didn't do just that, right now.~
@5533 = ~[ARAN] Here, have a hand up, eh? All that gigglin' makes th' pain a bit more worthwhile. Your eyes sparkle when you laugh, you know. You want somethin' from the bar?~
@5534 = ~[PC] Actually, I was hoping you would take me in your arms, lead me back over into that dark corner over there, and we could practice some scribing with our lips.~
@5535 = ~[PC] I think I have had enough excitement for now. You go on, though. And put something cold on that lip, before it swells!~
@5536 = ~[PC] No, I want you to be confused, bewildered, off-balance, and firmly under my spell.~
@5537 = ~[PC] It might be nice if someone were to dance with me.~
@5538 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I be a bit forward, but you smell right nice, all cuddlin' up wi' me. This feels good.~
@5539 = ~[PC] Yes, it does. It is a pity we have so many clothes in the way, or this could feel so much better...~
@5540 = ~[PC] It might be nice if someone were to take a little walk with me, and perhaps warm my lips up a little. They feel so cold right now.~
@5541 = ~[ARAN] (His smile spreads across his face like sunrise on a mountaintop.)~
@5542 = ~[ARAN] Now what be your meanin', here? What did you want?~
@5543 = ~[PC] I said I wanted a private tutoring session. I would love to play with your quill.~
@5544 = ~[PC] I was hoping you would ask me to your room to see your sketches.~
@5545 = ~[PC] I asked for help scribing, someplace where I could feel more comfortable.~
@5546 = ~[PC] Err... I said I wanted a private tutoring session in penmanship?~
@5547 = ~[PC] I asked you to teach me, not make eyes at me, or try to touch me, or anything else. But on second thought, I don't know if being alone with you is such a good idea. You might get the wrong idea. I should say, you will definitely get the wrong idea.~
@5548 = ~[ARAN] I know that look. You get that hungry look in your eyes right before... err... well, I know that look. If you be meanin' what I think you be meanin', I am ready an' willin'.~
@5549 = ~[PC] I was asking for help scribing, someplace where I could feel more comfortable.~
@5550 = ~[PC] Err... I said I wanted a private tutoring session in penmanship? What look are you talking about?~
@5551 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a pickup line if I ever did here one. I am only happy to oblige. Just tell me when an' where, an' I will do my best to please you.~
@5552 = ~[PC] Ooooh, goody. Meet me at the gates of hell, when it freezes solid.~
@5553 = ~[PC] I could happen to leave my door unlatched tonight...~
@5554 = ~[PC] I was thinking of taking a walk outside this evening, in the moonlight. Perhaps we could walk together.~
@5555 = ~[PC] I was thinking of taking a walk outside. Perhaps we could walk together.~
@5556 = ~[PC] Right now. Right here. I can't wait.~
@5557 = ~[PC] Oh, great. I forgot I was supposed to... I can't do this. I am sorry. I was about to make an excuse, but you deserve the truth. I just can't do this with you.~
@5558 = ~[ARAN] Now, I must o' heard somethin' wrong, or jumped to some conclusion or other, on account o' I thought you were givin' me th' go ahead to get right personal wi' you.~
@5559 = ~[PC] You heard wrong.~
@5560 = ~[PC] You heard correctly, but I changed my mind.~
@5561 = ~[PC] Look, I am not good at all of this. I just don't know what I want.~
@5562 = ~[PC] Aran, I want romance, not someone who tries to jump me every chance he gets.~
@5563 = ~[PC] You should stop listening to my words, and start watching my reactions. I think I lowered my head to one side, smiled, and batted my eyelashes at you. And my hand resting on your arm should tell you I am saying one thing and meaning another.~
@5564 = ~[ARAN] I can do that, an' I'd be right happy too, but not right now. But you could always ask me again, someplace a bit more private. I think right now I am likely to be more entertainin' than I want to be for th' bartender, eh?~
@5565 = ~[ARAN] Hells no. I be more o' th' kind what leaps into bed first an' starts questionin' later. But I have to say I am afraid I am feelin' a mite bit under th' weather, an' I want to be able to pay all o' my attention on you. So for now, I'm off to nap for a bit.~
@5566 = ~[ARAN] Now, I didn't say that. I like it just fine. I was just wonderin' what your intentions be, an' all.~
@5567 = ~[PC] Why, are you committed to a 'no touching before I am married' rule?~
@5568 = ~[PC] I don't intend anything. I am just sitting here with my good friend Aran. Friends do that, don't they?~
@5569 = ~[PC] I intend you to be confused, bewildered, off-balance, and firmly under my spell.~
@5570 = ~[ARAN] I think th' public doesn't need that kind o' entertainment. But we can be upstairs in two seconds flat, an' by th' gods I will carry you if you slow down or falter one bit.~
@5571 = ~[ARAN] You know, you have some troubles wi' th' whole male an' female thing, I think. Gods know I do, too. But wi' you... if I make a mistake, in word or behavior, I don't rightly know if you will be fine wi' it, or if you will just smash me like a blighted eggshell. You don't realize just how powerful you are. Or how dangerous to my whole soul. You surely confuse me.~
@5572 = ~[ARAN] I think I needs best be gettin' a good drink. Or a solid splash o' ice-cold water. Or both. I will see you later, <CHARNAME>.~
@5573 = ~[ARAN] You have a right fine idea, there. Mayhap a bit o' somethin' from th' bar will ease my sufferin'!~
@5574 = ~[ARAN] Grumbar's Clay Fist, I have never had so much trouble readin' when it be business an' when it be pleasure. You got me thinkin' all sorts o' things, an' I can't rightly get my head on straight. Sorry about that. Just business, I get it. Mayhap someday I will figure you out. But I'm not rightly goin' to hold my breath on that one.~
@5575 = ~[ARAN] Right. Hey, you be a mite bit heavy on my lap, an' mayhap I need a bit more to drink. Why don't I go get somethin' nice for both o' us, an' you keep practicin' here? I'll go get us somethin'.~
@5576 = ~[ARAN] Shar's Kiss... well, I be right sorry I said anythin'. Here, let me help wi' some o' this washin' an' then I will clear out right quick.~
@5577 = ~[ARAN] There. All cleaned up, as much as can be done. No harm, no foul. Sorry I misread you. I'll head back downstairs.~
@5578 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I do know. But where be th' fun in that. Workin' together, my chin on your shoulder, now that be a fine way to scribe.~
@5579 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I be a bit too forward at times. Sorry. This does feel nice, though.~
@5580 = ~[ARAN] Ma'am, yes ma'am! Sorry, I done read you wrong again. I'll just concentrate on helpin' you scribe.~
@5581 = ~[ARAN] Well, m'Lady, mission accomplished. You can add happy, interested, aroused, an' thoroughly uncomfortable to that list if you want, too. But I'd best be helpin' you wi' scribin', on account o' we might be attractin' a few looks here an' there.~
@5582 = ~[ARAN] An' here I thought my wayward charm was workin' its magic, an' sparkin' wi' you. Serves me right. But I do say I'm right fine wi' this. I'd consider myself one hells of a lucky dog if you were just to sit wi' me like this for a bit.~
@5583 = ~[ARAN] Accidents do happen, they do. Right now, though, I think I might be a bit better off if you practice a bit. An' me, I... well, I think I needs best be gettin' a good drink. Or a solid splash o' ice-cold water. Or both.~
@5584 = ~[ARAN] See you tomorrow, eh?~
@5585 = ~[ARAN] Well, thank you right kindly. It were a mite bit small for so large a healin' touch, but I do appreciate it. I think I needs best be gettin' a good drink, or mayhap a bit o' cold water to slow th' swellin'. Hey, no gigglin'!~
@5586 = ~[ARAN] (You work together for a time, his strong hands guiding yours over copywork again and again, shaping and moving words and figures, until at last the ink is spent.)~
@5587 = ~[ARAN] It would be rude not to oblige, m'lady. I think I can assist you wi' that.~
@5588 = ~[ARAN] I never did have so much fun doin' absolutely nothin'. Just be careful, eh? On account o' you are completely intoxicatin'.~
@5589 = ~[ARAN] Shar's Spite an' Spit, you do like harmin' a lad, don't you. Fine. I got better things to be doin' than this.~
@5590 = ~[ARAN] *cough* Oh, now, what did I be talkin' about? Right, I do remember. That line was just fine. Now you need to just practice a bit. An' me, I... well, I think I needs best be gettin' a good drink. Or a solid splash o' ice-cold water. Or both.~
@5591 = ~[ARAN] A little too good, I think... but then again, who am I to be judgin' what be good and bad.~
@5592 = ~[PC] You could judge what feels good and what feels right. Do I feel good and right to you?~
@5593 = ~[PC] I can judge. And from what I am feeling right now, it seems that scribing like this stiffens your quill.~
@5594 = ~[PC] Do I have the right... stroke?~
@5595 = ~[PC] Hey, watch the hands. Seriously. You are taking liberties I don't want.~
@5596 = ~[PC] You really have no concentration at all. I should just drive a dagger into your knee, to remind you of who is in charge here.~
@5597 = ~[PC] Enough. I am leaving. You can stay here and play with your toys. I will go find something much more interesting to do.~
@5598 = ~[PC] (Pick up the proffered quill and begin tracing on the parchment he offers.)~
@5599 = ~[PC] (Wiggle a bit on his lap, adjusting yourself and making a show of picking up the quill.)~
@5600 = ~[PC] Ouch! (Jump up off of his lap, rubbing at your backside, blushing.)~
@5601 = ~[ARAN] That would be a pleasure. I'll show you some runes I found, an' you can trace 'em to test your skills.~
@5602 = ~[ARAN] Careful, now. Don't rightly just hurl yourself into a man's lap. You can harm a lad that way.~
@5603 = ~[PC] Come on, Aran. You are always poking about scrolls with that quill of yours. Teach me to scribe something interesting.~
@5604 = ~[PC] That assumes you are a man. Somehow, I think you will come to no harm.~
@5605 = ~[PC] Are you a 'lad'? I think I can feel something that seems more in the 'manly' category, very hard, right here...~
@5606 = ~[PC] What happens if I wriggle up against you like this?~
@5607 = ~[PC] Ouch! (Jump up, rubbing at your backside, blushing.)~
@5608 = ~[ARAN] All right, enough o' this. Hells, I am goin' to have  a difficult time walkin', but I needs be doin' that right this instant.~
@5609 = ~[PC] What is the matter? Too much starch in your shorts?~
@5610 = ~[PC] Oh, just when things were getting interesting. Are you sure you don't want to stay right here?~
@5611 = ~[PC] I'm sorry. I wanted to have some harmless fun. I didn't mean to make you uncomfortable.~
@5612 = ~[ARAN] Now, what can I say? You have a right strong effect on me, you do.~
@5613 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, that be doin' things to my libido what you might not intend, eh?~
@5614 = ~[PC] ARAN! (Jump up from his lap, giggling and blushing.)~
@5615 = ~[PC] ARAN! (Jump up from his lap, shocked and angry.)~
@5616 = ~[PC] (Continue to rock back and forth in his lap, teasing him.)~
@5617 = ~[PC] I would think you would just relax and enjoy the feeling.~
@5618 = ~[PC] Well, if you can't control yourself, I will head off for some fun elsewhere. I'll see you later. No, don't get up... you might have some troubles doing that anyways, from the feel of things.~
@5619 = ~[ARAN] Want to? Yes. Comfortable doin' so? Well, let's just be sayin' that I am a mite bit goal-oriented, an' right now that goal be to leave here before I get a mite bit too excited for my own good.~
@5620 = ~[ARAN] I do appreciate that. You can do this any time you might want to, an' I would be right happy for th' experience. But right now I am feelin' a mite bit too good, an' a mite bit too interested for a public area.~
@5621 = ~[ARAN] Aye, well... I suppose I can do that. But mayhap I just wanted to spend a mite bit o' social time wi' you.~
@5622 = ~[PC] You can have plenty of fun without me. I intend to avoid you for the entire time we are here.~
@5623 = ~[PC] Perhaps another night, Aran. Tonight I want to do something else.~
@5624 = ~[PC] I... you confuse me, you know. I don't think it would be a good idea tonight. I will see you later.~
@5625 = ~[PC] Well, when you put it that way, I could change my plans. What did you have in mind?~
@5626 = ~[ARAN] I can do that.~
@5627 = ~[ARAN] (It is a scant few steps before you are walking together outside.)~
@5628 = ~[ARAN] You know, if that be your idea o' a joke, it surely don't find me laughin'. I be man enough to meet your needs, an' then some.~
@5629 = ~[PC] I Really? And what are my 'needs'?~
@5630 = ~[PC] Oh, come on. Have a sense of humor. Aren't I cute enough for you to joke with?~
@5631 = ~[PC] You know, you talk a great game, but you never seem to actually do half of what you say. I thought you were a big ladies' man.~
@5632 = ~[PC] I'm not joking. If you were a real man, I would have been carried off in your arms a few minutes ago.~
@5633 = ~[PC] Just order me a drink. I have had enough of your talk.~
@5634 = ~[ARAN] No call to bother him at all, none at all. It would be my pleasure to accompany you. Mind if I walk a bit behind for a minute or two?~
@5635 = ~[PC] Why, so you can stare at my rear end and make inappropriate comments about "twin fauns moving together on a cloudy heath"?~
@5636 = ~[PC] No, you go three paces ahead. I want you where I can see you.~
@5637 = ~[PC] We can walk together.~
@5638 = ~[PC] Yes. In fact, forget it. You can't just be a good friend and go for a walk without making it some sort of attempt at flirting, can you?~
@5639 = ~[PC] (Blush deeply.)~
@5640 = ~[ARAN] Since when was it a blighted capital offense to admire th' gods an' goddess' handiwork? Tymora an' Sune would both be right ticked if I didn't at least make th' effort.~
@5641 = ~[ARAN] Well, I hadn't rightly thought that far ahead. But we could sit together an' think up somethin'.~
@5642 = ~[ARAN] To tell th' whole truth, it might be right fine for both o' you ladies to go off on a good walk. I think I needs be seein' about gettin' a nice nap, an' mayhap some sort o' massage. You two have a right good time, eh?~
@5643 = ~[ARAN] Well, one be that you need to get th' nine hells off my blighted lap an' let me clean up th' spill you just made all down my front.~
@5644 = ~[ARAN] That be my dagger scabbard, <CHARNAME>. Look careful next time, eh?~
@5645 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap so. On th' other hand, doin' that might pose a bit o' a public display, an' somehow I think you might find havin' a night where th' whole universe actually lets you alone a bit very restful.~
@5646 = ~[ARAN] Until I done met you, I think I was. Now, well... there be other things what occupy my mind.~
@5647 = ~[ARAN] Well, I could do a bit o' walkin' wi' you. Th' gear be safe enough on its own, I suspect.~
@5648 = ~[ARAN] You know, I might just give this time a miss, eh? My legs be tired enough as it is. You go on. I'm headed for some shut-eye.~
@5649 = ~[ARAN] I understand that sentiment, I do. Mayhap another time, eh?~
@5650 = ~[ARAN] Since when did you turn everythin' I say into a pass at you? Blighted hells, if I wanted to look at your rear, I'd do it, an' not ask.~
@5651 = ~[ARAN] You do turn th' most captivatin' shades o' color. No worries, I was doin' naught in th' way o' oglin' you. I just had to lace this boot up a mite bit.~
@5652 = ~[ARAN] Now, I'd like that right fine. But there be a good bit o' mileage on these here legs o' mine. If you insist, I'll accompany you, I guess.~
@5653 = ~[PC] Never mind. Don't do me any favors. I am sure that someone with more charisma than you can walk with me... I wouldn't want to task those weak little legs of yours.~
@5654 = ~[PC] Perhaps I should just ask <PLAYER2>. You do not seem that interested in accompanying me.~
@5655 = ~[PC] Perhaps I should just ask <PLAYER3>. You do not seem that interested in accompanying me.~
@5656 = ~[PC] Perhaps I should just ask <PLAYER4>. You do not seem that interested in accompanying me.~
@5657 = ~[PC] Perhaps I should just ask <PLAYER5>. You do not seem that interested in accompanying me.~
@5658 = ~[PC] Perhaps I should just ask <PLAYER6>. You do not seem that interested in accompanying me.~
@5659 = ~[PC] It is the thought that counts. I think I need to rest rather than walking, but I am glad you would go wandering about with me.~
@5660 = ~[PC] I would like it. In fact, I insist.~
@5661 = ~[ARAN] (A step away, and you are walking together outside.)~
@5662 = ~[ARAN] (You walk together outside, Aran leading the way.)~
@5663 = ~[ARAN] (He sits quietly, eying the crowd over the edge of his drink.)~
@5664 = ~[ARAN] (He is laughing and talking animatedly with a grizzled dwarf.)~
@5665 = ~[ARAN] (He sits alone, tipping his chair back and staring up at the ceiling.)~
@5666 = ~[ARAN] (With a grunt, he flips several coins onto the tabletop, and leaves without a word or glance.)~
@5667 = ~[ARAN] (He pulls a rolled up piece of parchment out of his pouch, and begins studying it carefully, scratching his head from time to time.)~
@5668 = ~[ARAN] (His knife scribes small shavings out of the tabletop, idly carving practice runes. When he sees the scowl of the tavern owner, he sighs and puts his blade away.)~
@5669 = ~[ARAN] (He looks around quickly, and shrugs. A moment later, though, he looks at you, nods once, and goes back to drinking.)~
@5670 = ~[ARAN] (He looks up quickly and stares directly at you, making faces and waving wildly.)~
@5671 = ~[ARAN] Aye now, I hate to call across th' room, but you don't have to sit over there spyin' on me. Pull up a chair an' have a drink, eh?~
@5672 = ~[ARAN] (He sits quietly, drinking slowly, eyes far away. The bright flash of coin dances from his hand onto the bar as he rises, and he catches sight of you. With a half-smile and a wave in your direction, he heads for the doorway, leaving you alone with your thoughts.)~
@5673 = ~[ARAN] Hey, by the way, your armor be all wrong. I know you be th' scourge o' Faerun, but you don't have to wear your heart on your sleeve, eh? In this case, someone else's, by th' look. Not a great morale boostin' thing, by my account.~ [c-aws075]
@5674 = ~[ARAN] Aye now, you be a sight for sore eyes.~ [c-aws109]
@5675 = ~[PC] So you like this dress? I was getting a bit tired of wearing the same functional clothing all the time.~
@5676 = ~[PC] I should have known you would be here. I suppose you have already chosen your evening's entertainment?~
@5677 = ~[PC] Dance with me.~
@5678 = ~[PC] Like I care what you think.~
@5679 = ~[PC] (Walk over and grab his chin, kissing him solidly on the lips).~
@5680 = ~[PC] I want a bath. Do you know where they are?~
@5681 = ~[PC] Teach me to scribe something new.~
@5682 = ~[PC] I want a bath, and some time to relax. Come on, show me where they are around here.~
@5683 = ~[ARAN] I'd like to do that, but I don't have th' right gear. You could come an' sit on my lap, though, an' mayhap see what comes up...~
@5684 = ~[PC] ARAN!~
@5685 = ~[PC] I might just be interested in that. Just watch where you put your hands.~
@5686 = ~[PC] Hmmm. You do make a nice pillow. Just... I thought you had an un-reinforced codpiece.~
@5687 = ~[PC] Hmmm. From the feel of things, I think you are remembering our last little experimentation.~
@5688 = ~[PC] I already know what will 'come up', and you are in all the wrong clothing for that to be very comfortable. Perhaps later, if you are a very good little boy.~
@5689 = ~[PC] No, thank you.~
@5690 = ~[PC] As a friend, I should tell you that your clumsy attempt at flirting is about as appealing as Luscan stew.~
@5691 = ~[PC] If you had anything worth my time hidden under that codpiece, I might think about it.~
@5692 = ~[PC] Forget it. I am tired, I ache, and I have had it with all this mess. Just get me a drink, please.~
@5693 = ~[ARAN] It has naught in th' way o' reinforcement... oh. Right. It might o' just got some. Perils o' havin' a ferociously fine female on a lad's lap, I guess.~
@5694 = ~[ARAN] Remember? I do believe I will remember that well past th' end o' time. Mayhap I needs get myself a drink, an' calm down a mite.~
@5695 = ~[PC] Oh, don't do that on my account. I think it is quite fun. I like things that are hard. I mean, difficult.~
@5696 = ~[PC] You need to calm down, and just be friendly. No, I don't mean put your hands on me. I mean just let me sit here and enjoy myself.~
@5697 = ~[PC] Get me one, while you are at it. I will sit here and just daydream about what we did.~
@5698 = ~[ARAN] Well, it does naught in th' way o' harm for a lad to try. Unless o' course he be tryin' to spark wi' a lass what has several large brothers an' happens to be a mage herself. I won't be makin' that mistake again. Though it did take me three times for to learn that lesson.~
@5699 = ~[ARAN] Do you be blushin', excited, or just angry at me? On account o' I am hopin' it be one o' th' first two.~
@5700 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Sweet Song, if you be in that kind o' mood, I'd better get us th' whole bottle.~
@5701 = ~[ARAN] Hands on th' table, I promise. Now, did we make any contract on whether or not I could let my lips do a mite bit o' exploration o' th' back o' your neck, or do that be against th' rules?~
@5702 = ~[PC] I suppose it would do no harm...~
@5703 = ~[PC] I will tell you what... if you don't flinch when I hit you, you can kiss my neck.~
@5704 = ~[PC] No, thank you. I am happy enough with things just the way they are.~
@5705 = ~[PC] Just my neck? I would bet several silver that your hands would attempt to cover all sorts of territory, and your kisses...~
@5706 = ~[ARAN] Aye, guilty as charged. But given how just one look at your profile drives any male an' even some females right mad wi' lust, you have to admit that only be natural.~
@5707 = ~[ARAN] You know, th' last time I said that to myself, I done got chased out o' th' inn by several strappin' younger brothers an' a right angry mother. Mayhap I'd better just let you relax back on my shoulder, an' count myself lucky to have th' sight an' scent o' you, eh?~
@5708 = ~[ARAN] OUCH. Blighted hells, girl, that were not just clothin', there... be easy on a poor lad, eh?~
@5709 = ~[ARAN] On second thought, if I needs be doin' that just to get a kiss, I blighted well want naught in th' way o' what you would do to me so's I could put my hands where I want.~
@5710 = ~[ARAN] You look right fine to me any day, but that dress might just be outlawed in some places, eh? You thinkin' o' perhaps kickin' up your heels, or did you think you might have a drink wi' me? There's no one else around right now.~
@5711 = ~[PC] I would love to dance, but I think it might cause... problems.~
@5712 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for someone else. But I'll have a drink, if you are buying.~
@5713 = ~[PC] I shudder to think what you call 'dancing', and I am not sure I should trust you as a drinking partner.~
@5714 = ~[PC] How about we skip all of this small talk and I start stripping you, right here, right now?~
@5715 = ~[PC] You know, the dress is fun, but I think it shows that I need to get some of the grime off of my legs. Shall we go find the baths, and have a nice wash?~
@5716 = ~[ARAN] There won't be no problems, <CHARNAME>. I know how to be discreet, an' if it's not in th' cards for a little romance right this minute, well then, I can handle a friendly dance.~
@5717 = ~[PC] I'm not interested in dancing. But I'll buy you a drink.~
@5718 = ~[PC] My feet still hurt from wandering all of Toril chasing personal demons. But you should buy me a drink.~
@5719 = ~[PC] I was just checking on how I looked, Aran. I'm off to catch my real quarry. Don't stay out too late.~
@5720 = ~[PC] Well, I think I would be more comfortable right here. (Sit down in his lap.)~
@5721 = ~[ARAN] Well, now. That young lass over there, the one wi' the hair like flame. She looks right sparkley to me, she does. But to tell th' truth, you might be a right better dance partner than she could be. You want to go for a spin?~
@5722 = ~[PC] Why, no, Aran. I think she is just the right type for you. I will go see about some curing potions, for the various diseases she will give you. Good night.~
@5723 = ~[PC] You would settle for that child? Really?~
@5724 = ~[PC] Suit yourself. I wouldn't mind dancing, but there are plenty of others to dance with.~
@5725 = ~[PC] (Look down at your hands and begin to cry.)~
@5726 = ~[PC] Actually, I came here to dance with you, Aran. Are you scared of me or something?~
@5727 = ~[ARAN] Well, to be right truthful, sometimes I am a mite scared o' you. Or o' me. Or somethin' like that. Hells, let's just go dance, or get a drink, or somethin', eh?~
@5728 = ~[PC] No, I think the mood is spoiled. Don't get too drunk, Aran. I think I will go do something else.~
@5729 = ~[PC] Is that why you keep staring at that little barmaid over there?~
@5730 = ~[PC] Just a friendly drink, then?~
@5731 = ~[PC] Just a friendly dance, then?~
@5732 = ~[PC] I am thinking more along the lines of something else. Like perhaps you could let your fingers wander through a few of my pages...~
@5733 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Shoulders, are you feelin' right fine? Oh... I get it. You be jokin' wi' me, eh? Don't tease a lad that way.~
@5734 = ~[PC] Well, that blush of yours has lit up the room sufficiently, and I think I shall go explore. Have a good night, Aran. We should be heading out of here early, so don't go far.~
@5735 = ~[PC] I was serious.~
@5736 = ~[PC] Actually, I came here to dance with you, Aran.~
@5737 = ~[PC] I think a drink is in order, if you please. I will let you buy.~
@5738 = ~[PC] Who said I was teasing?~
@5739 = ~[ARAN] *Ahem* Well, now, I... umm... hey, I think I'd best be gettin us some drinks, eh? Then I done got to call it a night. Big day tomorrow. Monsters to slay, an' them weapons don't rightly sharpen themselves.~
@5740 = ~[PC] You are so gullible. Have a good time, Aran. I am going off to explore the culinary delights all by myself. We should be heading out of here early, so don't go far.~
@5741 = ~[PC] Well, you simply don't know what you will be missing.~
@5742 = ~[PC] Just one drink. Or two. Or bring the bottle.~
@5743 = ~[ARAN] Now, then, you can trust me right proper. At least, I'm relatively predictable, eh?~
@5744 = ~[PC] Very. Have a great time, Aran. I think I will go look for something else to do.~
@5745 = ~[PC] If you move that hand any farther up my arm, you will not enjoy the consequences. But you can buy me a drink by way of apology.~
@5746 = ~[PC] Feet. Dancing. Now. Please?~
@5747 = ~[PC] You. Me. Dancing. Now. That is an order.~
@5748 = ~[ARAN] Oh, Selune's Silvery Hair, I done somethin' wrong. I'm right sorry, <CHARNAME>... you want a drink? A dance?  Mayhap somethin' by way o' an apology?~
@5749 = ~[PC] No, thank you. You have done enough already. Leave me alone.~
@5750 = ~[PC] What is so wrong with me, that you will pay attention to a barmaid but not the person you are traveling with?~
@5751 = ~[PC] (Look up with a sorrowful expression) Why, I would love that jeweled dagger in the weapons shop...~
@5752 = ~[ARAN] Now, what was that for? Not that I'm complainin', mind. See, this be me, not complainin'.~
@5753 = ~[PC] No particular reason. Now get me a drink, and then leave. Don't let me see your face here again tonight. You have guard duty, and I will not have you drunk on duty.~
@5754 = ~[PC] Just shut up and keep kissing.~
@5755 = ~[PC] (Slap him hard across the cheek.)~
@5756 = ~[PC] A moment of weakness, I guess. Don't worry, it probably won't happen again. Have a nice time, Aran. I'm off to explore.~
@5757 = ~[PC] I see your hand has found something very interesting to play with.~
@5758 = ~[ARAN] Do you have any objections?~
@5759 = ~[PC] None whatsoever. It feels rather good. Just don't get any funny ideas about extending your range.~
@5760 = ~[PC] Only if turnabout is fair play... hmmm. Silky smooth. Warm.~
@5761 = ~[PC] Yes. Remove that hand or lose it.~
@5762 = ~[PC] Aran... I... This is making me feel very uncomfortable.~
@5763 = ~[ARAN] Now, that were not th' endin' I was hopin' for.~
@5764 = ~[ARAN] Ouch! Blighted...~
@5765 = ~[ARAN] Wouldn't dream o' it. Well, actually, that be a big fat lie. Mayhap I should say I'm happy enough wi' what you let me do.~
@5766 = ~[ARAN] Good gods, woman... I am havin' a mite bit o' trouble keepin' all this hidden from view, eh? Not that I be complainin' so loudly, whisperin' close to you like this.~
@5767 = ~[PC] You seem to have to apologize to me a great deal of the time.~
@5768 = ~[PC] No. I think I have had enough of you for now.~
@5769 = ~[PC] Just buy me a drink.~
@5770 = ~[PC] Just sit with me, Aran. I could use a friend right now.~
@5771 = ~[PC] I like emeralds. Rubies, too. Sometimes a diamond, or a rogue stone can really make an apology stick.~
@5772 = ~[ARAN] Now, you don't beat around th' bush, so to speak, do you? Right, then. I'll be on th' lookout for somethin' like that.~
@5773 = ~[ARAN] What can I say? I always did be a slow learner.~
@5774 = ~[ARAN] Aye, that I can do.~
@5775 = ~[ARAN] If that be what you want, <CHARNAME>, then by Malar's Sharp Teeth that's what you be gettin'. I'll see to it as soon as I be able.~
@5776 = ~[PC] Well, alright. Now get me a drink, and don't let me see your face here again. It is your turn to guard, and I will not have you drunk on duty.~
@5777 = ~[PC] Now that you mention it, there are a few other things I would like. I will help you draw up a list. Go get your workdesk, scribe...~
@5778 = ~[PC] You don't really have to buy my friendship, Aran, or anything else. Forget the dagger. Just get me a drink.~
@5779 = ~[ARAN] Mielikki's Quickened Bowstring, I'd best watch both my feet, eh? I'll try to keep up wi' you right proper.~
@5780 = ~[ARAN] (Bright quick music lifts his feet, the clapping hands and the chatter of the surrounding crowd washing away all cares. For an evening, there is only the spritely step and twist of the dance.)~
@5781 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, it wouldn't rightly be gentlemanlmmmmmfff...~
@5782 = ~[ARAN] Your coin's no good here, nohow. I'll be right happy to step up. Here you go, then. One for you, one for me. Here's to our adventure. 'Success to th' Company, an' Confusion to our Enemies.' We'll settle in a bit, an' have a good comradely evenin', an' mayhap we get a few others to join us. Bottoms up...~
@5783 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now. No cause for to take offense. I was talkin' about dancin', not sparkin'. An' she obviously love to dance. Come on, no strings attached - just you an' me, eh? Come an' dance.~
@5784 = ~[PC] I am *so* sure that is what you meant. I wouldn't mind dancing, but there are plenty of others to dance with. Have fun, you are on your own.~
@5785 = ~[PC] I was just checking on how you are doing, Aran. I'm off to catch my real quarry. I would say not to do anything I wouldn't do, but I think you will anyways!~
@5786 = ~[PC] Look, just buy me a drink.~
@5787 = ~[PC] Look, let's just dance.~
@5788 = ~[ARAN] Now by Helm's Left Arm, what was that supposed to mean?~
@5789 = ~[PC] Nothing. Look, just buy me a drink.~
@5790 = ~[PC] Nothing. Look, let's just dance.~
@5791 = ~[PC] It means I am a little tired of seeing you everywhere I go, Aran. Go find somewhere else to plant yourself. I want some time alone.~
@5792 = ~[PC] Look, forget I said anything. Teach me to scribe something new.~
@5793 = ~[ARAN] There's naught wrong... hey, for th' love o' Corellon, stop th' waterworks, lass... There be naught wrong wi' you at all, <CHARNAME>. I wasn't thinkin', not one bit.~
@5794 = ~[PC] You don't mean that. You would rather go toss that silly little redhead's skirts up around her ears than stay here with me.~
@5795 = ~[PC] I guess that I just am not pretty enough, or smart enough for you.~
@5796 = ~[PC] (Grin maliciously at Aran) So, the big soft Aran can be swayed by a few crocodile tears. Useful information.~
@5797 = ~[ARAN] You be prettier to me than an Elven Queen's handmaiden. You are more woman than that little slip o' a child will ever be. Don't be comparin' no dandelion to a full blown rose, <CHARNAME>.~
@5798 = ~[PC] Go on...~
@5799 = ~[PC] I guess I just don't have much self confidence right now, Aran.~
@5800 = ~[PC] Don't patronize me, you stupid sellsword. Get out of here, and take your overbearing patronage and jackass face with you.~
@5801 = ~[PC] Actually, I feel like heading back to the room. I will see you later, Aran.~
@5802 = ~[ARAN] Right, then, I'm off. I got to get some o' th' gear settled more careful anyways.~
@5803 = ~[ARAN] With th' strain you been under, there be no wonder about that at all. Tell you what - no drinks, no dancin', an' I'll keep my fat mouth shut. Let's th' two o' us sit right here an' watch people go about their business. There be somethin' comfortable about knowin' that on spite o' all this craziness, there's someplace what's got business as usual.~
@5804 = ~[ARAN] I do like a good bath, <CHARNAME>, but... well, there's no polite way to say this, but it looks like th' particular one here might have been used for some non-bathin' uses, if you catch my drift. Trust me... you don't want to be in there at all. Smells like a Calimshan pleasure palace.~
@5805 = ~[PC] Really? And how do you know what that smells like?~
@5806 = ~[PC] And here I had my heart set on a nice soak, with you attending to my every whim.~
@5807 = ~[PC] Isn't a nice bath a great way to get closer to a companion and fellow adventurer?~
@5808 = ~[PC] That was not a request. That was a command.~
@5809 = ~[ARAN] Errr... look, just trust me on this one. This set o' baths, well, they just aren't what you be lookin' for.~
@5810 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>! Just th' lady I wanted to see. Bring your purse on over here, an' let's have a game o' chess, eh?~
@5811 = ~[PC] I think that would be a very nice distraction. Why do I need my purse?~
@5812 = ~[PC] I would rather dance. Leave that stuffy game, and let's see if the musicians can keep up with us!~
@5813 = ~[PC] I am just here for the scenery, Aran. You go find someone else to play with.~
@5814 = ~[PC] I'm here with someone already, Aran. But don't mind me. Go have fun.~
@5815 = ~[PC] This place is too stuffy an warm. I think that you should escort me on a moonlit walk.~
@5816 = ~[PC] This place is too stuffy and closed up. I think that you should escort me on a nice quiet walk.~
@5817 = ~[ARAN] On account o' th' money you'll lose to me, for each piece I take, o' course.~
@5818 = ~[PC] Oh, of course. What else. Whatever was I thinking.~
@5819 = ~[PC] On second thought, I would rather go dancing. Come on, just a few times around the floor...~
@5820 = ~[PC] I have a better idea. Why don't we try a different challenge.~
@5821 = ~[ARAN] Right then, dancin' it is. Lead on, m'lady.~
@5822 = ~[ARAN] (Bright breathless music leads you both a merry chase. A series of country dances passing in a blur of candlelight, quick movement, and activity. The tempo slows down to a stately waltz, and Aran looks at you questioningly.)~
@5823 = ~[PC] (Slip your arm around his waist and place your hand on his shoulder.)~
@5824 = ~[PC] (Slip both your arms around his waist and lean your head against him.)~
@5825 = ~[PC] (Nod gently to him, and leave the common room.)~
@5826 = ~[PC] Aran... don't you think we could be more comfortable upstairs?~
@5827 = ~[ARAN] I'm not sure I'm understandin', <CHARNAME>, but if you are sayin' what I think you are sayin', well, I'd be a fool not to want to. But I'd better not right now. There's complications what I got to think out, first.~
@5828 = ~[ARAN] (Aran looks wistfully at you as you leave, his gaze lingering for as long as he can see you.)~
@5829 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then, that I will. Have fun!~
@5830 = ~[ARAN] (Aran soon engages another to play chess, but you notice his constant glances are keeping close watch of what you are doing.)~
@5831 = ~[PC] (You flirt discreetly with a bar patron.)~
@5832 = ~[PC] (You shamelessly and brazenly make out with a bar patron.)~
@5833 = ~[PC] (You find a comfortable corner and settle into a good book, frowning over the pages intently.)~
@5834 = ~[PC] (You relax comfortably, letting time pass and your spirits recover.)~
@5835 = ~[ARAN] Now then, let's see what sort of player you are. Choose a fist, an' let's get playin'.~
@5836 = ~[PC] (You play carefully and calmly, sweeping the board of his pieces and trapping his king only after decimating the board.)~
@5837 = ~[PC] (You play poorly, allowing him to win, his grin increasing with each piece he takes. Eventually, your king is stripped of all companions, and you tip him over to indicate your loss.)~
@5838 = ~[PC] (You play carefully and calmly, but at every turn your moves are thwarted... and Aran wins the game.)~
@5839 = ~[PC] (You cheat mercilessly, leaning forward and exposing soft skin to him whenever possible until his distraction is complete - as is his loss.)~
@5840 = ~[PC] (You play with wild abandon, sacrificing pawns with no reason and generally causing chaos on the board, until no one is sure exactly what rules, if any, are in play. As it appears Aran is going to win, you clear the board with a broad sweep of your hands, covering the board with your body.)~
@5841 = ~[ARAN] Hey, that's not rightly fair, there, girl!~
@5842 = ~[PC] Who said I would play fair? I sure didn't.~
@5843 = ~[PC] Oh, stop whining, and perhaps I will let you lose again.~
@5844 = ~[PC] You didn't teach me the ground rules, Aran! How do you know I can even play chess?~
@5845 = ~[PC] Everything is fair in love and war.~
@5846 = ~[ARAN] Well, I do guess you be right. An' they say all's fair in love an' war, eh?~
@5847 = ~[PC] Do not get your hopes up, Aran. You might not want to risk either love or war with me. I'm not likely to take prisoners.~
@5848 = ~[PC] It is a game, silly. Now go get us a drink, and let's have some more fun.~
@5849 = ~[PC] Love, war, games of chance, wild romance... all might be a nice challenge at times. But right now, what I could really use is a drink.~
@5850 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, that's not fair either, there. I'm not whinin', just complainin'! There be a difference, see. Whinin' is when there's naught you can do about it, a' complainin's when I can do this... (With a quick tug he pulls the board out from under you, and holds it aloft, grinning.) He who done controls th' board, wins! Go get me a drink, <CHARNAME>!~
@5851 = ~[PC] Hah. A feeble ploy taking advantage of my innocent state. Fine, I'll buy you a drink. Now let's go cause some trouble somewhere!~
@5852 = ~[PC] In your dreams, Aran. But I'll let you buy me two or three, and see if you can get me all giggly.~
@5853 = ~[PC] What a child. Go get yourself a drink, sellsword. I am off in search of more interesting entertainment.~
@5854 = ~[ARAN] You spent all o' that time in Candlekeep, an' you think you can pass yourself off as not knowin' chess? Don't be playin' cards wi' me, then, on account o' you can't bluff for crap!~
@5855 = ~[PC] How do you know I was taught chess, when there are so many games scholars like to play?~
@5856 = ~[PC] Assumes facts not in evidence, Aran. I never told you what I did for fun in Candlekeep.~
@5857 = ~[PC] Silly games, silly opponent, silly evening... suddenly, I feel like doing something completely different. See you around, Aran.~
@5858 = ~[ARAN] An' here I thought we were plain' a game. Which one o' those are you holdin' me to, love, or war?~
@5859 = ~[PC] Why, Aran, I'm not holding you to anything. I'll let you figure out which one might be more fun...~
@5860 = ~[PC] War, of course. I have plenty of love already, and it will be fun to see if I can twist your poor brain into knots.~
@5861 = ~[PC] I'm holding you to another game, another day, and that is enough for me.~
@5862 = ~[PC] I will see you later, Aran.~
@5863 = ~[ARAN] Right. I suppose there be some good in just havin' a decent night's sleep. Or indecent, if a lad could find a partner, eh?~
@5864 = ~[ARAN] Now I don't know whether I be comin' or goin'. You seem to have all th' pieces covered, eh?~
@5865 = ~[ARAN] Well, on both counts, looks like you succeded. I might just have a drink or two an' then let my poor addled brain sleep in th' resultin' alcohol-induced hazy bliss, eh?~
@5866 = ~[ARAN] (The evening passes in a warm, relaxed haze of comfort.)~
@5867 = ~[ARAN] Well, what did you have in mind, then?~
@5868 = ~[PC] How about a concentration contest. You hold this little book here, and don't move. I will see if I can make you move. The winner buys the drinks.~
@5869 = ~[PC] Oh, I don't know... how about a little game of hide and seek.~
@5870 = ~[PC] I think it is time you earned your keep. Give me a back rub.~
@5871 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be right simple. I'll be takin' your money right quick, I will.~
@5872 = ~[PC] (You walk around Aran as he holds the book out at arms length, watching the strain gather on his face.)~
@5873 = ~[PC] (You watch Aran hold for a time, but grow impatient. You slam your heel hard into his instep, smiling at him sweetly.)~
@5874 = ~[PC] (You stand at the corner of Aran's vision, and very slowly begin to loosen your clothing.)~
@5875 = ~[PC] Hey, Aran, where did I put that sales contract for the horses?~
@5876 = ~[ARAN] (In the kitchen, a mug clatters to the floor, and Aran instantly drops the book and grabs for his weapon. He straightens, smiling sheepishly, and hands you back the book.) Corellon's Fire, I thought I had you, <CHARNAME>. Right, then, two drinks, comin' right up.~
@5877 = ~[ARAN] (Aran cocks his head to one side, thinking for a second, then steps toward his writing desk rolled up on a nearby table.) Well, let me see. I do believe... Bane's Broken Bond, you got me! Stop that laughin' <CHARNAME>. I done been tricked into buyin' by an apprentice's prank!~
@5878 = ~[ARAN] (Aran keeps trying to look in your direction, but never quite gets you in plain sight. Just when you are about to have to choose whether to break away or risk exposure, he starts laughing uncontrollably and drops the book.)~
@5879 = ~[ARAN] Well, you won, <CHARNAME>, but I think you'd better look at what your surroundin's are before playin' dangerous games like that. The poor busboy, he's turnin' bright red over there, an' the lad's not seen fourteen years!~
@5880 = ~[ARAN] Mask's Mighty Menace, you blighted little weasel! I'll kick you a good one, I will! (Aran's threat would be more credible if he were not grabbing his foot and hopping about trying to keep his balance.)~
@5881 = ~[ARAN] (He mutters a bit, but goes and retrieves two drinks, setting them down on the table. He raises his glass and slams it back, grimacing at his foot.)~
@5882 = ~[PC] (Not to be outdone, you follow suit, throwing the drink down your throat.)~
@5883 = ~[PC] (You smile sweetly, and dump the drink over his head.)~
@5884 = ~[PC] (You pour the drink into his lap.)~
@5885 = ~[PC] (You get up and leave.)~
@5886 = ~[ARAN] (The resulting fire in your mouth and throat are excruciating.)~
@5887 = ~[ARAN] Aye, you might want a bit o' bread, <CHARNAME>. I figured if you liked your gamin' spicy, you might like a mite o' hot pepper oil mixed into your drink. I can play any game you can, darlin'. Might not win, but I'll give you a right good run for your money, I will.~
@5888 = ~[ARAN] (He sputters and yelps, grabbing for his eyes. Foul curses fly from his mouth as he makes his way out of the room.)~
@5889 = ~[ARAN] (He sputters his drink across the table and yelps. Foul curses fly from his mouth as he makes his way out of the room.)~
@5890 = ~[ARAN] Well, that be a child's game.~
@5891 = ~[PC] Not the way I play it. I was going to hide something on me, and then let you try and find it.~
@5892 = ~[PC] Children don't play the way I do. You hide something on your body, and I will try to find it.~
@5893 = ~[PC] Let's be children, then, and relax a little. Come on, it will be fun!~
@5894 = ~[ARAN] Hmmm. Well, I guess I could give that a shot. An' I am supposed to say 'warmer' an' 'colder', right, on when you get closer or farther from th' object? Well, search away, girl, if you have th' guts. Find my Flamin' Fist musterin'-out medallion.~
@5895 = ~[PC] Hmmm. Is it here? (Run your hand gently along his belt and point to his belt pouch.)~
@5896 = ~[PC] Hmmm. Is it here? (Brush your fingers across his chest and point to his side under his shirt.)~
@5897 = ~[PC] Hmmm. Is it here? (Walk your fingers up his arm and point to the leather tie holding a locket out of sight under his shirt.)~
@5898 = ~[PC] Hmmm. Is it here? (Gently run your palm down to the center of his back, pressing close to him and looking up into his eyes.)~
@5899 = ~[PC] Hmmm. Is it here? (Gently tug at his belt, loosening it and slipping your fingers under his clothing.)~
@5900 = ~[PC] I think I will do better with a whole body search. (Turn around and look coyly over your shoulder at him, while nestling your back up against him and wiggling your hips.)~
@5901 = ~[ARAN] Right you are, in one! An' for winnin' I'll get you a right fine drink, an' we can sit an' chat a bit. Innkeeper, Rashemi Firewine, straight. None o' that watered crap, neither!~
@5902 = ~[ARAN] Well, a bit warm, there. But not quite right. Try again.~
@5903 = ~[ARAN] Well, a bit cold, there. Try again.~
@5904 = ~[ARAN] Now, I don't think you are playin' fair, there, <CHARNAME>. Try again, only for real this time, eh?~
@5905 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's voice is rough and close in your ear.) Bloody hells, girl, you are goin' to kill me, you are. How about I give you th' medal, an' we call it a game? This is teasin' me right proper.~
@5906 = ~[ARAN] Oh, no you don't. I'm not playin' that game wi' you. I don't trust myself to stick to th' straight an' narrow, so to speak! I've got some business elsewhere, anyways. But have a drink on me before I head out.~
@5907 = ~[ARAN] (Time falls away, with memories of the Candlekeep Library and childhood games with Imoen filling your senses. Darting around the stairways and rooms, startling guests, and generally acting like only ten summers have passed for each of you, the evening is a happy relaxation from your cares.)~
@5908 = ~[ARAN] I do have a mite bit o' experience. I did short-haul work on th' galleys tradin' into Calimport for a year or so, an' there were some right fine massages to be had in that city. I done had an "apprenticeship o' observation". Learned that phrase from a man named Lortie. Here, relax in this chair, eh?~
@5909 = ~[PC] (Your body begins to melt, your head moving in a gentle circular motion as his thumbs press and knead the back of your neck. Slowly, your cares begin to melt away.)~
@5910 = ~[PC] (His hands are strong and capable, but you want more.) Lower, Aran. And harder.~
@5911 = ~[PC] On second thought, I have better uses for those hands. Come sit here.~
@5912 = ~[ARAN] Now, if I press much harder, I'll be hurtin' you a bit, on account o' those knots I can feel under my thumbs. There... that be a mite better. You just relax an' let me get you back into shape, eh?~
@5913 = ~[PC] (Your body begins to relax. Slowly, your cares begin to melt away.)~
@5914 = ~[PC] And how much did you "observe"? I have heard that there are lots of ways to end a Calishite massage...~
@5915 = ~[ARAN] Well they do say Mask likes idle hands, but I best not be sittin' too close to you, or my hands won't rightly be doin' nothin...~
@5916 = ~[PC] Now, Aran. I have heard you have wonderful hands, and a reputation for using them in some very interesting ways...~
@5917 = ~[PC] You would not take advantage of a friend like that, now would you?~
@5918 = ~[ARAN] Why now, my <PRO_LADYLORD> <CHARNAME>. I wouldn't know nothin' about that. Not one bit. Not me, no <PRO_SIRMAAM>. Right, then, stop that laughin'. I've been framed right proper, I have!~
@5919 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's arms hold you firmly, carefully, a little gingerly. The music dissolves the surroundings into a melange of shadows and light, and for a time there is nothing but the two of you moving together.)~
@5920 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's chest is warm and hard against your cheek, and his strong arms hold you close as the steps pull you along in the waltz. Suddenly, he pushes you away, holding you at arms length, ears burning while the two of you dance.)~
@5921 = ~[PC] Aran, what is wrong?~
@5922 = ~[PC] That is a natural reaction to being close together with a woman you desire, Aran. Relax, and come back here.~
@5923 = ~[PC] (Blush brightly.) I... I think it is better to dance this way, Aran. We should probably stop now anyways.~
@5924 = ~[PC] (Scowl at him.) Hey, get control of yourself. I was enjoying myself.~
@5925 = ~[ARAN] Sorry about that. You smell right nice, like a warm rain in th' spring. Sometimes, there be times when a man's a man, no matter what's right or wrong. I'll watch m'self. Let's just enjoy th' dancin', an' all.~
@5926 = ~[ARAN] Now then, <CHARNAME>, I do believe I won. Hand it over, then!~
@5927 = ~[PC] (Lean forward on your arms, displaying a bit more cleavage and smiling up at him.) Would you really take my coin for such a game, Aran? Are you sure there is nothing else I can settle my debt with?~
@5928 = ~[PC] Here you go, Aran. Oh, wait a minute - I hold the party purse. And we are in an inn. And there is a bar right over there. I think for your own safety, I shall hold onto it for you!~
@5929 = ~[PC] I don't think I will, Aran. (Drop the coins down the front of your outfit.) I think you may have to come and get them.~
@5930 = ~[PC] You know me better than that. I don't like to lose, and I won't bother paying a debt to you.~
@5931 = ~[PC] Rematch?~
@5932 = ~[PC] You win. Here is your coin.~
@5933 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's gaze drops to where it is intended to go, and he flushes.) Now, then, that be fine. I don't hold no debt against you, nohow. It was a good game, an' I took my winnin's while we played. You missed a button or two there, an' I had a great show most o' th' night!~
@5934 = ~[ARAN] Why did I figure that was the way it was goin' to be? Let's see if I can rustle a mite o' food out o' that innkeeper, an' we'll discuss payday right proper.~
@5935 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's hand flashes out toward your chest, almost taking you by surprise.)~
@5936 = ~[PC] (Remain still, your gaze daring him to touch you.)~
@5937 = ~[PC] (Pull your top open and lean forward, allowing him access.)~
@5938 = ~[PC] (Slam his hand down hard onto the table with your fist.) Naughty, naughty. You can't touch me - just the coins.~
@5939 = ~[PC] (Stand quickly.) My, my. Look at the time. I think I will go find some other entertainment.~
@5940 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's other hand catches your wrist, and yours catches his - stalemate. He pulls you closer to him across the table, but a slow smile spreads across his face as he casts his glance down your body.) Pity there's all this table in th' way, <CHARNAME>. There's a right fine view o' your charms from this angle. How about we settle this in another game?~
@5941 = ~[ARAN] (His eyes never leave yours as his hands meet your warm skin. He takes his time gently exploring, seeking coins and finding many other things along the way. Eventually, he sits back breathing heavily, with only a few coins to show for his efforts. His voice is husky...)~
@5942 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I bet you didn't think I had it in me, eh? I'd better stop there, <CHARNAME>, an' let you keep the rest o' that coin. I could do more explorin' but this is a mite public. Why don't you go grab us a drink or two. I don't think I should stand up right now.~
@5943 = ~[ARAN] (His face pulls close to yours in a contest of wills, eye to eye, forehead to forehead. Suddenly, he laughs.) This round to you, m'lady teaser... I know better'n to go wanderin' about your body without no permission. I'll go get us a drink or two, an' we'll discuss another game.~
@5944 = ~[ARAN] Well, it was right entertainin' just playin', anyways. I'll go get us somethin' to drink an' eat. You hold onto my winnin's and we'll see if I can charm 'em out o' you next time we run up against a good weaponsmith.~
@5945 = ~[ARAN] Now then, <CHARNAME>, I do believe I lost. Problem is, I don't have no coin, not right now. Double or naught'?~
@5946 = ~[PC] Well, I think I can draw my winnings in other ways, Aran. (You reach a foot under the table and place it gently between his legs.)~
@5947 = ~[PC] I have no choice but to punish you, then. (You kick him hard under the table.)~
@5948 = ~[PC] It was a silly idea to wager on chess, Aran. But it was fun playing with you.~
@5949 = ~[ARAN] That be right kind o' you, <CHARNAME>. I promise, I'll pay my losses, I will. That was a good bit o' fun to play.~
@5950 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's chair flies back as he jumps up with a startled oath.) That's a mite tender, there, <CHARNAME>, in spite o' those healin' potions! I promise, I'll pay my losses, I will.~
@5951 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then, get some rest, <CHARNAME>. There's a mite more scribin' for me, an' then I'll turn in proper. Unless you want some company to chase th' bedbugs away, o' course.~
@5952 = ~[ARAN] (Aran soon loses interest in the game, possibly because his tactics never quite make it to the level of strategy. Finally, he leaves the game to better players. With a heavy *thud*, he settles himself at a table near you. Spreading out a scroll and carefully arranging ink and quills, he begins scratching away in companionable silence. The lights go dim as you sit near each other, his occasional glances at you broken only by the occasional scrabble of quill to parchment.)~
@5953 = ~[ARAN] (Aran casts glances in your direction frequently, to the detriment of his game and his purse. Eventually, he stands up and stretches, grins at you, and heads upstairs.)~
@5954 = ~[ARAN] (Each glance in your direction turns Aran's face an angrier shade of red, and he rapidly loses his purse. Standing quickly, he strides out of the room muttering oaths under his breath.)~
@5955 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's ears turn red and his concentration wavers, resulting in a series of costly losses. Eventually, he pushes back from the table, grumpily heading to settle his gear.)~
@5956 = ~[ARAN] Now, what be your pleasure, eh?~
@5957 = ~[PC] This place is too stuffy and warm. I think that you should escort me on a moonlit walk.~
@5958 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER2>. Have you seen her?~
@5959 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER3>. Have you seen her?~
@5960 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER4>. Have you seen her?~
@5961 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER5>. Have you seen her?~
@5962 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER6>. Have you seen her?~
@5963 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER2>. Have you seen him?~
@5964 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER3>. Have you seen him?~
@5965 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER4>. Have you seen him?~
@5966 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER5>. Have you seen him?~
@5967 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking for <PLAYER6>. Have you seen him?~
@5968 = ~[PC] Time for a language lesson.~
@5969 = ~[ARAN] Right over there, I do believe. But you could stay an' keep me company instead o' botherin' her, you know. I won't rightly bite, unless you tell me to. Wouldn't mind it a bit, come to think on it.~
@5970 = ~[PC] Why do you seem to always lead with an attempt at flirting?~
@5971 = ~[PC] Well, in that case, you can bite me.~
@5972 = ~[PC] I think I need to go over there. Have fun, but not too much fun.~
@5973 = ~[PC] Well, I guess we could have a language lesson.~
@5974 = ~[ARAN] Right over there, I do believe. But you could stay an' keep me company instead o' botherin' him, you know. I won't rightly bite, unless you tell me to. Wouldn't mind it a bit, come to think on it.~
@5975 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. What did you be wantin' to learn? I know a few.~
@5976 = ~[PC] That would be "Absolutely. What language are you interested in learning?"~
@5977 = ~[PC] On second thought, forget I said anything. Have fun, but not too much fun.~
@5978 = ~[PC] I meant that it is time for you to learn how to speak, and I will teach you.~
@5979 = ~[PC] I was hoping for a lesson on the effect of geopolitical upheaval and mass migration on Trade-speak, operating from the etymological exploration of the word "blighted".~
@5980 = ~[ARAN] I don't seem to be able to stop tryin', when it comes to you.~
@5981 = ~[PC] If it were just me, it wouldn't be a problem. But you seem to want to flirt with anything female.~
@5982 = ~[PC] Errr... "When it is in reference to you, I do not seem to be able to stop trying to flirt."~
@5983 = ~[PC] Find a way.~
@5984 = ~[ARAN] That be what I said, eh?~
@5985 = ~[PC] "I think that is what I said".~
@5986 = ~[PC] You are missing what I am saying. I am trying to teach you how to speak.~
@5987 = ~[ARAN] Aye, you said that, but before you said it I was th' one doin' th' sayin', an' I said that.~
@5988 = ~[PC] No, no... "Yes, you said that, but I said it before you did."~
@5989 = ~[ARAN] Blighted... you know what, I do believe what we be havin' here be a failure to communicate. Mayhap I'd better just get us some drinks an' shut my mouth, on account o' we just don't seem to be talkin' th' same game.~
@5990 = ~[ARAN] Well, I do appreciate th' females, that be for sure. But I'd rather appreciate you, if I could get a chance to do so.~
@5991 = ~[PC] Now would be a good time.~
@5992 = ~[PC] You will not get an opportunity if you cheapen it by sharing. If you were a little smarter, you would realize that I might want to be the center of your attention, not just a "first among equals". Or perhaps you have forgotten your basic combat tactics for conquest... focus your forces, concentrate on your objectives...~
@5993 = ~[PC] What should I do? Throw myself onto your chest, flutter my eyelashes, glance shyly up into your face, and whisper how handsome you are?~
@5994 = ~[ARAN] I do guess I asked for that one.~
@5995 = ~[ARAN] I'd say there be naught in th' way o' havin' "too much" fun, but I know better. It be all fun an' games until th' bouncer drops you on your face in th' muck an' mire.~
@5996 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be right kind o' you, but my jaw works just fine. It don't rightly need healin'. An' if you mean correct my accent an' grammar, let's just get on wi' doin' somethin' easier, like mayhap seein' th' faces o' all th' Masked Lords o' Waterdeep, or gettin' Shar to share a romantic kiss wi' Corellon Latherian.~
@5997 = ~[ARAN] I... err...~
@5998 = ~[ARAN] Heh. I have a line a second ready when it be not called for, but when it matters, my quiver be empty. Tymora done thrown Her Coin against me today, an' that be a fact.~
@5999 = ~[ARAN] That might just do th' trick.~
@6000 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, that be a great debate. Do it resolve from th' Chondathan 'spellblight', multiple non-sourced derivations what come from gods destroyin' things when Ao were dividin' up sides, or mayhap th'...~
@6001 = ~[ARAN] Hells. You be laughin' at me. Fine. Be that way.~
@6002 = ~[ARAN] Now, this don't rightly be an ordinary Company, eh?~
@6003 = ~[CERND] There are no ordinary Companies, only collections of different abilities. Like the snow falling from the sky, there are only individuals who move into random patterns.~
@6004 = ~[EDWIN] The rest of these lackeys are ordinary. But you are correct. With my presence, this group becomes extraordinary. (With that imbecile along, perhaps I should say extraordinarily stupid.)~
@6005 = ~[JAHEIRA] What do you think is 'ordinary'?~
@6006 = ~[MINSC] We are not ordinary! We have Boo!~
@6007 = ~[KORGAN] Ordinary enough ter shut yer yap, boyo. You ask too many questions.~
@6008 = ~[VICONIA] If you have a difficulty with my presence, jaluk, spit it out.~
@6009 = ~[ARAN] Hey, Drowess, I was talkin' to <CHARNAME>. I can work with most anybody. Though this is the first time I have seen your kind on this side of the shield wall, so to speak.~
@6010 = ~[YOSHIMO] Indeed, what do you consider ordinary, my friend?~
@6011 = ~[ARAN] An 'ordinary' Adventurin' Company is close to a Merchant's Guild Fist. Sword, Knife, Stave, Wand, and Pen, all working together. And they don't usually carry such powerful gear.~
@6012 = ~[PC] Well, that's colorful. Some definitions? Because I really didn't understand you.~
@6013 = ~[PC] No, this is not an ordinary group. But you will fit in fine, I am sure.~
@6014 = ~[PC] Curiosity killed the cat. Keep your comments to yourself, Aran.~
@6015 = ~[PC] I see your mouth moving, and I hear sounds. But they make no sense.~
@6016 = ~[PC] You will find your own way with us, if you are useful enough. You have already made it clear that you tend to talk while traveling.~
@6017 = ~[ARAN] Them's what fight well an' be armored well enough concentrate on formin' a line, an' lock shields together to form a barrier. Then, th' enemy charges, an' they hit the wall. They get thrown back in confusion, an' the wall steps forward an' attacks, reforms, repeat until they be dead or runnin'.~
@6018 = ~[KELDORN] There are some strengths to having a shield wall in large combat, but I have seen the concept fail with smaller parties.~
@6019 = ~[ANOMEN] It is a useful tactic. It preserves the more important forces and expends the weaker.~
@6020 = ~[ARAN] You mean it preserves nobles, at th' cost of lesser classes lives.~
@6021 = ~[ANOMEN] I believe that is what I said.~
@6022 = ~[ARAN] Typical tin-can crap. <CHARNAME>, done right, it be no class warfare - th' concept is that the wall protects th' spellcasters, an' the spellcaster protects th' wall - it's like creatin' our own turtle, so to speak.~
@6023 = ~[PC] I can see some problems with that combat setup.~
@6024 = ~[PC] What happens if the enemy doesn't charge?~
@6025 = ~[PC] You put your faith up front, then, Aran. I can see why you decided to become a cleric. Fighting in that line would force any being to reevaluate their place on the Great Wheel.~
@6026 = ~[PC] So that is why you decided to add 'investigative skills' to your fighting? Safer to hide and seek than stand in harm's way?~
@6027 = ~[PC] I knew there was a reason you began studying spellcraft. Not quite as much danger when you are not standing directly in harms way.~
@6028 = ~[PC] Look, no more talking. We are in a rush, and you talk too much anyways.~
@6029 = ~[ARAN] Lightnin', fireballs, an' acid fog take out large chunks of a Wall, but that's why you got spellcasters to fight that off. Plus, any time th' Wall is takin' heat, your spellcasters can go to work on their spellcasters right harsh.~
@6030 = ~[VALYGAR] Once again, the misuse of the Weave causes death and destruction. Is there no other way to work with the wall than to protect it with magic?~
@6031 = ~[ARAN] Not every group has spellcasters, so sure thing. I never did see a spellcaster get off a successful spell when he's got an arrow through his left eye. That's archery at work, or cavalry chargin' round the flank an' smashin' 'em but good.~
@6032 = ~[VALYGAR] A very satisfying thought.~
@6033 = ~[ARAN] Sure enough. Like what, exactly?~
@6034 = ~[VICONIA] Must we discuss this with a common sellsword? A Drow child could outwit him. Our enemies will not wait patiently while he attempts to fumble through his lack of knowledge with you.~
@6035 = ~[PC] A wall must take a huge hit from any spellcasters around. It sounds like it makes a big target.~
@6036 = ~[PC] I think that is enough analysis.~
@6037 = ~[PC] You are relying on weight and numbers to hold back the enemy. What happens when I charge a shield wall with magical weaponry that cleaves through shields like a hot knife through butter?~
@6038 = ~[PC] A well placed fireball, or perhaps some lightning, or simply a gaseous cloud... there are lots of ways I could break up that wall, Aran.~
@6039 = ~[PC] Outdoors, a druid must eat shield walls as a light snack. I might call lightning, if I could, and fry them all. Or entangle them and allow archery to finish them.~
@6040 = ~[PC] I would probably sneak around back, and take them out one by one. Or simply avoid the whole wall, make your way past them, and get rid of the spellcasters.~
@6041 = ~[PC] A full audience, drawn up into a line, just for me? If I can't beguile them or terrorize them with my music, I would have to reevaluate my bardic skills.~
@6042 = ~[PC] There are many ways, both spiritually and physically, to influence such a formation. Perhaps you would enlighten me as to the weaknesses you have seen yourself?~
@6043 = ~[PC] Well, you are supposed to be the tactics expert. Consider it a test of your knowledge. You tell me.~
@6044 = ~[ARAN] O' course, I didn't say it were a perfect solution. I just think it would help us out.~
@6045 = ~[KORGAN] All this namby-pamby talk o' tactics makes me wanna hit something. Cut the blabber so we can get going.~
@6046 = ~[ARAN] Ho, shortaxe, got up on th' wrong side o' bed this century?~
@6047 = ~[VICONIA] It is right that the weaker and lesser cattle should be expended as shields.~
@6048 = ~[ARAN] I wasn't talkin' to you, drowess... you can kiss my arse.~
@6049 = ~[ARAN] Not much in th' way o' help if we have all spellswords, I think. But other than that, a Wall be a right powerful tactic.~
@6050 = ~[ANOMEN] You surprise me. I thought you had very little training in strategy and tactics.~
@6051 = ~[ARAN] Book-study, that I be light on. But there be no better teacher than an organized an' implacable enemy what wants to kill a lad.~
@6052 = ~[KELDORN] Is this Flaming Fist training?~
@6053 = ~[ARAN] To tell th' truth, th' Fist be better at barroom brawls an' guard duty, for th' most part. But there be some smart officers what use any opportunity to teach in th' field. Improves th' survival odds, it does.~
@6054 = ~[PC] I think that is enough analysis. We should move along.~
@6055 = ~[PC] I will think about bringing on more swords, Aran. But I can't promise anything.~
@6056 = ~[PC] I will think about it, Aran. But I am more likely to get a skilled thief or two to complement our skillset.~
@6057 = ~[PC] I will think about it, Aran. But I am more likely to get a paladin to assist us.~
@6058 = ~[PC] I will think about it, Aran. But I am more likely to get some spellcasters to assist us.~
@6059 = ~[PC] I think you should avoid discussing tactics with me from now on. I think I have things well in hand.~
@6060 = ~[ARAN] That would work right fine, an' roll right up th' flank, until you got exposed. Then there'd be th ' hells to pay, I bet.~
@6061 = ~[ARAN] I suppose you could look at it that way. On th' other hand, one little spell o' silenc, an' there might be all th' hells to pay for you, you know.~
@6062 = ~[ARAN] Book-study, that I be light on. But there be no better teacher than an organized an' implacable enemy what wants to kill a lad. You learn to keep your wits sharp an' never forget a leeeon learned through hard experience.~
@6063 = ~[ARAN] Lots o' ways. Most o' them have to do wi' breakin' morale, or disruptin' th' formation in some way or other. Not a problme for a strong will like yours, but most soldiers don't appreciate havin' stingin' nettles grow up around 'em, or gettin' plagued by insects.~
@6064 = ~[CERND] You surprise me. I thought you had very little training in the strategy and tactics of nature.~
@6065 = ~[ARAN] Truth be told, now that I think o' it, th' Wall be a right fine tactic when there be larger numbers. Mayhap it would not apply so well here after all, on account o' we have so few in th' party to begin with.~
@6066 = ~[MAZZY] We might be better served by keeping our numbers small. Large groups require supply lines, move at slower speeds...~
@6067 = ~[ARAN] Banes Bones, you be right. I should have thought o' that before openin' my mouth, eh? I guess we have th' right composition for a small, mobile force wi' out al th' trouble o' mass logistics an' organization.~
@6068 = ~[KORGON] Gods, shut yer blighted yap, Whitehand. You blather on.~
@6069 = ~[ARAN] Keep your britches on, shortaxe.~
@6070 = ~[ARAN] Well, then th' Shield Wall is protection for archers an' spellcasters. Acts like a livin' stone wall to hide behind, an' it can move forward an' take on all comers.~
@6071 = ~[MAZZY] That comes at a price in lives, Aran.~
@6072 = ~[ARAN] Sometimes. Then again, we ain't exactly playin' a simple card game, Mazzy. Folks hired for the Wall know their business, an' the risks.~
@6073 = ~[ARAN] I'm not stupid, <CHARNAME>, just a mite slow to come to conclusions sometimes. Mages get th' big firepower, an' they get protected. 'Course, they also get targeted first, so really it was out o' the fryin' pan and into the fire, so to speak. But change can be good.~
@6074 = ~[EDWIN] (The idiot thinks he can weave spells. Amusing.) By all means, waste coin on more fighters, <CHARNAME>. Having more targets in front of me will provide amusement when they inevitably die.~
@6075 = ~[ARAN] Forewarned is fore-armed. I've been on the raw end o' enough deals to realize I want to know more about th' opposition before someone decides to put me on the wall.~
@6076 = ~[JAN] Forearmed? When did anatomy become part of this discussion? You sound like my Uncle Gertan, who kept talking about his body parts until finally one day it caught up to him.~
@6077 = ~[ARAN] I meant 'prepared', see... but somehow I figured this was more about your Uncle Gertan than what I was sayin'. OK, how'd it catch up to him?~
@6078 = ~[JAN] He mentioned his superior foot bones one too many times to Aunt Petunia, and she proceeded to show him how to put his superior foot bones between his superior mandibles, and took off with a follower of Denir. A nice gnomish lad from west aways. I hear they are very happy, preaching somewhere near the Border Kingdoms.~
@6079 = ~[ARAN] I have seen th' Wall fail with petrification spells in small groups, as it's easy enough to go around a few swords what aren't move or are slowed. Big battles, with long stretches, that's not a problem.~
@6080 = ~[KELDORN] I have also seen the shield wall crumble from siege engine attacks, and from gryphon or dragon attack. Something as simple as a gnomish airship can cause enough distraction to stop a wall's chief strength, that of locked shields.~
@6081 = ~[ARAN] How'd you stop that kind o' problem?~
@6082 = ~[KELDORN] More rigorous training.~
@6083 = ~[MAZZY] But what of the differences in size? If we were to lock shields, Aran, my shield would be at your kneecap. I doubt it would work as you describe.~
@6084 = ~[ARAN] Aye, true enough, Mazzy. I never did see what happens when a group o' mismatched shields tried it. It might work, though. You'd be in a position to get up under their defense, I suspect.~
@6085 = ~[ARAN] I guess th' central question boils down to th' basics - which be mightier, th' pen or th' sword?~
@6086 = ~[EDWIN] Bah. It is not the tool. It is how one uses it. (Imbeciles. Let them prattle on about swords. My superior intellect shall shatter them in a heartbeat.)~
@6087 = ~[HAERDALIS] A fine feather from a wise sparrow, my friend. Penned works last for centuries after the creatures who wrote them have turned to dust, for they immortalize the stories that we pass on. But I do not think I would place them in a duel together to decide the result.~
@6088 = ~[JAHEIRA] Unless you are talking of the destruction of the forests for paper and the harvesting of sheepskin to produce vellum, I do not see how the pen can be mightier than the sword. Nature needs no written word to show her power.~
@6089 = ~[KELDORN] I think that I disagree with both points. Neither pen nor sword can sway a determined heart. Faith is stronger than both.~
@6090 = ~[KORGAN] I'll take me axe, an' you take yer pansy little feather, an' I bet you your purse I'd beat th' crap outta ye.~
@6091 = ~[MINSC] Swords, not words, Boo! That is my motto.~
@6092 = ~[NALIA] I might scribe a scroll of lightning, and do the damage of a hundred swords. But I am not sure it is really the pen that does it.~
@6093 = ~[AERIE] I... I might scribe a scroll of lightning, and do the damage of many swords. But I am not sure it is really the pen that does it.~
@6094 = ~[KORGAN] *whack*~
@6095 = ~[AERIE] That was not very nice, Korgan. You cut his quill in half!~
@6096 = ~[PC] Good one, Korgan. Ah, trail talk about philosophy. The 'might versus write' debate. I think I would rather be boiled in oil or served raw to a pack of gibberlings.~
@6097 = ~[PC] A feather. A sharpened feather, dipped in ink. Versus weapons. I think Korgan just answered you, Aran.~
@6098 = ~[PC] Cut straight to the point, didn't he?~
@6099 = ~[ARAN] Well now, Let me be seein' if I done got all this straight...~ [c-aws105]
@6100 = ~[ARAN] <PLAYER1>, <PLAYER2>. All present an' accounted for. Well, mostly, anyways. Ain't no accountin' for some o' us, perhaps.~
@6101 = ~[ARAN] <PLAYER1>, <PLAYER2>, <PLAYER3>. All present an' accounted for. Well, mostly, anyways. Ain't no accountin' for some o' us, perhaps.~
@6102 = ~[ARAN] <PLAYER1>, <PLAYER2>, <PLAYER3>, <PLAYER4>. All present an' accounted for. Well, mostly, anyways. Ain't no accountin' for some o' us, perhaps.~
@6103 = ~[ARAN] <PLAYER1>, <PLAYER2>, <PLAYER3>, <PLAYER4>, <PLAYER5>. All present an' accounted for. Well, mostly, anyways. Ain't no accountin' for some o' us, perhaps.~
@6104 = ~[ARAN] <PLAYER1>, <PLAYER2>, <PLAYER3>, <PLAYER4>, <PLAYER5>, <PLAYER6>. All present an' accounted for. Well, mostly, anyways. Ain't no accountin' for some o' us, perhaps.~
@6105 = ~[ARAN] We are richer than Sune's temple coffers, that's for sure. We could buy us a whole army o' mercenaries. I hear the Windriders are available.~
@6106 = ~[ARAN] We have plenty o' coin, though not quite enough to start our own tradin' coster... Tymora's been right kind.~
@6107 = ~[ARAN] We don't have much in the way o' coin, but we have some. Ilmater would be right proud o' us keepin' so close to the bone, but then I favor Tymora, so she might say we need to press our luck a little an' get us goin' a bit more lively, so to speak.~
@6108 = ~[ARAN] We're flat out broke, as barren as Bane's Bones.~
@6109 = ~[ARAN] We have a reputation for doin' good works, whether deserved or not. In fact, most folks think we're some kind o' paladins of some sort, goin' about fixin' th' world. We're so good, Lathander's Golden light shines out our... well, that's neither here nor there.~
@6110 = ~[ARAN] We 're known by most folks as reasonably decent to have around.~
@6111 = ~[ARAN] We don't exactly have the most 'goody two-shoes' reputation. More like "Goody. Give us those two shoes. Y'ain't gonna be needin' 'em nohow, on account o' we are about to break your legs."~
@6112 = ~[ARAN] We are the meanest, nastiest, most self-servin' sons n' daughters o' bitches ever to walk Faerun. Or at least that's what folks say about us, when they scare their kids into goin' to bed at night.~
@6113 = ~[ARAN] Well, now. Comin' up with decent meals is more tricky than it appears. It helps to know what you have, an' what you might be doin' next. I mean, cookin' a light meal before fightin' a Great Wyrm is a good idea. Eatin' spicy food before explorin' a dark place that smells like a Calimport sewer, well, that is an invitation for disaster.~
@6114 = ~[ARAN] It's only the two of us, anyways. So it won't take much time.~
@6115 = ~[ARAN] Three to cook for, no problem. I'll set it up next time we rest.~
@6116 = ~[ARAN] We will need to take a bit o' time to cook for so many, but it could be worth it.~
@6117 = ~[ARAN] I think a full roast, honey glazed an' served with a juniper berry reduction. We have some blackbread I picked up in Athkatla, an' some Rashemi FireWine to round it out.~
@6118 = ~[ARAN] I cook a mean curry, fit to wake th' dead. Lamb an' peas, a few roots, an' a packet o' spices from Calimshaw. I even have a mite bit o' oil.~
@6119 = ~[ARAN] I think a stone-cooked flatbread, some o' that dried venison stirred in wi' vegetables for a decent curry, an' we're in business. It uses some supplies what cost a mite, but we can't be eatin' iron rations every night.~
@6120 = ~[ARAN] I think I can spit a few berrygobblers on a stick, nicely seasoned, an' give 'em a good roast. Otherwise, I'd be usin' supplies what cost coin, an' we don't have it to spare.~
@6121 = ~[ARAN] I know, I know - we probably ought to give some o' it away for the less fortunate, an' all that. Well, not this time.~
@6122 = ~[ARAN] I think I can keep it mostly smokeless, an' bank th' coals well. We don't want to attract much attention.~
@6123 = ~[ARAN] I'd joke about servin' up the stewed hearts o' our enemies, but I'm not sure that you'd see th' joke. So I'd better stick to what I know how to cook. Besides, some o' them might have been poisoned.~
@6124 = ~[ARAN] Look, combat be right easy to work through. You have to know your opponent, an' make plans quick, but it gets to be a habit. Say I'm workin' wi' an elven ranger, a wizard, an' a light-fingered halfling. The elven ranger can probably fight and cast, and she is likely used to working solo, so give her room to move. The wizard has spells what probably can hurt both friend an' foe alike, so get to a position to cover him from arrows but stay out from between him and whatever he is looking at, or you are serious toast, crisped to a fault, m'<PRO_GIRLBOY>. The halfling rogue is goin' to play hide an' seek, so that side is uncovered - play along, an' don't protect that side, an' probably some fool will take th' bait an' open up to a quick backstab.~
@6125 = ~[AERIE] I had little enough time to study such things. Among the Avariel, the warriors handled protecting us all. And at the Circus, Uncle Quayle taught me how to survive, not how to plan a fight.~
@6126 = ~[ANOMEN] The studies of tactics are important to those seeking knighthood and service. I doubt many sellswords think beyond their next meal.~
@6127 = ~[CERND] Nature provides both instinct and aggression for self protection, and often allows intellect for planning. Not for gibberlings and some other swarming creatures, but for much of nature.~
@6128 = ~[EDWIN] The most efficient tactic is to place you between the enemy and the more intelligent members of the party. (The simian may need to be prompted to recognize my superior intellect. He shows little sign of independent thought.)~
@6129 = ~[JAHEIRA] Sometimes habits of thought are useful. I find that messy thoughts end up in messy actions. Aran, straighten your legging, it is catching on the ground again.~
@6130 = ~[KELDORN] I am afraid that experience shows there is need for more flexibility. Having a plan is important, but how you react cannot become instinctive, or your enemy will use your own predictability against you.~
@6131 = ~[KORGAN] You think too much.~
@6132 = ~[VALYGAR] I prefer to observe first, then decide on the correct course of action.~
@6133 = ~[VICONIA] With such simplistic strategies, I am surprised you have survived so long, rivvil.~
@6134 = ~[YOSHIMO] There are many different ways of preparing, it seems. In my homeland, lightweight armor and well-crafted katanas blend with magic. Here the armor is often heavier, and I have even seen what you would call "twin swords" style put to use. Each require different methods for use.~
@6135 = ~[ARAN] Now, <CHARNAME>, you an' I both know there's a mite o' help to be had wi' our spells, castin' wards an' blastin' things apart. But I did find one thing that trumps most o' that, taught in some o' the far reaches o' Faerun.~
@6136 = ~[ARAN] Now, <CHARNAME>, you an' I both know there's a mite o' help to be had wi' support from mages an' clerics added to us, castin' wards an' blastin' things apart. But I did find one thing that trumps most o' that, taught in some o' the far reaches o' Faerun.~
@6137 = ~[ARAN] Now, <CHARNAME>, you an' I both know there's a mite o' help to be had wi' support from spellcasters like you, castin' wards an' blastin' things apart. But I did find one thing that trumps most o' that, taught in some o' the far reaches o' Faerun.~
@6138 = ~[PC] What is that?~
@6139 = ~[PC] Go on.~
@6140 = ~[PC] I don't think I want to know.~
@6141 = ~[ARAN] Well there's all sorts o' fancy tactical writin's an' trainin' to be had, an' there's plenty o' different ideas on what counters what.~
@6142 = ~[ARAN] That be the last time I get leatherwork done cut rate. This blighted bootlace is breakin'. Anyone got a spare?~ [c-aws106]
@6143 = ~[JAHEIRA] You should be better prepared. Think ahead next time, Aran.~
@6144 = ~[AERIE] I - I'm sorry, I don't have anything extra.~
@6145 = ~[KORGAN] It will cost you a trade bar.~
@6146 = ~[EDWIN] (Idiot.) Perhaps we would move faster if you held still while I carved a new one from your hide.~
@6147 = ~[MINSC] Here, Aran, I have a bootlace!~
@6148 = ~[ARAN] By the fire giant's gods, whomever they are... Minsc, you are a big, big boy. Thanks. I'll take a third o' that length.~
@6149 = ~[CERND] If you use leather to bind that, I would hope that you use the rest of the animal to good purpose. As Nature herself demonstrates, nothing should be wasted.~
@6150 = ~[ARAN] Mystra's Magnificent Mouth, Cernd... given the choice between my feet in battle an' the animal, I am considerin' the animal a distant second.~
@6151 = ~[PC] For the god's sake, slow down with the swearing, will you?~
@6152 = ~[PC] Here, have a lace of mine. But why are you blaspheming over something so minor, Aran?~
@6153 = ~[PC] You take every opportunity to swear, don't you, Aran.~
@6154 = ~[PC] Here you go, Aran. No need to cut up Minsc's spares. And be careful of your language, you might offend someone.~
@6155 = ~[PC] Alright, move along, everyone. The sellsword is having troubles again. Catch up fast, Aran.~
@6156 = ~[ARAN] Three things you shouldn't take from a man, <CHARNAME>... his swearin', his drink, and his weapon.~
@6157 = ~[HAERDALIS] Ah, fair fledgling, I think you should simply say 'his voice'. And of course, no man or woman should ever lose that.~
@6158 = ~[KELDORN] Invoking the gods is a natural stress release, Aran. But as you grow more powerful, the gods tend to listen more closely. They may take exception to having their name used so freely.~
@6159 = ~[MAZZY] My mother often told me that swearing was not to be taken lightly, for it speaks to your soul as well as the gods.~
@6160 = ~[NALIA] Swearing is both vulgar and common. A gentleman does not use such language.~
@6161 = ~[ARAN] I thought you were into helpin' th' 'common man', there, Nalia. I never claimed to be no gentleman.~
@6162 = ~[NALIA] Teaching the commoners respect for the gods goes along with teaching respect for themselves, Aran.~
@6163 = ~[VICONIA] Speak your words loudly, sellsword. I want to see your face just before an Avatar destroys you.~
@6164 = ~[ANOMEN] Your language offends me. Then again, your presence in general offends me.~
@6165 = ~[ARAN] Bugger off, jackass. Come talk wi' me when you got somethin' more than the foul smell o' breakin' wind from your mouth.~
@6166 = ~[KORGAN] Let the sorry bastard say his piece.~
@6167 = ~[PC] Hey, it is your business if you go around haphazardly calling random gods. But when one answers, you had better be prepared for the surprise.~
@6168 = ~[PC] Without faith, you are nothing.~
@6169 = ~[PC] I thought you were a cleric, Aran. That should mean you only swear by your own god.~
@6170 = ~[PC] I am not taking any of those, Aran. Just settle down and choose one god or goddess, will you?~
@6171 = ~[PC] I was speaking of being less socially awkward. The theology does not interest me. There are no gods, just very powerful beings that demand worship and followers.~
@6172 = ~[VALYGAR] Why not risk the gods wrath? Their love or their displeasure amounts to the same thing.~
@6173 = ~[ARAN] Aye, now, you can't rightly believe that, Valygar.~
@6174 = ~[VALYGAR] I most certainly do. Praise them or curse them, praise by them and curse through them, it matters not.~
@6175 = ~[ARAN] That is too far for my blood, friend. I claim Tymora as my favorite from time to time, an' swear usin' some other on other days, to be sure. But no faith in the gods is askin' for trouble I want no part of.~
@6176 = ~[VALYGAR] I think it would be better to not discuss my feelings on the 'gods', and the damage done by believers everywhere.~
@6177 = ~[ARAN] Aye, true enough. Didn't mean to offend you, now. It be right true that discussin' politics or religion is like standin' in the middle o' Athkatla's Promenade an' practicin' magic without a license. Bound to attract trouble, eh?~
@6178 = ~[PC] True enough, Valygar. There are no gods, just very powerful beings that demand worship and followers.~
@6179 = ~[ARAN] Do you see the glass as half full or half empty? Be ye optimist, pessimist, or somethin' else?~
@6180 = ~[YOSHIMO] Ah, the eternal question. The glass is half full, of course.~
@6181 = ~[MINSC] I do not understand. You are holding no glass, Aran.~
@6182 = ~[ARAN] Aye, my large friend. It's a metaphor. Somethin' not real... hey.  I'll explain it later.~
@6183 = ~[KORGAN] Stupid questions. Who cares if it is half full, or half empty, as long as it is mine.~
@6184 = ~[JAHEIRA] I am certain that the glass is neither half full nor half empty. Someone simply did not complete the task of filling the glass, and needs to be reminded.~
@6185 = ~[EDWIN] (Mind games from children. How droll.) The glass is half empty. The more pertinent question is whom to punish for it.~
@6186 = ~[KELDORN] I once heard a learned sage change this question, speaking of a third option. The pessimist complains about the wind; the optimist expects it to change; the realist adjusts the sails.' I prefer to avoid the question by picking up the pitcher and filling the glass until it overflows.~
@6187 = ~[VALYGAR] I have heard a different interpretation. An optimist believes that this is the best of all possible worlds. A pessimist fears that the optimist is correct'. The glass, though, is half empty.~
@6188 = ~[CERND] I find that there are only optimists. A pessimist is an optimist who has been wounded by disappointment, and a realist is one who cannot trust themselves to feel either extreme. And the glass is half full.~
@6189 = ~[PC] The glass is half full, Aran.~
@6190 = ~[PC] The glass is half empty, Aran.~
@6191 = ~[PC] The glass simply exists, Aran. Pick it up and use it, and stop bothering with how much is in it.~
@6192 = ~[PC] The glass simply exists, Aran. The fates will decide whether it is full or empty. We are simply required to drink.~
@6193 = ~[PC] Who cares, as long as there's enough to drink?~
@6194 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a right big shame. Pretty, rich, an' bored out o' her skull...~
@6195 = ~[ARAN] So she meets up wi' this handsome sellsword an' decides to try a life on th' road, right, rubbin' his back at night an'... oh, hells, sorry. It be your story. I'll be just shuttin' up an' listenin'. You go on.~
@6196 = ~[ARAN] Now why would I want to hear about someone what be so borin'? I mean, you are plenty interestin', an' this wallflower 'Emma' don't rightly have no story what to speak of, an'... oh, hells, sorry. It be your story. I'll be just shuttin' up an' listenin'. You go on.~
@6197 = ~[ARAN] Hey, hey, no, naught wi' th' tales o' them Red Wizards takin' over peoples brains an' usin' them for their nefrar.. neffere... dammit, nefarious deeds!~
@6198 = ~[EDWIN] (Buffoon. A true literary masterpiece, thrown as pearls before swine.) <CHARNAME>, silence this overgrown ape and continue.~
@6199 = ~[ARAN] No, none o' that. Tell me somethin' nice an' happy, wi' a sellsword what finds all th' riches he wants, an' a fair lass to bed, an' another to marry, an' mayhap a third what to dally with on occasion just to keep things spicy...~
@6200 = ~[ARAN] No, none o' that. Tell me somethin' nice an' happy, wi' a sellsword what finds all th' riches he wants, an' wins away your heart, an' lives right happily ever after exceptin' when they go out together an' whup up on some bad-arsed giants just for fun...~
@6201 = ~[ARAN] So, what be th' word?~
@6202 = ~[ARAN] Things look a mite grim, don't they?~
@6203 = ~[ARAN] Looks like we might not have time for sparkin'. I was hopin' more for a "happy ever after" endin', an' all.~
@6204 = ~[PC] Aran, I have no right to throw your life into this battle. You have served well. It might be time for you to move on.~
@6205 = ~[PC] Are you with me, Aran? This is bigger than anything we have ever faced before.~
@6206 = ~[PC] Aran, it is time you left. There is nothing to be gained by throwing away your very existence.~
@6207 = ~[PC] What is your evaluation, Aran. Is this unwinnable?~
@6208 = ~[PC] I love you, Aran. I need your counsel. Do you think this is unwinnable?~
@6209 = ~[PC] Just hold me for a moment.~
@6210 = ~[PC] Where is all your faith, Aran?~
@6211 = ~[PC] So, sellsword. Are you man enough to follow me to your doom?~
@6212 = ~[ARAN] You know, I swear by plenty o' gods, <CHARNAME>. And make no mistake, I'm right scared.~
@6213 = ~[ARAN] But I got more faith that you will prevail than in th' entire pantheon. If you leave it to me, I'll choose to be where I belong, backin' your play, no matter th' odds.~
@6214 = ~[ARAN] Besides my own god, I hold no other bein' before you. If it is  all right wi' you, I'll stay where I belong - backin' your play, no matter th' odds.~
@6215 = ~[ARAN] I came out o' th' Moonshae Isles wi' a fair amount o' experience, an' a decent respect for th' mercenary life. I wanted shut o' th' Axes, anyways, an' a friend mentioned there were some right heavy troop deployments on the border wi' Amn. So, I went an' signed up for th' highest pay I could. Just in time for a series o' pitched battles against th' Chill an' them Iron Throne bastards, though we didn't rightly know who it was reinforcin' them at th' time. I served my battles, an' some police duty, an' I developed decent respect for th' Flamin' Fist.~
@6216 = ~[ARAN] But things got a mite bit awkward. You done talked to Dosan on this, I am right sure, an' from both your an' his perspectives it was a mite more than awkward, eh?~
@6217 = ~[ARAN] But things got a mite bit awkward. Strange orders, an' stranger countermands, an' then a big reorganization up top somewhere.~
@6218 = ~[ARAN] So a bunch o' us decided we needed a transfer south.~
@6219 = ~[ARAN] They say th' gear don't make th' man. But it do help, eh?~
@6220 = ~[DMTOWN1] Take it from one who spent a little time in Maztica. Good gear saves lives.~
@6221 = ~[ARAN] Brother, I hear you. You spend a long time?~
@6222 = ~[DMTOWN1] Two years before I came to my senses and went back to civilian life. I'll take my chances with the dangerous nightlife around here. At least that I can predict.~
@6223 = ~[ARAN] Well, good luck to you. I don't think I could take th' quiet life for too long, but it seems to have agreed wi' you.~
@6224 = ~[DMTOWN1] Good luck and a pearl to you.~
@6225 = ~[ARAN] Why, do you know o' any?~
@6226 = ~[DMTOWN2] Well, there's always some hirin' o' watchmen, and sometimes they need a bouncer at some inns.~
@6227 = ~[ARAN] So, long story short, you got nothin'.~
@6228 = ~[DMTOWN2] Hey, don't get touchy. We were just makin' conversation!~
@6229 = ~[ARAN] Civilians. Can't live with 'em, can't live wi' out 'em. An' if you take 'em out back to beat some sense into 'em, you end up wi' a tenday in jail an' a stiff fine.~
@6230 = ~[ARAN] Why, sure thing. I can help you out right quick. You ever heard o' th' Jerva's Jerkins? They be th' toughest, most fierce company Amn has to be offerin'. An' I can get you an introduction, for only 5 gold.~
@6231 = ~[GMTOWN02] I don't have that much. What will 3 gold get me?~
@6232 = ~[ARAN] Well, I could hook you up wi' a lad what served in th' regulars in Maztica...~
@6233 = ~[GMTOWN02] I really don't have more than 3 copper pieces to spare. What will that get me?~
@6234 = ~[ARAN] For 3 coppers, I can start your hazin' ritual right away, by takin' your coin an' tossin' both you an' your bloody coin in th' nearest latrine.~
@6235 = ~[ARAN] Now that be true enough. Though I doubt there be anythin' around here like those in Calimport, eh?~
@6236 = ~[GMTOWN01] We have a much more civilized approach to bathing here in Amn. Although it does not appear that you are familiar with the concept of bathing.~
@6237 = ~[ARAN] Bane's... right. Don't suppose it would do us much good if I respond. Shuttin' up an' soldierin'.~
@6238 = ~[ARAN] Right behind me, eh? Right, then, I do be guessin' there's a mite bit o' muck about me. I thought I'd be cleanin' some off, but company might be nice.~
@6239 = ~[ARAN] (The bank of the stream is muddy and slippery, but the water runs clear and deep. Before you can think of even partially disrobing, you feel yourself slipping down the bank...)~
@6240 = ~[ARAN] (...and your recovery would be perfect, as usual, one foot balanced delicately along a ready branch, were it not for rough hands gripping your waist and tossing you directly into the crystal water.)~
@6241 = ~[ARAN] (...and your recovery might have been possible through the counterbalance of your wildly flailing arms, were it not for rough hands gripping your waist and tossing you directly into the crystal water.)~
@6242 = ~[ARAN] (...and you resign yourself to the inevitable clumsy sprawl in the mud. Surprisingly, you feel strong hands gripping your waist and tossing you farther out into the crystal water.)~
@6243 = ~[PC] (Gather your dignity, standing up, water cascading from your body) Very funny, Aran. This water is cold!~
@6244 = ~[PC] (Stand quickly, spitting water toward Aran) I think it is about time I thrashed you.~
@6245 = ~[PC] (Swim deeper, holding your breath in the icy water.)~
@6246 = ~[PC] (Push up to the surface after grabbing a clod of mud in your hand.)~
@6247 = ~[PC] (Surface quickly, turning your back to Aran, fumbling at your wet clothing) C-c-cold... cold.. so cold...~
@6248 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be a sight. Th' stars, all lightin' up in th' sky. I never tire o' lookin' at them.~
@6249 = ~[PC] (Gaze silently up at the twinkling lights far above you.)~
@6250 = ~[PC] There are lots more interesting things to look at than those far off lights.~
@6251 = ~[PC] Are you feeling all nostalgic and weepy again? Good god, man. You must be in love.~
@6252 = ~[PC] It kind of makes you think. What kind of powerful creatures can wander around those far-off tings at will?~
@6253 = ~[PC] Is this another attempt to get me into your bedroll?~
@6254 = ~[PC] (Study his profile carefully, his face slightly glowing in reflected starlight.)~
@6255 = ~[PC] Right. This is a waste of time. I'm tired. Have fun staring vacantly at the sky.~
@6256 = ~[ARAN] (Aran's face turns towards yours, and he smiles.)~
@6257 = ~[ARAN] Aye. Now that be a right powerful truth.~
@6258 = ~[ARAN] For a moment there, sound, thought, an' even time all seemed a might bit unimportant. Your face... well, it be more beautiful even than them there stars.~
@6259 = ~[ARAN] Well, that were a moment. Come to think of it, I get right tired o' lookin' at things outside o' my grasp. What I needs be doin' right now is tryin' to figure out how to get me a woman. Have a good night, eh?~
@6260 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap you be right. For one thing, there was this barmaid in Calimport, one o' them young ladies what dance, see? She had jewels all over her most interestin' areas what sparkled like those stars. Th' difference was, when you took off those stars, she were a sight more beautiful. Plus she were in arm's reach, so to speak.~
@6261 = ~[ARAN] Hells, no. Lust, mayhap, but that be a healthy thing for a young lad to be in, eh? Come to think of it, I should be writin' a nice letter to her right now, so's to warm her up for when I come callin'. Have a good night. I'll go find me a good light to work by.~
@6262 = ~[ARAN] Hells, man. Give us a few more years, an th' two o' us will be stridin' between 'em like two boys on a lark, an' gatherin' 'em up to hand over to adorin' admirers. After all, we done faced more powerful bein's than most folks know exist. An' on that happy thought, I'm off to bed. Your turn at watch, I think.~
@6263 = ~[ARAN] Hells, a man has to look up at th' sky just to tell him that there be more than th' dirt, eh? Way to spoil th' mood. An' on that happy thought, I'm off to bed. Your turn at watch, I think.~
@6264 = ~[ARAN] For a while there, I thought we might never get topside again. I did not relish th' thought o' endin' up stuck down in th' Underdark permanent-like.~
@6265 = ~[PC] Oh, it wasn't so bad. At least we knew almost everything we met was just waiting for a chance to kill us.~
@6266 = ~[PC] The classic Whitehand juxtaposition - say something nice, but add a swear word or two strong enough to blister the ears of young children.~
@6267 = ~[PC] Good, you are up. Get some food going, fast. I am starving!~
@6268 = ~[PC] Hey, I am not done with you yet. I still have some unattended romantic business to finish...~
@6269 = ~[PC] Shhh. Not so loud. I am going back to sleep for awhile.~
@6270 = ~[ARAN] We don't have to be in Underdark for that to be true, eh? If danger be th' spice o' life, then I think you be cayenne, paprika, an' burnin' oil all rolled into one!~
@6271 = ~[ARAN] Fervent feelin's fill foul phrases full, eh? I guess I should o' said "Mystra's Tears", or "Lathander's Smile", or some such.~
@6272 = ~[ARAN] Praise be to th' gods, we don't have to worry about no strange creatures showin' up in th' food, an' there be not a mushroom or fungus in sight. Real meal, an' open air.~
@6273 = ~[ARAN] Good gods, woman. You are like to kill me. We can always stop for a mite later, but we'd best be movin' on.~
@6274 = ~[ARAN] Now, pop right out o' that there bedroll, <CHARNAME>... my cookin' muscles have been all cramped down underground. I can feel a first-class meal comin' on. An' I be in th' mood for a right fine <DAYNIGHT> o' travel an' adventure!~
@6275 = ~[ARAN] We don't have to be in Underdark for that to be true, eh? If danger be th' spice o' life, then I think we have had one hells of a strong curry, topped wi' hotsauce an' mayhap some liquid fire.~
@6276 = ~[ARAN] There you are. I thought you might be off tryin' to get some sleep. Hells, there be a shortage o' candles in this place, eh? It be gloomier than a one legged man at a dancin' contest. Anyways, I needed to bend your ear a mite.~ [c-aws112]
@6277 = ~[ARAN] Well, <CHARNAME>, you done got yourself a nice little operation to run. Gamblin', prostitution, light theft, "protection", spyin', an' a cute little trainin' program to boot. Question is, what are you goin' to do with it.~ [c-aws123]
@6278 = ~[PC] Anything I want.~
@6279 = ~[PC] Whatever serves the greater good.~
@6280 = ~[PC] Are you jealous? After all, you have some minor skills in gathering either information or whatever is not tied down. Strike that. Especially things that are tied down.~
@6281 = ~[PC] I am not sure you would understand, all wrapped up in your books and scribing. It takes coin to keep you in quills, parchment, and spell components.~
@6282 = ~[PC] Say a prayer or two for me. I want this as a base of operations and an income stream, but I hear that there is only one way out of the Guild, and it involves me having a minor accident.~
@6283 = ~[PC] Well, I have your sword arm to back me up. Sometimes, a little subtle action is useful. Other times, the situation calls for the trademark "Whitehand Technique"...  kill anything that moves, and then resurrect anyone who we did not mean to kill.~
@6284 = ~[PC] I know this is not the most honest, upright way of doing things. But right now we need the resources, and shutting this all down puts people at risk of far worse owners.~
@6285 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us a nice place to set up base camp. I don't rightly know what a Ranger territory means, though, really. Anythin' special we got to do?~ [c-aws124]
@6286 = ~[PC] Just do what I tell you to, when I tell you to, and everything will be fine.~
@6287 = ~[PC] Whatever serves the greatest good for the greatest number of our charges.~
@6288 = ~[PC] It's good to know you are paying attention to our progress, Aran. Your scrivening will be useful handling all this. But stick to weaponry and contracts, and let me handle management.~
@6289 = ~[PC] Well, you have some minor skills in gathering either information or whatever is not tied down. Strike that. Especially things that are tied down.~
@6290 = ~[PC] Say a prayer or two for me. I want this as a base of operations and an income stream, but I know that helping protect a wide territory is a great deal of work.~
@6291 = ~[PC] I know this is not really what I spent my life training for. But right now we need the resources, and these people need someone to look after them.~
@6292 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us a nice place to set up a base. Th' Order's back room there be plain, but clean an' secure. I don't rightly know what they will do to me, on account o' my language bein' so rough, though. Any words o' advice?~ [c-aws125]
@6293 = ~[PC] We do what the Order says, when it asks. Until then, we take advantage of the stability they offer.~
@6294 = ~[PC] Whatever serves the greatest good.~
@6295 = ~[PC] Well, you have some minor skills in gathering information. That might make a useful addition to the Order, and secure our relationship with them.~
@6296 = ~[PC] Say a prayer or two for me. I want this as a base of operations, but I know that helping the Order is a great deal of work and returns very little coin.~
@6297 = ~[PC] I know this is not really what I spent my life training for. But right now we need the backup, and having the backing of the Order will allow us more freedom to operate.~
@6298 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us an odd place to set up base camp. I don't rightly know if wanderin' 'round the Planes be a good idea. Seems like we got enough trouble right here on Faerun.~ [c-aws126]
@6299 = ~[PC] We do whatever I want to do, and use the Sphere to accomplish those goals.~
@6300 = ~[PC] We will do whatever serves the greatest good for the most people.~
@6301 = ~[PC] Say a prayer or two for me. I want this as a base of operations, but I know that managing apprentices and dealing with the Sphere will be a great deal of work.~
@6302 = ~[PC] I know this is not really what I spent my life training for. But right now we need all the resources we can get, and this is too important an object to be left lying around unused.~
@6303 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us a nice place to set up permanent. Bein' a landlord has some advantages, too, with that coin comin' in. I don't suppose we can call up an army as well as use th' Keep as a home, eh?~
@6304 = ~[PC] We will have to investigate that. At the very least, we might be able to gather some idiots who will be useful spell-fodder and distractions before they die.~ [c-aws127]
@6305 = ~[PC] We will do whatever serves the greatest good for the most people who are tied to this Keep and its lands.~
@6306 = ~[PC] Well, you have some minor skills in gathering either information or whatever is not tied down. Strike that. Especially things that are tied down. You could investigate the books and see what might be possible.~
@6307 = ~[PC] No armies. I am not sure you would understand, all wrapped up in your books and scribing. It takes coin to keep you in quills, parchment, and spell components. It takes much, much more coin to build an army, even a conscripted one.~
@6308 = ~[PC] I know this is not really what I spent my life training for. But right now we need the backup, and having a fortress and tenants allows us more freedom to operate.~
@6309 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us a nice place to set up base camp. I don't rightly know what a Druid territory means, though, really. Anythin' special we got to do?~ [c-aws128]
@6310 = ~[PC] I use it to further my goals. You use it however I choose to let you.~
@6311 = ~[PC] We do whatever serves the entire Grove's creatures best.~
@6312 = ~[PC] I am not sure you would understand, all wrapped up in your books and scribing. Nature is a harsh mistress, and protecting this place will take a great deal of focus and attention.~
@6313 = ~[PC] Say a prayer or two for me. I want this as a base of operations, but I know that helping protect a wide territory is a great deal of work.~
@6314 = ~[PC] I know this is not really what I spent my life training for. But right now we need the backup, and having nature on our side could have huge advantages.~
@6315 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us a secure place to set up a base camp, complete wi' the protection o' a god. Anythin' special we got to do?~ [c-aws129]
@6316 = ~[PC] Whatever we can get away with.~
@6317 = ~[PC] Whatever serves the Temple.~
@6318 = ~[PC] I am not sure you would understand, all wrapped up in your books and scribing. There is more here than ways to keep you in quills and parchment.~
@6319 = ~[PC] Say a prayer or two for me. I want this as a base of operations, but I know that being involved in a Temple is a great deal of work.~
@6320 = ~[PC] I know this is not really what I spent my life training for. But right now we need the backup, and having the backing of the Temple will allow us more freedom to operate.~
@6321 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us a nice place to set up base camp. I don't rightly know much about playwritin', but you want help wi' the castin' couch, you just let me know.~ [c-aws130]
@6322 = ~[PC] We do whatever it takes to increase my fame and fortune.~
@6323 = ~[PC] We do our best to keep these people employed and helping lift spirits. These are dangerous, horrible times for most people, and they need good entertainment.~
@6324 = ~[PC] Say a prayer or two for me. I want this as a base of operations and an income stream, but I know that managing a successful Theater is a great deal of work.~
@6325 = ~[PC] Well, I have your sword arm to back me up. Sometimes, a little subtle action is useful. Other times, the situation calls for the trademark "Whitehand Technique"...  if something stands between you and your goal, whack it with something until it goes away.~
@6326 = ~[PC] I know this is not really what I spent my life training for. But right now we need resources, and having the Theater will allow us more freedom to operate.~
@6327 = ~[ARAN] Well, you done got us a nice place to set up base camp. I don't rightly know much about playwritin', but I do decent copywork. I think I done told you that before. How can I help?~ [c-aws131]
@6328 = ~[PC] This sudden offer to help would not be because some of the ingenues are pretty little redheads with wide, innocent eyes and low cut dresses, would it?~
@6329 = ~[PC] I think I can handle a theater company. After all of the dangerous beasts we have clobbered, how hard could handling a group of stage musicians, actors, and suppliers possibly be?~
@6330 = ~[ARAN] Denir's Dexterous Digits, I am goin' crazy. What wi' all o' these strongholds to maintain, there be so much paperwork that I be usin' potions o' healin' on th' paper cuts. An' some idiot decided it were unkind to kill animals an' trees to use for buildin' parchment an' vellum, so now I have that ranger cabin an' druid grove on verbal contract.~ [c-aws132]
@6331 = ~[ARAN] That senechal at th' Keep be whinin' about taxes not addin' up, th' Thieves Guild dues we paid twice on account o' "clerical error", an' somehow those bloody apprentices wanted spell components similar to the temple's order so th' order components got cross-shipped. Don't rightly know how more messed up this can get.~
@6332 = ~[ARAN] Hey, find me somethin' to kill, eh? I am shut o' paperwork for a good while. Or mayhap get me a nice personal assistant, what can keep up with th' filin'.~
@6333 = ~[PC] You asked to help, remember? Don't come crying to me now.~
@6334 = ~[PC] You have done a good job, and you will get through this. Just clear your head, take a day or two off, and then focus on getting things back in order.~
@6335 = ~[PC] If you can't handle it, we will find someone else to do the job.~
@6336 = ~[ARAN] I do believe right about now we should go back an' inspect that whole Keep you have under your command. If I had a wish, I'd spend it on that. I would even volunteer to check all th' beds, one at a time. A lad can never get enough comfort or sleep, eh?~
@6337 = ~[PC] Tired of living the exciting life of travel and adventure?~
@6338 = ~[PC] Oh, come on. You would waste a wish on traveling to a dusty old stronghold, just to lie in a comfortable feather bed?~
@6339 = ~[PC] I bet you two iron tradebars that your first wish would actually be something about women or alcohol.~
@6340 = ~[PC] If this is another complaint about your feet hurting from all the walking, then keep your whining to yourself.~
@6341 = ~[PC] I agree. But you should check out the storerooms. I'll check out the beds. Some tasks are too important to delegate.~
@6342 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. Note to self... don't mess wi' a ranger and <PRO_HISHER> territory, on account o' they will be right snippy about it. I will be goin' about my business, eh?~
@6343 = ~[ARAN] Right nice o' you, all things considered. Me, I'd be wonderin' how to get someone extra hired on, makin' sure your wishes got done while you be runnin' about Faerun huntin' mad mages and miscellaneous mischievous maniacs. But that be me, always thinkin' an' talkin' way too much.~
@6344 = ~[ARAN] Look, it will turn out fine for you, no matter what. Just a bit o' occasional paperwork, some meetin's, an' mayhap some decisions to make later on, eh? We get a base o' operations, mayhap some coin, an' who knows what else. Worst comes to worst, we walk away clean and let fate take a hand.~
@6345 = ~[ARAN] Takin' advantage o' the Order o' the Radiant Heart sounds right smart. It be up there among th' top "smart" things to do, alongside rippin' the mask off a Lord o' Neverwinter, crossin' the Shadow Thieves, takin' a piss on a Dryad's oak, an' havin' wild sex wi' random dragons.~
@6346 = ~[ARAN] Sounds just like those wet-behind-the-ears recruit squires I seen cleanin' privys. The Order's goin' to like havin' us around right fine.~
@6347 = ~[ARAN] Was this th' part where we break into low evil chuckles, followed by increasin'ly disturbin' laughter, followed by a thunderclap an' some ominous music?~
@6348 = ~[ARAN] Well, I surely don't know what wanderin' around in a glorified fishbowl randomly crushin' parts o ' towns will do for th' greater good, but it sure will be fun tryin' not to smash the thing up on th' landin's. At the very least, it ought to be good for a laugh or two.~
@6349 = ~[ARAN] Auril's Icy Aura, remind me not to piss you off, eh? I have heard o' cold, but th' last bastards what went for those tactics were Iron Throne.~
@6350 = ~[ARAN] Savras' Foresight, I understand right fine. An' I bet it will be a mite useful to have this place. Tell you what, you find somethin' I can do wi' my little quill, an' I will help out.~
@6351 = ~[ARAN] Well, I'll give it a shot. Somehow, I just hope they don't ask too many questions on how I get th' information or th' resources. Could be just a mite ticklish, eh?~
@6352 = ~[ARAN] Savras' Foresight, forewarned be forearmed, or somethin' like that. Runnin' this place will take information, good record keepin' an' an eye for detail. I be just th' right man for th' job. Now, where do they keep th' strong drink around here? I'll be wantin' to take a right good inventory...~
@6353 = ~[ARAN] I'm right on th' prayer angle, <CHARNAME>. But if you were afraid o' a little bit o' hard work, well... you'd be dead, an' some blighted arse would be makin' life hell for me by sendin' out waves o' murderin' bastards to set up bathtubs o' blood for a nice afternoon wash. So, all things considered, a little paperwork an' a few decisions be a small price to pay.~
@6354 = ~[ARAN] Hey, do I get royalties on that? On account o' I think most of the sly bastards we be fightin' seem to have th' same idea. Well, except for th' ones who give some long monologue about how they be the baddest arseholes around, an' we will be sorry we tangled wi' 'em. Poor sods.~
@6355 = ~[ARAN] Now, don't you be gettin' all star an' stage struck, <CHARNAME>. Next thing you know, you'll be dumpin' all your gold into a massive production of 'Lyra, the Masked Lady of Destiny; a Love Story In Three Acts', fendin' off demands from th' Actor's Guild an' th' Stage Workers Union. Worse, you might have to be dealin' with publicity agents.~
@6356 = ~[ARAN] Good entertainment? You be kiddin' me, right? The average person out there be more interested in watchin' th' drama o' whose daughter slept wi' whom, an' how many gibberlin's a man can be run over by in an hour. Hey... that's not bad. Mayhap we got a new show, cheap to produce. Sell tickets, then put a group o' commoners out in a field armed wi' butter knives, an' send in a wave o' gibberlin's. We could call it "Survivor: Athkatla".~
@6357 = ~[ARAN] Sharess' Sensual Caress, what ever put that fool idea into your head? Now, if you just send 'em over to me, I'll draw up a list o' measurements, an' such. Costumes don't rightly sew themselves into proper fit, you know. Busy, busy time. Knock before you enter th' wardrobe room, eh?~
@6358 = ~[ARAN] Waukeen's Wanderin' Worshipers, you never did no community theater productions, I take it.~
@6359 = ~[ARAN] Sure, sure... kick a man when he be down. Right. I can fix it up. You go on conquerin' Faerun, an' I'll just be in th' back, sortin' out supply requisitions.~
@6360 = ~[ARAN] Right you are. Tymora's Bright Smile, I done had worse troubles to iron out, like that time th' 'Fist accidentally took a contract for both protectin' an' sackin' the same fiefdom. No worries. I will take a breather, an' get back on it as soon as my head clears.~
@6361 = ~[ARAN] Hey, I studied enough magic to know how important that blighted Gond-Meets-Mystrul-an'-Mystra construct be. I just don't rightly see how you are goin' to be able to leverage it against th' bastards we are fightin' right now. You can't hide in an' among th' Planes when your opponents have eyes everywhere, an' when we don't know where they are, we can't just drop in unannounced. But I guess you be right. It is a damned fine place to take a nap, at least.~
@6362 = ~[ARAN] Now that you have a solid defensible position, mayhap you want to gather an army, an' get settled a mite before takin' on th' rest of the world, eh? Not that you have to listen to me, tryin' to tell you what to do. I just keep these lips flappin' way too much.~
@6363 = ~[PC] Actually, I had some other ideas for those lips of yours. I think I need a respite from all this heavy responsibility.~
@6364 = ~[PC] I agreed to help Nalia because it was in my best interests. We will wait for as long as it takes me to figure out how to best profit from all of this.~
@6365 = ~[PC] We have to make sure that the Keep is secured, and things are settled. But we need to move on as quickly as we can, too. I am debating whether to take Nalia along, or leave her here to make sure things get reorganized.~
@6366 = ~[PC] You have no idea what you are talking about, and even if you did, what makes you think I want to hear it from you?~
@6367 = ~[PC] Aran. Shut up. Go away. Now.~
@6368 = ~[PC] I think we had better move on quickly. I do not think we can afford to wait.~
@6369 = ~[PC] Actually, I was thinking of taking a bath. I think there is a set of washtubs in the master suite.~
@6370 = ~[ARAN] That sounds like a right nice idea. Just so you know, though, one o' th' maids was askin' about you, for some odd chore or somethin'. I'd duck in an' out o' there right quick, so you don't get no more things to handle tonight. But about my questions, do you have some time, or not?~
@6371 = ~[ARAN] Riiiight. A bath. Got it. Just be a mite bit more careful when you get in that water, eh? There were a powerful lot o' screamin' an' laughin' last time, an' I think some o' th' servants are beginnin' to talk. But before you go dippin' your various parts into various things, do you have that mite bit o' time?~
@6372 = ~[ARAN] What are you blighted well talkin' about? This be my forte, eh? I thought you'd be wantin' some help gettin' this place in order.~
@6373 = ~[PC] I can handle things myself. Just go get some sleep, and I'll give you orders in the morning.~
@6374 = ~[PC] If I wanted some unwashed idiot spouting orders about how to do things, I would have asked Edwin to run things for me. Even he would give better advice than you.~
@6375 = ~[PC] If I wanted some unwashed idiot spouting orders about how to do things, I would have asked Minsc to run things for me. Even he would give better advice than you.~
@6376 = ~[PC] If I wanted some unwashed idiot spouting orders about how to do things, I would have asked Minsc or Edwin to run things for me. Both would give better advice than you.~
@6377 = ~[PC] I appreciate the input, but I have too much on my hands right now. How about we have a good night's sleep, and then you draft up some plans on how you would go about defending this place. We can have a meeting some other time to go over it, ok?~
@6378 = ~[PC] Hey, don't get upset. You get all cute and kissable when you are upset, and I might be too tired to resist your charms.~
@6379 = ~[PC] Hey, don't get upset. I am just too tired to think about this right now. We are all heroes, here - why don't you go relax by flirting with one of the cute chambermaids? They probably won't be able to resist your charms.~
@6380 = ~[PC] Well, talk, then. But make it quick.~
@6381 = ~[PC] I'm sorry. That was a little short. Blame it on the lack of sleep, and this whole "save the world every day" thing we seem to have going.~
@6382 = ~[ARAN] Well fine. But there be some good tactical thought behind stayin' put for awhile. These lands have had th' crap kicked out o' 'em, and mayhap seein' you around a couple more times will give them a morale boost. Plus, give us a mite bit o' a rest to build up some scrolls an' supplies before movin' on.~
@6383 = ~[ARAN] Bloody hells, <CHARNAME>... look at you! There be half an inch o' you what hasn't been ripped, torn, or otherwise mauled. You need a good solid rest, some magical healin', an' mayhap an armorsmith to put th' party gear back in operation. An' there be some good tactical thought behind stayin' put for awhile. These lands have had th' crap kicked out o' 'em, and mayhap seein' you around a couple more times will give them a morale boost. Plus, give us a mite bit o' a rest to build up some scrolls an' supplies before movin' on.~
@6384 = ~[ARAN] Now, hold on one second. Do you think I be so easy you can just have your way wi' me any time you want?~
@6385 = ~[PC] Well, seeing as you are not really complaining while I am currently wrapping my arms around your neck and brushing your cheek with my eyelashes, yes.~
@6386 = ~[PC] Judging by how close you are holding me, and how your lips keep grazing my ear, yes.~
@6387 = ~[PC] Look, all that grabbing at my waist with your hands is very much unwanted. Go find someone else, because I am just not interested.~
@6388 = ~[PC] On second thought, I don't know if this is the time and place, Aran. I'm not even sure I want this kind of attention from you.~
@6389 = ~[PC] I let you flirt because it keeps you in line, but I am very much in love with someone else. I am not sure we should be sneaking around, even if it is fun.~
@6390 = ~[PC] You are so easy to tease. Forget it, Aran. I told you I did not want you to flirt with me. I just wanted to see what you would say.~
@6391 = ~[ARAN] Now, I'm not rightly goin' to argue wi' you. A little kissin' never hurt nobody, an' there be naught else we can do in just a stolen moment, eh? So do you want to kiss, or not?~
@6392 = ~[PC] Nope. Tactical distraction. Works every time. Now, why don't you say what it is you were trying to say?~
@6393 = ~[PC] I was joking, Aran. The thought of kissing you actually is quite disgusting. What is it you are annoying me with now?~
@6394 = ~[PC] You are easily misdirected with the mere offer of affection. That is a tactical weakness that I do so enjoy exploiting. One day, it will kill you.~
@6395 = ~[ARAN] Well, I did have me some ideas for th' security an' defense o' this place, but I have naught in th' way o' resistance to your womanly wiles, eh?~
@6396 = ~[ARAN] I was just offerin' some help, is all. I done found some o' th' architectural drawin's, an' land levies for militia service. I wanted to get a word in wi' you on how to proceed.~
@6397 = ~[PC] No time like the present, though I wish I could have rested first. I think I will drip blood all over this parchment. Let's see... yes. Go ahead and call up these militia for at least one tenday service, until we can get everything covered with professionals.~
@6398 = ~[PC] I think I will sit down for a minute, seeing as most of my body hurts.  Let's see... yes. Go ahead and pull what you need from manpower and supplies to block off that section. Less to defend means more attention on rebuilding.~
@6399 = ~[PC] Hmmm. Yes, this makes sense. Go ahead and pull what you need from manpower and supplies to block off that section. Less to defend means more attention on rebuilding.~
@6400 = ~[PC] No time like the present, though I wish I could have rested first. Let's see... yes. Go ahead and call up these militia for at least one tenday service, until we can get everything covered with professionals.~
@6401 = ~[PC] I will take a look at this information tomorrow, Aran. But if you are all fired up about working, you could go over the tax levies, and draw up a short list of those we could extort for more money.~
@6402 = ~[PC] Why are you bothering me with all of this? I want your skills focused on finding how much there is left in the treasury, and how much we have to help with the rebuilding.~
@6403 = ~[PC] Why are you bothering me with all of this? I want your skills focused on finding how much there is left in the treasury, and how much we can raise taxes.~
@6404 = ~[PC] I am well versed in fighting. All we need is the strength to hold this place for awhile. You are too interested in the details.~
@6405 = ~[PC] If you think it will help, go bother with all that petty detail. All I am really interested is wandering the library, and checking for spell components.~
@6406 = ~[PC] I am sure you mean well, but I don't have time to concentrate on the details. What I really need is time to pray to my god and gather my strength.~
@6407 = ~[PC] All we need is the illusion of strength to hold this place for awhile. Being pinned down to a fortress is not my idea of being subtle. Do I really need to be bothered with all these details?~
@6408 = ~[PC] I am more interested in the stories, songs, and poetry that our conquest of this place will inspire. I need some time and space to sit down and concentrate. Do I really need to be bothered with all these details?~
@6409 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. Inventory, check what be left o' th' raided treasury an' what can be built back up, check into th' land leases, th' whole audit.~
@6410 = ~[PC] And Aran... find every single way you can to get us more coin.~
@6411 = ~[PC] And Aran... don't you dare leave this room without kissing me.~
@6412 = ~[PC] And Aran... send me some food up from the kitchen. No dogmeat. Just real food.~
@6413 = ~[PC] You have your orders, so now will you please just let me go to sleep?~
@6414 = ~[ARAN] Now that be an order I can't rightly refuse. An' why would I want to, anyhow?~
@6415 = ~[ARAN] Whoa, now, I misread you right solid, I did. If this be a hostile takeover, you'd better let me know right quick, so I can set up a second set o' books.~
@6416 = ~[PC] You would do that? Cheat these people?~
@6417 = ~[PC] That's right, make a joke about these poor people and what they have suffered through. Do you really think I want you to do that?~
@6418 = ~[PC] Look, forget I said anything. I am tired and short-tempered. I just want to be left alone so I can go to sleep.~
@6419 = ~[ARAN] Whoa, now, I misread you right solid, I did. I thought you were givin' her a hand on account o' she be quite easy on th' eyes, an' everyone knows a hero has more of a chance with beddin' th' fair maid. If this be a hostile takeover, you'd better let me know right quick, so I can set up a second set o' books.~
@6420 = ~[ARAN] Me? Hells, no. Just wanted to see your face when I said it, eh? I guess it weren't that funny.~
