@8179 = ~[PC] (Throw his clothes in his general direction and flee back to camp.)~
@8180 = ~[PC] (Keep your eyes on his face as he walks toward you.)~
@8181 = ~[PC] Come and get them. Wait... never mind, because they are out there! (Throw his clothes into the water.)~
@8182 = ~[PC] (Watch his progress with interest.)~
@8183 = ~[PC] Here you go. One set of clothes, slightly dirty. Now get dressed. We have places to go and things to kill.~
@8184 = ~[ARAN] Now, then. These clothes might just be mine, eh? Hand 'em over.~
@8185 = ~[PC] (Lean forward, bringing every possible bit of you into contact with him, and smile into his face.)~
@8186 = ~[PC] I think I have seen enough of you, anyways.~
@8187 = ~[PC] Actually, I think I am laying claim to them. And to everything they cover, as well.~
@8188 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know. But then again, somehow I think you don't rightly know either.~
@8189 = ~[PC] What do you mean by that?~
@8190 = ~[PC] Leave the deep thoughts to others, Aran. I don't need the hassle.~
@8191 = ~[PC] Aran Whitehand, soldier, sailor, scribe... you will break your own rhyming scheme if you add philosopher.~
@8192 = ~[ARAN] Nothin'. Just I don't think you know what you be wantin'.~
@8193 = ~[PC] I know what I want, and it isn't you.~
@8194 = ~[PC] And you do?~
@8195 = ~[PC] I might know what I want, but just be hiding it. Perhaps I will tell you someday. Perhaps not.~
@8196 = ~[ARAN] No deep philosophy here. Just observational intelligence gatherin' an' a keen sense o' how I feel when you be unhappy.~
@8197 = ~[PC] What does my happiness have to do with you?~
@8198 = ~[PC] You let me worry about my happiness. You concentrate on keeping me alive.~
@8199 = ~[PC] Look, let's just get back to camp. This whole conversation is not really interesting me at all.~
@8200 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Sounds an' Scents! (His diving and crashing toward his clothes sends odd echoes bouncing everywhere.)~
@8201 = ~[ARAN] Coward!~
@8202 = ~[ARAN] Suit yourself. I won't be much longer.~
@8203 = ~[ARAN] (His lean form cuts back into the water like a dolphin, and he speeds his way away from you.)~
@8204 = ~[ARAN] I'll be along in a bit. I needs be gettin' dried off an' gather my gear, but I have to stretch out a mite bit more first.~
@8205 = ~[ARAN] Sometimes I do, an' sometimes I don't.~
@8206 = ~[ARAN] Yes, I do. What be botherin' you, eh?~
@8207 = ~[PC] Nothing. Except... Look, nothing. You swim. I'll just watch.~
@8208 = ~[PC] I don't know. But it might be better if someone just holds me for awhile. No funny business, and you better wrap up well in that towel.~
@8209 = ~[PC] I don't know how to ask for what I want.~
@8210 = ~[ARAN] (Aran swims to the bank and pulls his towel free of his clothing, wrapping himself as he comes out of the water. In a few quick strides he is beside you, his arms enfolding you in a comfortable embrace. You stand there together for a time, the world held at bay, with the occasional drip of water droplets falling against your cheek.)~
@8211 = ~[ARAN] What be wrong wi' just plain askin' it?~
@8212 = ~[PC] I... I want to feel loved.~
@8213 = ~[PC] I want you to make love to me.~
@8214 = ~[ARAN] (He moves to close the distance between you quickly, water cascading from his shoulders.)~
@8215 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be a fine thought, an' it takes courage to ask. But there be more than one way o' lovin'. Somethin' tells me you want someone to stay beside you an' let you know you be important.~
@8216 = ~[PC] You don't understand me at all. I enjoy the power of control and the respect fear brings. But right now, I just want someone to hold me and tell me that I am actually important to them.~
@8217 = ~[PC] You don't understand. I want someone to make passionate love to me. I want to feel special. I want you to stop splashing about and pay attention to me.~
@8218 = ~[PC] Is it too much to ask that you just come up here and kiss me?~
@8219 = ~[PC] You don't understand. That figures. Look, I can't have this conversation. You stay here. I will see you back at camp.~
@8220 = ~[ARAN] Now, wait...~
@8221 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells. I just don't rightly understand women, naught a single one, not one bit.~
@8222 = ~[ARAN] (Aran swims to the bank and pulls his towel free of his clothing, wrapping himself as he comes out of the water. In a few quick strides he is beside you, his arms enfolding you in a comfortable embrace. His lips meet yours, warmth contracting with the chilled water droplets that fall about you.)~
@8223 = ~[ARAN] (You stand there together for a time, the world held at bay.)~
@8224 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be a right good idea, but there is not much time to be playin' about. Come to shore, an' let's get back to camp.~
@8225 = ~[PC] What is your rush? Are you scared of being alone with me?~
@8226 = ~[PC] Well, I seem to be removing anything that stands between us. And the water is very nice. And I think it would be very interesting if you were to come and hold me in your arms. Or are you scared of me?~
@8227 = ~[PC] Coward. Fine. I'll swim alone. And you will shamelessly follow every curve of my body, watching in speechless admiration.~
@8228 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap, mayhap not... on account o' I can feel things pressin' on my back right closer than modesty be allowin', eh?~
@8229 = ~[PC] Well, in that case, I shall let you go and have your swim. I wouldn't want to corrupt your high morals or something.~
@8230 = ~[PC] It feels good, doesn't it?~
@8231 = ~[PC] If you think that is immodest, then what ever are you going to say when my hands start exploring this area right...~
@8232 = ~[PC] You seem to be interested, but you are holding back. Are you scared of being alone with me?~
@8233 = ~[ARAN] Well, that be open to some interpretation, eh? I think I would have naught in th' way o' objection to bein' corrupted, a little.~
@8234 = ~[ARAN] Oi! Careful! You can harm a lad that way, you know.~
@8235 = ~[PC] Oh, I know. But you must understand there is a penalty for teasing me.~
@8236 = ~[PC] I don't want to harm anything. I just want someone to come out and play for a little bit.~
@8237 = ~[PC] I seem to have captured your attention quite handily.~
@8238 = ~[PC] Well, time to get back to camp. I suspect you will dream of me tonight, won't you?~
@8239 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, I'd have to check right careful, wouldn't I? An' I do believe that falls into my duties as contracted. But mayhap we want to go someplace a bit warmer, drier, an' mayhap less likely to leave mud an' sand in awkward places, eh?~
@8240 = ~[ARAN] Now, this be right fine. Mayhap you want to move somewhere more comfortable, an' commence some serious negotiations?~
@8241 = ~[PC] What is wrong with negotiating right here and right now?~
@8242 = ~[PC] I am being very forward with you, and you seem to want to take control. Are you trying to make me angry?~
@8243 = ~[PC] My body, my needs, my rules. Are you denying me what I want, right here and now?~
@8244 = ~[ARAN] Well, there be this odd sensation o' th' mud an' rock, an' to tell th' truth I'd rather follow amorous pursuits somewhere th' weeds have naught in th' way o' findin' places they should not.~
@8245 = ~[PC] Are you scared of me? Or of what I am offering?~
@8246 = ~[PC] I... I agree. But I intend to follow up on this train of thought later on. Though I have this feeling you will not let me forget I was interested...~
@8247 = ~[ARAN] You know, teasin' a lad be a right dangerous thing to do, I hear.~
@8248 = ~[PC] My body, my needs, my rules. Are you denying me what I want?~
@8249 = ~[PC] I live for danger.~
@8250 = ~[ARAN] Well, havin' a big sloppin' pile o' mud on my face does a lad some harm to his dignity, eh?~
@8251 = ~[ARAN] I think I lost both o' those a long, long time ago.~
@8252 = ~[ARAN] Now that, that be a truth.~
@8253 = ~[ARAN] Somehow, I think my life just got a bit more interestin'' than I wanted it to be, eh?~
@8254 = ~[ARAN] No, not scared. In fact it be downright excitin'. But seein' as I just saw somethin' movin' under this water, I think th' more prudent course o' action is to get th' nine hells out o' there, before we end up wi' yet another battle wi' some rare an' powerful creature which thinks you be th' sweetest meal ever created, eh?~
@8255 = ~[ARAN] True enough, true enough. An' I' think I'd do a mite bit better travelin' about wi' somethin' coverin' me up. Though I did hear tell o' a tribe or two o' berserkers what fight naked. Somehow, th' thought o' that be more appealin' than the reality, I expect.~
@8256 = ~[ARAN] Now, do I have naught in' th' way o' a say in this matter?~
@8257 = ~[PC] No. I have said it, and therefore it is the unshakeable truth. I insist on sealing it with a kiss.~
@8258 = ~[PC] Yes. You can say 'yes'. Unless you prefer the penalty option...~
@8259 = ~[PC] Of course you do. But somehow I think you are unlikely to raise any objection.~
@8260 = ~[PC] Only if you want to make me angry. You wouldn't like me when I am angry.~
@8261 = ~[PC] ...aaaaand there goes the mood. Sorry, boyo, you lost your chance. Pity you are too scared to take advantage of an opportunity when it throws itself at you.~
@8262 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I want to hear more about this 'penalty' option, eh?~
@8263 = ~[PC] The penalty option is I walk away right now, and leave you to your own devices.~
@8264 = ~[PC] Well, there would be whips. And chains. And lots and lots of leather. Or not.~
@8265 = ~[PC] Well, there would be honey. Lots of honey. Applied in interesting places. Or are you scared of a little experimentation?~
@8266 = ~[PC] Trust me. You do not want to find out what the penalty phase entails. Some things are just too hideous to contemplate.~
@8267 = ~[ARAN] An' here I thought mayhap this would turn out like some o' th' wild romantic wanton sex what happens in bard's tales. Then again, I am not sure havin' fun in th' mud an' rocks an' such be actually romantic. More like painful an' itchy, eh?~
@8268 = ~[ARAN] You know me so well, you do.~
@8269 = ~[ARAN] Now, that rightly depends on how angry you get, eh? When you start to get angry, there be a litle extra sparkle in your eyes, an' your lower lip does this thing where...~
@8270 = ~[ARAN] ...you know, never you mind. Somehow, I think I am about to put both feet in my mouth at th' same time, so to speak. Time to cut my losses an' run for th' hills, I think!~
@8271 = ~[ARAN] Now, do it be fair that you be out o' th' water, an' holdin' my clothes hostage?~
@8272 = ~[PC] No, I don't think so. Perhaps I should join you. (Strip off your clothing and dive into the water next to him.)~
@8273 = ~[PC] No, I don't think so. Perhaps you should join me.~
@8274 = ~[PC] (Smile at him, lowering your eyelashes.)~
@8275 = ~[PC] (Frown at him, turning your face to the side and averting your gaze.)~
