@8319 = ~[PC] (Smile slightly and nod as you stand up and brush yourself off.)~
@8320 = ~[PC] (Frown slightly and shake your head as you stand up and brush yourself off.)~
@8321 = ~[ARAN] Now, there be no call to be that way. Just a little harmless fun, is all I were havin'. You could have averted your eyes.~
@8322 = ~[PC] I suppose you are right. I... I don't mind the view, precisely. It just made me feel uncomfortable.~
@8323 = ~[PC] You were just trying to provoke a reaction from me. You did. Though I think it was not the one you were hoping for.~
@8324 = ~[PC] A little harmless fun like that can lead to some interesting places.~
@8325 = ~[ARAN] No, I can't rightly say as I am. Now, on th' other hand... usin' my mind's eyes, I could see you, standin' in my place, as naked as at birth, wi' th' water clingin' to every single one o' your curves...~
@8326 = ~[PC] Aran... your modesty is being uncovered, I think. Or else you have something else in there moving under that towel.~
@8327 = ~[PC] Don't think about me that way.~
@8328 = ~[PC] In your dreams, boyo. I have enough common sense to actually cover up instead of standing around soaking wet and catching a cold.~
@8329 = ~[ARAN] Sorry. I meant naught in th' way o' harm. I didn't know you would take offense.~
@8330 = ~[PC] Thank you for the apology. I will see you back at camp.~
@8331 = ~[PC] Too late. You know better than to flaunt your body around and try to make me feel uncomfortable.~
@8332 = ~[PC] I take no offence. You just don't have anything I am interested in right now.~
@8333 = ~[ARAN] Somehow, I feel just a mite dirty. Just a big ol' slab o' meat out for th' prurient appetites o' a wanton wild woman, I am.~
@8334 = ~[ARAN] No call to be embarrassed. There be nothin' wrong wi' th' human body, you know.~
@8335 = ~[PC] There is nothing wrong with your body. I just... oh, never mind. I'm headed back to camp.~
@8336 = ~[PC] I know that. Don't treat me as if I were a child to be instructed. And don't look at my backside as I walk away, either.~
@8337 = ~[PC] Well, a girl can blush because she is embarrassed, or because she is angry, or sometimes because she is excited... but you will never find out which from me. See, this is me, walking back to camp before you get any silly ideas.~
@8338 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I'd better get back to camp an' get some dry things for th' both o' us. Don't look now, but you have one solid smear o' mud, right th'... well... in a very conspicuous place, eh?~
@8339 = ~[ARAN] Are you goin' to be swimmin' wi' all those clothes on, or do you think you might want to shed a few?~
@8340 = ~[PC] Oh, I think I could dispense with a few things. Like this old thing... and this... and this...~
@8341 = ~[PC] Don't be rude. I am fine swimming as I am.~
@8342 = ~[PC] Oh, I think I have the strength to swim while keeping this on. You may like to share the sight of your body to any passing stranger, but I have a little thing called modesty.~
@8343 = ~[PC] (Shyly duck your head and shed your clothes slowly, turning halfway away from him.)~
@8344 = ~[PC] (Shake your head quickly, and swim out away from him.)~
@8345 = ~[PC] I think that quick dip was enough for me. I need to get out and get dried off.~
@8346 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a fair bit disappointin'. All that beauty revealed to nature, an' I can see naught o' you under th' water.~
@8347 = ~[PC] I have little or no control over the reflective and refractive properties of water. Besides, you shouldn't really be looking.~
@8348 = ~[PC] Hey. Keep your eyes and your comments to yourself.~
@8349 = ~[PC] I am glad to hear that. I can see you like to share the sight of your body to any passing stranger, but I prefer to keep some limited mystery about me.~
@8350 = ~[PC] (Smile at him as you lift your hair up out of the water, smoothing it back away from your face.)~
@8351 = ~[ARAN] Well, that be a right fine sight, anyhow, whether I can see clear enough o' what be under th' surface o' th' water or no. It mayhap be rude to so say, but you have a beautiful body.~
@8352 = ~[PC] I am glad you like it. I certainly do.~
@8353 = ~[PC] Stop being an idiot. I know that my body is anything but a thing of beauty.~
@8354 = ~[PC] Do you say that to all the girls, or just the ones who decide to go swimming with you with no clothes on?~
@8355 = ~[PC] (Smile, and swim out away from him.)~
@8356 = ~[PC] (Frown at him, turning your back and making a small splash in the water.)~
@8357 = ~[PC] I came here to swim in friendly companionship, not be ogled and leered at. Have fun swimming by yourself. I am getting out and going back to camp.~
@8358 = ~[ARAN] Right. I get th' message. Swimmin' be fine, commentin' an' flirtin' be off limits.~
@8359 = ~[PC] See, you can be trained. Let's just swim.~
@8360 = ~[PC] Crude and rude comments do nothing for me. If you want to flirt, I prefer more romance, and less coarseness.~
@8361 = ~[PC] What? The great Aran Whitehand, giving up so easily?~
@8362 = ~[PC] (Smile at him.)~
@8363 = ~[PC] (Frown at him.)~
@8364 = ~[PC] I think I have had enough of all this.~
@8365 = ~[ARAN] Mystery an' hidden virtues be a right powerful thing, but wi' me, I prefer th' clear an' open opportunity to communicate, I do.~
@8366 = ~[PC] So in other words, if you have it, flaunt it?~
@8367 = ~[PC] I disagree. We are not talking about communicating. We are talking about physical attraction.~
@8368 = ~[PC] And you are so, so mysterious. A veritable enigma wrapped in a conundrum and tied up in a riddle.~
@8369 = ~[ARAN] (A smile crosses his face as he rolls in the water, stretching and scrubbing at his face.)~
@8370 = ~[PC] I think I like swimming. At least, I like it when you are here.~
@8371 = ~[PC] You could be a little less obvious. In fact, you could be a lot less obvious.~
@8372 = ~[PC] Do I look that bad? You seem to be trying to scrub the sight of me out of your eyes.~
@8373 = ~[PC] (Smile at him, swimming away a little farther.)~
@8374 = ~[PC] (Frown at him, swimming away a little farther.)~
@8375 = ~[ARAN] Were it somethin' I said, or were it what I did? You don't rightly seem pleased.~
@8376 = ~[PC] Oh, don't mind me. I am not in a good mood. Combat has taken its toll on me, I guess.~
@8377 = ~[PC] I don't like all this splashing about naked.~
@8378 = ~[PC] What gave it away?~
@8379 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I should just say that there be no harm in showin' off what th' gods have granted.~
@8380 = ~[PC] Perhaps you are right. Sometimes it is nice to see and be seen. Sometimes it isn't. But right now, it is.~
@8381 = ~[PC] Oh, there is all sorts of harm in showing the gods' gifts. It can lead to all sorts of unforseen consequences, and some very obvious ones, too.~
@8382 = ~[PC] So you think that the gods granted you a superior physique? I take it you are feeling particularly modest and humble today.~
@8383 = ~[PC] (Smile at him, swimming away glancing over your shoulder.)~
@8384 = ~[PC] (Frown at him, swimming away.)~
@8385 = ~[ARAN] I'll try to remember that. But I do say, I think that you underestimate just how th' sight o' you moves me. You don't see through my eyes.~
@8386 = ~[PC] I like the way your admiration makes me feel. Though  am not sure you are seeing with clear eyes. I think perhaps your emotions are clouding them a little.~
@8387 = ~[PC] This is not the kind of attention I want right now. You are making me feel uncomfortable.~
@8388 = ~[PC] I think you underestimate my underestimation of your reaction. Do you want to continue all this talk? Because then I would be underestimating your underestimation of my underestimation of your underestimation.~
@8389 = ~[ARAN] You know, it be hard to say whether you be serious or not. In fact, sometimes I think you be serious about not bein' serious, an' other times you be not serious about bein' serious...~
@8390 = ~[ARAN] Wait. I think I done got that all confused.~
@8391 = ~[PC] Perfect. All is right wih the world. You are confused, and I have prevailed.~
@8392 = ~[PC] When are you not?~
@8393 = ~[PC] Me too. But seeing as we are not solving all of Toril's problems singlehandedly right now, confusion is as good a state to be in as any.~
@8394 = ~[ARAN] (He swims close beside you, his passage sending waves curling about your body.)~
@8395 = ~[PC] So, do you swim around attempting to drown helpless maidens for fun, or is this a career for you?~
@8396 = ~[PC] There is plenty of room for both of us. Don't crowd me, please.~
@8397 = ~[PC] (Reach out and run your hand along his shoulder, tracing down his arm.)~
@8398 = ~[ARAN] (He swims farther apart from you, frowning slightly.)~
@8399 = ~[PC] Don't get all upset. We came here to swim. Let's swim.~
@8400 = ~[PC] So you are going to leave me to fend for myself?~
@8401 = ~[PC] The water feels nice.~
@8402 = ~[ARAN] Well, if I could make a career out o' flirtin' wi' you, I'd sign on right quick. But right now, I needs be gettin' th' kinks out o' my muscles. I be headed for that section over there, right quick. Catch me if you can!~
@8403 = ~[ARAN] Aye. I can do that. An' then we'd best get back to camp. I hear th' lady what be in charge o' this adventure be a right harsh taskmistress, an' I want naught in th' way o' trouble from her.~
@8404 = ~[ARAN] Now that feel right good, it do. An' I would return th' gesture, as I somehow think it were wanted...~
@8405 = ~[ARAN] (His hand is light and warm as it smooths the water off of your face.)~
@8406 = ~[ARAN] But we came for a swim, an' we could try some other pursuits th' moment we get back on land.~
@8407 = ~[ARAN] Unfortunately, it looks like our swim be over. I think th' wildlife be investigatin' up on th' bank, an' I for one want naught in th' way o'creatures nibblin' on my gear!~
@8408 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap we just swim for a bit longer, then, an' rest. It seems like th' worries are crowdin' up in your head. We'll wash 'em out, eh?~
@8409 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, you might want to talk, but I do have a bit on my mind.~ [c-aws116]
@8410 = ~[ARAN] Bane's Blood, am I a jumpy one or what? Here I be, talkin' to myself. An' worse, I seem to be answerin' back. Must o' had too many sips o' liquid courage back there.~
@8411 = ~[ARAN] No offense, <GABBER>, I just don't rightly have much to say to you right now.~
@8412 = ~[ARAN] Can this wait a bit?~
@8413 = ~[ARAN] I'd be right happy to spar wi' you later, though, Ajantis. But on that whole 'squires clean tack an' gear' thing, I think I be givin' it a pass, eh?~
@8414 = ~[ARAN] Unless o' course it be about th' coin you owe me. An' in that case, payin' up beats talkin'. Actions speak louder than words, that be my motto.~
@8415 = ~[ARAN] No, no, I have not finished that transcription you be wantin'. You have a way wi' words, boyo, but your handwritten notes, they need one o' them Scrolls o' Identify to figure out what your scrawl be sayin'. I should charge you extra for th' headaches.~
@8416 = ~[ARAN] An' if this be about th' coin I owe you, stick it up Clangedden's Arse. Next time, we use my dice, instead o' your cheatin' ham-fisted stealin' ways. I mean than nice-like, you know. But if you were goin' to steal from me, just whack me on th' head an' take my purse, eh? No need for th' cheat.~
@8417 = ~[ARAN] An' stop pawin' my belongin's lookin' for things to eat. Or not eat. Or whatever. I swear, Montaron, you'd think you were raised in a pack o' insane wolves.~
@8418 = ~[ARAN] An' yes, I do realize you be far more intelligent than I be, Quayle. But th' whole teachin' me how to clean up my speechifyin' habits, well... don't you have naught else to do?~
@8419 = ~[ARAN] An' no, I will not carry that pack for you, Safana. Unless, o' course, you decided to model some o' those lightweight magical armors what leave absolutely nothin' to th' imagi... OUCH! Blighted hells, that hurt!~
@8420 = ~[ARAN] I know we be overdue for a rematch on th' sparrin' front, Shar-Teel, but you have to give a lad a few days what to heal both bruised ego an' bruised body, eh?~
@8421 = ~[ARAN] Skie, I know most o' my gear don't rightly make th' best fashion statement. But then again, it gets a mite bit covered in gore an' blood on a semi-regular basis. So th' whole commentin' on how my appearance could be improved be one hells o' a wast o' breath, darlin'.~
@8422 = ~[ARAN] An' don't you be lookin' at me wi' those cold speculative eyes, there, Xzar. I done had enough o' th' unannounced 'testin' you do to me. Gives me th' shivers, it do. An' mayhap more than just a few shivers up th' spine, if I am not very careful, eh?~
@8423 = ~[ARAN] You could say a prayer or two for me, though, Yeslick. Not that I be thinkin' o' convertin'. But it would be right handy to have th' Axe think kindly on us, eh?~
@8424 = ~[ARAN] If it be that trade you wanted to do, Arath, I be in for it. I can make th' carvin' out o' deadwood, an' you just have at th' design. I never did like bloodsuckers nohow, an' I think a custom carved stake be just th' ticket for a permanent-like cleanup o' th' undead.~
@8425 = ~[ARAN] Besides, we might have a chat over weapons cleanin' later on, Angelo. I never did hear how you got free 'o that' Cyric-buggerin' bastard Sarevok, not from your perspective. I'll bring th' flask, you bring th' stories.~
@8426 = ~[ARAN] Though if you are lookin' for a partner to try a few practice runs, Anishai, You could always try to get a good feel o' what's in my pocket... by Mask's Mighty Mouth, you could charm th' trousers off o' me, you could.~
@8427 = ~[ARAN] Besides, Azure, I know better than to be makin' time wi' you. Sharo's a pretty sensitive wolf, an' might not take kindly to us takin' too long, private -like.~
@8428 = ~[ARAN] BLOODY HELLS, OUCH! By Lathander's Sunny Sh... Gavin, what in th' hells do you think I'm usin' to walk with, my hands? Look, I know I don't rightly use th' tops o' my feet for much, but that's no reason for you to use 'em as steppin' stones.~
@8429 = ~[ARAN] I'm goin' to kick myself for sayin' that, too, Haldamir, on account o' you don't talk much to anyone, an' here you go tryin' to start a conversation. Talk about bad timin'.~
@8430 = ~[ARAN] An' you can stop lookin' at me w' those cold stone grey eyes, y' old shortaxe. I like Lathander well enough, an' you don't need to go convertin' me to your ways.~
@8431 = ~[ARAN] Though how you got into this adventurin' party, Britt, is a mystery to me, you know. I thought you were just pullin' my leg about joinin' on. I suspect there's been some divine intervention what's made you take up adventurin'.~
@8432 = ~[ARAN] An' lay off th' advice, Touchstone, m'boyo. You Wild Elves have been around a mite longer than me an' my kinfolk, I know, but here's more to th' world than trees, bugs, an' grass. Well, at least there's also mud, soot, an' grime, based on what you be wearin' right now.~
@8433 = ~[ARAN] An' stay ahead o' me, Callisto. Mask's Blade, you are a right fine fighter, but you worry me, you do. You get all out o' control, an' there's nothin' what can stop you. I wouldn't want to have no 'accident' or nothin'.~
@8434 = ~[ARAN] Besides, if it be that coin I owe you, Bruce m'boy, I'm tapped out until <CHARNAME> loosens those purse strings. So don't go all 'beat your arse' this an' 'youse gonna get yours' on me, eh? Just get <CHARNAME> to drop a few coin my way, an' I'll get square wi' you.~
@8435 = ~[ARAN] I don't want to drive you away, none, Branwen you are a fine figure o' a woman. All that 'Tempus' Shield' talk, though, it worries me a mite. I'd offer you some companionship, but I'd rather not be askin' you to heal th' parts o' my body you might cut off.~
@8436 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I did check up on th' idea, Jonathan, an' you'd be a fine addition to any one o' three different Guilds. I can write up th' letters for you, if you want, but the again, what be th' hurry? Th' Guilds take a tithe, an' you are doin' right fine as an independent, watchin' <CHARNAME>'s back.~
@8437 = ~[ARAN] In fact, Chloe, let's just pretend we done talked already, an' call it quits. You scare th' crap out o' me.~
@8438 = ~[ARAN] Not that I don't appreciate some bubbly happiness an' sunshine in my day, m'darlin' Alora, but I need to concentrate right now. An' that 'happy happy joy joy' spirit o' yours might break it. Plus, last time you got all huggy wi' me, half my purse mysteriously went missin'... don't you play "Happy Hin" wi' me, lassie! I can't rightly afford it right now!~
@8439 = ~[ARAN] I don't have much time for no bloodsucker, nohow, Miriam. Especially when I don't rightly know which 'we' is you. I don't know why <CHARNAME> don't just throw a stake through your heart an' be done wi' you.~
@8440 = ~[ARAN] I'll tell you what, though, Nikitalleria. When we next camp, I will trade you fair an' square. You teach me a little sleight o' hand, an' I will teach you a mite on parryin' versus Waterdeep double-swords. An' I won't make no pass at you, neither. This is just friend to friend, see?~
@8441 = ~[ARAN] Besides, m'lady Ninafer, shouldn't you be chattin' up Anomen or somethin'? I think you are a right fine woman, an' all. But the boy's the jealous type, an' an officer an' all. I got enough o' him ridin' my back without you makin' it worse.~
@8442 = ~[ARAN] An' stand where I can see you, Coran. Th' ladies might like your 'charmin' rogue' act, but me, I'm not that impressed.~
@8443 = ~[ARAN] An' stay an arm's length away, SilverStar. Unless you want a nice mutton, lettuce, an' tomato sandwich, or somethin'. Then where would your Mary be, eh? Have fun stormin' that particular castle.~
@8444 = ~[ARAN] You can charm the breath out o' me an th' trousers off o' me, Alassa, with just the bat o' an eyelash. An' worse, you know it. But keep those gorgeous eyes an' pert lips out o' my business. You would skin me an' serve me raw if it got you an extra few coin, laughin' all the way to Calimport.~
@8445 = ~[ARAN] By Tempus' Shield, Branwen, you are a sight for sore eyes. But I don't have no time to talk about following Tempus right now. Come talk to me when we are campin', or some such time.~
@8446 = ~[ARAN] M'lady Wychlaran, I don't mean no disrespect. An' please don't turn me into no toad, nor squirrel, nor naught like that, Dynaheir. I just don't have no words t' speak right now.~
@8447 = ~[ARAN] I'm no prude, Fade, an' I respect th' Guild rightly enough. An accomplished Knife's a right good part o' a party, an' you keep th' Shadow Thieves appeased. But I don't trust no tiefling, no way, no how. So unless it's business, keep to yourself, girl.~
@8448 = ~[ARAN] Come by an' chat later, though, Andrei. We can spar a bit, an' swap stories. Or, I can tell stories an' you can listen. Did I ever tell you about th' time Kirran an' me an' BrightFire got into a mite o' a spat wi' some boys servin' th' wi' Black Company? Now, that were a fight for a bard to describe...~
@8449 = ~[ARAN] Though you could do me a right good favor, Sebastian, an' lay off Andrei. The lad's a decent enough sort, an' he needs some breathin' room you don't give him. I'll watch his back, don't you worry.~
@8450 = ~[ARAN] I don't have nothin' to say to you nohow, Irenicus. I spoke my piece back when we kicked your sorry arse. I'd tell you to get lost in any o' th' hells, but you've already done that.~
@8451 = ~[ARAN] But come have a drink wi' me when you can, Ghareth. I want to hear more about th' Cowled an' their ways. Forewarned is forearmed, an' all that time enforcin' for 'em has got some good stories, I bet. I'll trade you, an' tell you about th' time I was servin wi' Moonshae an' we had a bit o' warlock trouble. Talk abut uncontrolled magic...~
@8452 = ~[ARAN] I know that look, Cassius love, an' you are about to charm me wi' those stories o' heroism an' such. Th' trouble wi' all you Skalds an' your tales is that when th' hero slays th' monster an' looks about, there's not much left o' th' rest o' th' party. Write one o' them tale where the kitchen maid an' her four friends beat th' crap out o' a dragon an' all live to tell the tale, an' I'll listen!~
@8453 = ~[ARAN] Better yet, keep yer distance, you floatin' eyeball. I can't rightly make out your accent anyways. An' people think *my* accent be hard to follow...~
@8454 = ~[ARAN] Now, hold on to your jawbone, an' stop scratchin' th' inside o' that left eyesocket, Horace. I got enough trouble stayin' un-spooked just lookin' at you, let alone talkin' to an animated skeleton!~
@8455 = ~[ARAN] I can promise you right proper, Sheena, I am not puttin' you off. I've sense enough not to cause no offense to a comrade what can be beautiful woman one moment, an' firedrake next. It be hard enough to stay on th' right side o' a regular woman, wi' out no draconic heritage.~
@8456 = ~[ARAN] Hey, none o' that sharp eyed glare, Kachiko. I'll gladly talk wi' you another time. By your Eight Million Kara-Turan Gods, I didn't mean to offend you none. Not all o' us have your Dragon Tongue's focus, you know. I needs must concentrate, or I'll be not attendin' to my duties well enough. I'm not a Sword Saint or anythin'.~
@8457 = ~[ARAN] An' by Lolth's Lengthy Legs, keep away from me, you heartless drow bitch. I'm not one o' your filthy spider-spawn males to order about, Xulaye, cover or no cover. You want somethin', you put it through <CHARNAME>, done correct on th' chain o' command.~
@8458 = ~[ARAN] I don't have naught to say to you nohow, Yasraena. You seem to be backin' <CHARNAME>, an' I see why. But the only good drow is... well, I'm not so sure I should finish that statement. Just stay where I can watch you, an' don't try to talk me up, an' I won't cause you no trouble.~
@8459 = ~[ARAN] Now, don't you be gettin' mad, there, Zaiya. I'm right interested in what you have to say. An' you are a right fine lookin' lassie, too, though sometimes it be dangerous to be around one o' those 'surges' o' yours...~
@8460 = ~[ARAN] Not that I'm puttin' you off for no reason, Kelsey. Come an' talk another time. I spent plenty o' time punchin' fists, Coster tradin' up an' down th' Sword Coast as a lad. We should talk shop some time soon, eh? I never did run a store, though I have done my share o' accountin' a' contract drafts. Reminds me o' th' good old days, when you raised an alarm for a stray urchin, a pickpocket, or a kobold or two, instead o' all the beasts th' nine hells can throw at us.~
@8461 = ~[ARAN] Tymora's Tantalizing Tits, you got a huge bundle o' nerve talkin' to me, Bruce m'boyo. You owe *me* two platinum orbs an' the names o' three reliable courtesans, an' you haven't paid up yet. Bugger off until you do, you lazy bastard!~
@8462 = ~[ARAN] Tell you what, Auren - talk to me later, an' we'll have a go at that attack an' counter routine we had a few days ago. You are winnin' three falls to two, an' I would rightly enjoy balancin' out th' game, so to speak.~
@8463 = ~[ARAN] An' don't you be startin' in on me about th' corruption magic causes, neither, Kindrek. I'll take whatever weapon th' gods hand me, if it gets the job done proper. An' one more word about my head decoratin' a pike bein' pretty, an' we'll just have to see if that fancy weapon o' yours will be stronger than my skills, boyo.~
@8464 = ~[ARAN] Sarah, lass-o-me-heart, I don't mean to be short wi' you. I'll make it up to you later. I can fix some decent flatbread an' honey, just like they serve back near Beregost, an' mayhap I can bribe you for a story or two. You keep too quiet, lass, an' I do appreciate your friendship.~
@8465 = ~[ARAN] On second thought, stay away, Kova. I'm not particular about my company, but in your case, I'm up for makin' exceptions. I'm not sayin' guilty, I'm not sayin' innocent - I'm just sayin' naught.~
@8466 = ~[ARAN] An' keep your Master O' th' Universe crap out o' my face, wonderboy. <CHARNAME> killed you once, remember? In my opinion, it were done too slowly, an' wi' not enough o' th' pain an' sufferin' on your part.~
@8467 = ~[ARAN] I'm not likely to have nothin' to say anyways, Amber. It seems like you are backin' <CHARNAME>, but while you ca take the lady out o' th hells, now, can you really take th' hells out o' th' lady? I don't rightly trust no tiefling, no matter how pretty.~
@8468 = ~[ARAN] Chende, I'm, err... well, I'm... not that I have anythin' against half-orcs, or nothin, on account o' I have worked wi' my share o' right proper comrades what's got my back as good as I watch theirs, regardless o' orcish blood. It's just you keep adjustin' your top, an' it bothers me a bit. There's a good healthy woman, an' then there's a need to get some clerical intervention. That's just not right, eh?~
@8469 = ~[ARAN] Ariena, don't be lookin' like that at me. I'm not shunnin' you, I just don't rightly have th' time right now! We'll try some sparrin' later on. Though this time, you done got to remember that we be sparrin', not fightin' for real. Last time, you bloody well busted a few o' my ribs.~
@8470 = ~[ARAN] An' no, I'm not interested in more discussions about Cyric an' his Dark Light, Kido. You spin a fine tale, but I'm stickin' wi' <CHARNAME> for <PRO_HISHER> sake, not on account o' any love for murder, death destruction, chaos, an' all that crap.~
@8471 = ~[ARAN] An' give me back my coinpurse, there, stickyfingers. Umberlee's Undulating Urges, Hessa, you should be lookin' for other marks, not messin' wi' my flat purse. <CHARNAME>'s holdin' all my share!~
@8472 = ~[ARAN] An' don't you be goin' all 'Ducky This' an' 'Ducky That' wi', me, Linton. You're a right fine woman, but I figure you're a mite too streetwise to come roll in th' hay wi' th' like o' me.~
@8473 = ~[ARAN] Now, you want me to carry that kitty cat o' yours about, I'm your man. An' I wouldn't mind a few riddles, nether, Tashia. How about when we camp, I wander on by an' we have a nice conversation, private-like. I'll brew some decent tea...~
@8474 = ~[ARAN] Come by later, though, 'Fletcher. We never did finish talkin' about that whole Trade Way skirmish wi' the Chill hittin' your squad o' Fist. I heard from Valis your party done got ambushed right proper, but fought all th' way out wi' only two casualties anyways. Now that is a story worth hearin' more'n once, it is. I'll provide th' spirits, you provide th' stories.~
@8475 = ~[ARAN] I mean no disrespect, o'course, m'Lady Ninde. I wouldn't want to be on th' wrong side o' one o' your tongue lashin's. Though if there's a right side, well, I'm your man for to call on. I'll just go get that gear straightened out a bit, eh?~
@8476 = ~[ARAN] Yeah, yeah, I done heard you th' first twenty times. 'Tiax Rules All'. 'When Tiax Rules, Aran Will Be Th' Boot-Scraper An' Will Have To Talk To Me'. Sune's Rambunctious Rump, someone get this insane shorty th' Nine Hells away from me.~
@8477 = ~[ARAN] No offense, Xan, but I want to keep my spirits up, eh? You are one powerful Tel Quessir, but you sure can bring on th' doom an' gloom.~
@8478 = ~[ARAN] Beggin' your pardon, m'lady Deheriana. I don't mean no offense to you nor your Ranger.~
@8479 = ~[ARAN] I'm downright flattered you want to talk to me, I am, Kivan - I don't mean no disrespect. There's just not rightly no time now for talkin'.~
@8480 = ~[ARAN] An' don't you be pesterin' me about all that cookin' wi' meat again, Allison. I know you be fond o' th' animals, but there's a right good purpose for them there bunny rabbits. Make good stew, they do!~
@8481 = ~[ARAN] Beggin' your pardon, o' course, vanimaberylellie en amin... no offense meant. I'd Like it fine if we could talk later, Kitanya. I'd like to learn some o' th' Tel Quessirim fightin' tactics, if you've a mind to share.~
@8482 = ~[ARAN] In fact, forget it. Shut your foul mouth, you Cyric-lovin' filth. If <CHARNAME> didn't keep you on a tight leash like some pet, I'd be servin' your heart up tartar-style, wi' a nice cup o' th' blood o' innocents you like to murder. Watch your back, bastard, on account o' I'm just waitin' for th' opportunity to plant somethin' between your third an' fourth ribs.~
@8483 = ~[ARAN] Hold on... I can do this right proper, I can. I've been readin'. *ahem*. Forsooth, it pains me greatly to cause you distress, my Lady Saerileth. But thy words best not the needs of the moment, and I must away anon. Perchance thy gracious lips would caress mine ears at the first pale glimmer of starlight; for in thine countenance I do see the beauty of life, the vivaciousness of youth, and the satin power of Tyr enobl'd and made feminine in the grace of your form. This poor sinner doth confess the lusts of both body and mind for such sweet discourse; a breath, a moment of your beauty is like the drop of divine wisdom from the countenance of Ao. *Ahem*. Sune's Salacious Succulence, talkin' that way'll kill a man dead, it will.~
@8484 = ~[ARAN] Come by an' talk later, though, Yikari. We can get a good stiff drink, an' loosen that still tongue o' yours. I want to hear more about th' far off lands, an' especially those Kara-Turan womenfolk!~
@8485 = ~[ARAN] Bugger all, Bruce, I told you I was tapped out clean. No coin, no trade bars, nothin'. Hells, man, here - take this flask. An' don't be drinkin' it straight in one shot, or it'll put you right over on your ares. Cut it wi' some water. Now leave me alone 'til payday!~
@8486 = ~[ARAN] Not meanin' to offend you, Sime, nor your father. I'd be right happy if you'd come talk later on. Perhaps I can buy you a drink or somethin', next opportunity. No pass, honest, just interested in swappin' some stories, playin' some dice, passin' the time.~
@8487 = ~[ARAN] I'm up for a mite o' a chat later, though, Neh'Taniel. You talk a deep set o' subjects, you do. I need most o' my mind on th' discussion if I want to keep up, eh?~
@8488 = ~[ARAN] Oh, I'm right sorry, I am. Skooter, I did promise a throw or two o' that stick, didn't I. Right then, here you go... one good toss down that way. Just don't get lost, eh, m'boyo? There's critters around here what could eat *me* for a light snack, let alone you.~
@8489 = ~[ARAN] I'm not that interested in talkin' to no drow, nohow, Solaufein. You may talk a good game, but me, I got both my eyes on you. Figuratively speakin' that is. It'd be a mite messy if I done popped 'em out an' stuck em' to you.~
@8490 = ~[ARAN] An' in any case, you'll be wantin' to talk to <CHARNAME>, not me.~
@8491 = ~[ARAN] Not meanin' to be short, m'darlin lassie, but I'd rather we have a talk later. Are you up for a walk tonight, Aerie? Mayhap just you an' me, under th' stars?~
@8492 = ~[ARAN] Anomen, if this is about my gear bein' not quite tidy enough, I done rightly heard you the first three times. An' I'll say it again - I don't answer to you, nohow. So bugger on about your business, m'lord, an' leave me to mine.~
@8493 = ~[ARAN] If it that talk you were wantin' to give me on th' ways o' th' birds an' th' bees, Cernd, well - that ship sailed a couple o' years ago. Though I can tell you o' some things I've learned what's great in th' bedroom, but don't quite fit under th' headin' o 'natural'...~
@8494 = ~[ARAN] Unless it be more stories o' your conquests, o' course, Edwin. You got more o' those, well, step right on over, an' we'll have a mite o' a chat. I still can't rightly believe a Chondathan girl can be trained to do what you described last time. Didn't know they bent that way.~
@8495 = ~[ARAN] An' lay of th' 'sparrowhawk', 'dovewing', an' birdy-birdy language for a mite, there, HaerDalis, eh? If you do, I'll let you look at a scrap o' parchment I found in a library outside o' Beregost, what's written in th' tongue o' Gold Dwarves...~
@8496 = ~[ARAN] I'm not pushin' you away, Imoen, really I'm not. I just know you have a mite on your mind, too, an' I'm not happy company right now. I'll walk by you for a bit, though, if you want.~
@8497 = ~[ARAN] Yes, Jaheira, I packed up my bedroll right tightly. No, Jaheira, I did not eat too much o' th' hardtack, an' cramp my bowels. Yes, Jaheira, I read that list o' spices you wanted me to try to get into th' dinner roster. Mielikki's Mysterious Mouth, I'm no bloody half-elf out o' your loins, I'm just a friend, eh? Go easy on th' motherin', for th' love of our friendship!~
@8498 = ~[ARAN] Tell you what, Jan. If th' story is about turnips, relatives, or craftin' new inventions, I can tell you I done heard it. In fact, if it was turnips, I done heard it twice. But we will have time to take on meal prep, an' then you can tell me about th' time the cute female turnip golem who was really your third cousin on your uncle's side managed to get you an idea for an invention what turned out to be th' best thing since th' gods created womenfolk.~
@8499 = ~[ARAN] I don't mean no disrespect, Keldorn. If you have somethin' you want me to do, just say the word. Otherwise, I need to attend to my duties right proper.~
@8500 = ~[ARAN] If this is about th' sharpenin' bar, Korgan, here it is. I don't need it no more nohow. An' I'm not so happy wi' havin' to rent it for two iron crescents an' a Trademeet trade bar. Xvim's Spit, that's bloody highway robbery.~
@8501 = ~[ARAN] I'll be happy to help on th' weapons cleanin' later, though, Mazzy. I want to see how you sharpen those arrows so fierce.~
@8502 = ~[ARAN] Oh, I'm right sorry, Minsc - didn't mean to be so short. Though when I'm standin' close to you, short is the word what springs to mind right quick, it does. You are blockin' most o' my view, big boy. You mind steppin' over a bit, so's I can see where we are headed?~
@8503 = ~[ARAN] An' I am not one o' th' Great Unwashed Little People, neither, Nalia. I 'll have you know I took a bath just last week. Well, parts o' me, anyways. Wanna see?~
@8504 = ~[ARAN] I'm right surprised you want to talk, anyways, Valygar. You haven't put two words together wi' me in nigh on a tenday.~
@8505 = ~[ARAN] On second thought, Viconia, don't even bother. I've got naught to say to a Shar-kissed spawn o' th' Nether Planes. Bugger off an' go screw an ettin, or somethin'.~
@8506 = ~[ARAN] Tell you what, Yoshimo - we'll talk next time we camp. I want to try that card game again. I don't rightly know how you won all five hands, an' I want a chance to make some o' those wages back.~
@8507 = ~[ARAN] We'll be talkin' over dinner prep anyways, Hubelpot. Don't worry none - I'll try not to get ripped limb from limb afore then, and with a bit o' luck, you won't be ground up bits o' parts neither. We can talk about real curry makin'!~
@8508 = ~[ARAN] You can't rightly expect much in th' way o' small talk from me, nohow, Iylos. You got a mission, an' I respect that. But fish around for information about <CHARNAME> from someone else. I don't serve more than one contract at a time, an' <CHARNAME> has that right now, an' probably 'til I'm arguin' wi' Kelemvor myself on where the prettiest girl souls be hidin' out.~
@8509 = ~[ARAN] You should know better than to sneak up on me like that, Banana. I got me a ton o' recipes wi' your name on 'em... hey, you got a cousin named Rosanna Bananadana?~
@8510 = ~[ARAN] Easy, there, lass - don't you be gatherin' your tail in a twist, an' all. Literally, I mean. You are blushin' redder than I done seen in a tenday! Kari, I'm just busy now, that's all. Come by when we settle in for th' night, an' I'll help you with that weapon sharpenin' you were askin' about.~
@8511 = ~[ARAN] How about you come by tonight, though, Keto, an' we trade some stories? I'd be lyin' if I didn't think I'd make you nice company. I have some nice Rashemi Firewine set aside, not even watered down...~
@8512 = ~[ARAN] Now then, miss foxy lass, I don't have no problems wi' talkin' to you, but now is not rightly th' time. Come by at dinner, Moddy, an' we'll share a bit o' talk, eh? Or better yet, a nice brace 'o rabbits.~
@8513 = ~[ARAN] Outsider an' necromancer... there's naught about you that sits right wi' me, Tsujatha. I' m tolerant for <CHARNAME>'s sake, an' that's about it. So don't look for small talk an' comradeship here.~
@8514 = ~[ARAN] An' stop spookin' me like that, Valen. I stay on one side o' <CHARNAME>, you stay on th' other, an' we will be fine. But I don't rightly think we should be havin' no private conversation. I'm likely to end up bein' an appetizer, or a light pre-dinner snack.~
@8515 = ~[ARAN] There might be time to talk later, though, Kiara. I want to hear more about that monk trainin'. I'll help wi' some breath-holdin' exercise, if you want, too. Though there be not much more between us, I expect. I know you might be a decent enough friend, but somehow it always ends up bein' more about you, an' less about anyone else.~
@8516 = ~[ARAN] Though between you an' me, I'd rather keep talkin' to you an' make some sort o' accommodation, Kiyone. I'd trust you to watch my back right proper.~
@8517 = ~[ARAN] I know that. I just be thinkin' we have enough troubles wi' out messin' with a great big stone cairn filled wi' unspeakable evil. We have already done that a few times, eh?~
@8518 = ~[PC] I did not have us take this task lightly. This could provide us with advantages we need later on in our travels.~
@8519 = ~[PC] Do not worry, Aran. We have prevailed so far. We will be laughing about this later on.~
@8520 = ~[PC] As I recall, there was a good bit of you running around screaming 'Kill it! Kill it! Cyric's Blood, kill it now!', while screaming like a little girl..~
@8521 = ~[PC] Look, I am good at getting information. Rather than complaining about the task, I think I will go find out what traps await us.~
@8522 = ~[PC] I have a divination spell or two up my sleeve. Rather than complaining about the task, I think I will get my magical energies flowing.~
@8523 = ~[PC] A prayer or two, perhaps a Chant or Bless might be a good idea. I will let you do all of the silly worrying by yourself.~
@8524 = ~[PC] The troubles will be far deeper than the first level, I am sure. But if we keep a watchful eye, this adventure could be very useful to us. Or have you lost your courage?~
@8525 = ~[ARAN] Oh, no problem, exactly. Except we seem to be traipsin' about, messin' with a great big stone cairn filled wi' unspeakable evil. We have already done that a few times, eh?~
@8526 = ~[ARAN] I might just do that. But I'm not sure about messin' with a great big stone cairn filled wi' unspeakable evil. We have already done that a few times, eh?~
@8527 = ~[PC] Would you rather I do it, Aran? I mean, if you think you need the help...~
@8528 = ~[PC] Would you rather <PLAYER2> do it, Aran? I mean, if you think you need the help...~
@8529 = ~[PC] Would you rather <PLAYER3> do it, Aran? I mean, if you think you need the help...~
@8530 = ~[PC] Would you rather <PLAYER4> do it, Aran? I mean, if you think you need the help...~
@8531 = ~[PC] Would you rather <PLAYER5> do it, Aran? I mean, if you think you need the help...~
@8532 = ~[PC] Would you rather <PLAYER6> do it, Aran? I mean, if you think you need the help...~
@8533 = ~[ARAN] I can get th' energies flowin' right fine. I just am a mite worried about messin' with a great big stone cairn filled wi' unspeakable evil. We have already done that a few times, eh?~
@8534 = ~[PC] Would you rather I cast some preparatory spells, Aran? I mean, if you think you need the help...~
@8535 = ~[ARAN] I can call on my spiritual side right fine. I just am a mite worried about messin' with a great big stone cairn filled wi' unspeakable evil. We have already done that a few times, eh?~
@8536 = ~[ARAN] I'm right proud to say I bet we can lick just about anythin' fair an' square, an' that's before we start fightin' dirty. I just am a mite worried about messin' with a great big stone cairn filled wi' unspeakable evil. We have already done that a few times, eh?~
@8537 = ~[PC] Would you rather I take point, Aran? I mean, if you think you need to guard the rear...~
@8538 = ~[PC] We could always have <PLAYER2> lead out. I mean, if you think you cannot handle taking point...~
@8539 = ~[PC] We could always have <PLAYER3> lead out. I mean, if you think you cannot handle taking point...~
@8540 = ~[PC] We could always have <PLAYER4> lead out. I mean, if you think you cannot handle taking point...~
@8541 = ~[PC] We could always have <PLAYER5> lead out. I mean, if you think you cannot handle taking point...~
@8542 = ~[PC] We could always have <PLAYER6> lead out. I mean, if you think you cannot handle taking point...~
@8543 = ~[ARAN] Oooh, you know how to hurt a lad, you do. Right, then. I'll get about adventurin'.~
@8544 = ~[ARAN] The question is, are we goin' to be laughin' a good, comradely belly laugh, or a shrill hysterical terror-filled laugh? 'Cause I be much more in favor o' th' first.~
@8545 = ~[ARAN] Right. I should o' guessed that was th' idea. Go mess with th' big evil thing what's been locked up, so's we can have some nice treasure an' get some great magical weapons. Tiamat's Terrible Teeth, I'd think you were jokin', if it didn't sound like what we do every day, all day...~
@8546 = ~[ARAN] (Aran walks beside you, glaring at the dark corners and shadows. His eyes gleam in the feral, unnatural light.)~
@8547 = ~[PC] Aran, your voice sounds strange. Have you been drinking again?~
@8548 = ~[PC] I hate random comments. Only talk about important things, Aran. Even then, try not to talk.~
@8549 = ~[PC] Hey, I have changed my mind. Go ahead and say what you want to say, Aran, any time you want to say it. Random comments are fine.~
@8550 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that Drow flail you are using. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8551 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that armor you are wearing. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8552 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that cloak you are wearing. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8553 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that halberd you are wielding. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8554 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that plate armor you are wearing. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8555 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that shield you are holding. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8556 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that lance you are wielding. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8557 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that scimitar you are wielding. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8558 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that longsword you are wielding. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8559 = ~[PC] Aran, you keep looking oddly at that crossbow you are using. Is there something wrong with it?~
@8560 = ~[PC] You keep looking at me. Is there something wrong?~
@8561 = ~[PC] We seem to be getting quite a reputation.~
@8562 = ~[PC] Do you want some help scribing a scroll?~
@8563 = ~[PC] Sparring practice might be useful.~
@8564 = ~[PC] Hey, stand over there. I want to practice sneaking up on you.~
@8565 = ~[PC] I will say a prayer for you, Aran.~
@8566 = ~[PC] Have you ever thought of following the ways of my order?~
@8567 = ~[PC] It is good to travel with a fellow paladin. Tell me, have you ever thought of following the ways of my order?~
@8568 = ~[PC] Here, catch. (Conjure a globe of light and toss it toward Aran.)~
@8569 = ~[PC] Perhaps you would like to meditate with me.~
@8570 = ~[PC] I have been writing a good deal about our travels. Perhaps you could lend me some vellum, so I can continue?~
@8571 = ~[PC] I think your spellcasting is getting better. At least, you seem less likely to catch part of me in your spell by accident.~
@8572 = ~[PC] We should discuss your fighting tactics sometime.~
@8573 = ~[PC] Have you worked on those lock-picking and de-trapping skills of yours lately?~
@8574 = ~[PC] Perhaps you should ask your god what we should do next, Aran.~
@8575 = ~[PC] How did a rough and tumble character like you ever get to become a paladin, anyways?~
@8576 = ~[PC] Aran, you are doing it again. Your left hand is sparking. Can you control yourself?~
@8577 = ~[PC] I thought monks were quiet, introspective, and subtle. That does not seem to be your style.~
@8578 = ~[PC] So, how is the great Chronicler coming along with the story?~
@8579 = ~[PC] You are a traveler of wide experience - have you ever been here before?~
@8580 = ~[PC] I need to be clear about this, Aran. I am not interested in a romance with you. Stop talking about it.~
@8581 = ~[PC] I think we are headed down the wrong path, Aran. It was fun while it lasted, but it is over. Let's just be friends.~
@8582 = ~[PC] Look, I know it is over. But I think I have changed my mind. Perhaps a romance with you might be interesting after all.~
@8583 = ~[PC] I like Anomen well enough, Aran. But you keep fighting with him. I want you to stop doing that.~
@8584 = ~[PC] I have changed my mind about fighting with Anomen, Aran. Go ahead and speak your mind.~
@8585 = ~[PC] You have to stop coming up to me and flirting. I do not want that behavior to continue, here or on the surface.~
@8586 = ~[PC] You have to stop coming up to me and flirting, even though I usually like it when you do. Down here, it would be a bad idea. Wait until we are on the surface again.~
@8587 = ~[PC] I know Drow are sensuous beings, Aran. You could chase me, just a little, and discreetly...~
@8588 = ~[PC] You do not pay attention to me the way you used to, Aran. I miss your company.~
@8589 = ~[PC] (You decide to flirt with Aran.)~
@8590 = ~[PC] Before we go any further, Aran... what do you think our "relationship" is?~
@8591 = ~[PC] Can you scribe a scroll for me?~
@8592 = ~[PC] Tell me again how you work with scrolls and spells.~
@8593 = ~[PC] Is that scroll done yet?~
@8594 = ~[PC] Aran... we could slip away, right here, right now... come away with me for a moment.~
@8595 = ~[PC] Didn't you want to get me alone for awhile, just the two of us? Now is the perfect time.~
@8596 = ~[PC] I have changed my mind about you visiting me the next time we rest. Now is not a good time.~
@8597 = ~[PC] Actually, never mind. I don't really have anything to talk to you about.~
@8598 = ~[ARAN] (Aran is beside you, watching the surroundings carefully.)~
@8599 = ~[PC] Your voice sounds strange. Have you been drinking again?~
@8600 = ~[PC] Well, do you have any advice for me, Aran?~
@8601 = ~[PC] Come on, Aran, liven things up a bit. Tell me a story.~
@8602 = ~[PC] These surroundings are a little gloomy, aren't they?~
@8603 = ~[PC] Dampness, darkness, random odd sounds... now this is not the best place to be wandering about, I think.~
@8604 = ~[PC] Hmmm... wandering about here certainly makes you wonder what the creatures who live here do for fun.~
@8605 = ~[PC] The sights and sounds of a darkened city, laid out before us...~
@8606 = ~[PC] You know, in the sunlight, these streets do not look half bad.~
@8607 = ~[PC] The sights and sounds of a busy bright day in the city, with a thousand adventures ahead...~
@8608 = ~[PC] Aran, what are you looking at? Is something watching us from the bushes?~
@8609 = ~[PC] There should be some wood lying around this place somewhere. Do you want to build up a nice cozy bonfire?~
@8610 = ~[PC] I think I like forests. Sure, they hold danger. But they also hold adventure.~
@8611 = ~[PC] Aran, are you ok? You keep staring right at that tree...~
@8612 = ~[PC] This area looks like a prime candidate for gathering firewood.~
@8613 = ~[PC] Hey, Aran, have you seen any place we can gather some water?~
@8614 = ~[PC] Do you know anything interesting about the Docks District?~
@8615 = ~[PC] Now, a traveler like you should know something about these slums. Do you have any information for me?~
@8616 = ~[PC] Have you ever been to the Bridge District before, Aran?~
@8617 = ~[PC] What can you tell me about this Promenade, here?~
@8618 = ~[PC] Great. Stinking, slimy sewers. Any suggestions on how to proceed?~
@8619 = ~[PC] I suspect we will all end up in a place like this graveyard. But do you have any ideas on how to delay that for as long as possible?~
@8620 = ~[PC] I suspect you have spent very little time in the Temple District. But have you heard anything about it?~
@8621 = ~[PC] The seat of governance. Just the place a smart sellsword would have done some research on...~
@8622 = ~[PC] Hey, careful where you step. It looks like no one has cleaned up Athkatla's streets lately.~
@8623 = ~[PC] Have you ever been here before, Aran?~
@8624 = ~[PC] Have you ever visited this wilderness before, Aran?~
@8625 = ~[PC] Have you heard anything about these ruins, Aran?~
@8626 = ~[PC] So, when was the last time you were in Trademeet?~
@8627 = ~[PC] Well, you asked for it, and now you made it here. Did you ever think that all that blasphemy would actually get you pulled all the way to the nine hells?~
@8628 = ~[PC] (Have a bar patron try to pick a fight with Aran.)~
@8629 = ~[PC] So, what is the deal with you and Erika?~
@8630 = ~[PC] So, what is the deal with you and Teldra?~
@8631 = ~[PC] So, what is the deal with you and Orrin?~
@8632 = ~[PC] Well, we are off to do some good old fashioned dungeon exploring, eh, Aran?~
@8633 = ~[PC] Well, what do you think of this place?~
@8634 = ~[PC] I do not think that this place was designed to let us in easily.~
@8635 = ~[PC] Have you had enough wandering around in the dark trying not to get killed?~
@8636 = ~[PC] Our challenges seem to be getting harder to overcome.~
@8637 = ~[PC] You are looking a little pale, Aran. Here, have some iron rations, and a bit of something to drink.~
@8638 = ~[PC] Look, I know it is over between us. But I think I have changed my mind. Perhaps a romance with you might be interesting after all.~
@8639 = ~[PC] You have to stop coming up to me and flirting. I do not want that behavior to continue.~
@8640 = ~[PC] Aran... I found a letter in your pack. I can't read it. Will you read it to me?~
@8641 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a right solid shame. I done seen sewers in Calimport what were better kept. O' course, they used th' beggars there as street cleaners. Useful, too, as most o' th' refuse there consisted o' their bodies.~
@8642 = ~[ARAN] You did what?~
@8643 = ~[PC] I went through your private things. I know it was wrong, but I was very curious. I found a letter I can't read. Will you tell me about it?~
@8644 = ~[PC] Hey. I don't trust anyone right now, not even you. I want to make sure our enemies are not getting inside information. What is in the letter?~
@8645 = ~[PC] Never mind. I was joking with you. But what do you scribble about so assiduously every chance you get?~
@8646 = ~[PC] I was worried you were writing to someone else, some other woman.~
@8647 = ~[PC] Look, I... I am sorry. I just... I can't believe you actually like me. I just assumed it was another woman.~
@8648 = ~[PC] I figured you might be writing some woman love notes, and I want to make sure that you aren't passing on information about what we are doing.~
@8649 = ~[PC] Forget I said anything.~
@8650 = ~[ARAN] No.~
@8651 = ~[ARAN] It be a private letter between me an' my sister. Eyes off, hands, off, an' blighted well thoughts off o' it, eh? A lad needs somethin' to call his own.~
@8652 = ~[ARAN] I'd be right unhappy about anyone pokin' in on my private thoughts, even you. Mayhap especially you. I thought you trusted me an' knew I support you. If you want to interrupt a lad writin' his sister, well, go find someone else to treat like dung, eh?~
@8653 = ~[ARAN] Nothin'. An' leave my gear alone, will you? It be hard enough on th' trail to get a moment to write in peace, an' here you go pokin' in on th' only place I can hold my private thoughts.~
@8654 = ~[ARAN] Mine own business. I'll forget this happened, or try to. That be a fair sight harder to do than you think, eh?~
@8655 = ~[ARAN] If you have to know, I be... I be writin' a story. An' mayhap I don't want no pryin' eyes on it. There be naught about you, nohow.~
@8656 = ~[ARAN] I don't take kindly to you pryin' in on letters to my sister. I'll swear on anythin' you want it be private, an' has no information what could be used against you in no context at all.~
@8657 = ~[ARAN] They do say curiosity killed th' cat, but in this case, it just pisses off th' sellsword. Mind your own business, eh?~
@8658 = ~[ARAN] Oh, odds, an' ends, an' such. Sometimes letters home to my sister, an' sometimes just keepin' my hand in.~
@8659 = ~[ARAN] This an' that. Nothin' important, but it be private. Mayhap you want your private life all exposed, but me, I don't take right kindly to it.~
@8660 = ~[ARAN] Well, I'd not be writin' to you, nohow. I can always talk to you. It be letters to my sister, is all. Nothin' about you, an' none o' your concern.~
@8661 = ~[ARAN] It is. But since she be my sister, I'd think you might not object so much. An' no, I won't read it to you. a lad's got to have some mystery, some secrets, eh, if he's to be attractive to a lady.~
@8662 = ~[ARAN] Letters to my sister. Though that be none o' your blighted business. An' no, I'm not settin' you up wi' her, either romantically, or wi' passin' on sensitive information. Blighted hells, that just be wrong, readin' a lad's private correspondence!~
@8663 = ~[ARAN] (He says nothing, but studies you through narrowed eyes before grunting and turning away.)~
@8664 = ~[ARAN] That will be blighted hard to do.~
@8665 = ~[ARAN] Not a blighted chance o' that. Mayhap I need more privacy.~
@8666 = ~[ARAN] There be no deal between us, not for lack o' desire. But after Gerris got all mad at me over that misunderstandin' on his daughter an' I had to move in here, I am not likely to be makin' serious passes at Erika. She has just seen 15 summers, an' she has a great sense o' humor.~
@8667 = ~[PC] So you flirt with underage barmaids?~
@8668 = ~[PC] She must have a good sense of humor, to put up with you.~
@8669 = ~[PC] I wonder if she might find me attractive.~
@8670 = ~[PC] She seems like she knows you very well.~
@8671 = ~[ARAN] She gets word o' work, an' sets up any freelancers around if she can't fill th' billet wi' regular mercenary company contracts. You could think o' her as a combination o' ombudsman an' recruiter, wi' a dose o' information collection on th' side.~
@8672 = ~[PC] Is she someone you are interested in? Should I put in a good word for you?~
@8673 = ~[PC] I was just wondering why she bothered having you as a client.~
@8674 = ~[PC] I don't suppose you could introduce me socially, and put in a good word. I think she is very interesting.~
@8675 = ~[PC] Useful knowledge to have.~
@8676 = ~[PC] Well, that was a bit of useless trivia I will forget as fast as I can.~
@8677 = ~[ARAN] Why, do you be jealous?~
@8678 = ~[PC] Sure. I am so jealous. After all, she must be the recipient of such fine wit, such unending devotion, such wild largess and rich gifts, under the spell of your silvery tongue.~
@8679 = ~[PC] Do you always make enemies this easily?~
@8680 = ~[PC] I don't think so. Is she someone you are interested in? Should I put in a good word for you?~
@8681 = ~[ARAN] Orrin has a way wi' jewelry an' gems, he does. He keeps a private stock, if you have coin enough or have earned his favor. He even lends money at times. An' he has a way wi' a blackjack that would put a monk to shame. He don't rightly hold wi' killin' a customer, an' he keeps an open mind when it comes to whom to serve.~
@8682 = ~[PC] Sounds like the sort of man it is good to know.~
@8683 = ~[PC] Would he lend me money?~
