@10034 = ~[ARAN] Not bad in a fight. Not so hot in th' ladies department, though. An' his farts smell like old feet.~
@10035 = ~[ARAN] Makes me a mite jealous, he does. Not many men can snore, belch, an' fart like that, an' to do all three at th' same time, now that takes bloody fine skills, eh?~
@10036 = ~[ARAN] I don't. Should I? I mean, he be right fine lookin', but I tend to think o' womenfolk. Why, did he ask about me? What did he say?~
@10037 = ~[ARAN] Not th' sharpest o' tacks, though he claims a good bit o' intelligence. What sort o' idiot wanders Toril in th' company o' a mixed group o' adventurers, followin' some young adventurin' Bhaalspawn to certain death an' destruction, probably by a slow an' painful means? I mean, really, come on. Any smart adventurer would say "Screw this. I'm hittin' th' nearest tavern, an' not leavin' until someone comes up wi' an adventure what don't pit me against opponents what be gods".~
@10038 = ~[ARAN] I think if I hadn't met you, naught but boredom an' ennui would o' happened for me. Well, sometimes I think that. Other times, I'm just starin' at you an' imaginin' you naked.~
@10039 = ~[ARAN] I think if I hadn't met you, naught but boredom an' ennui would o' happened for me. Don't rightly know whether to thank you for that, or tell you to stick Helm's Fist up your arse an' give it a good twist.~
@10040 = ~[ARAN] Too kind o' you, lookin' out for me an' all. But I think you'd be a mite bit disappointed in my performance, eh? On account o' I might not be able to see where to fit th' key in the hole wi' everythin' spinnin' around so much, so to speak.~
