@10300 = ~[AERIE] All right.~
@10301 = ~[ANOMEN] A mighty opponent, and a just victory. Might has made Right.~
@10302 = ~[HAERDALIS] Oh, my sweetlings, my sparrows. This is a victory that shall reach ears even on planes of existence where ears themselves are but stories told to frighten children!~
@10303 = ~[YOSHIMO] A worthy adversary. I would prefer that we find less worthy challenges in the future.~
@10304 = ~[CERND] It is a shame to have to destroy such a fine dragon. But all of us are tested, even as the tree scorched by forest fire is tested. And we have prevailed.~
@10305 = ~[EDWIN] A paltry task. I would have taken care of him myself, had I not tripped on my hem while casting.~
@10306 = ~[ARAN] Got it. That's why you went all green and white, started shivering, and started spouting those curse words. I thought you was scared. But I guess I was mistaken.~
@10307 = ~[ARAN] We fought hard, and won, to be sure. But I just don't know, <CHARNAME>. Is there really anything more frightening, more rightly terrifying, than an adult dragon? I suspect not. Bloody glad any o' us survived.~
@10308 = ~[JAHEIRA] Actually, there are much worse things to encounter than dragons. There are pit fiends, and swarms of tanarri, and...~
@10309 = ~[ARAN] Jaheira...~
@10310 = ~[JAHEIRA] Yes, Aran?~
@10311 = ~[ARAN] You aren't helping.~
@10312 = ~[JAHEIRA] Oh.~
@10313 = ~[ARAN] Changed your mind? I can fight, write, an' cook a mean curry.~ [c-aws080]
@10314 = ~[PC] Why are you looking for work?~
@10315 = ~[PC] Sounds good enough. Join up, then.~
@10316 = ~[PC] Stand aside, citizen. You are between me and the bar. Not a safe place to be.~
@10317 = ~[PC] Go away, little man.~
@10318 = ~[PC] Nope. Still not interested.~
@10319 = ~[PC] I was just checking to see if you were still here.~
@10320 = ~[PC] Ask me again and I will have you thrown out of here.~
@10321 = ~[PC] No. But I sure could use a drink. Buy me one?~
@10322 = ~[PC] What is it you can do for me again?~
@10323 = ~[PC] Yes. I could use your services. But shares only, no hiring fees, and you join us as a partner.~
@10324 = ~[PC] Not right now. I will let you know if we change our mind.~
@10325 = ~[PC] Hire on with us, then. Follow my instructions, and you will be welcome. Cross me, and things could get unpleasant for you.~
@10326 = ~[ARAN] Aye then, you showed up at a right good time. Aran Whitehand, Sword an' Pen. Accounts audited, contracts written, foes slain. I heard you might be interested in a sellsword for adventurin'.~ [c-aws081]
@10327 = ~[PC] Perhaps later. Right now, I just want a drink.~
@10328 = ~[PC] I'm afraid we can't afford a mercenary right now. I need to save a good bit of coin to rescue a friend.~
@10329 = ~[PC] Fighter and scribe? Do you do magic as well?~
@10330 = ~[PC] We might be able to use a good sword, but I am interested in your scribing. Can you make scrolls?~
@10331 = ~[PC] I am not sure that I can use you right now. But perhaps you might be able to help me. I am looking for a mage named Irenicus. Have you heard of him?~
@10332 = ~[PC] I sure could have used you awhile ago. Now I am not so sure. What can you do for me?~
@10333 = ~[PC] Nope. Just not interested.~
@10334 = ~[PC] I was just checking to see if you were working here.~
@10335 = ~[ARAN] Do you be sure? It looks like you could use me. An' I be a mite tired o' just sittin' around.~ [C-ARAN01]
@10336 = ~[PC] What part of 'go away' do you not understand?~
@10337 = ~[PC] I prefer to hire people who can actually... well... speak common.~
@10338 = ~[PC] If you can't take 'no' for an answer, perhaps I should have you thrown into the gutter.~
@10339 = ~[PC] Hire on with me, then. Follow my instructions, and you will be welcome. Cross me, and things could get unpleasant for you.~
@10340 = ~[PC] Tell me why are you looking for work again?~
@10341 = ~[ARAN] No, can't say as I can do magic. Though I wouldn't mind studyin' it, if that's what you are after. My usual scribin' be trade work, not scrolls, but I can help craft some scrolls if I work closely with a mage.~
@10342 = ~[PC] Look, you are cute and all, but really - ask me again and I will simply have to have you thrown out of this establishment.~
@10343 = ~[PC] I need a fighter who can write contracts like the Sword Coast needs gibberlings. Get lost.~
@10344 = ~[PC] What else can you do?~
@10345 = ~[PC] The rest of the group shares what I choose to share, and they are glad to get that much. Do you have a problem with that?~
@10346 = ~[ARAN] Then I am your man. I can keep account o' what you have built up. Tell you what - I'll even go in for shares, instead of coin. That way I get whatever the rest of the group gets.~
@10347 = ~[PC] So you can fight, and you can do accounts. What else can you do for me?~
@10348 = ~[ARAN] Aye, can't say as I can do the work alone, but with a mage I can do some minor scroll work. My usual scribin' is trade work, not scrolls.~
@10349 = ~[ARAN] That be a story in itself, eh?~
@10350 = ~[ARAN] Bugger all, you be a tough one to convince. If you change your mind, I'll be here.~
@10351 = ~[ARAN] Ilmater's Blood, I had my hopes up. Look, when you need me, I'll be at the bar.~
@10352 = ~[ARAN] I'd rather be workin' with you than sittin' around here on my arse. Come back when you need a good fighter.~
@10353 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Bosom. I might have to take that trade ship job to Calimport after all. I'll be here a few more days, if you change your mind.~
@10354 = ~[ARAN] Elminster's Left Buttock. More sittin' around.~
@10355 = ~[PC] You know Elminster?~
@10356 = ~[ARAN] Like I said, I can fight. Got three campaigns under my belt, an' a ton of more informal fightin'. I have Guild membership in both Trader's Guild an' Scribe's Guild, so I can help with some scroll preparation, do basic contracts, an' keep accounts. I'm always on the lookout for new opportunities, so I can add a trade if you want. An' I love cookin'. Curry, 'specially.~
@10357 = ~[PC] No thanks.~
@10358 = ~[PC] We really don't need your services right now.~
@10359 = ~[PC] Perhaps later.~
@10360 = ~[ARAN] Fine by me. I'll take up a contract with you. I'll grab my gear.~
@10361 = ~[ARAN] Do you be kiddin' me? If I did, I would not be sittin' around here lookin' for my next contract, now would I.~
@10362 = ~[ARAN] Err... haven't we had this same blighted conversation once before?~
@10363 = ~[ARAN] Elminster can go stick his staff up his rear, for all I care... unless he be hirin'. I need work.~
@10364 = ~[ARAN] We seem to be caught in some variant o' one o' those "time stop" spells, only time keeps loopin' back instead o' just stoppin. Some fool mage must be experimentin' again, off th' books. Not smart, I'd say, seein' as th' blighted Cowlies don't take kindly to messin' wi' reality.~
@10365 = ~[ARAN] No, can't say as I have. I came in last month from the Sword Coast, an' I have been actin' as cook and accountant here ever since. I don't get much chance to catch up on stuff around here.~
@10366 = ~[PC] Why are you looking for work, then? It sounds like you have a good job here.~
@10367 = ~[PC] We don't have any need for you right now.~
@10368 = ~[PC] Sorry, we don't need you.~
@10369 = ~[PC] What is it you can do for me?~
@10370 = ~[ARAN] Well, I'm here now. I can fight, write, an' cook a mean curry.~ [C-ARAN01]
@10371 = ~[PC] I don't need you. I was just checking to see if you were still here.~
@10372 = ~[PC] I don't have much need for your services right now.~
@10373 = ~[ARAN] I know better than to get between a <PRO_MANWOMAN> an' <PRO_HISHER> drink. Th' bar be out front, just to th' south. If you needs be hirin' me on, I expect I will be right here.~
@10374 = ~[ARAN] Well, I suppose I could look around an' see what else there be to do. But if you change your mind, I expect I will be right here.~
@10375 = ~[ARAN] Well, let's just say there's a certain difference of opinion on what is proper behavior with th' cook's daughter. No harm, I can tell you that, an' no foul, but she sweared on Ilmater's Blood that she'd seen sixteen years, an' she wore the flower in the correct ear signallin' interest. But Gerris didn't see it that way, seein' as she's not of age to make her own mind.~
@10376 = ~[CERND] Wearing the flower is but one part of the ritual. You must have seen her age, yet your base nature continued to possess you.~
@10377 = ~[EDWIN] More ridiculous foreign customs. The trollop should be punished, or sold into slavery. <CHARNAME>, dismiss this overgrown ape and let us continue.~
@10378 = ~[HAERDALIS] Ah, my eagle, the stories we could swap...~
@10379 = ~[JAHEIRA] A grown man should know a child from a woman. He should also know that children like to play adult long before they are ready for true partnership.~
@10380 = ~[JAN] Well, now, that is an entirely different matter. My Uncle Matthias always said that females were trouble. They were, too; every time he said it, Aunt Petunia hit him with a frying pan.~
@10381 = ~[KELDORN] There are reasons for the ritual, but it takes common sense and a willingness to look carefully at the situation before accepting.~
@10382 = ~[KORGAN] Aye, good on ye. If she wants ter play wi' th' big boys, then it's her own business. Next time, though, you'd be better served takin' the trade, so a few coins saves ye th' trouble.~
@10383 = ~[YOSHIMO] A custom of flowers behind the ears denoting availability? Interesting.~
@10384 = ~[AERIE] Oh, that poor girl. Oh, you poor man. I have seen the flowers used and misused in the crowds surrounding the circus. You should have asked her father, first, though.~
@10385 = ~[ANOMEN] <CHARNAME>, come away from this baseborn scum. He seems unable to handle his sword after all.~
@10386 = ~[PC] I can see that would be a problem. Can you keep your hands to yourself while adventuring?~
@10387 = ~[ARAN] Experience be a hard teacher. So's Gerris. He trained with the Old Order. Wish he was a monk who followed the Sun Soul path, as Sune would have had him winkin' one eye at her brazenness, but no, he had to be one o' the orders what frown on that sort o' thing. I can keep to myself an' concentrate on the work.~
@10388 = ~[CERND] Experience teaches us many things. Bruises teach us many more.~
@10389 = ~[EDWIN] So you think to accept a fool who cannot control his animal lusts. Perhaps he will be useful as a decoy. Or an arrow holder.~
@10390 = ~[HAERDALIS] No, no, my fine friend, you should embrace the moment! <CHARNAME>, take pity on this poor man, and allow him his nature.~
@10391 = ~[JAHEIRA] The sword might be useful, as well as the pen. If you join, learn how to handle all of your equipment with equal discretion.~
@10392 = ~[KORGAN] Another blighted mouth to feed. Ain't my show, <CHARNAME>. You wanna deal wi' him, deal wi' him. I'm goin' off ter get drunk.~
@10393 = ~[YOSHIMO] We might be able to use a fighter. And I am intrigued to learn more of this scribing. I have seen penmanship as art for most of my life.~
@10394 = ~[AERIE] I would love to work on some scrolls with him. He is.. he is very interesting, <CHARNAME>.~
@10395 = ~[ANOMEN] We do not need this sellsword. Come away, <CHARNAME>.~
@10396 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Sweet Cheeks... I...~ [c-aws082]
@10397 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>? Bloody hells, it is good to see you. Filthy bloodsuckers had me right out o' my head. I can feel th' queen bitch be gone. Showed her how we do things downtown, eh? An' me, too.~
@10398 = ~[PC] It is good to see you back to your old self, Aran.~
@10399 = ~The Final Battle with Bodhi.

While I had feared for some time that Bodhi's final revenge on me would be to take away Aran forever, it seems that the information in the lorebook was right...  Amaunator's idol has restored Aran not only to life, but has removed the vampiric curse from him, as well. And more to the point, it appears his language is quite unaffected.~
@10400 = ~[PC] (Grab Aran by both shoulders and wrap your arms around him, kissing him deeply.)~
@10401 = ~[PC] You didn't look like you were resisting her all that much.~
@10402 = ~[PC] I am glad we were able to rescue you. But I think that this is where we say goodbye, at least for now.~
@10403 = ~[PC] Rescued you. Yes, I did that. But you abandoned me, and no one switches allegiance from me and lives. Your life is mine to do as I please.~
@10404 = ~[ARAN] No contracts wi' you. I have had my fill o' killin' babies an' destroyin' worlds.~ [c-aws083]
@10405 = ~Whitehand Withdraws

Aran Whitehand deserted the party today. I always suspected that he did not have the strength to follow me. If our paths cross again, it is likely that he will become very sorry that he ever showed his face to me.~
@10406 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Sweet Buttocks, but you are a pain in my arse.~ [C-ARAN01]
@10407 = ~[ARAN] Hey, I'm right out, if that's what you want. You want me in, out, or somewhere else?~ [c-aws084]
@10408 = ~[PC] I want you to stay in the party, Aran.~
@10409 = ~[PC] I am terminating your contract permanently, Aran. The paper one. I don't mean to sound ominous or anything. Go find work with someone else.~
@10410 = ~Aran Whitehand Rejoins

Aran has rejoined me. With any luck, I will be able to rely on his talents while I face my next challenge.~
@10411 = ~[PC] I am terminating you, Aran. Permanently. Die well.~
@10412 = ~[PC] Aran, wait here for me, will you? I will be back.~
@10413 = ~[PC] Aran, go on and make your way alone. I will join you when I am able.~
@10414 = ~[ARAN] Well, you had me a mite bit confused, for a minute there. Sure thing, I be stayin'.~
@10415 = ~[ARAN] Aye. Teldra might even have some good stories to swap, an' I can always bother Erika. Mayhap I will go find th' dice table, an' win me some interestin' trinkets, eh?~
@10416 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, I haven't had a good lusty sing in a bit. I'll go over there an' see what new songs I can learn. Mayhap trade a few o' th' bawdy... errr well, hells. I'll just go wet my whistle, an' learn what I can learn.~
@10417 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I will find a nice place in a corner, an' see what tere be to see. Not one for th' pits m'self. Too many ways things like that can leave a man less than he used to be, body or soul, eh?~
@10418 = ~[ARAN] Hmmm... what did you say? Got a mite bit distracted there. Wait here? Fine by me. You run along, an' come pick me up later, eh? I'll just enjoy th' scenery.~
@10419 = ~[ARAN] Right. Leave th' poor sellsword to do th' books an' clean up th' accounts, while you go galivantin' around Faerun solvin' th' world's problems. Sune's Sweet Sighs, don't actors realize all those special effects cost coin? Usin' a blighted spell wi' a pearl in th' components, when a minor cantrip would work. We need to hire on an illusionist, before th' blighted players sped us out o' house an' home!~
@10420 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. I might be able to sweet-talk th' cook into tradin' for some nice spices. That larder... hells, someone knows how to blighted well cook.~
@10421 = ~[ARAN] Right. Wait here, don't gawk, avoid gettin' into trouble, keep my nose clean, don't spit on th' floor, an' keep an eye out for trouble. Hey, do you think they have D'Tranion on tap?~
@10422 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. Mayhap they even have one. A monkey, I mean. Don't rightly see how a monkey can be vulgar, but... hey, what do you be lookin' at me like that for?~
@10423 = ~[ARAN] Good singin', better playin' an' a fair number o' relatively rich folk. If I get thrown out o' here, look around for me, eh? This place holds a good bit o' promise.~
@10424 = ~[ARAN] Hells, I'd rather not sit around doin' nothin', but I think I can talk my way into some fun around here. Don't you worry naught... I'll be all talk an' no action, an' keep a lookout for interestin' news.~
@10425 = ~[ARAN] I can do that. I saw me some interestin' games over there. Mayhap I can get a good flush o' luck, an Tymora will reward me wi' a bit o' extra coin, eh?~
@10426 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. Mayhap I can find a good vintage among these cut-rate drinks, eh? Not that I am hopeful, on account o' I think some o' that wine really be grapes pressed through old socks an' a dash o' spirits added. I'm not blighted well tryin' any o' th' ale. On Gond's Gonads, I'm not that stupid.~
@10427 = ~[ARAN] I'll be right here. Well, I'll likely be right here, or over wi' th' lads, singin', or drinkin'. So, sort o' here, eh?~
@10428 = ~[ARAN] I was wonderin' when you would show up. I have been checkin' out the area, but I were startin' to worry.~ [c-aws085]
@10429 = ~[ARAN] Well, I was just thikin' to myself, 'Self, where do <CHARNAME> be?'. An' then you pop up. I hope I didn't just squander one o' them wish spells by accident.~
@10430 = ~[ARAN] Well, there be a sight for sore eyes, eh?~
@10431 = ~[ARAN] There you are.~
@10432 = ~[ARAN] Good to see you. In fact, great to see you. Mayhap th' best news I have had this day.~
@10433 = ~[ARAN] Right then, contract's up, eh? Well, I'll be off. There be some work I wanted to do up north a ways in Waterdeep, anyways. Mayhap I will see you sometime a few years hence, when I have made my mark on th' world.~
@10434 = ~[ARAN] Hey! Cyric's Buttocks, you traitorous dungheap... I'll not go wi' out a fight...~
@10435 = ~[ARAN] Bring me back somethin' nice, will you?~
@10436 = ~[ARAN] Selune's Misty Eyes. I hope there isn't much dangerous around here. It could harm a lad, you know.~
@10437 = ~[ARAN] I'll just be thinkin' about that last inn. Or any inn.~
@10438 = ~[ARAN] Just don't be gone too long, eh?~
@10439 = ~[ARAN] I'll scout around a bit, and settle somewhere around here 'til you get back.~
@10440 = ~[ARAN] Chauntea's Basket, I could grow moss waitin'. So don't be long, eh?~
@10441 = ~[ARAN] There's got to be somethin' I can ferment around here. I'm runnin' short o' ale.~
@10442 = ~[ARAN] Tymora's Luck - I'd be a mite happier if I was along wi' you. But you call th' shots, so here I stay.~
@10443 = ~[ARAN] Well, I can try. Where do you be wantin' me to go?~
@10444 = ~[PC] Head for the Brynlaw docks.~
@10445 = ~Whitehand Sailing

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me at the Brynlaw docks. He did mention that getting there would be a problem, but he would find his way.~
@10446 = ~[PC] Head for the Athkatla docks.~
@10447 = ~Whitehand Docked

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me at the Athkatla docks. He mentioned that he enjoyed watching the ships, and that he would probably take up fishing if I took too long.~
@10448 = ~[PC] Meet me in the Market District in Athkatla.~
@10449 = ~Whitehand Sold on Staying

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me at the Market District in Athkatla. He mentioned that he might go shopping, but he would would probably end up at The Broken Sword, inhabiting his old room.~
@10450 = ~[PC] Meet me outside of the de'Arnise Keep.~
@10451 = ~Whitehand Keeping Still

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me in the lands surrounding the de'Arnise Keep. He mentioned trying to look up some old friends and seeing if he could put down his bedroll in an outpost.~
@10452 = ~[PC] Meet me in Trademeet.~
@10453 = ~Whitehand Trading

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me in Trademeet. He mentioned something about a good pub, and not waiting around without having some form of entertainment.~
@10454 = ~[PC] Meet me outside of the Umar Hills.~
@10455 = ~Whitehand Heads for the Hills

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me at the outside of the Umar Hills. He will probably find a local pub and try to get into some sort of trouble.~
@10456 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. I'll take up a charter, mayhap work th' oars. I may have one blighted hells o' a time findin' th' Cyric-kissed place, but I'll be there when you get there. I just hope you have some coin for me when you do.~
@10457 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. I'll take up fishin'. I do like to look at th' ships an' such, so mayhap I will go lean on th' worn old stone an' watch th' big fishnest get dragged in.~
@10458 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. There's bugger all to do around here anyways. I'll go check on th' shops an' resupply. Or even better... I will go see how things are at th' Broken Sword, eh?~
@10459 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. I'll wait around outside th' Keep. If I scout out a bit, mayhap I can find some old friends what signed on as guards for th' de'Arnise family awhile back. I'm right sure there will be an outpost what will let me lay down a bedroll, if I be lucky.~
@10460 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. Trademeet it is. I done heard o' a fine pub there. Mayhap I will be inside, mayhap outside, when you come callin'. Either way, I'll be close to Vyatri's place there. Good ale, an' they have a bard or two worth listenin' to.~
@10461 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then. Might be somethin' interestin' to do around that little village, there, I guess. More'n likely there be a pub what can stave off a lad's thirst, as well.~
@10462 = ~[ARAN] Is that all you be havin' to say to me?~
@10463 = ~[PC] Yes. Please, join with me again.~
@10464 = ~[PC] I'm sorry, but I don't have room for you in the party right now. Make your way out of here alone, and we will meet later.~
@10465 = ~[PC] It hurt so much seeing you following her orders, turning on me... but I know you could not resist. I missed you by my side.~
@10466 = ~[PC] I am glad it is over.~
@10467 = ~[ARAN] (His kisses rain fire on your lips, your neck, your hair.) Aye, I wished I was dead, I did. To feel th' deadness inside, it was a small taste o' what you must feel wi' out your soul. Let's get goin', eh?~
@10468 = ~[PC] Do not ever leave my side, Aran.~
@10469 = ~[ARAN] What? I was dominated right proper. I swear, <CHARNAME>, I'm your man an' no one else's!~
@10470 = ~[PC] I am not sure. I saw the way you looked at her, the hunger, the yearning. I did not know you had so strong a passion for short black leather skirts and sharpened teeth.~
@10471 = ~[PC] I understand. Please, join with me again.~
@10472 = ~[ARAN] What? I was dominated right proper. I swear, <CHARNAME>, I'm your man an' no one else's! An' you want me to go away? I don't rightly understand.~
@10473 = ~[PC] On second thought, join with me again. But things may be different. I do not know if I can trust you with my heart any more.~
@10474 = ~[PC] It hurt so much seeing you following her orders, turning on me... but I know you could not resist. For my sake, leave now, and do not come back.~
@10475 = ~[PC] I thought you were lost to me forever.~
@10476 = ~[PC] Good. Join with me again. But if your allegiance wavers again for any reason, then my soft kisses can turn as sharp as Bodhi's bite. I will not tolerate another calling you her 'toy'.~
@10477 = ~[PC] I accept that. I'm sorry, but I don't have room for you in the party right now. Make your way out of here alone, and we will meet later.~
@10478 = ~[PC] There is no excuse. Because you have been... useful, I will give you a head start. Drop your gear and start running.~
@10479 = ~[ARAN] Banes Blazin' Bones! Out o' th' fryin' pan an' into th' fire! I thought you was jokin'!~
@10480 = ~[ARAN] (His hands close hard around yours, drawing you face to face.) I swear by any an' all gods, that I am your Sword. If I turn again, kill me. For if you don't, I will take my own life.~
@10481 = ~[ARAN] I'll be gatherin' my gear an' gettin' back to th' routine. An' <CHARNAME>... Thank you.~
@10482 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands. Hopefully, he will find a good place to wait, and be there when I return.~
@10483 = ~[ARAN] Aye, then, I'll be gatherin' my gear an' gettin' back to th' routine.~
@10484 = ~[ARAN] An' <CHARNAME>... Thank you.~
@10485 = ~[ARAN] Look, <CHARNAME>, by Sune's Sweet Scent, there was naught I could do... Ilmater's Pity, you are jokin', aren't you.~
@10486 = ~[PC] Yes, you silly man. I missed you so much! Please, join with me again.~
@10487 = ~[PC] We will see. I'm sorry, but I don't have room for you in the party right now. Make your way out of here alone, and we will meet later.~
@10488 = ~[ARAN] Right, pull on both o' my legs. I know when I be th' butt o' th' joke. I think.~
@10489 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, that be between me an' him, anyways.~
@10490 = ~[ARAN] That be a harsh set o' words for me to hear you be sayin'. I may not talk quite th' way you would like, an' mayhap not always behave, but I be right loyal, I am.~
@10491 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Sweet Song, I didn't want to hear that, now, eh? I be right loyal, but I 'd rather hear th' criticism on my fightin' an' such, on account o' that be more impersonal.~
@10492 = ~[ARAN] I'd be right happy to leave here wi' you, you know. Action o' any kind beats sittin' around.~
@10493 = ~[PC] Sure. Join me.~
@10494 = ~[PC] Just checking on how you are doing. Wait here.~
@10495 = ~Whitehand Seems Interested in Me

I am not sure how I feel about it yet, but Aran seems to be watching me with more than just friendship in his glances. I will have to decide if this is something I will pursue.~
@10496 = ~[PC] Wait here. And try not to get into any trouble. I have eyes and ears everywhere.~
@10497 = ~Whitehand Waits

I told Aran Whitehand to wait for me right where he currently stands, bothering the patrons of The Broken Sword. Hopefully, he will be there when I return.~
@10498 = ~Whitehand Waits

