@10510 = ~[PC] As long as you promise to stop staring at <PLAYER4>'s hair when she is not looking, you can join us.~
@10511 = ~[PC] If you stop gawking at <PLAYER5>'s legs, you can join us.~
@10512 = ~[PC] As long as you promise to stop staring at <PLAYER6>'s decolletage, you can join us.~
@10513 = ~[PC] Aran, go on and make your way alone someplace else. I will join you when I am able.~
@10514 = ~[ARAN] That sounds like it might be a mite uncomfortable. I'll just be stickin' wi' my two an' two configuration.~
@10515 = ~[ARAN] You... fine. You want to be that way, it be your loss. I have more interestin' women to hunt anyways. Ones what appreciate what I can give.~
@10516 = ~[ARAN] You know, I deserve a bit more than to be dumped in th' refuse pit like I was some cast-off toy. You yank me out o' my life an' drag me here... just lookin' to screw wi' my life an' torture me before discardin' me on th' trash heap? Mayhap I be rough an' not th' finest, but I be bloody loyal.~
@10517 = ~[ARAN] Aye, now... that be a plan I can live with. I might even seal it wi' a kiss, when there be none to see. You will just have to be expectin' th' unexpected.~
@10518 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I have been knocked on th' head, but I am sure I would remember anythin' to do with you, <CHARNAME>. I... why, what do you know that I don't?~
@10519 = ~[PC] You remember it correctly, Aran. I was just teasing you.~
@10520 = ~[PC] You remember it correctly, Aran. All except... well, I thought we had a few stray glances, and the way your eyes look at me, I think you want more than just a little friendship. Nothing has really happened.~
@10521 = ~[PC] Shall I jog your memory, and describe some of the things we have done together?~
@10522 = ~[PC] No. I think you have it just the way I want it. Thank the gods for memory lapses.~
@10523 = ~[ARAN] I would love that.~
@10524 = ~[PC] You remember it correctly, Aran. All except the stray glances, whispers, and the way you look at me. It is like you are hungry, but not for food.~
@10525 = ~[PC] You remember it correctly, Aran. All except the bold glances, whispered conversations, and some very deep kisses.~
@10526 = ~[PC] You remember it correctly, Aran. All except the stolen whispered conversations, the feel of your fingers tracing runes across my body, the feel of the bare skin of your chest under my palms... and kisses that set us both on fire.~
@10527 = ~[PC] Aran... we have spent so much time together, the only thing we haven't done is...~
@10528 = ~[PC] Aran... I know the touch of you, the feel of all you, and that little strained look you get just before you...~
@10529 = ~[ARAN] Well, you had me off balance, there. I be right happy we both agree. I was worried, mayhap because any time a woman asks about 'relationship status', there be a powerful lot o' pitfalls an' traps a lad can fall into, eh?~
@10530 = ~[ARAN] I can stop you right there, with a kiss. I can't rightly forget anythin' about us, but it sure does feel good to hear you speakin' o' us like this. I was just a mite off balance, is all. Mayhap because any time a woman asks about 'relationship status', there be a powerful lot o' pitfalls an' traps a lad can fall into, eh?~
@10531 = ~[ARAN] Wait a mite bit, here... No gifts o' welcome, an' no party? It has been a mite bit dull around here.~
@10532 = ~[PC] I could use your help right now. Join up.~
@10533 = ~[PC] Actually, I wanted to talk to you about how things are between us.~
@10534 = ~[PC] I might let you rejoin the party, if you promise to behave yourself.~
@10535 = ~[PC] I might let you rejoin the party, if you promise to stop that tuneless whistling you are so fond of inflicting on us.~
@10536 = ~[PC] I might let you rejoin the party, if you promise to let me teach you how to speak.~
@10537 = ~[PC] I might let you rejoin the party, if you promise to learn how to cook.~
@10538 = ~[ARAN] I blighted well be lookin' forward to joinin' up wi' you again.~
@10539 = ~[PC] As long as you promise to stop staring at <PLAYER2>'s rear end, you can join us.~
@10540 = ~[PC] As long as you promise to stop staring at <PLAYER3>'s bustline, you can join us.~
@10541 = ~[ARAN] Right. Stay here. Watch my life waste away doin' naught but guard duty on a big patch o' nothin'. Got it.~
@10542 = ~[ARAN] I'll take me a look around, an' see what' to be seen..~
@10543 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. Mayhap I can catch up on some writin'. Though from th' looks o' this place, mayhap not.~
@10544 = ~[ARAN] Hurry on back, eh? If I keep sharpenin' my dagger, it will grind away to naught.~
@10545 = ~[ARAN] An' here I thought th' military were th' only place where "hurry up an' wait" were words to live by.~
@10546 = ~[ARAN] I don't mind scoutin', an' I don't mind hangin' about waitin'... well... hells. Scoutin's all right, but this hangin' around doin' naught just plain stinks.~
@10547 = ~[ARAN] Sure thing. If you happen on any birds, get me some new feathers, eh? I have done run out o' quills to scribe wi'.~
@10548 = ~[ARAN] I'd rather not. But you be th' one callin' th' shots.~
@10549 = ~[ARAN] Th' number o' times you had me waitin' about, then pickin' me back up, it makes me think you have a mite bit o chaos at th' soul level, eh? No matter. I'll wait.~
@10550 = ~[ARAN] Look, I've had enough times bein' kicked out an' told to wait that I had time to crochet this nice scarf for you. I guess I'll just start on a sweater while I be sittin' around, waitin' for you, again.~
@10551 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, fine. I have gotten into th' habit o' sittin' around doin' nothin'. Either that, or you have one hells o' a bad script stutter on your hands. Either way, I am not goin' anywhere soon.~
@10552 = ~[ARAN] I done whittled you this little keepsake for you, <CHARNAME>, but by Chauntea's Grain Basket, I done just lopped off too much. I'll be havin' to keep workin' on it a bit more.~
@10553 = ~[PC] Time to join up again, Aran.~
@10554 = ~[PC] I think <PLAYER2> likes you, Aran. Either that, or she has been planning your funeral.~
@10555 = ~[PC] <PLAYER3> has been muttering under her breath about how nice it is not waking up to you greeting the morning with a swearword and a laugh.~
@10556 = ~[PC] What do you look at, now that you don't have a constant eye on <PLAYER4>'s attributes?~
@10557 = ~[PC] Did you get <PLAYER5> a gift? It might ease some of the 'foot in mouth' problem.~
@10558 = ~[PC] <PLAYER6> has been just pining away for you, Aran.~
@10559 = ~[PC] So, what do you really think of <PLAYER2>? You have had a little time to yourself to judge objectively.~
@10560 = ~[PC] <PLAYER3> says you are useful. I am not so sure what he means, but I am hoping that is a positive and not a negative.~
@10561 = ~[PC] Have you paid <PLAYER4> his winnings? I thought you lost that last game, to the tune of eight tradebars and your trousers...~
@10562 = ~[PC] Do you happen to have <PLAYER5>'s length of rope? He has been poking about trying to remember if you returned it.~
@10563 = ~[PC] <PLAYER6> is wondering if you cooked up something nice, or if you have just been sitting around drinking.~
@10564 = ~[ARAN] So, do you be thinkin' about usin' my skills again?~
@10565 = ~[ARAN] Now, you look like a bright mornin' sunrise, you do, <CHARNAME>. What did you do wi' your hair? I did certainly miss you.~
@10566 = ~[ARAN] I was in th' middle o' th' most suprisin' dreams when you walked up. Or mayhap you walkin' up inspired some right warm dreams.~
@10567 = ~[ARAN] I swear, you look a sight finer each time I see you.~
@10568 = ~[ARAN] Now I wish I'd taken th' time to do a bit o' laundry. You wouldn't happen to be able to spare a lad a clean handkerchief, eh?~
@10569 = ~[ARAN] Back to work. At least wi' you, there be no such thing as a borin' day. Nor quiet night, for that matter.~
@10570 = ~[ARAN] Gear, check. Weapons, check. Coinpurse... coinp... oh, blighted hells. Give a lad a hand, an' help me find th' bloody thing before we move on, eh?~
@10571 = ~[ARAN] Right. I done re-packed most o' th' important stuff. O' course, there were some odds an' ends what were left out. Don't rightly know what I wanted wi' a left-handed ivory mustache comb, nohow.~
@10572 = ~[ARAN] Right. I'm on it.~
@10573 = ~[ARAN] Joinin' up on an adventure. Just what my mother always told me was about as smart as pickin' a fight wi' an ogre.~
@10574 = ~[ARAN] Just call me 'Al'. Hells, call me anythin' you want. Never did get what that song were all about nohow.~
@10575 = ~[ARAN] OK. I got me a pound o' flour for to throw about findin' invisibles, some butter for greasin' things up, two eggs for grenades, some o' this yeast... wait a moment. Strike that. This be cookin' supplies.~
@10576 = ~[ARAN] Now, there be a right fine idea. I'll just get my arse back where it belongs, watchin' your... err... followin' your lead!~
@10577 = ~[ARAN] Bloody great to see some o' you survived wi' out me. Got a spot open?~
@10578 = ~[MINSC] Ah, welcome! We shall fight evil together!~
@10579 = ~[MINSC] Boo has missed you, Aran! Why do you go off alone so much?~
@10580 = ~[MINSC] <CHARNAME>, must we keep leaving Aran behind and then picking him up again? Boo's whiskers are turning grey with the confusion.~
@10581 = ~[EDWIN] Wonder of wonders. The simian survived separation from its protectors.~
@10582 = ~[EDWIN] You survived. Another triumph of stupidity over natural selection.~
@10583 = ~[EDWIN] I would not waste more time on him, <CHARNAME>. But if we must suffer, we must.~
@10584 = ~[ANOMEN] You are quite overconfident in your assessment of your usefulness, are you not?~
@10585 = ~[HAERDALIS] An eagle returned to the fold!~
@10586 = ~[IMOEN] Heya. I'll let <CHARNAME> fill you in on what's happened so far.~
@10587 = ~[ARAN] I was gettin' tired o' cookin' for one, all by myself.~
@10588 = ~[JAHEIRA] Then you will be glad to cook tonight. I have several ingredients that will be most interesting to add.~
@10589 = ~[JAN] Have you any new turnip recipes? I am always trying new things with turnips. Why, just the other day I tried ground ankheg chitin as a spice, and it was perfect - it did not overpower the turnip taste at all. It even cleaned my teeth while I ate.~
@10590 = ~[YOSHIMO] Indeed. Cooking alone is as lonely as eating alone.~
@10591 = ~[ARAN] Missed me, did you, <CHARNAME>? I did certainly miss you.~
@10592 = ~[ARAN] No real fightin' around here so far. Perhaps they are waitin' for you to show up, <CHARNAME>.~
@10593 = ~[KELDORN] That would seem to be the case so far this adventure.~
@10594 = ~[KORGAN] They just wanna try me on fer size.~
@10595 = ~[VALYGAR] It would seem that fighting follows us everywhere.~
@10596 = ~[ARAN] Ilmater's Bloody Wrists, but there were naught to do around here. I thought I might find th' rest comfortable, but to tell Ilmater's Truth, it be just bloody borin'.~
@10597 = ~[MAZZY] Unfortunately, where we have been has not been precisely 'boring'.~
@10598 = ~[NALIA] I do need someone to take care of some of the cleaning and cooking.~
@10599 = ~[VICONIA] Let me kill this surfacer slug, <CHARNAME>. His odor offends me.~
@10600 = ~[AERIE] Hello, Aran... could you please put me down?~
@10601 = ~[ARAN] Why, sure enough. Sorry, got a bit carried away, there.~
@10602 = ~[ARAN] That were a friendly gesture, nothin' more, <CHARNAME>, I swear it.~
@10603 = ~[C-MALCER] Well now, here's a pretty sight. One <PRO_RACE> girl, not too bad looking, and here we have all three of us just looking for a good time. Come in and have a drink with Taman, here, and if you are friendly enough, we might leave peaceably.~
@10604 = ~[C-OSKUT] Hey, that sellsword looks like he's with her.~
@10605 = ~[C-TAMAN] Nah, he won't be a problem. A few coins, and he'll look the other way. Or we just kill him.~
@10606 = ~[PC] How dare you! Aran, are you going to let these people talk to me like this?~
@10607 = ~[PC] I do not bother with trivialities and insignificant worms. Aran, go take care of these idiots.~
@10608 = ~[PC] (Hide behind Aran and grip his arm tightly, pushing him toward the group.)~
@10609 = ~[PC] Aran, I think that you should take care of this situation...~
@10610 = ~[PC] Fine...Drop your trousers and if I like what I see, I won't cut it off. Otherwise, you lose both your manhood and your tongue. Still want to play, *boys*?~
@10611 = ~[PC] Out of my way, Aran. I would take their heads off, but it probably would do no harm. I will start with their feet, instead.~
@10612 = ~[C-MALCER] Oh, come on, girl. You haven't had a good time until you have had a drink with the three of us. We can have a little fun, too. You might even enjoy it. And this piss-ant sellsword couldn't handle me, let alone me and my friends.~
@10613 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be large talk from a Raven. Don't you boys have a sergeant what to teach you manners?~
@10614 = ~[C-TAMAN] I smell 'Fist on you. We fly overhead while you grub in the mud, newlie.~
@10615 = ~[PC] He can hold his own in a fight. But you should be more worried about me. I tend to get over-excited, and might end up removing that tongue. Or perhaps other parts of your body.~
@10616 = ~[PC] Insignificant, insolent worm. You are beneath my notice. Aran, kill him slowly. I want to hear him scream for mercy.~
@10617 = ~[PC] Aran, I think that you should take care of this situation, quickly.~
@10618 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. You heard the lady, lads. Do you be wantin' to settle this on arm wrestlin', brawlin', or should we just skip right to it an' see what th' insides o' your guts look like when they be spread over th' wall over there?~
@10619 = ~[C-MALCER] Look who's a big man, now. Are you looking for a fight?~
@10620 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, laddie... I don't rightly look for fights. But by Bane's Bloody Buttocks, so far there's naught that I have left unfinished. Do you feel lucky?~
@10621 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, laddie... I don't rightly look for fights. But by Bane's Bloody Buttocks, so far there's naught that I have left unfinished. Besides, there be three o' us an' three o' you. Do you feel lucky?~
@10622 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, laddie... I don't rightly look for fights. But by Bane's Bloody Buttocks, so far there's naught that I have left unfinished. Besides, there be more o' us... look careful, on account o' we all be together. Do you feel lucky?~
@10623 = ~[C-TAMAN] See, I told you he would be a problem.~
@10624 = ~[C-OSKUT] Yeah, yeah... I know you are all edjumucated and such. I think he will go down in the first few swings.~
@10625 = ~[C-OSKUT] Hey... Malcer. They look familiar. Hold up, this might be a bad idea.~
@10626 = ~[C-MALCER] I hear lots of hot air, but they don't look that tough, even with the backup.~
@10627 = ~[ARAN] Now, <CHARNAME>, you go on back in an' have a nice cup o' tea, mayhap do your nails. I think these boys have had just a mite bit too much to drink.~
@10628 = ~[C-OSKUT] I am serious. I recognize her, now. They say she has a collection of drow ears and dragon's teeth, and that she personally smashed the Iron Throne.~
@10629 = ~[C-MALCER] So, big protector, eh? I didn't know prostitutes around here had the money for a mercenary escort. What's she worth, 2 coppers a night? You get out of the way, or you will be sorry.~
@10630 = ~[ARAN] I'm goin' to rip your head off an' piss down your neck.~
@10631 = ~[C-MALCER] Oh, big man, having her fight your battles for you.~
@10632 = ~[ARAN] Believe me, son, you don't be knowin' her like I do. Last one who ticked her off only lost a few pints o' blood an half his scalp. O' course, that was me, an' she needs me around for to carry stuff an' such. You, not so much.~
@10633 = ~[C-MALCER] I hear lots of hot air, but you don't look that tough, either of you. Come on, boys... they don't need all that coin. Get 'em.~
@10634 = ~[C-MALCER] Drow ears?~
@10635 = ~[C-TAMAN] Dragon's teeth?~
@10636 = ~[C-OSKUT] Err... we were just leaving. Just a few high-spirited remarks, no harm meant.~
@10637 = ~[C-MALCER] R... right. We'll just head on, and... you just do whatever it is you were doing.~
@10638 = ~[ARAN] No problem, lads. Only don't be comin' round here much, eh? Me, you might be able to fight to a standstill. Her, she looks like a shrinkin' violet, right up until th' time you realize her hand's holdin' what's left o' your intestines. An' then she starts gettin' mean.~
@10639 = ~[PC] Oh, my hero. I should fall at your feet and kiss them for saving me from the big bad evil thugs. You do realize you will pay for spoiling my fun, don't you?~
@10640 = ~[PC] Well, we scared them off well enough. I wish more of these idiots would choose to walk away. Do you think we could scare Irenicus into surrendering with that routine?~
@10641 = ~[PC] Tea. Nails. You are in so much trouble.~
@10642 = ~[PC] What is it with men, that they think that being great hulking aggressive brutes is attractive?~
@10643 = ~[PC] And here I thought I was ending the evening entertaining three men in my bedchamber. I guess I have some free time, and absolutely nothing to do...~
@10644 = ~[PC] Hey, that was fun. Did you see the way the little one turned all white in the face? Come on, let's follow them!~
@10645 = ~[C-AW01P1] Mercenary life is great. Lots of pointless fighting for fools who see you as expendable, lots of bad food and worse ale, and no real pension plan to speak of.~
@10646 = ~[C-AW01P1] So if you are here to recruit me, sod off. Or, buy me a drink, and then sod off.~
@10647 = ~[C-AW01P1] Seeker's Soul, do you go around botherin' regular folk all the time? You need a hobby.~
@10648 = ~[C-AW01P1] I worked for the Blue Boars for two campaigns. They have way too many officers, most of whom can't fight. But the pay is good.~
@10649 = ~[C-AW01P2] They say the prophecies of Aulando are coming true. I've heard that before, though. Usually right before they raise taxes.~
@10650 = ~[C-AW01P2] You know, I need to stop drinking. I am beginning to smell like a drunken Luscan. Wait... I am a drunken Luscan. Never mind.~
@10651 = ~[C-AW01P2] So, are you buying the next round? I make a good friend. Good listener, you know. As long as the drinks keep coming, I keep listening.~
@10652 = ~[C-AW01P2] Some folks say Firewine is the best. Me, I don't care what is pouring, as long as there is plenty of it and it is cheap.~
@10653 = ~[C-AW01P2] I served in the colony for awhile. After a few months of battling insects the size of small houses and the occasional odd animal, I decided to go for someplace nice and comfortable, far from fighting. So I am off to join up in Trademeet.~
@10654 = ~[C-AW01P2] I wanted to be with the 'Fist, up toward Nashkel. There was a woman up there who knew how to look past my green skin, and she offered me work, I think her name was Vai.But I got lured into colonial work. Worst job ever.~
@10655 = ~[C-AW01P3] I'm contracted out for the next three tendays, so if you are looking for another sword, I'm not available.~
@10656 = ~[C-AW01P3] Don't sign anything from the Flaming Fist without checking the contract carefully. I ended up fighting some Chill up Nashkel way for half a year, and had to pay for my own food. Lousy recruiters... always looking to take advantage.~
@10657 = ~[C-AW01P3] They say the mercenary life is exciting and special. I suppose that might be true for some. I'd characterize it more like hard and painful.~
@10658 = ~[C-AW01P3] I work hard, play hard, and drink hard. Then again, my play and my work involve drinking, so I could just say "bottom's up".~
@10659 = ~[C-AW01P3] Your equipment is way too fancy for a regular, and all mismatched besides. Were you expecting this place to be invaded by an army? Gods, go get a decent equipment locker.~
@10660 = ~[C-AW01P3] Look, I am almost drunk enough to find you attractive. So move along, now. I am probably going to do something stupid, and then the boys will have to bail me out of the local jail. Again.~
@10661 = ~[C-AW01EP] You look like the right sort. If you want, The Broken Sword is that door west of you. No civilians allowed, unless they are hiring. This place is only for people who live and die on the sharp edge.~
@10662 = ~[C-AW01EP] If you are looking for sellswords, step on in. Daggerford isn't the only hiring place, you know.~
@10663 = ~[C-AW01EP] Look, this ain't Asbravn. If you want hospitality, step inside. If you don't, blighted well move along.~
@10664 = ~[C-AW01EP] Yeah, yeah... tell it to the 'Fist. My whole contract is to stand outside and make sure idiots who can't hold their own in a fight stay out here. You folks can go on in anytime.~
@10665 = ~[C-AW01EP] This duty is boring enough, I am almost tempted to sign up for another tour in Maztica. Almost.~
@10666 = ~[C-AW01EP] Door. There. West. You know, the opposite of East.~
@10667 = ~[C-AW01EP] If you are looking for sellswords or mercenaries, The Broken Sword is the right place. If you are looking to fight anyone in particular, bugger off and do it some place else. I cause enough trouble all on my own.~
@10668 = ~[C-AW01EP] Drinks, yes. Rooms, yes. Goods and services, a few. Look, if you really have to ask this, you really shouldn't wander in. Nothing starts a fight faster than some blighted greenhorn fool making a crack about the Red Cloaks or the 'Fist. Last time, we had to scrub the blood out of the woodwork with wet sand for a week.~
@10669 = ~[C-AW01EP] Would I recommend drinking here? Sure. It's your funeral.~
@10670 = ~[C-AW01EP] Do I look like a signpost? Tyr's Eye, just blighted well go in and hire someone. Or, get a decent contract and get the hells out of this place. Gods know things are strange enough around here to make anyone need hirelings. Talk to Teldra. She'll set you up, either way.~
@10671 = ~[ARAN] Hells, Manson, what did you do to Teldra to draw this blighted contract again?~
@10672 = ~[C-AW01EP] Does it matter? I'm in the doghouse until she says otherwise.~
@10673 = ~[C-AW01EP] Someone said the Han make lousy fighters.~
@10674 = ~[ARAN] Oh. Terria. Right. I'll drink to that one's memory for you. Good sword.~
@10675 = ~[C-AW01EP] Another fight. I have no blighted idea why I can't just relax.~
@10676 = ~[C-AW01EP] It was their fault. But there were three of them. Probably not the best idea to take them all on at once with no backup.~
@10677 = ~[ARAN] You know, we could help out a bit wi' that fightin' problem. Mayhap get an intelligence potion, or mayhap two...~
@10678 = ~[C-AW01EP] Oh, shove it up your arse, Aran.~
@10679 = ~[C-AW01EP] The usual. Don't worry none, though. I'll be back working soon enough.~
@10680 = ~[ARAN] You have th' worst luck, boyo. Fighting again, eh?~
@10681 = ~[ARAN] I thought you had headed out for Rasheman on that caravan contract. Problems wi' your fists again, or just your mouth?~
@10682 = ~[ARAN] Better you than me, eh? How did you piss Teldra off this time?~
@10683 = ~[ARAN] Manson, my friend... when are you goin' to learn to lead wi' your brain, an' not wi' your brawn?~
@10684 = ~[C-AW01W1] Orders for food or drink are at the bar, <SIRMAAM>. If you are looking for anything else, it is not on the menu.~
@10685 = ~[C-AW01W1] I will get you as much water as you like, as quickly as I can.~
@10686 = ~[C-AW01W1] Did you order the D'Tranion and Meat Pie? I have two orders, both getting cold, and not a patron to claim it. But if you want to pay for it...~
@10687 = ~[C-AW01W1] We have a good selection of food and spirits. We can even help you with some money changing, if you want...~
@10688 = ~[C-AW01W1] You do realize I am just a barmaid, not a Lorekeeper of Oghma, right?~
@10689 = ~[C-AW01W1] Drinks are ordered at the bar, and then if you sit at a table I can bring them to you.~
@10690 = ~[C-AW01W1] Well, you look like you could use a drink. Just see Orrin, at the bar.~
@10691 = ~[C-AW01W1] I know I have told you this before. I really can't take drink orders, only Orrin can.~
@10692 = ~[C-AW01W1] Orrin will be happy to help you, I am sure.~
@10693 = ~[C-AW01W1] Orrin handles everything but the cleanup.~
@10694 = ~[C-AW01W1] Orrin is over at the bar.~
@10695 = ~[C-AW01W1] I do not handle any coin. You will have to deal with Orrin.~
@10696 = ~[C-AW01W1] I need to get this order out right away, so go talk to Orrin.~
@10697 = ~[C-AW01W1] Oooh, sorry... that drink spilled, just a little. I hope it doesn't stain anything.~
@10698 = ~[C-AW01W1] Was this order yours? Wait... no, it was for Teldra, in tha back room. Sorry.~
@10699 = ~[C-AW01W1] Table four, did you order the Rashemi Firewine?~
@10700 = ~[C-AW01W1] Yes, I know these clothes are too nice. I plan on going out after my shift.~
@10701 = ~[C-AW01W1] Hey! Who pinched me! Shame on you! I'm a nice girl, and way too young for the likes of you!~
@10702 = ~[C-AW01W1] I only speak two languages, and table two is speaking some strange thing I have never heard. Does anyone know what Zyzzlup is, and if we have it?~
@10703 = ~[C-AW01W1] Keep your feet off of the table, please, Master Whitehand. This is a respectable establishment.~
@10704 = ~[C-AW01W1] Perhaps you should take Aran to a place more worthy of his status... like a stable. Or a pigsty.~
@10705 = ~[C-AW01W1] Let me guess... Aran wants a nice curry, and he expects it on his tab. Gods forbid that he actually pay for anything.~
@10706 = ~[C-AW01W1] I see you are still saddled with this sorry excuse for a sellsword. I'd renegotiate that contract, if I were you.~
@10707 = ~[C-AW01W1] Dirty feet, wayward gleam in the eyes, sniffing around every available kitchen... wait, was I talking about the cat, or Aran?~
@10708 = ~[C-AW01W1] You will make some poor girl marry you someday, Aran, but not until you learn to GET YOUR FEET OFF THE TABLE.~
@10709 = ~[ARAN] Ah, Erika, m'ladylove... I would go to th' ends o' Faerun for you.~
@10710 = ~[C-AW01W1] I am sure you would. But would you remain there?~
@10711 = ~[ARAN] How come you are not married off yet, Erika?~
@10712 = ~[C-AW01W1] Well, I am still of apprentice age, for one thing. For another, marriage always seems to saddle a girl with a baby.~
@10713 = ~[ARAN] Not always. You don't have to have children, you know.~
@10714 = ~[C-AW01W1] I was talking about the husband.~
@10715 = ~[ARAN] Any news worth repeatin' around here, Erika?~
@10716 = ~[C-AW01W1] Not to you.~
@10717 = ~[ARAN] Do you realize you must have told me to get my feet off o' th' table a million times by now?~
@10718 = ~[C-AW01W1] Yes. Next time I shall ask Teldra to call in a favor, and have your ankles broken. She owes me a favor or two, you know.~
@10719 = ~[ARAN] Get me an ale, eh, lass?~
@10720 = ~[C-AW01W1] Now, Master Whitehand, you look like someone just killed your best friend.~
@10721 = ~[ARAN] I be pinin' away, on account o' your hard heart, Erika.~
@10722 = ~[C-AW01W1] Do it quickly, then, and make sure you remember me in your will.~
@10723 = ~[ARAN] Now, when are you goin' to give a lad th' chance to compliment you, eh? I keep tryin'.~
@10724 = ~[C-AW01W1] I prefer actions to words... HEY! Not that kind of action...~
@10725 = ~[ARAN] Now, Erika, I can pay good coin. I have come up in th' world, you know.~
@10726 = ~[C-AW01W1] Well, that is good, because you couldn't go much further down!~
@10727 = ~[C-AW01W1] Why, yes, there is. I heard Alisson was by the other day, looking for you.~
@10728 = ~[ARAN] errr... Did she say why?~
@10729 = ~[C-AW01W1] I think it was something about a broken heart, or broken promises, or some other sob story. But don't worry. She was very discreet, if you call screaming 'I am going to make him pay!' at the top of her lungs 'discreet'.~
@10730 = ~[ARAN] Ah, blighted flask... I have to get me one o' those infinite flasks one day. Fill me up, eh, Erika?~
@10731 = ~[C-AW01W1] You look like someone just tossed you in an unmarked grave.~
@10732 = ~[C-AW01W1] Oooh, the words I have been waiting for, all of my life! I'll go tell Orrin where he can shove this job...~
@10733 = ~[C-AW01W1] ...You should see your face, Aran. I don't think I have ever seen a man turn that particular combination of white, red, and panicked.~
@10734 = ~[C-AW01TK] Any word on that work you were doing for me? I do hope you can come with Aran in tow. He is Guild, and I cannot pay off a contract without him present and in good health. Teldra holds most of my business hostage. One bad word from her, and my entire clientele will go elsewhere.~
@10735 = ~[PC] Not yet. I wish to peruse your selection of services, if I may.~
@10736 = ~[PC] I am working on it. But I was thinking... I have heard that a wealthy, well connected person might peruse some of the more... interesting wares?~
@10737 = ~[PC] I wish nothing at this time.~
@10738 = ~[PC] Is there anything of interest that you might tell me? Interesting goings on, or work available?~
@10739 = ~[PC] I have the package. I just have not delivered it yet.~
@10740 = ~[PC] I have delivered the package, but I think I want to renegotiate my fee before giving you the receipt...~
@10741 = ~[PC] What do you think - does this outfit match my hair?~
@10742 = ~[PC] Can I ask you what is going on with that big burly fighter in the back rooms?~
@10743 = ~[PC] Can I ask you about that half-orc woman in the back rooms?~
@10744 = ~[PC] Can I ask you what that cleric is doing in the back rooms?~
@10745 = ~[C-AW01TK] Any word on that work you were doing for me? I do hope you have delivered it, and returned with a receipt.~
@10746 = ~[C-AW01TK] Ah, the package. My thanks to you for your assistance in this small matter. I feel sure that it was nothing for a person of your stature.~
@10747 = ~[PC] Actually, it was quite difficult. So difficult, in fact, that I am going to have to request a greater reward.~
@10748 = ~[PC] It was nothing. I was glad to be of help.~
@10749 = ~[PC] Judging by the number of stupid 'take this packet and go from here to a random person, then return' errands I seem to attract, it seemed like a usual day of adventuring.~
@10750 = ~[PC] Look, next time, handle your own parcel delivery. That was a large chunk of my life I just wasted playing fetch-and-carry.~
@10751 = ~[PC] Hey, even Aran can't mess up a simple delivery.~
@10752 = ~[PC] What package?~
@10753 = ~[C-AW01TK] Tidings to you, <CHARNAME>. A word of concern... Your reputation is less than stellar. Teldra does not take kindly to those who break her contracts. She provides most of my business, as well as a good deal of protection. Stay away from her, please. Actually, the same applies to my humble personage.~
@10754 = ~[PC] I wish to peruse your selection of services, if I may.~
@10755 = ~[PC] I am doing business with you, not Teldra. Just show me what you have.~
@10756 = ~[PC] I am here to take a look at your more select offerings. We had a deal, remember?~
@10757 = ~[C-AW01TK] Good tidings to you. How might I be of assistance?~
@10758 = ~[PC] Do you say that to every customer?~
@10759 = ~[PC] Perhaps you can lighten up a little, and give out a few complimentary drinks.~
@10760 = ~[PC] I have heard a rumor that you used to be an adventurer yourself.~
@10761 = ~[PC] How is life?~
@10762 = ~[PC] I have heard that a wealthy, well connected person might peruse some of the more... interesting wares?~
@10763 = ~[PC] You seem to have a wide variety of people here. Is that man over there really a Mindulgulph?~
@10764 = ~[PC] So, what is the deal with you and Teldra? Are you two... you know?~
@10765 = ~[PC] Is Erika attached? She seems to be unreceptive to flirting.~
@10766 = ~[PC] How are things going around here?~
@10767 = ~[C-AW01TK] No, nothing at all. Not much of interest.~
@10768 = ~[PC] Are you just saying that, or is there really nothing to find here?~
@10769 = ~[PC] Yes. You seem like a very interesting man. Perhaps we could share a drink, and get to know each other.~
@10770 = ~[PC] I suppose that everyone around here is just minding their own business and would not be paying any attention to rumors anyways, right?~
@10771 = ~[C-AW01TK] Nothing, of course. Do you wish anything else?~
@10772 = ~[PC] Not right now.~
@10773 = ~[PC] Oh, come on. You have not seen anything of interest around here at all?~
@10774 = ~[PC] I would not mind a few free drinks, and perhaps some entertainment.~
@10775 = ~[C-AW01TK] Certainly, <SIRMAAM>. But somehow, no matter how grandly or decrepitly one dresses, the weight of your coinpurse is all that matters to me. Perhaps my <LADYLORD> would prefer the more usual offerings?~
@10776 = ~[PC] Yes, that will be fine.~
@10777 = ~[PC] What might you consider a weighty enough purse?~
@10778 = ~[PC] Actually, I think I will be moving along.~
@10779 = ~[PC] Hmmm. You seem like a very interesting man. Perhaps we could share a drink, and get to know each other. Perhaps work out an alternate arrangement...~
@10780 = ~[C-AW01TK] If I can assist you, please let me know what I may do to make you comfortable in this establishment.~
@10781 = ~[PC] Just show me your services, then.~
@10782 = ~[PC] Can you tell me about how I might get freelance work in the area, or tell me about anything interesting happening?~
@10783 = ~[C-AW01TK] Now, is there anything I can get you?~
@10784 = ~[PC] No. I do not need anything right now.~
@10785 = ~[PC] Just show me your usual wares, then.~
@10786 = ~[C-AW01TK] Did you want anything else?~
@10787 = ~[C-AW01TK] I am afraid that falls into the old saying, 'if you have to ask, then you do not have enough'.~
@10788 = ~[PC] Has anyone ever told you that you have a supercilious attitude?~
@10789 = ~[PC] You mean my winning personality and minor notoriety are not enough?~
@10790 = ~[C-AW01TK] This was mildly entertaining. A pair of dwarves visited a few days ago, attempting some expedition for some reason or other. Something about temples, and dead gods, and finding mithral. Unfortunately, they had a falling out, and left unhappy. Alive, but unhappy. I do not know where they went after that minor incident.~
@10791 = ~[PC] Are you sure there is nothing else of interest that you might tell me?~
@10792 = ~[PC] No, I think I am done here.~
@10793 = ~[PC] You don't happen to know where I could purchase some pure mithral, do you... I heard that you might have a private stock you are willing to sell.~
@10794 = ~[C-AW01TK] There were some travelers seeking protection on their journeys to Trademeet here yesterday, but Teldra already set them up with assistance from one of the minor mercenary groups she represents. There could be others who are interested in such protections, I imagine.~
@10795 = ~[C-AW01TK] I have heard that the Copper Coronet has many opportunities for freelance work. I wish that I had the connections that establishment seems to have, for I could greatly increase my profit. Most of what Teldra offers is long term... which means she empties my bar as well as my ale supplies.~
@10796 = ~[PC] You seem to have the same greeting for me each time I meet you. Do you say that to every customer?~
@10797 = ~[C-AW01TK] I heard that the Blue Boars have begun recruiting for a campaign against some young woman claiming to be a Bhaalspawn up Tethyr way. They say the Prophecies are coming to pass, but I am not so sure. I suspect it is all the usual subjects... trade rights, taxes, and who gets to control what.~
@10798 = ~[C-AW01TK] ...Hmmm. To tell you the truth, I have heard little that could be of true interest to you.~
@10799 = ~[C-AW01TK] I am flattered. I must decline.~
@10800 = ~[PC] Fair enough. Just business then.~
@10801 = ~[PC] What, do you not find me attractive?~
@10802 = ~[PC] Do you have some policy against fraternization with potential customers?~
@10803 = ~[PC] Have you not felt the grace of Sune? Would you deny the warmth and comfort of friendly companionship, even if chaste?~
@10804 = ~[C-AW01TK] Nothing of interest, <SIRMAAM>. Unless...~
@10805 = ~[C-AW01TK] If you are looking for work as a hired soldier, there is a mercenary recruiter wandering around collecting fools and madmen. Ask around for Teldra.~
@10806 = ~[PC] Perhaps I will do that. I might be back later.~
@10807 = ~[PC] I have already met her, thanks. Just show me what you have available.~
@10808 = ~[PC] I heard you were the right man to sell some goods to, no questions asked.~
@10809 = ~[C-AW01TK] My dear <PRO_SIRMAAM>, you surprise me! Why, a certain mercenary named Whitehand has expressed just such sentiments. Though you pronounced the words with much clearer diction, and less colorful additions.~
@10810 = ~[C-AW01TK] I do have a standard response, of course. I find it helps keep customers happy if I am civil, impartial, and dispassionate. It reduces the chances of someone taking offense.~
@10811 = ~[C-AW01TK] Blacktalons are welcome here as equally as Solara's Elite. Every mercenary needs a place to go where the battles remain outside, and good stories can be told. If a rust monster from Mindulgulph Mercenaries wants to drink, I will give him a stoneware mug and ask he not drip on the other customers.~
@10812 = ~[C-AW01TK] I do draw a clear line, though. A contract is a contract, and I do not serve those who break their word. I have had a Blue Boar thrown out of The Broken Sword, and my word drummed him out of his corps and his noble title. Guild is Guild. You do not break your word to another, though tomorrow you may have to kill them if a contract requires it.~
@10813 = ~[C-AW01TK] My drinks often receive compliments, but I rarely hear them giving commentary to my customers, complimentary or not. If you mean give you free access to my wares, I must decline.~
@10814 = ~[C-AW01TK] Well, if it were your business, I might be persuaded to answer. Since it is not, I will politely decline to respond.~
@10815 = ~[C-AW01TK] Alas, my adventuring consisted of delving deep into a small set of ruins, and being poisoned by the very first trap I encountered. When my party revived me, I decided that support roles were much more my style.~
@10816 = ~[C-AW01TK] Erika may be young, but she has spent much of that time fending off unwanted advances from inebriated mercenaries. I think that it would take a very special person to convince her to even attempt a minor flirtation.~
@10817 = ~[PC] That explains it.~
@10818 = ~[PC] Perhaps the grace of Sune will warm her heart, and quell any fears about my interest.~
@10819 = ~[PC] Perhaps I will just let her do her job, and not bother her.~
@10820 = ~[PC] Ah. A conquest. I do like a challenge.~
@10821 = ~[PC] Pity. She could find so much happiness with me.~
@10822 = ~[PC] Perhaps she has a thing for Aran.~
@10823 = ~[C-AW01TK] I might be able to find something to complain about, but then I would have to seek out someone who actually cared to listen. So, a polite "everything is going well" will have to suffice.~
@10824 = ~[C-AW01TK] I have it on good authority that it beats the alternative.~
@10825 = ~[C-AW01TK] I am sure the Copper Coronet could serve you better than I, then. Do come back when you wish fair services rendered for fair prices.~
@10826 = ~[C-AW01TK] No, I think that is much more friendly teasing than romance. She has seen enough of Aran's... peculiarities.~
@10827 = ~[C-AW01TK] Undoubtedly.~
@10828 = ~[C-AW01TK] I usually refrain from commenting on a customer's choice in fashion attire. Surprisingly, many mercenaries get a little touchy about the strangest things.~
@10829 = ~[C-AW01TK] I believe that is what I indicated.~
@10830 = ~[C-AW01TK] I do not think negotiation is appropriate at this time. Aran is Guild. That means payoff or any discussion of that comes when he is healthy, present, and part of your team. That is all part of the contract.~
@10831 = ~[C-AW01TK] Well I do hope you can finish that soon. I need that matter resolved.~
@10832 = ~[C-AW01TK] Consider my establishment your home away from home, with the exception of the small matter of remaining fully clothed in all public areas at all times.~
@10833 = ~[C-AW01TK] Enjoy your time here, then. Just remember, I have decent drinks, reasonable prices, and a low tolerance for shenanigans.~
@10834 = ~[C-AW01TK] I wish you well, then. Be sure to think of The Broken Sword after your next successful campaign. We handle parties as large as a standard platoon.~
@10835 = ~[C-AW01TK] Good <DAYNIGHT> to you, then. If you happen on jewels and gems in your travels, please remember our services.~
@10836 = ~[C-AW01TK] A Pearl to you, and to your return visit.~
@10837 = ~[C-AW01TK] You heard incorrectly. Rather, to be more precise, you received incorrect information. Whether or not your hearing is impaired is something that I cannot judge.~
@10838 = ~[ARAN] I am afraid that if I granted such requests to every famous or notorious personage ever to grace my establishment, I would no longer be in business. Rustybeard Orcwall himself could not sway me, even if he brought half of the Vilhon Company with him.~
@10839 = ~[C-AW01TK] Certainly, <SIRMAAM>.~
@10840 = ~[C-AW01TK] Certainly, <SIRMAAM>. But if the Watch comes calling on me, rest assured the Guild will not take kindly to your interference.~
@10841 = ~[C-AW01TK] I do have a lad who needs some work, if you are hiring. He is a bit rough around the edges, but he means well. Here, take one of his advertisements.~
@10842 = ~[PC] I'll take a look at it later. Why are you helping him out?~
@10843 = ~[PC] Actually, I am not interested right now. I wish to see your selection of services.~
@10844 = ~[PC] Sure, sure... but I am more interested in what you can do for me. Rumor has it that a wealthy, well connected person might peruse some of the more... interesting wares?~
@10845 = ~[PC] You seem a little stiff. Do you say the same thing to every customer?~
@10846 = ~[PC] I think I am done here.~
@10847 = ~[PC] No need for the broadside. I do not want the thing weighing down my pack. But you could tell me where to find him.~
@10848 = ~[C-AW01TK] I saw you talking to Teldra, but a copper piece is a copper piece. I get one for every broadsheet I give. I do have a lad who needs some work, if you are hiring. He is a bit rough around the edges, but he means well. Here, take one of these. I insist.~
@10849 = ~[PC] Sure, sure... but I am more interested in what you can do for me. I have heard that a wealthy, well connected person might peruse some of the more... interesting wares?~
@10850 = ~[PC] You have to be joking. He gives you a copper piece for each of these pieces of flimsy wood pulp you hand out? Is it really worth your time?~
@10851 = ~[PC] So, where is this mercenary?~
@10852 = ~[C-AW01TK] At a copper per broadside given to new customers, I will not gain much. Still, anything that provides a profit, no matter how small, is worth pursuing. In addition, he is running up quite a bar tab, and getting him employed might mean I get some return on my loans to him.~
@10853 = ~[PC] So... you loan out money? Any chance I could get one of these loans?~
@10854 = ~[C-AW01TK] Where he always seems to be. Standing at the bar, with my ale running down his throat and my barmaid trading insults with him. Wait... no, he seems to have stepped to the back. Try the center room. There are usually some dice or card games progressing there.~
@10855 = ~[C-AW01TK] No, I am afraid I am not in a position to help you. I am sure there are others who can do so, but my own ventures have me stretched rather thin right now. Besides, twenty percent is more interest than most are willing to pay.~
@10856 = ~[PC] I am still interested. Is there nothing I can do to persuade you?~
@10857 = ~[C-AW01TK] Nothing can sway me, I assure you. I have already tied up any capital I might have. But I do hope you find Whitehand useful. Perhaps he will be able to repay me after some successful adventuring in your company.~
@10858 = ~[C-AW01TK] My esteem, and of course permanent access to some of my grander wares, hidden from view of those with little coin. Perhaps even a single jewel, from among my minor wares. It is a small enough task, but as I must get this done immediately I am willing to be magnanimous.~
@10859 = ~[C-AW01TK] Paperwork. The costs of doing business in this fair city do not rest solely with Linvale's tithes and the common bribes to Cowled Enforcers and the Flaming Fist goons. Unfortunately, legitimate businesses have the registry. And since my usual messenger has suddenly become available in a way not favorable to good business, of course the first punishment I receive is an audit.~
@10860 = ~[PC] I think we can help you accomplish this.~
@10861 = ~[PC] No. I am not interested~
@10862 = ~[PC] Do you really expect me to believe you would send an entire adventuring party to deliver paperwork?~
@10863 = ~[C-AW01TK] With the problems and challenges facing this city, I am certain that I wish to ensure safe delivery. I have enough troubles with Linvail right now that I do not wish to antagonize anyone else. It is obvious that the audit I face is a punishment arranged for me, and I wish it to be over without delay or any hint of noncompliance. This is truly a simple delivery, for legitimate business. If you do not wish to help, I will pay the same to the Flaming Fist to have the delivery made.~
@10864 = ~[C-AW01TK] So, will you accept this small task, and gain my esteem and admiration?~
@10865 = ~[C-AW01TK] I thank you, and my business thanks you.~
@10866 = ~[C-AW01TK] Ah, I apologize for thinking you would entertain such a menial task. I am afraid the work is time sensitive, so I will find another who can accomplish it. No matter.~
@10867 = ~[C-AW01TK] I can but guess at the troubles that you faced in such an insurmountable task. I shall remain forever in your debt. But my rewards are not negotiable.~
@10868 = ~[C-AW01TK] My thanks for this. I shall remember your kindness, and of course reward your efforts.~
@10869 = ~[C-AW01TK] Of course. Oh my... I seem to have just found a few gems lying about, lonely and unclaimed... I shall go over there and help some customers.~
@10870 = ~[C-AW01TK] This is awkward. I do not ordinarily serve those who break contracts. Teldra is my biggest source of income, and she has indicated she feels you have broken your word. Ordinarily, I would simply refuse to serve you.~
@10871 = ~[C-AW01TK] Unfortunately, I did make a contract with you, if only a paltry one. And I do not break my word. So, grudgingly, I will honor my contract.~
@10872 = ~[C-AW01TK] Ah, I  must not have made myself clear. Teldra contracts mercenaries. Therefore, mercenaries come here, and they spend coin. They trade for gems and jewelry. They talk to each other, and they drink. If Teldra goes away, most of my business follows her.~
@10873 = ~[C-AW01TK] In addition, I have a reputation to maintain. I serve Blue Boar and Blacktalon equally, under the bond that says 'a contract is a contract - nothing personal'. That only works when everyone knows there is a single golden rule... don't break a contract.~
@10874 = ~[C-AW01TK] Rumor has it that you break contracts. So, I am afraid that you have become persona non grata here. I am sure you can find another establishment to frequent. Do have a nice day.~
@10875 = ~[C-AW01TK] I am sure you can find some place more suited to your kind. Your abrupt departure would be appreciated.~
@10876 = ~[ARAN] Now, to be fair, there have been a few o' these what turned out to be true adventures, eh? Just not this one.~
@10877 = ~[JAHEIRA] We waste time with such diversions.~
@10878 = ~[KELDORN] It is hardly an intrusion. A small task, helping a citizen deal with the governance of this city. The Council rules as they will, and everyone knows this. We can show honor in even minor matters, if we treat the task with respect.~
@10879 = ~[KORGAN] Well, the pay best be bloody well worth it, if I'm to be wandering through the wilderness, hacking away at bears and squirrels and other such beasties.~
@10880 = ~[AERIE] I... I am not sure any of them have turned out to be so simple.~
@10881 = ~[MAZZY] Arvoreen will reward us for our patience. I do think there are more important matters to attend to, though.~
@10882 = ~[EDWIN] You must be a mad<PRO_MANWOMAN>! Is this all that we are to be used for, now?  Some minor errand?~
@10883 = ~[ANOMEN] There must be more noble tasks than acting as couriers for minor townspeople. It would be well for the opportunity to present itself immediately.~
@10884 = ~[YOSHIMO] One takes what opportunities are presented.~
@10885 = ~[JAN] Speaking of opportunities, have I told you about my Uncle Roderick? He was a messenger for years. He finally retired when the cost of Raise Dead spells outweighed his yearly profits.~
@10886 = ~[VICONIA] Doesn't it seem simpler, easier in flavor?  There were less entanglements, far less chaos.  We aren't always exploring some dank, ruined place.~
@10887 = ~[HAERDALIS] Ah, but true adventures require the flight of fancy, the excitement of risk.~
@10888 = ~[NALIA] Look at it this way: perhaps it is just the gods' way of telling you that there are far more people who need assistance in minor ways than in major ways, yes?~
@10889 = ~[C-AW01TK] You do seem to be a talkative lot. But I appreciate your attention to this small matter.~
@10890 = ~[ARAN] I should have guessed Orrin would be payin' off usin' stock. His business has not been that solid lately, on account o' all th' hirin' out. Everyone comes in tradin' for coin, then spendin' it on gear an' such elsewhere.~
@10891 = ~[EDWIN] (mutter) Should have left the lot of you log ago.~
@10892 = ~[HAERDALIS] The reward is not as interesting as the task, my sparrows... or, perhaps it is.~
@10893 = ~[JAHEIRA] I told you we were wasting our time with minor distractions.~
@10894 = ~[JAN] Ah, jewels and gems. My Cousin Gardenia had a soft spot for all things sparkley and shiny. When her husband Oneshoe passed away, she showed up at his funeral destitute. The family asked where all of their money had gone, and she gave an accounting... 50 gold for the funeral, 200 gold for the mourners, 500 gold to the Temple, and 20,000 gold for the memorial stone. We all asked, of course, how large a 20,000 gold piece memorial stone was.~
@10895 = ~[JAN] Her reply was to show her left hand, and say 'Five carats'.~
@10896 = ~[KELDORN] We need no reward, and I would not accept.  <CHARNAME>, however, leads this party.~
@10897 = ~[KORGAN] Aye, now, there it is.  There be no profit it in these scrawny innkeepers. At least they serve ale.~
@10898 = ~[NALIA] It's not a matter of what he has to offer, but what we should offer his kind. I am sure he simply does not have the resources to give more. Helping the less fortunate is worth a little walk.~
@10899 = ~[VICONIA] It would not be adequate regardless. I suspect magical torture would make him much more forthcoming.~
@10900 = ~[ANOMEN] Then enough talk. Go! Let us travel onward, for my patience is at an end.~
@10901 = ~[PC] Well, a simple quest gets a simple reward.~
@10902 = ~[PC] Orrin owes me access to his best items now. A quick favor, with a good return on the investment.~
@10903 = ~[PC] The standard letdown. I drag myself around Faerun doing odd little favors here and there, for little or no reward. I need a drink.~
@10904 = ~[PC] Perhaps I shall teach Orrin a lesson. No one turns me into a messenger and then drops a paltry gem and vague promises. I expected hard, cold coin, and a good deal of it.~
@10905 = ~[PC] Coin and a few gems, for walking back and forth with a package? I was lucky to get a coin or two for fetching Hull's sword for him back in Candlekeep. I think I have come up in the world.~
@10906 = ~[ARAN] I did no such thing, you stuck-up ol' bugger!~
@10907 = ~[C-AW01TK] Really? Ah, you are correct, of course. You could not spell 'supercilious', let alone say it. My error, I do so apologize.~
@10908 = ~[ARAN] No worries. It is tough for you, after all, stuck in this place all day, wi' no hope o' adventure. Makes a sorry life, eh?~
@10909 = ~[C-AW01TK] I shall endeavor to live vicariously through your heroic efforts, of course. By the way, you still have not made your latest payment...~
@10910 = ~[ARAN] Oh, blighted... right. I will get that to you by th' end o' th' tenday.~
@10911 = ~[C-AW01TK] You have Whitehand along, which makes it unlikely you would successfully make it past two orcs and a kobold. Do I need to say more?~
@10912 = ~[ARAN] Grumbar's Clay Fists, that be right mean! I say bugger off, you blighted ol' jackass!~
@10913 = ~[C-AW01TK] Now, now... it was a jest. Seriously, I hesitated to suggest the menial messenger task, but I need to get this done immediately. And despite our verbal acrimony, Whitehand can be trusted. therefore, you probably can be trusted.~
@10914 = ~[C-AW01TK] Perhaps you are looking to settle Whitehand's accounts?~
@10915 = ~[ARAN] Now, I done settled wi' you clean an' fair, Orrin. Don't be playin' any games wi' my employers, eh?~
@10916 = ~[C-AW01TK] Why, so you did. Well, you can't blame me for trying, of course. It is all part of the job.~
@10917 = ~[C-AW01TK] I see that you have been unable to remove Aran's presence from your company. Perhaps I can interest you in a wide assortment of mercenary-be-gone amulets?~
@10918 = ~[ARAN] Oh, funny, you jewel of a man. Just remember who knows what an' how, eh?~
@10919 = ~[C-AW01TK] Of course. I do so enjoy our little sparring, Whitehand.~
@10920 = ~[C-AW01TK] By now, I am sure the esteemed mercenary Whitehand has appraised you of my interest in any jewels or jewelry that you might come across in your travels...~
@10921 = ~[ARAN] Actually, you told me to keep my fat mouth shut, an' I did. So who be th' blabbermouth now, eh?~
@10922 = ~[C-AW01TK] My, I am astounded. Well, no matter. I am a collector, of course. So if anything does happen to cross your path, I would be very interested.~
@10923 = ~[C-AW01TK] I see that you have not yet succumbed to the inevitable death and destruction inherent in your profession, Aran.~
@10924 = ~[ARAN] Well, I wouldn't exactly say that, now. But it be true I haven't taken up no permanent job pushin' up flowers from underneath, so to speak.~
@10925 = ~[C-AW01TK] It is a blessing and a pearl that you have not yet been torn from our presence and sent along the Great Wheel.~
@10926 = ~[C-AW01TK] And Aran, I do have a letter for you. One straight from Waterdeep, I might add. It is yours for only four iron crescents.~
@10927 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. It came paid, on account o' she never sends anythin' unpaid. But here be a crescent for your troubles.~
@10928 = ~[C-AW01TK] Why, so it did. It must have slipped my mind. Your letter, sir. Do you require my literary services to decrypt the contents? I am not sure that you can actually read.~
@10929 = ~[ARAN] Funny, there. On account o' you had me run up two sets o' books for you, an' get that contract work all squared away. But you'd forget your arse, if it weren't stuck right on your face permanent-like.~
@10930 = ~[C-AW01TK] Ah, <CHARNAME>... well met. Aran, given our longstanding friendship and good relations...~
@10931 = ~[ARAN] Cut the bullshit an' stop lyin' through your nose, you soddy ol' bastard. What do you be wantin'?~
@10932 = ~[C-AW01TK] As gracefully eloquent as ever, I see. Actually, I would say this is so meager a request that only you need to be present, but perhaps your adventuring party might enjoy a small walk in the fresh air.~
@10933 = ~[ARAN] Your regular messenger get sick?~
@10934 = ~[C-AW01TK] In a manner of speaking. Apparently he developed sticky palms, and Linvail had them cured.~
@10935 = ~[ARAN] That were nice o' him. Do we now call th' lad Righty, or Lefty?~
@10936 = ~[C-AW01TK] I am afraid we call him Dusty.~
@10937 = ~[ARAN] Oh, now, that changes things a mite. Nothin' like goin' straight to the heart o' the matter.~
@10938 = ~[C-AW01TK] In this case, I am afraid Linvail felt this was a matter of head rather than heart.~
@10939 = ~[ARAN] Nothin' messes up your day more than losin' your head, that be for sure. So, you need somethin' delivered?~
@10940 = ~[C-AW01TK] Yes, and I am ashamed to say it is even a legitimate delivery, one to the Government District. A small package, delivered to Corneil at the Council Building.~
@10941 = ~[PC] What is the reward?~
@10942 = ~[PC] I suppose there will be trouble, and we will get into a fight, and nothing will be as it appears...~
@10943 = ~[PC] This is a small enough task. I think we can help you.~
@10944 = ~[PC] No thank you. I have had my fill of wandering Faerun as an itinerant errand<PRO_GIRLBOY>.~
@10945 = ~[PC] What is in the package?~
@10946 = ~[C-AW01TK] And Aran, you look as... distinctive, I would say, as the day I met you.~
@10947 = ~[ARAN] An' you are th' same ol' slick bastard what emptied my purse an' delivered me up to Teldra wi' a smile an' bow, eh?~
@10948 = ~[C-AW01TK] Just business, of course. And you have prospered, from what I can see.~
@10949 = ~[C-AW01TK] You seem as aware as you usually are, Aran. I do hope the cooking experiments are more successful now?~
@10950 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly hear no complaints.~
@10951 = ~[C-AW01TK] You must be traveling with such polite companions, then. I feel sure that they will appreciate a well cooked meal from this fair establishment.~
@10952 = ~[C-AW01TL] Greetings and a pearl to you. If you come to me seeking sellswords and mercenaries looking for contracts both long and short, you have come to the right place.~
@10953 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking to be employed myself. Is there any short term work available?~
@10954 = ~[PC] I just thought you were the barmaid. Do you work here?~
@10955 = ~[PC] Is business good right now?~
@10956 = ~[PC] I was admiring the curve of your breastplate.~
@10957 = ~[PC] You are very pretty, in a "cross-me-and-I-will-kill-you" kind of way.~
@10958 = ~[PC] I was thinking perhaps you might be up for some fun, clothing optional.~
@10959 = ~[PC] Do you have any good prospects to assist an adventuring party?~
@10960 = ~[PC] I might be interested in hiring some help. Orrin, the tavernkeeper over there, mentioned a sellsword who can read and write. Where can I find him?~
@10961 = ~[PC] I am afraid Aran is no longer among the living.~
@10962 = ~[PC] Have you talked to Aran lately? I am looking for him.~
@10963 = ~[PC] Do you have any other good prospects to assist an adventuring party?~
@10964 = ~[PC] What do you think of this Aran Whitehand I have heard so much about?~
@10965 = ~[C-AW01TL] Greetings and a pearl to you. Sellswords, mercenaries, contracts both long and short. You have come to the right place.~
@10966 = ~[PC] Do you know of any weapons trainers, or jewelers?~
@10967 = ~[C-AW01TL] Back again, I see. Greetings and a pearl to you. Mercenary contracts long and short, that's my business. Might be yours, too, if anything becomes available.~
@10968 = ~[C-AW01TL] Greetings and a pearl to you, <CHARNAME>. What brings you back to me?~
@10969 = ~[PC] Actually, I was looking to be employed. Is there any short term work available?~
@10970 = ~[C-AW01TL] Well, you sure know how to compliment a woman.~
@10971 = ~[PC] Are you related to the barmaid?~
@10972 = ~[PC] It has been nice meeting you, but we should get going.~
@10973 = ~[PC] Sticking around here sounds about as exciting as reading Volo's works on the Dung Beetles of Neverwinter. Why don't you step out and adventure yourself?~
@10974 = ~[PC] Sticking around here sounds about as exciting as shoveling out a stable. Why don't you step out and adventure yourself?~
@10975 = ~[PC] Sticking around here sounds about as exciting as watching kobolds mate. Why don't you step out and adventure yourself?~
@10976 = ~[PC] Sticking around here sounds about as exciting as watching for a Masked Lady of Waterdeep to show her face. Why don't you step out and adventure yourself?~
@10977 = ~[PC] Perhaps I will be back to talk to you later.~
@10978 = ~[C-AW01TL] So, what can I do for you?~
@10979 = ~[PC] You know, you are dazzlingly beautiful, in a raw, rough kind of way.~
@10980 = ~[C-AW01TL] Erika? No. No relation. Why?~
@10981 = ~[PC] You both seem to have very similar reactions to Aran, here.~
@10982 = ~[PC] You are both dazzlingly beautiful.~
@10983 = ~[PC] I was wondering if she had any suitors. She seems very interesting.~
@10984 = ~[PC] Usually when I wander around talking to random strangers, they have some important piece of news to impart. But all she does is take my drink order.~
@10985 = ~[PC] Oh, no reason.~
@10986 = ~[C-AW01TL] Proactive self defense. Aran here thinks "hey, will you pass me that drink" means "I want you to make sweet love to me". To be fair, most mercenaries around here think that, male or female.~
@10987 = ~[PC] So he is unreliable?~
@10988 = ~[PC] I think I will pass. I don't need that kind of person around making life difficult.~
@10989 = ~[PC] Interesting information. I will see you later.~
@10990 = ~[C-AW01TL] Unfortunately, not right now. The last group headed out Dalewards, headed for reinforcement of some campaign or other. Tethyr just closed out recruitment for some squabbles they are having, The 'Fist has their hands full re-training what they already have for guard duty and caravan protection, and you don't look like the Mindgulph's type. Blue Boars... perhaps.~
@10991 = ~[C-AW01TL] I will keep my ears open for anything available, though. Odd things pop up from time to time, and it might be beneficial to both of us to have some problems solved on a lesser contract. Not every problem needs swatting with a batillion of armed regulars.~
@10992 = ~[C-AW01TL] Not really. There are few recruitable people left to enroll. Every day we get more mercenary work, what with uprisings and rebellions and needed protection. Whole armies are on the march, and no one is completely sure why.~
@10993 = ~[C-AW01TL] But in spite of all the action, there is little available save shipping mercenaries off on three or four year contracts. No real short-term or specialized work available, really.~
@10994 = ~[PC] But I will make a great candidate for any work the regular companies can't or won't take, right?~
@10995 = ~[PC] At least you have a full purse now.~
@10996 = ~[PC] I thought there could never be too much business.~
@10997 = ~[PC] Well, perhaps you will have to turn to prostitution. I could be your trial run, if you wanted.~
@10998 = ~[PC] Well, it is good talking to you. I will see you later.~
@10999 = ~[PC] Do you mind if I ask you a question?~
@11000 = ~[C-AW01TL] I do have a good prospect for you, if you need someone who can fight and keep an accounting ledger.~
@11001 = ~[PC] I already have Kelsey here to keep the books, and while he can't fight very well he is a strong enough spellcaster.~
@11002 = ~[PC] You actually have something of use to me? I just thought you were another barmaid.~
@11003 = ~[PC] I might be interested in hiring some help. Where can I find this sellsword?~
@11004 = ~[PC] What can you tell me about this sellsword?~
@11005 = ~[C-AW01TL] Take a look in the room just north of here. North is that way, by the way. Well, unless one of those Cowled Wizards has been hassling someone over a 'deviant act', as they call it, and messed up the compass directions again. I guess Amn feels madmen are the best keepers of madmen.~
@11006 = ~[PC] Hey, what do you think about him? You know, the sellsword?~
@11007 = ~[PC] Thanks for the help.~
@11008 = ~[PC] What do you know about the Cowled Wizards?~
@11009 = ~[C-AW01TL] I live to serve. Well, actually, that is complete bullshit, but you look like a person who might be either a client or an employee someday, so it never hurts to put a little shine on, right?~
@11010 = ~[PC] Employee, I bet. You look like the kind of impossibly attractive lady who lives to send people like me out to get all bruised and battered while you sit there drinking and counting your profit.~
@11011 = ~[PC] Client, I bet. You look like the kind of dashing stranger I would hire to clean my boots.~
@11012 = ~[PC] What do you think about Aran Whitehand? Just the high points.~
@11013 = ~[PC] Sure. I will be moving along, now.~
@11014 = ~[C-AW01TL] Good man in a fight. Can read and write in more than one language, though he speaks common like the most illiterate trades-way bastard I ever did hear. Translates, too. Done service in at least two mercenary companies; I think he grew up in a trading family. Thinks he's a gift from the gods to every woman, and tries to prove it. He has a room here, second door on your left.~
@11015 = ~[PC] Is he reliable?~
@11016 = ~[PC] Is he cute?~
@11017 = ~[PC] Where was his room again?~
@11018 = ~[PC] How much do I owe you for the information?~
@11019 = ~[PC]...gift from the gods to every woman... Should I be worried?~
@11020 = ~[PC] He doesn't sound useful enough to me. Anyone else? Or anything I can do to get some coin?~
@11021 = ~[C-AW01TL] Any other questions?~
@11022 = ~[PC] Seriously... is he reliable?~
@11023 = ~[PC] No more questions.~
@11024 = ~[PC] His interest in women... Should I be worried?~
@11025 = ~[C-AW01TL] Well, regardless, Aran can be a good man in a fight. He can read and write in more than one language, though he speaks common like the most illiterate trades-way bastard I ever did hear. Translates, too. Done service in at least two mercenary companies; I think he grew up in a trading family. Thinks he's a gift from the gods to every woman, and tries to prove it. He has a room here, second door on your left.~
@11026 = ~[C-AW01TL] You obviously missed some of his better works. His treatise on campaign tactics and the influence of gibberling horde movement on supply rerouting was quite interesting. Not bad, for a civilian writer.~
@11027 = ~[C-AW01TL] The only difference between mercenary work and cleaning out stables is where the dung lands. Most of the time, stable work is removing it after the fact. Mercenaries, on the other hand, tend to be more directly under the source as it is expelled.~
@11028 = ~[C-AW01TL] Why, do you make a habit of watching kobolds mate? I guess everyone has a guilty pleasure.~
@11029 = ~[C-AW01TL] I worked for a Masked Lord once. Fair contract. Good man. Good pay. So back off on them, or we might have some problems, you and I.~
@11030 = ~[C-AW01TL] Now, is there anything else, or can I get back to fleecing these poor lads out of all their gambling money?~
@11031 = ~[PC] Nothing else. I think I'll come back later.~
@11032 = ~[PC] Is there any short term work available at all? I am short on funds, and looking for pretty much any work, as long as it pays.~
@11033 = ~[PC] I just thought you were the barmaid. Do you run the gambling here, as well?~
@11034 = ~[PC] Fleece, fleece, by all means. I didn't mean to interrupt your work.~
@11035 = ~[C-AW01TL] Anything else? The cards are getting lonely, and I need to comfort them. Not that they are running in my favor right now, but it is the principle of the thing.~
@11036 = ~[PC] I have some skill at cards. And even some skill at table-talk.~
@11037 = ~[C-AW01TL] Anything else you want to ask? Not much in this hand, anyways, I think. Ah, well... it is only a few coins.~
@11038 = ~[C-AW01TL] Anything else I can do for you?~
@11039 = ~[PC] Not really. But you look like you are setting up for a card game, and I would not mind sitting in.~
@11040 = ~[C-AW01TL] Any more questions?~
@11041 = ~[PC] Not really. But I would not mind hearing about what is going on around Amn.~
@11042 = ~[C-AW01TL] So, anything else?~
@11043 = ~[PC] I was hoping we could share stories, trade information. I think we could both benefit.~
@11044 = ~[C-AW01TL] Well, pull up a chair and rest a bit. No work right now, so there is little enough to do, and I bet you could tell me some great stories... that would distract them from their cards.~
@11045 = ~[PC] Aren't you going to take my drink order?~
@11046 = ~[PC] I was admiring the curve of your breastplate. I especially like the lack of appropriate protection from slashing attacks.~
@11047 = ~[PC] Look, Teldra, I don't know how to say this... but perhaps we could go some place more private?~
@11048 = ~[PC] I am the conquering all-powerful <CHARNAME>. I have come for your soul.~
@11049 = ~[PC] I will talk if you buy the drinks.~
@11050 = ~[PC] I was hoping you could swap a story or two.~
@11051 = ~[PC] On second thought, some other time, perhaps.~
@11052 = ~[C-AW01TL] Well, then, pull up a chair.~
@11053 = ~[PC] Look, Teldra... perhaps we could go some place more private?~
@11054 = ~[PC] I was hoping you could swap a story or two. Who goes first?~
@11055 = ~[C-AW01TL] Heh. What soul? I sold that for a few iron tradebars when I was fourteen. Now, if you have come for my body, buy me a drink and we will get down to some serious negotiation.~
@11056 = ~[PC] Soul, body... whatever gets you into my bed, or me into yours.~
@11057 = ~[PC] Why, Teldra, I am surprised. Why so forward?~
@11058 = ~[PC] You said there is no work at all? I really need some coin.~
@11059 = ~[PC] I... I am not comfortable with this. We should keep things friendly, but not too friendly.~
@11060 = ~[C-AW01TL] Now, what you really need is a good stiff drink, sitting here swapping combat stories, and forgetting your troubles for a time. We all need that.~
@11061 = ~[PC] I don't have the time. There are so many things to do, monsters to slay, opponents to loot... I don't even have time for a drink.~
@11062 = ~[PC] Why are you leaning forward like that? I can see right down your cleavage, you know.~
@11063 = ~[PC] You may. I don't.~
@11064 = ~[PC] Have you ever thought of joining me? Adventuring with me?~
@11065 = ~[C-AW01TL] Hey, if you have it, flaunt it, I always say. I can't tell you how many times some poor sod is on the fence about signing on, and all it takes is a judicious leaning forward and a slight wardrobe malfunction, and I have met my quota.~
@11066 = ~[PC] You don't have that much to flaunt, you know.~
@11067 = ~[PC] Well, about that drink, and that negotiation...~
@11068 = ~[PC] Huh. I heard you were both easy and cheap, but luring poor innocent farmers into becoming fodder for mercenary companies is just a little over the top.~
@11069 = ~[C-AW01TL] Says you, sister. Besides, it isn't how much you have, it is how much you 'accidentally' show. No one can resists the allure and mystery of the forbidden fruit, whether it is a peach or a melon.~
@11070 = ~[PC] I'll drink to that. Though I will resist your allure, I'm sure.~
@11071 = ~[PC] That is a big change in attitude. One would think you were trying to tempt me.~
@11072 = ~[PC] We should keep things friendly. No need to muddle business and pleasure.~
@11073 = ~[C-AW01TL] Says you, boyo. Your eyes keep wandering down that way whether you realize it or not. Besides, it isn't how much you have, it is how much you 'accidentally' show. No one can resists the allure and mystery of the forbidden fruit, whether it is a peach or a melon.~
@11074 = ~[C-AW01TL] Look, I am not easy, and I am not cheap, but I like powerful, effective people. And I look at you, and what is there not to like? So shall we negotiate, or shall we go upstairs and screw like wild rabbits?~
@11075 = ~[PC] I was thinking of leisurely romance, a bottle of wine, the long slow teasing and sultry looks.~
@11076 = ~[PC] Wild rabbits it is.~
@11077 = ~[PC] I don't have the time right now, but I would love to have this conversation another time.~
@11078 = ~[PC] Huh. I heard you were both easy and cheap.~
@11079 = ~[C-AW01TL] What can I say. You may have won me over, and when I see what I want, I go for it.~
@11080 = ~[PC] Bedding like wild rabbits it is.~
@11081 = ~[PC] I don't have the time right now, but I would love to have this conversation later.~
@11082 = ~[C-AW01TL] I don't put up with unreliable. Whitehand is reliable, remarkably flexible, and can do the job. You just have to watch him when it comes to fraternization with females, be they mercenaries, townsfolk, waitstaff, geese, ducks, pigs...~
@11083 = ~[C-AW01TL] You look like you are gathering an adventuring party. I can tell by the slightly haunted look in your eyes, you appearing in a sudden explosion on the Promanade, and all the screaming and yelling that accompanied that particular event.~
@11084 = ~[C-AW01TL] Reliable? Yes. Predictable? Mostly. Annoying? At times. Useful? Yes.~
@11085 = ~[C-AW01TL] If you like that sort of thing, sure. A bit rough around the edges, but if you tell him to keep his hands to himself and check in with him from time to time, and you won't have any problems.~
@11086 = ~[C-AW01TL] Are you sure you are interested in a sellsword? I can recommend a decent healer for your deafness problem, or perhaps removal of the feeblemind spell you seem to be under. Go out the way you came in, turn north, look to your left, and there will be a big brown wooden thing we like to call a "door". You look for the funny brass thing halfway down the left hand side, grab hold of it, and it will make the big brown wooden thing open. He's in there.~
@11087 = ~[C-AW01TL] If you like that sort of thing, sure. But like I said, he likes the ladies a fair sight better than he should. If you are looking for a little romance on the trail, keep dreaming. That's about all you are going to get to do.~
@11088 = ~[C-AW01TL] Nothing. He's Fighters Guild, but freelance. Any work he gets from me, I take a percentage from his cut. Any work he gets freelace, he pays his dues, so it is covered. He owes me some money, so getting him employed is in my best interests.~
@11089 = ~[C-AW01TL] Look, I don't know where you hail from, but around here barmaids don't have scars like these, or equipment like this.~
@11090 = ~[C-AW01TL] The nice thing about looking like this is idiots walk right up within sword range and leer at me, which gives me just enough room to put them out of my misery~
@11091 = ~[C-AW01TL] The swordbelt should have given it away. Or the duelling scar. Or the fact that I am NOT SERVING DRINKS.~
@11092 = ~[C-AW01TL] Keep dreaming. That's about all you are going to get to do.~
@11093 = ~[C-AW01TL] And you are very alluring yourself, in an "I-am-so-desparate-I-will-proposition-anything-that-moves" kind of way. Go tell it to the 'Fist. I hear some of their recruits are so horny they will sleep with Chill.~
@11094 = ~[C-AW01TL] Sure thing. You go find us a nice room, strip naked, and tie yourself to the bedpost. I'll be in just as soon as I can. Oh, wait... I made a promise to myself to avoid sleeping with obnoxious idiots. Sorry.~
@11095 = ~[C-AW01TL] Sure enough. It never rains without a benefit to someone. Lucky you. Except...~
@11096 = ~[C-AW01TL] Look. You seem to have plenty going on as it is. My employers are not likey to hire someone who causes trouble. Like being involved with mages blowing the crap out of the Promenade. You pobably should look elsewhere for work.~
@11097 = ~[C-AW01TL] For now, yes. And with all the movement, there will be plenty of accounts to manage and enough to keep me going for quite some time. But these things are cyclical. Eventually, I am going to be sitting here keeping dozens of out of work mercenaries entertained and occupied, so that they don't tear half of Amn apart out of sheer boredom and cussedness.~
@11098 = ~[C-AW01TL] Supply and demand, m'<PRO_BOYGIRL>, supply and demand. It is great to have strong demand, but when it outstrips supply, I end up on the pointy end of the spear. So far, that last has been only a figure of speech, because I don't subcontract Chill work. Best decision of my life.~
@11099 = ~[C-AW01TL] Hey, what a great idea. I have an even better one. You bend over, and I'll go find something large and spiky to ram up your rear.~
@11100 = ~[C-AW01TL] Friend, the less you know the better. I know they have a tight grip on magic use, and getting permits from them is worse than trying to get blood from a stone. They don't like me much. The feeling is mutual.~
@11101 = ~[C-AW01TL] Well, suit yourself. I am not planning on going anywhere, so I will keep a spot warm for you.~
@11102 = ~[C-AW01TL] Drop by any time. I will be right here. I might even be sober.~
@11103 = ~[C-AW01TL] You have the wrong woman for that. I favor complete discretion, quick negotiation, a thorough examination of the physical goods, a detailed exploration of skills and sevices, and rapid conclusion of the contract to the mutual pleasure of both parties. Oh, and a no-fault clause... I don't sign up for long term comittments.~
@11104 = ~[C-AW01TL] Good. I favor complete discretion, quick negotiation, a thorough examination of the physical goods, a detailed exploration of skills and sevices, and rapid conclusion of the contract to the mutual pleasure of both parties. Oh, and a no-fault clause... I don't sign up for long term comittments.~
@11105 = ~[C-AW01TL] For a brief tumble in the bedchamber? Yes. And now that you are not likely to be a client of mine in the near future, the thought keeps occurring to me. But joining you as an adventurer, no. I have a good position here, and a good life.~
@11106 = ~[C-AW01TL] Fine by me. For the record, though, I favor complete discretion, quick negotiation, a thorough examination of the physical goods, a detailed exploration of skills and sevices, and rapid conclusion of the contract to the mutual pleasure of both parties. Oh, and a no-fault clause... I don't sign up for long term comittments.~
@11107 = ~[C-AW01TL] Well, if you are going to joke about it, forget it. You are cute, but I don't like attitude in the bedroom. Unless it is "yes, please, may I have another?".~
@11108 = ~[C-AW01TL] Well, if you are going to be that way, forget the whole flirting business. You are cute, but I don't like attitude in the bedroom. Unless it is "yes, please, may I have another?".~
@11109 = ~[C-AW01TL] You just sit here, and the first round is on me. I'll tell you about the time I had a contract dispute between the Steels and the Mindgulphs, and had to hire the Blue Boars to keep the peace while we sorted it all out.~
@11110 = ~[C-AW01TL] You just sit here, and the first round is on me. So, tell me... what is it like to be one of the most powerful forces on the face of Toril?~
@11111 = ~[C-AW01TL] You just sit here, and the first round is on me. So, tell me... what do you know about the Harpers?~
@11112 = ~[C-AW01TL] You just sit here, and the first round is on me. So, tell me... is it true that there is a secret entrance to Candlekeep?~
@11113 = ~[C-AW01TL] Me? Joining you as an adventurer? No. I have a good position here, and a good life.~
@11114 = ~[C-AW01TL] She doesn't get out much.~
@11115 = ~[C-AW01TL] I think I like you, smartass. Come talk to me sometime.~
@11116 = ~[C-AW01TL] Fine by me.~
@11117 = ~[C-AW01TL] Occupational hazard. But if you tell me where his body is, I'll pass it on to his family.~
@11118 = ~[C-AW01TL] He is definitely around here somewhere. He seems to have enough coin to get himself in trouble, but not enough to leave.~
@11119 = ~[C-AW01TL] Aran sure looks mostly dead, there. He doesn't have revivification insurance, if you are after some coin to get him raised. But I'll donate a few tradebars, if you are taking up a collection.~
@11120 = ~[C-AW01TL] Gerald the Strong? Don't pay him any attention. He has been upset ever since he found out his last contract badmouthed him to the guild. Apparently he was prone to demonstrating his strength, and the repair bills were too high. He will be fine, once he sobers up a bit.~
@11121 = ~[C-AW01TL] Cheris Nothar, or Nothrar, or something. Between the tusks and the accent, I never can make out what she is saying. She is a good fighter, though a bit young and prone to outbursts. She is resting up for her next contract. I think it is intelligence work for the Mindgulph. I don't know why they don't subcontract to the Thieve's Guild.~
@11122 = ~[C-AW01TL] Kavain? He is under contract, and not happy about the whole thing. But he has to do the job. I told him it was a bad idea signing up for an employer without checking who they really work for. I hope he can square things with his god, or there will be some serious repercussions.~
@11123 = ~[C-AW01TL] I know Orrin, the owner of this place, does trading in gems and jewelry. I have heard he even has decent stock if you have lots of coin, or do him a favor or two. But as for weapons trainers, not really. Unless you count Aran.~
@11124 = ~[C-AW01TL] I make a decent living coordinating hires for mercenaries, nothing else. If you want a matchmaker, find someone else.~
@11125 = ~[C-AW01TL] Gods, another one. Look, boyo, you are kind of cute, but business is business. Keep all that sweet talk for the next drunken half-orc female who wanders by. Now, on the subject of business...~
@11126 = ~[C-AW01TL] Gods, a female Aran. Look, you are kind of cute, and I am very.... flexible, in all the right ways... but business is business. Keep all that sweet talk for the next drunken half-orc who wanders by. Now, on the subject of business...~
@11127 = ~[C-AW01TL] Aran sure looks worse for the wear, there. I hope that heals up nicely. Hells, I hope it heals, period.~
@11128 = ~[C-AW01TL] So, what brings you back to me?~
@11129 = ~[C-AW01TL] That being said, I'll see you upstairs. Drink up... I intend to find out just how much endurance you have!~
@11130 = ~[ARAN] Ho, Teldra. I think you do get prettier every time I see you.~
@11131 = ~[C-AW01TL] Pity I can't say the same about you.~
@11132 = ~[ARAN] Meaner, too.~
@11133 = ~[C-AW01TL] Oh, I didn't see you there, Aran. Wipe that stupid grin off your face and tell me what is troubling you, and therefore me.~
@11134 = ~[ARAN] This be th' smartest grin I know.~
@11135 = ~[C-AW01TL] That figures. Looking for a contract?~
@11136 = ~[ARAN] Got one. But mayhap <CHARNAME> here might be lookin' for somethin' short term.~
@11137 = ~[C-AW01TL] For you, Aran, I could find something, if you get kicked out of your current contract with <CHARNAME>. I hear there is a need for stable hands.~
@11138 = ~[ARAN] Hey, I do be callin' foul, pun intended! I never did hear any complaints from you.~
@11139 = ~[C-AW01TL] I have low standards.~
@11140 = ~[C-AW01TL] You know, you say that almost every time you greet me.~
@11141 = ~[ARAN] And it be true every time.~
@11142 = ~[C-AW01TL] You are so full of horsedung.~
@11143 = ~[ARAN] Any work for me? I mean, do there be any work for us?~
@11144 = ~[C-AW01TL] Not really. But I have no place else to be, if you want to talk a bit.~
@11145 = ~[C-AW01TL] Worried? Personally? Oh, no, nothing like that. He minds his business, just not his manners. Tell him what you want, talk to him, and if necessary lay down some ground rules. But he knows no means no.~
@11146 = ~[ARAN] You two know I be standin' right here, eh?~
@11147 = ~[C-AW01TL] Be a good lad and shut the hells up when we are negotiating contract, Aran. Make yourself useful and take notes.~
@11148 = ~[ARAN] Ma'am, yes ma'am.~
@11149 = ~[C-TORAN] Hey, don't poke me... I don't want any trouble.~
@11150 = ~[C-TORAN] Worst deal I even made. I'll move over here, out of the way.~
@11151 = ~[C-TORAN] No problem here. I  will keep my mouth shut.~
@11152 = ~[C-TORAN] Just drinking my wages, same as always.~
@11153 = ~[C-TORAN] Every time I get a contract finished, I say I am going to quit and invest the money. Then I come here, and all I invest in is more drink.~
@11154 = ~[C-TORAN] Too many contracts for guard duty. It starts to eat at you, standing there for hours, watching a wall. Makes a man want to drink.~
@11155 = ~[TORAN] The <PRO_MANWOMAN> here tells me you used to serve with the pukes that call themselves the Flaming Fist.~
@11156 = ~[ARAN] Now then, you are a big strappin' boy, you are. I might have. What be your problem wi' th 'Fist?~
@11157 = ~[C-TORAN] The cowardly crabs got into my business.~
@11158 = ~[ARAN] What business was that?~
@11159 = ~[C-TORAN] None of yours. You talk like a 'Fist, asking lots of questions.~
@11160 = ~[ARAN] Always pokin' my nose in, that be me.~
@11161 = ~[C-TORAN] I don't like you.~
@11162 = ~[ARAN] That be your prerogative, now, don't it.~
@11163 = ~[C-TORAN] I think you look like a drow-loving orc that has been used too many times in a pleasure pit.~
@11164 = ~[ARAN] An' I be thinkin' that you are a mite bit slow, an' perhaps a bit drunk. So run along, laddie, an' you an' me, we'll ignore each other, eh?~
@11165 = ~[C-TORAN] The Fist is a bunch of cowardly orc-loving bastards, and it is a pity every last one of them wasn't killed when the Iron Throne took over. They should have screamed their last breaths on the torturers wheel, instead of throwing their lives away protecting vermin.~
@11166 = ~[ARAN] Bugger off.~
@11167 = ~[C-TORAN] I said you are a coward, an orc-loving drow-screwing piece of filth who needs to be cleaned up by his mommy. Now what are you gonna do about it?~
@11168 = ~[C-AW01TK] Bets pay off here. That was five provocations before Aran punched him. Erika, you owe me two tradebars.~
@11169 = ~[ARAN] I'm right sorry, I am. I done spilled some o' my drink on that poor boy's head. Well, I suppose it might wash some o' th' blood away, anyways. Orrin, a refill, eh? An' one for my fine friend here, too. What did that little 'entertainment' set you back, <CHARNAME>?~
@11170 = ~[PC] What are you talking about? That drunk accosted me, and pawed at me. I told him you were with the 'Fist to get him off of my back! I expected you to protect my honor.~
@11171 = ~[PC] 2 gold for the attack, 5 gold for learning what words to say to you.~
@11172 = ~[PC] You disappoint me. I thought you would fight like a man, and take your time killing him piece by piece.~
@11173 = ~[PC] Not enough, apparently. A girl can only do so much. It might be more fun if you were the one provoking, and sending them to me to be sliced and diced. You just keep refusing to do that.~
@11174 = ~[PC] I brought you a present. A strong young buck, all ready to be clobbered. I like watching your muscles ripple as you manhandle someone. It is... exciting.~
@11175 = ~[PC] You looked like you needed a good fight to clear your head. You moved too quickly, though. I thought it would last longer.~
@11176 = ~[PC] Impressive. I wanted to see exactly how much control you have outside of the battlefield.~
@11177 = ~[PC] Why did you wait so long? I would have punched him much earlier.~
@11178 = ~[ARAN] That might be your idea o' 'fun', <CHARNAME>, but not mine. I don't see no sport in goadin' drunks to their death, when they be no more threat than a fly 'til they get their wings torn off. To each their own, I suppose.~
@11179 = ~[ARAN] Aye, thought as much. Next time, don't be given too much coachin', eh? Th' giveaway was that a man what can't take a dump wi' out lookin' up how to say 'grunt' said somethin' like 'screamed out their last breaths'. Boys like him, they got two words... 'drink', an' 'screw'. Wi' him, I'm not sure he'd know what th' second was nohow.~
@11180 = ~[ARAN] Well, no real harm done. Th' lad was probably lookin' for a good solid bar fight to let off some steam. He got what he had comin' to him. Thing is, I don't rightly think we want that level o' attention right now. Mayhap next time, things will be a little easier, an' we can have a good rough 'n tumble. But tonight, I figured it be a bad idea.~
@11181 = ~[ARAN] I can control myself right fine when push comes to shove. I get that way on account o' I don't want to start somethin' unless it be necessary. Once it be started, I have to finish it. I learned that th' hard way up in Targos, talkin' bigger than I could fight. Took three weeks, an' more than a few healin' potions.~
@11182 = ~[PC] I have to deliver this from Orrin at The Broken Sword. Where do I go?~
@11183 = ~[BREGA] That looks like a standard tax form. Any of the clerks here can help you.~
@11184 = ~[PC] The last time I tried this, there was a big hassle with forms and stamping and getting the documentation right... and all I wanted to do was get authorization to talk to a prisoner here.~
@11185 = ~[PC] Thank you. Have a good <DAYNIGHT>.~
@11186 = ~[PC] Clerks. I would rather entrust you with this.~
@11187 = ~[PC] Do I look like the type of person who bothers with intermediaries and minor functionaries?~
@11188 = ~[PC] Does everything in this city always end up in the Government District?~
@11189 = ~[BREGA] Most of the commerce and management comes through here, of course. This is not a small backwater town. It takes a large civil service to handle and balance the needs of the citizens.~
@11190 = ~[BREGA] There is no need for concern. You hand that to a clerk, and they give you a standard receipt.~
@11191 = ~[CLERK01] Move along, please. I am on break.~
@11192 = ~[ARAN] Are you th' person to see about delivering some paperwork?~
@11193 = ~[CLERK01] Yes.~
@11194 = ~[ARAN] Well, can you just take this here package an' hand us a receipt, eh?~
@11195 = ~[CLERK01] No.~
@11196 = ~[ARAN] It looks like they be right there. There, on th' left.~
@11197 = ~[ARAN] So, do a good deed, eh, an' just hand over th' receipt.~
@11198 = ~[CLERK01] I am on break.~
@11199 = ~[PC] I don't believe this. I am going to get the runaround again, aren't I?~
@11200 = ~[PC] I have to deliver this from Orrin at The Broken Sword. He needs a receipt.~
@11201 = ~[PC] Never mind... I may come back later.~
@11202 = ~[PC] Do you actually do anything around here except shuffle paper and waste people's time?~
@11203 = ~[PC] What if I told you I have a tax form with completely inaccurate figures, manufactured to make sure it appears that little or no income was taken in?~
@11204 = ~[PC] What does a winsome minor government functionary do to relax, anyways? I find a man with ink stains on his fingers so... appealing.~
@11205 = ~[CLERK01] Look, I get a few minutes peace per shift. It isn't much. Then it is back to long lines of people who want detailed explanations about things way above my pay grade. Meaningless forms that disappear into an abyss never to see the light of day.~
@11206 = ~[CLERK01] Please, just go find one of the other three scribes. They can help you. I am on break.~
@11207 = ~[CIVIL01] Next, please... what can I do for you today?~
@11208 = ~[ARAN] Hey, can you...~
@11209 = ~[CIVIL01] No, for the thousandth time, no. I don't handle civil service recruitment. I do not have an employment form. I can't help you get a job scribing here.~
@11210 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, I done got me a job already! We aren't here on account o' that.~
@11211 = ~[PC] I am not going to get the runaround again, am I?~
@11212 = ~[PC] What if I told you I have a tax form from The Broken Sword that has completely inaccurate figures, manufactured to make sure it appears that little or no income was taken in?~
@11213 = ~[CIVIL01] I just do my job. Is that a Writ of Quarterly Taxable Income, Commercial, Standard Form you have there?~
@11214 = ~[PC] Yes. Can I get a receipt?~
@11215 = ~[PC] No. It is a Writ of Quarterly Bribes to Bloodsucking Bloated Government Toadies Who Mess With People Because They Can With Impunity, Long Form. Here, take it. I will not tell you where you can put it... I leave that to your imagination.~
@11216 = ~[PC] Actually, I am not sure what this is. I was told to deliver it, and get a receipt.~
@11217 = ~[PC] You look like an interesting person. What are you doing after work?~
@11218 = ~[PC] I was supposed to deliver this, but I think I will wait for a bit.~
@11219 = ~[PC] What if I told you these were completely inaccurate figures, manufactured to make sure it appears that little or no income was taken in?~
@11220 = ~[CIVIL01] Ah, yes. A Writ of Quarterly Taxable Income, Commercial, Standard Form. My signature... here. I have received this on behalf of the City and its Citizens. Here is a receipt for The Broken Sword's accounts and its owner of record, one Orrin Thedale, resident of aforementioned premises. Next in line, step up...~
@11221 = ~[CIVIL01] Right. My signature... here. I have received this on behalf of the City and its Citizens. Here is a receipt for The Broken Sword's accounts and its owner of record, one Orrin Thedale, resident of aforementioned premises. Next in line, step up...~
@11222 = ~[CIVIL01] I will be here. Unfortunately. Counting the days until retirement.~
@11223 = ~[CIVIL01] Nope.~
@11224 = ~[CIVIL01] Move along, then. There are other people in line.~
@11225 = ~[CIVIL01] There is no call for that attitude. Here is your receipt. The Citizens of this Fair City thank you. NEXT.~
@11226 = ~[CIVIL01] Bribing a government official is not allowed. Charming them is frowned on, and raising their hopes of a wild time on the town with you only to be left miserable and heartbroken is just plain mean. Besides, you are not my type. Do you have business, or shall I call the guard?~
@11227 = ~[PC] Whoa, I didn't mean... look, here is something from Orrin over at The Broken Sword. Can I get a receipt?~
@11228 = ~[PC] Forget I said anything. I have a Writ of Quarterly Bribes to Bloodsucking Bloated Government Toadies. Here, take it. I will not tell you where you can put it... I leave that to your imagination.~
@11229 = ~[PC] Jump to conclusions much? Here. I am not sure what this is. I was told to deliver it, and get a receipt.~
@11230 = ~[PC] I was supposed to deliver this, but I think I will wait for a bit. Perhaps someone else can help me.~
@11231 = ~[PC] Your loss. Pity, too... I can be very fun. Very. Anyways, here is something from The Broken Sword.~
@11232 = ~[CIVIL01] I could not care less. That is not my department. You could talk to the Auditor General, but the last three AG's have died under mysterious circumstances and the post has been vacant for at least two years. So, do you have something to give me, or not?~
@11233 = ~[CIVIL02] Step closer, please. May I help you?~
@11234 = ~[ARAN] No worries, I am not here for a job. I done found one.~
@11235 = ~[CIVIL02] Now that is a pity. They just reopened a search for a new Auditor General, and I thought immediately of you.~
@11236 = ~[ARAN] Well, that is right kind o' you. Auditor General, eh? That sounds important.~
@11237 = ~[CIVIL02] It is important enough that the last three people to hold that office met mysterious ends.~
@11238 = ~[ARAN] Sounds about like my current contract. Only not so much on th' mysterious... usually, I can see what be about to kill me in plenty o' time to wonder why I ever signed up as a mercenary.~
@11239 = ~[PC] I hope so. I am not going to get the runaround again, am I? The last time I was here...~
@11240 = ~[CIVIL02] I just do my job. Is that a Writ of Quarterly Taxable Income, Commercial, Standard Form you have there?~
@11241 = ~[CIVIL02] Ah, yes. A Writ of Quarterly Taxable Income, Commercial, Standard Form. My signature... here. I have received this on behalf of the City and its Citizens. Here is a receipt for The Broken Sword's accounts and its owner of record, one Orrin Thedale, resident of aforementioned premises. Next in line, step up...~
@11242 = ~[CIVIL02] Right. My signature... here. I have received this on behalf of the City and its Citizens. Here is a receipt for The Broken Sword's accounts and its owner of record, one Orrin Thedale, resident of aforementioned premises. Next in line, step up...~
