@11247 = ~[CIVIL02] Bribing a government official is not allowed. Charming them is frowned on, and raising their hopes of a wild time on the town with you only to be left miserable and heartbroken is just plain mean. Besides, you are not my type. Do you have business, or shall I call the guard?~
@11248 = ~[CIVIL02] I could not care less. That is not my department. You could talk to the Auditor General, but the last three AG's have died under mysterious circumstances and the post has been vacant for at least two years. So, do you have something to give me, or not?~
@11249 = ~[PC] Yes, one  Writ of Quarterly Bribes to Bloodsucking Bloated Government Toadies Who Mess With People Because They Can, Long Form. Here, take it. I will not tell you where you can put it... I leave that to your imagination.~
@11250 = ~[CIVIL03] Tax forms to the front of the line, please... ah. I think I see one right there, in your hand, <PRO_SIRMAAM>.~
@11251 = ~[ARAN] You can see that right from th' outside?~
@11252 = ~[CIVIL03] When you have seen as many 1720-3a Writ of Quarterly Taxable Income, Commercial, Standard as I have, you can see them, smell them, and even have dreams about them.~
@11253 = ~[ARAN] That sounds blighted unnatural, that does.~
@11254 = ~[CIVIL03] Tell me about it. You should see the dreams. Waking nightmares, every one.~
@11255 = ~[PC] I hope you can help me. I am not going to get the runaround again, am I? The last time I was here...~
@11256 = ~[CIVIL03] I just do my job. Is that Writ of Quarterly Taxable Income, Commercial, Standard Form you have there completed?~
@11257 = ~[PC] yes, but you miss-titled it. It is a Writ of Quarterly Bribes to Bloodsucking Bloated Government Toadies Who Mess With People Because They Can With Impunity, Long Form. Here, take it. I will not tell you where you can put it... I leave that to your imagination.~
@11258 = ~[CIVIL03] Ah, yes. One W-QTI, Commercial, Standard Form. We call them "Cuties".~
@11259 = ~[CIVIL03] Of course, that gets confusing, when there are forms for Quarterly Treasury Information, Quantum Universal Time Irregularities (Ex-communicated Spellcasting), and the real C.U.T.I.E... Customs Utilization: Thayvian Inventory Evaluation.~
@11260 = ~[CIVIL03] My signature... here. I have received this on behalf of the City and its Citizens. Here is a receipt for The Broken Sword's accounts and its owner of record, one Orrin Thedale, resident of aforementioned premises. Next in line, step up...~
@11261 = ~[CIVIL03] Right. My signature... here. I have received this on behalf of the City and its Citizens. Here is a receipt for The Broken Sword's accounts and its owner of record, one Orrin Thedale, resident of aforementioned premises. Next in line, step up...~
@11262 = ~[CIVIL03] I will be here. Unfortunately. Counting the days until retirement.~
@11263 = ~[CIVIL03] Nope.~
@11264 = ~[CIVIL03] Move along, then. There are other people in line.~
@11265 = ~[CIVIL03] There is no call for that attitude. Here is your receipt. The Citizens of this Fair City thank you. NEXT.~
@11266 = ~[CIVIL03] Bribing a government official is not allowed. Charming them is frowned on, and raising their hopes of a wild time on the town with you only to be left miserable and heartbroken is just plain mean. Besides, you are not my type. Do you have business, or shall I call the guard?~
@11267 = ~[CIVIL03] I could not care less. That is not my department. You could talk to the Auditor General, but the last three AG's have died under mysterious circumstances and the post has been vacant for at least two years. So, do you have something to give me, or not?~
@11268 = ~[ARAN] Well now, let me think a bit... our relationship. Put a lad on th' spot, eh?~
@11269 = ~[ARAN] Currently, we be fightin' mad at each other, or so it seems.~
@11270 = ~[ARAN] You done told me to quit makin' all sorts o' random comments.~
@11271 = ~[ARAN] You done told me I should be leavin' Anomen alone an' not fightin' wi' him.~
@11272 = ~[ARAN] I seem to not have ticked you off to th' point where you drop me for good, eh? I think we even be friends. Why do you be askin'?~
@11273 = ~[ARAN] I seem to not have ticked you off to th' point where you drop me for good, eh? You done told me no sellsword has th' right to be called "friend". Why do you be askin'?~
@11274 = ~[ARAN] You haven't told me to not try a bit o' sparkin' from time to time. Then again, you done got a huge amount to think about lately. I think we be friends, more's th' pity. Why do you be askin'?~
@11275 = ~[ARAN] We might rightly be called 'involved', I think. I am not sure what you get out o' th' deal, but I'm not rightly complainin'. Mayhap I can coax you into a kiss or two someday. Why do you be askin'?~
@11276 = ~[ARAN] We might rightly be called 'involved', I think. I am not sure what you get out o' th' deal, but I'm not rightly complainin'. Mayhap I can coax you into more than a kiss or two someday. Why do you be askin'?~
@11277 = ~[ARAN] We might rightly be called 'involved', I think. I am not sure what you get out o' th' deal, but I'm not rightly complainin'. Mayhap I can coax you into somethin' more than kissin' an' touchin' someday. Why do you be askin'?~
@11278 = ~[ARAN] We might rightly be called 'involved', I think. I am not sure what you get out o' th' deal, but I'm not rightly complainin'. I can rightly say I live for th' times when we get physical wi' each other. Mayhap someday we will take that final step. Why do you be askin'?~
@11279 = ~[ARAN] We might rightly be called 'involved', I think. I am not sure what you get out o' th' deal, but I'm not rightly complainin'. An' I won't never forget spendin' time wi' you all tangled up, explorin' everythin'... why do you be askin'?~
@11280 = ~[ARAN] I seem to not have ticked you off to th' point where you drop me for good, eh? I think we even be friends. We could have a bit more, but I guess things didn't work out th' way you wanted. Why do you be askin'?~
@11281 = ~[ARAN] You haven't told me to bugger off permanent, though you do seem a trifle short wi' me from time to time. Then again, you done got a huge amount to think about lately. You also let me prattle on an' on about whatever I like, which is blighted nice o' you. I think we be friends. Why do you be askin'?~
@11282 = ~[ARAN] You told me to not try to confuse things by bein' friends, so we be supposed to keep to th' professional side. You command, I follow. Then you pay me. You do let me prattle on an' on about whatever I like, which is blighted nice o' you.  Why do you be askin'?~
@11283 = ~[ARAN] You haven't told me to bugger off permanent, though you do seem a trifle short wi' me from time to time. Then again, you done got a huge amount to think about lately. You also told me not to talk so much. I think we be friends. Why do you be askin'?~
@11284 = ~[ARAN] You told me to not try to confuse things by bein' friends, so we be supposed to keep to th' professional side. I also am supposed to keep my blighted mouth shut most o' th' time. You command, I follow. Then you pay me. Why do you be askin'?~
@11285 = ~[ARAN] Hey... you know, I be havin' one hells o' a blighted time figurin' out just what I think o' our relationship. I mean, that belt... it confuses me right proper, it do.~
@11286 = ~[PC] I was just wondering.~
@11287 = ~[PC] Oh, I just thought you might realize that I depend on you as one of my closest friends. I may not treat you exactly the way you would like, but I count on you.~
@11288 = ~[PC] No sellsword ever has the right to call me "friend".~
@11289 = ~[PC] It is good to know that you know your place.~
@11290 = ~[PC] In your case, I will make an exception. I think we are friends.~
@11291 = ~[PC] I think we have headed down the wrong path, Aran. Let's just be friends.~
@11292 = ~[PC] I think I am... very interested in you. Romantically speaking.~
@11293 = ~[PC] I think we could be together, if you were discreet. I have other lovers who are much less forgiving than you. Play by my rules, and we might just see what happens...~
@11294 = ~[PC] I think I am... interested in you. But I don't like things to move so fast. Perhaps we should be friends, and explore becoming more?~
@11295 = ~[PC] I can't believe you have forgotten all of the passion. You are so physical, but you can't remember with whom?~
@11296 = ~[PC] Just checking. I guess this belt has as odd an effect on you as it has on me.~
@11297 = ~[ARAN] Aran Whitehand, sword and scribe. His jaw is as hard as granite, and he keeps flexing his hands. He looks up, his eyes meeting yours.~
@11298 = ~[PC] (A slight sound startles you awake. Aran's voice whispers from beside you.)~
@11299 = ~[PC] (As you prepare for your rest, you recall the words you spoke to Aran earlier.)~
@11300 = ~[PC] (You decide that now is not a good time for a romantic encounter, and warn him off.)~
@11301 = ~[PC] (Perhaps he will remember, as well.)~
@11302 = ~[PC] Tell me about Aran Whitehand.~
@11303 = ~[VOLO] Of all the great warrior poets and scribes to walk the face of Faerun, Aran is the most... unrefined. His swearing has reached legendary status, and sparked theological debates as far as Rasheman. Indeed, it is said that the gods themselves wager on his inventiveness.~
@11304 = ~[ARAN] Denir's Quaint Quill, you done said that already.~
@11305 = ~[VOLO] Fill my glass, and perhaps I might be persuaded to change my mind. But probably not. I do have a reputation for independence to maintain, after all.~
@11306 = ~[ARAN] Mystul's Glass Skull, you make out like every word I say be a blighted swearword.~
@11307 = ~[VOLO] You of all people should know, dear boy, that a bard relies on exaggeration to better entertain his listeners.~
@11308 = ~[ARAN] Well, Mystra's Mantle, that be mite bit o' consolation, I guess. So I don't swear every bloody minute, eh?~
@11309 = ~[VOLO] That depends. Are you speaking during each minute?~
@11310 = ~[ARAN] Mystul's Glass Skull, no words on me an' th' lady here? Nothin' about dangerous romance, an'...~
@11311 = ~[VOLO] Ah, the plot thickens! Hold on, do let me get a quill. I sense a great story here...~
@11312 = ~[ARAN] Blighted... err... I was makin' it up. Nothin' to discuss, actually. None o' your business, an' all.~
@11313 = ~[VOLO] Oh, come now, my lad. Such claims would elevate you to legendary status. The Man Who Tamed <CHARNAME>? The humble, ill-mannered sellsword who enticed the most powerful woman on the face of Toril?~
@11314 = ~[ARAN] Bloody hells, man, are you tryin' to get me killed? Either that is a glint o' laughter in her eyes, or she's about to kill you or me or both o' us at once. Forget I said anythin', eh? I needs be gettin about findin' a suitable gift to get out o' th' doghouse.~
@11315 = ~[PC]Bring me Aran Whitehand, the fighter and scribe.~
@11316 = ~[PC]Bring me my former lover, Aran Whitehand.~
@11317 = ~[PC]Bring me my love, Aran Whitehand.~
@11318 = ~[ARAN] That be a nice sight, there, Aerie. Congratulations. Just watch out where he points that other 'finger', eh? An' I might suggest a bit o' cloth, for when he gets an urge to... heh. Too late.~
@11319 = ~[ARAN] Ilmater's Mercy, shut up, Korgan. We don't be wantin' to offend th' nice priestess what can help us, now, do we, laddie?~
@11320 = ~[KORGAN] You never did have any humor, jackass. You can kiss my arse.~
@11321 = ~[ARAN] Well, there be my standin' offer for you to take me under anythin' you want, eh?~
@11322 = ~[NALIA] Hey, keep your hands to yourself!~
@11323 = ~[ARAN] An' by pointless, he means that there'd be lots o' blood, some screamin', an' unfortunately none o' it would be theirs. That whole curtain wall, there, that be...~
@11324 = ~[SAREVOK] ...~
@11325 = ~[ARAN] Right. What he said. Shuttin' up.~
@11326 = ~[ARAN] I'd be a mite more interested in what you have in th' way o' quills, myself.~
@11327 = ~[ARAN] Grumbar's Glands. I needed some good parchment to restock, an' mayhap some ingredients for ink, too.~
@11328 = ~[ARAN] Bloody one-track mind, <CHARNAME>. I done had those feelin's myself, when I couldn't find naught for supplies. Until we find that blighted spellbook o' his, two gold says he's not goin' to talk about anythin' else.~
@11329 = ~[ARAN] Do all you wyrms get together an' swap notes? Seems like all o' you have been watchin' us all in great amusement. Hells, you could get more fun out o' a night in a Calishite harem an' be done wi' it, eh?~
@11330 = ~[ARAN] Oi! I resemble that remark!~
@11331 = ~[ARAN] We mercenaries prefer th' term 'sellswords', or 'bastards what can kill things for coin', or just plain 'sir'.~
@11332 = ~[ARAN] Ten tradebars an' a bottle o' D'Tranion Ale says he isn't buildin' all this up for a takeover o' Tethyr. Monks usually be more subtle than that.~
@11333 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Bloody Breath, boyo... don't be wishin' for that life. Go learn an honest trade, like bartender. Or blacksmith. Th' hours are better, an' th' ladies like a man what has solid, steady work.~
@11334 = ~[ARAN] I think they should change th' motto o' th' Harpers to 'Enigmatic Information Given, Lives Screwed'. Either that, or 'What, I Didn't Mention There Would Be Dragons?'.~
@11335 = ~[ARAN] The problem wi' undead liches is that they are so bloody predictable. O' course, the other problem is they are tough to kill, on account o' they be dead already.~
@11336 = ~[LICH] We shall start the killings with the mouthy one!~
@11337 = ~[ARAN] The problem wi' undead liches is that they are so bloody predictable. O' course, the other problem is they are tough to kill, on account o' they are already dead.~
@11338 = ~[ARAN] Corellon's Bowhand, tell me she did not. There be mercenary companies where th' whole town would be slaughtered, just to make a point. Hells, even th' 'Fist would hang a thief what's been caught in th' act.~
@11339 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, I be thinkin' we'd rather help these upset gentlemen take you apart, piece by piece, real slow-like.~
@11340 = ~[ARAN] I'd say it might end wi' your head makin' th' sound a ripe melon makes when it's been dropped from th' top o' a watchtower.~
@11341 = ~[ARAN] Torm's Left Testicle. Now we be fightin' whole armies. I hope there be a raise in pay comin' soon, eh?~
@11342 = ~[ARAN] Bloody hells. Either you be mad, or you be th' most driven individual I ever done met.~
@11343 = ~[ARAN] Is that what that smell be? An' here I thought I'd just spiced up th' curry too much.~
@11344 = ~[ARAN] Wyrms. Th' gods have no sense o' imagination. No giant toadstools barrin' our paths, no huge grasshoppers, just th' same ol' three... Liches, Vampires, an' Dragons, oh my. Just once, I'd like to see a giant cup o' tea barrin' th' path, wi' a side o' toast.~
@11345 = ~[ARAN] Wyrms. Th' gods have no sense o' imagination. No giant toadstools barrin' our paths, no huge grasshoppers, just th' same ol' three... Liches, Vampires, on Dragons, oh my. Just once, I'd like to see a giant cup o' tea barrin' th' path, wi' a side o' toast.~
@11346 = ~[ARAN] Every time we turn around, there be another layer o' servants. I gotta get me some o' them. Spruce a place up, they do.~
@11347 = ~[ARAN] O' course it is. You sure there be no liches? What about a bloodsuckin' vampiric dragon-lich? We wouldn't want to make this easier, eh?~
@11348 = ~[ARAN] You bloody well sound like that lass I was tryin' to spark with back when I was in Calimport.~
@11349 = ~[ARAN] You bloody well sound like that lass I was tryin' to spark with back when I was in Calimport. Err... that was a mite o' time before I met you, <CHARNAME>.~
@11350 = ~[ARAN] Now, to be fair, <PRO_HESHE> had a mite bit o' help, eh? Speakin' for myself, I'm not always th' sharpest tack in th' toolshed, but I get th' job done.~
@11351 = ~[ARAN] Go on, <CHARNAME>, don't hesitate, on either path. At least not on account o' me. You done become a goddess in my heart a long, long time ago.~
@11352 = ~[ARAN] You know, I think I told you once, I swear by plenty o' gods, <CHARNAME>. I done served you well, but I beg you, let some other poor bastard get stuck bein' a god. We could go take over Tethyr, or kick th' Caliphs out o' Calimshaw.~
@11353 = ~[ARAN] You know, I think I told you once, I swear by plenty o' gods, <CHARNAME>. But I got more faith that you will prevail than in th' entire pantheon. If you leave it to me, I'll choose to back your play, no matter what you be choosin'.~
@11354 = ~[ARAN] I be not the most polished knight, but I have been right loyal to you. Whatever you decide, your son has my sword pledged to his cause, for good or ill.~
@11355 = ~[ARAN] What, no foreplay?~
@11356 = ~[GUARD] Sound the alarm!~
@11357 = ~[ARAN] A witch? Will she turn me into a newt?~
@11358 = ~[ARAN] Just one. Why in th' nine hells are all you witches messed up in th' head?~
@11359 = ~[ARAN] Nyalee is I  - nope, accordin' to <CHARNAME>, here, that should be 'I am Nyalee'. See, I done listened to all that teachin' you keep pushin' on me.~
@11360 = ~[ARAN] Somehow, I doubt there be any good in those reasons, eh, on account o' th' whole servin' evil thing.~
@11361 = ~[ARAN] To be a successful merchant in Calimshan, that takes a bit o' ruthlessness, a bit o' magic, an' a large amount o' coin.~
@11362 = ~[MARLOWE] It took all of that, and some... assistance.~
@11363 = ~[ARAN] Now, you be slippery little bitch, eh? Right smart. Waste o' a nice lookin' body, too, when we have to carve it all up into pieces, eh?~
@11364 = ~[ARAN] Don't we all, boyo, don't we all. It would come in right handy for us right about now.~
@11365 = ~[ARAN] Now, there, lad... back wi' th' Fist, we didn't take kindly to...~
@11366 = ~[MERCENARY] The Flaming Fist are weak-bellied buttock-licking camp followers.~
@11367 = ~[ARAN] Tsk, tsk. Such language. Burn's a lad's ears, it does. Suit yourself.~
@11368 = ~[MERCENARY] Attack!~
@11369 = ~[ARAN] Chauntea's Basket - what in th' nine hells did he just say?~
@11370 = ~[ARAN] Politics. Even durin' a crisis, no one pulls together. Ilmater's Mercy, <CHARNAME>, there be times when I think you should just start takin' over th' world. At least then we'd know where we all stood, eh?~
@11371 = ~[ARAN] Torm's Breath! There be limits to havin' fun wi' th' help. Mayhap we see how they like a little o' turnabout, eh?~
@11372 = ~[ARAN] Torm's Breath! I know, I know, might makes right. I'll shut my mouth an' go stand in th' corner like a good little sellsword. But if it were up to me, I'd show 'em some right strong might, myself.~
@11373 = ~[ARAN] Bloody hells, girl, you be in serious need o' a drink. You seem to have a mite too much energy. Make that several drinks.~
@11374 = ~[ARAN] Now if I had a trade bar for every evil creature what confided in an old crone in th' wilds, I'd be a rich man. Good thing you don't rightly need one, <CHARNAME>.~
@11375 = ~[ARAN] Now if I had a trade bar for every evil creature what did that, I'd be a rich man. Speakin' o' that, where be your old crone confidant, <CHARNAME>?~
@11376 = ~[ARAN] Given our bloody luck, there'd be a might more'n nothin'. More like a whole pile o' trouble.~
@11377 = ~[MELISSAN] I wish that I had a better answer for you.~
@11378 = ~[ARAN] Been there, eh? Not a pretty sight. No control, an' a bit o' trouble spirals into murder, rape, an' worse.~
@11379 = ~[MELISSAN] You say that as if there could be worse.~
@11380 = ~[ARAN] Monks. Well, I done fought alongside some. Might be a base o' operations after all.~
@11381 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Bouncin' Breasts, <CHARNAME> gets all the fun.~
@11382 = ~[ARAN] Shar's Silvery Strands, fifty gold? A trained wench in Calimport only costs 5 gold, an' is happy to do anythin' anyone could ever dream up. What do you get for fifty gold?~
@11383 = ~[PROSTIVAMP] More than you could possibly imagine.~
@11384 = ~[ARAN] You got quick eyes, an' big ears, eh? Might be you could profit by usin' em instead o' that smart mouth o' yours.~
@11385 = ~[ARAN] Th' only good Drow be a dead Drow, eh? Kiss Shar's arse for me.~
@11386 = ~[SENDAI] I spit on you.~
@11387 = ~[ARAN] Ilmater's Bloody Hands, that sounds like Drow-bastards. Did they be carryin' crossbows?~
@11388 = ~[WOODCUTTER] I didn't see.~
@11389 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Balls. Never did see th' day when one o' you one-eyed wonders was a right good sort.~
@11390 = ~[FUNBEHOLDER] Don't let it get around. I have a long memory, and a great work ethic. Wouldn't want to have to hunt you down, you know.~
@11391 = ~[ARAN] My mother always told me never miss a good chance to shut up... but then again I'm not rightly one to follow advice. I hate to leave folks to fate, but we don't have enough supplies to run a refuge, eh?~
@11392 = ~[ELFLEADER] We would not ask such a thing.~
@11393 = ~[ARAN] Whatever Guild you belong to, I'd be havin' a talk wi' your representative, eh? You done got th' worst assignment I can think of, short o'cleanin' up ogre pens in a circus.~
@11394 = ~[ARAN] Mielikki's Mithral Mane, that slippery bastard be havin' us walkin' into a trap?~
@11395 = ~[ARAN] Hey, you look right happy, you do. Why so chipper?~
@11396 = ~[AERIE] No particular reason.~
@11397 = ~[ARAN] Oh, come on now, you can tell an old friend. Between you an' me, your usual attitude is a fair bit south o' worried, wi' a slight spice o' sad. Things started improvin' when you finally got it in your head that <CHARNAME> were th' best thing that ever happened to you, but now, look at you. You even eat!~
@11398 = ~[AERIE] I'm just happy, that is all.~
@11399 = ~[ARAN] Happy? You look positively beamin'. An' let me tell you, it looks a might bit fairer than th' usual keen sense o' despair you sometimes projected, back in th' day. Let me guess. He proposed to you.~
@11400 = ~[AERIE] The Avariel do not have all these rituals, Aran.~
@11401 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, girl, <CHARNAME> must o' proposed to you in secret, an' that be why you are so happy! Well, good wishes an' a long life to both o' you. Just tell me when th' weddin' be, an' I will be there.~
@11402 = ~[AERIE] (sigh) I don't think you are hearing me, or listening...~
@11403 = ~[ARAN] What, I be good enough to watch your back on th' trail, but not good enough for attendin' th' weddin'? That don't rightly sound like you.~
@11404 = ~[AERIE] Absolutely, Aran. If we have a formal wedding, you will be invited.~
@11405 = ~[ARAN] Oh, right... mum's th' word, 'til th' banns be announced. Now, I got me a mite bit o' research to do, on account o' I need to find a gift. Do you two be allergic to any particular foods or such?~
@11406 = ~[ARAN] It be lookin' like you just took a run down a hillside an' tripped a few times, eh? You must o' had another nightmare.~
@11407 = ~[PC] As I recall, there was a good bit of you running around yelling 'Kill it! Kill it! Cyric's Blood, kill it now!', while screaming like a little girl..~
@11408 = ~[PC] Somehow, the mental image of you licking our adversaries just turns my stomach. And maybe excites me a little, too.~
@11409 = ~[ARAN] That were an ugly sight, for sure. Th' whole city sacked. Enough to give anyone a right nasty set o' dreams.~
@11410 = ~[PC] I couldn't close my eyes at all. I kept seeing the city of Saradush... burning.~
@11411 = ~[PC] I slept well enough, though I do have sympathy for those hurt because of my kind.~
@11412 = ~[PC] What? Did I miss something? I slept like the dead.~
@11413 = ~[PC] I had you as a distraction. I slept well enough.~
@11414 = ~[PC] I have seen worse. Saradush is not the first time I have experienced full-scale slaughter of innocents.~
@11415 = ~[PC] I... I do not want to talk about it.~
@11416 = ~[ARAN] I feel th' same. I worried a mite bit that you would feel distant. I went through that, for a time. It... well, it didn't turn out to be th' best way to handle things.~
@11417 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>, you have a depth to you what makes th' difference between those what rise to power at every cost an' those who pick an' choose th' costs. That marks you as different from most wi' th' kind o' power you wield.~
@11418 = ~[PC] I am not sure you are correct, but I share your concern. I will see to it that this kind of thing cannot happen again.~
@11419 = ~[PC] I don't choose. War is like any other large force, like wind, or lightning. We can seek to control part of it, but unless we are gods, we can only change a very small portion. We only have so much power to change things.~
@11420 = ~[PC] I know, and I am tired of the choices others are making. I will be noticed. I will be a power to be reckoned with.~
@11421 = ~[PC] I am sick of having so much power, but no way to change things for the better. I don't think I can handle this.~
@11422 = ~[PC] I don't want to talk about this.~
@11423 = ~[ARAN] Those o' your... blighted hells, <PRO_MANWOMAN>, what exactly be "your kind"? I be hopin' you haven't lost your senses. We done already seen that 'Bhaalspawn' be varied just like any other race - if you can call it such.~
@11424 = ~[ARAN] War an' power go hand in hand, true enough. Th' expense o' the fallen in Saradush - if you look at th' pain an' sufferin', it be wrong. If you look at th' waste o' useful lives, even potential slaves, it be wrong. If you look at th' loss o' goods an' services, it be wrong. Hells, even if you be a soul-eatin' demonic Drow-child, this be just plain useless to anyone's plans.~
@11425 = ~[ARAN] There be only two ways this makes sense; one, someone tryin' to create a legion o' undead, or two, someone who revels in chaos an' sufferin'.~
@11426 = ~[PC] Either way, the chaos will to be my advantage. I will use this as an excuse to eradicate every power which refuses to follow my wishes.~
@11427 = ~[PC] It does not matter. I will make sure things like this never happen again.~
@11428 = ~[PC] War and power may go hand in hand, but love can bind those hands and still them.~
@11429 = ~[PC] You are forgetting the true cost. This means all of the Prophecies are coming true. There will be no refuge or allies for us, anywhere. We will be hunted like animals.~
@11430 = ~[PC] Pain. Suffering. Waste. These are just symptoms. Someone has to wipe out war itself.~
@11431 = ~[PC] I look at things like this, and I just want to turn back time. I want to go back to Candlekeep, and hide somewhere in the stacks, locked away, protected from all this madness and death.~
@11432 = ~[ARAN] Distraction may be nice, but a thing like this will scar any man or woman what sees it.~
@11433 = ~[PC] I keep seeing the city of Saradush... burning. It is not a pleasant sight.~
@11434 = ~[ARAN] Me neither. But I never got so callous as not to feel anythin'. Th' waste, th' ugliness...~
@11435 = ~[PC] It is beautiful, isn't it? The raw power, loosed untamed and unfettered, drenching everything in blood and meaningless death...~
@11436 = ~[PC] It is sickening.~
@11437 = ~[PC] I want revenge. I want the... things. The things that did this. I want them to suffer.~
@11438 = ~[PC] None of this is our concern. We did the best we could to save the city.~
@11439 = ~[ARAN] No bein' in their right mind does. But you will sleep better if you do.~
@11440 = ~[PC] What is there to say? The weak get killed by the strong. War has a power of its own. There is nothing I can do about it.~
@11441 = ~[PC] It is my fault. I should have split the party, leaving behind someone to help.~
@11442 = ~[PC] I said I don't want to talk about it. Be quiet, or I will make sure you can't speak for a whole day.~
@11443 = ~[PC] You have been in war. What do you do with the feelings of guilt?~
@11444 = ~[PC] I sleep just fine, thank you. I understand that some things are beyond my power to control.~
@11445 = ~[PC] If I ever get a chance, I am going to put a stop to all this bloodshed.~
@11446 = ~[ARAN] Th' end result would have been worse. One o' us tryin' to take on an entire army might have delayed things an hour or so. But even th' avatar of a god can be taken down when th' odds are thousands to one.~
@11447 = ~[PC] Does saying that make you feel better?~
@11448 = ~[PC] I guess you are right. I just keep feeling that this is so wrong, so utterly wrong. I can't get it out of my mind.~
@11449 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>, I think this be not th' first time I have mentioned that you scare th' livin' crap out o' me.~
@11450 = ~[ARAN] Impossible. Unless you eradicate every creature on this plane o' existence, an' mayhap beyond, you won't stop somethin' as ugly, wasteful, an' horrible from happenin' again, even if you were Ao incarnate. But I sure as Helm's Ever-Seein' Eyes will back you tryin' to make sure it don't happen very often.~
@11451 = ~[ARAN] That be a nice sentiment. I don't think it be practical, but then again, if you say it... mayhap it will come true.~
@11452 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be an awful thought.~
@11453 = ~[ARAN] No sane one o' us could. But you have a right bit o' depth to you, <CHARNAME>. You can handle this, an' more. Just remember, right or wrong, good or bad, I'd rather have you makin' th' choices rather than th' bastards what would slaughter everyone for no reason at all. I have faith. You will prevail.~
@11454 = ~[ARAN] Before I met you, I tried to forget. I drank, I caroused, I swore, I did anythin' what made me feel like I had some control over a small portion o' my life.~
@11455 = ~[ARAN] Now that I have met you, I put those feelin's into a task, an' an idea. Basically, you be th' reason I can deal wi' everythin'. For right or wrong, when I be at your side, I have a place an' a purpose. That be enough for me.~
@11456 = ~[ARAN] No. But it be a good thing to remind any o' us mere mortals that we are not th' center o' everythin'. An' we can look at this an' let it fuel our revenge, on account o' th' perpetrators o' this atrocity needs be hunted down an' slain like th' beasts they be.~
@11457 = ~[ARAN] That be a nice sentiment. I don't think it be practical, but then again, sometimes I make myself a little space in my head an' go there, all by myself, just to remember what I be fightin' for. Just... just don't be stayin' there too long, eh?~
@11458 = ~[ARAN] Th' problem wi' hidin' away in your head is that your head be attached to th' mortal world. An' hidin' for a little mayhap gives some respite, but it does naught for actually changin' things or protectin' us from bein' th' next target o' this bloodshed.~
@11459 = ~[ARAN] I know I have been awkward an' all, but I should know better. You call th' shots, <CHARNAME>. Do we be fine wi' each other?~
@11460 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a sight. Those stars seem  to cover th' whole sky, or what we can see o' it.~
@11461 = ~[PC] I prefer to keep my eyes focused nearer to reality. The only good use for starlight is exposing your enemies when they are stupid enough to move across open terrain without cover.~
@11462 = ~[PC] They do have a way of reminding us that some things never change. All we do, all we attain, all we suffer... they just keep shining, completely untouched.~
@11463 = ~[PC] They are very cold. Almost eyes, watching us, judging us, evaluating us.~
@11464 = ~[PC] I think they are like small campfires, a host of ones like ours, warm in the night.~
@11465 = ~[PC] I think they seem like they are mocking me. Kind of like women, all shiny and sparkly, yet cold and distant.~
@11466 = ~[PC] They seem... romantic, somehow. Always there, no matter what.~
@11467 = ~[PC] They certainly have one thing going for them. They don't stand around gawking, wasting time, and blathering.~
@11468 = ~[ARAN] Aye. Spoken like a true warrior. Although all killin' an' no imagination probably leaves things a mite bit dull, don't you think?~
@11469 = ~[PC] I don't know. There are so many fascinating and different ways to kill. Why, just think of all the possibilities acid has for creative application.~
@11470 = ~[PC] True enough. I suppose a little time to see the sights is not a bad way to relax.~
@11471 = ~[PC] I have plenty of other thoughts to occupy my mind right now. Some of them are rather unpleasant, but so far we have come out on top. I will sleep as well as can be expected.~
@11472 = ~[PC] You might be right. Sometimes it is nice just to sit and think.~
@11473 = ~[PC] Given the choice between watching the stars, listening to you, and committing ritual suicide, I am pretty sure ritual suicide comes out a winner.~
@11474 = ~[ARAN] They sure be beautiful. So powerful, shinin' down like that. An' so far out o' reach.~
@11475 = ~[ARAN] Talos' an' Teos' Twisted Temper... Thanks a bunch, eh? Now I'll be havin' nightmares all night.~
@11476 = ~[ARAN] You know, you look right fine lit by stars an' th' moon. I can guess why there be so many worshipers o' Selune.~
@11477 = ~[PC] I... I am tired. Have a good night, Aran.~
@11478 = ~[PC] Hey, easy on the compliments. Friends, remember? You are starting to sound all romantic and weepy.~
@11479 = ~[PC] Talking with you here is a nice rest from all of the day's cares. But then again, lots of things besides talking can happen beneath those little twinkling lights.~
@11480 = ~[PC] You are so... stupid. And pushy. Go away and leave me in peace.~
@11481 = ~[ARAN] Well, I'm off. Got th' first watch anyhow. Have a dream or two for me.~
@11482 = ~[ARAN] Gods.~
@11483 = ~[PC] They had a little to do with it, I think. But not much. We survived through our own strength.~
@11484 = ~[PC] Was... was what that ...thing... what it said. Was it true?~
@11485 = ~[PC] (Throw yourself into his arms and press your face against his chest.)~
@11486 = ~[PC] I don't know what to say.~
@11487 = ~[PC] So, a little history lesson for both of us?~
@11488 = ~[ARAN] Th' sounds... gods.~
@11489 = ~[PC] You *are* crying. You let it get to you.~
@11490 = ~[PC] It was so real. An illusion, but so real. I could hear Gorion, and it sounded just like him. See, I am crying, too.~
@11491 = ~[PC] Stop. There is no point in letting the shades of our pasts hurt us like this.~
@11492 = ~[PC] Don't... don't cry. I can't hold things together when you cry.~
@11493 = ~[ARAN] (His arms crush you close, his face hidden from your sight.)~
@11494 = ~[ARAN] That thing... it might have been only a powerful spirit, a reflection. But... It spoke o' things we have not talked about.~
@11495 = ~[PC] It spoke twisted lies to hurt and confuse us, and to separate us.~
@11496 = ~[PC] I don't want to hear any more. The past is the past. For both of us, the past is the past.~
@11497 = ~[PC] (Look into his eyes.)~
@11498 = ~[PC] Aran, look at me... Look into my eyes. I love you.~
@11499 = ~[PC] You heard a twisted view of my life. I heard a twisted view of yours. It is over, and I never want to discuss it ever again. We need to move on, now. Pick up your gear, and help me get things back in order.~
@11500 = ~[ARAN] Truth be th' only way to really clear this burden. What that abomination said, it were true, to a point.~
@11501 = ~[ARAN] There be times when you know an order be just plain wrong, an' you have to make a choice. I chose to follow.~
@11502 = ~[ARAN] Th' details don't rightly matter, but th' result be an ugly truth. Good men can do horrible evil, just by followin' instead o' thinkin'.~
@11503 = ~[PC] Then you have more strength in you than I thought.~
@11504 = ~[PC] I don't want to hear any more. The past is the past. For both of us, the past is the past. Can we stop discussing this?~
@11505 = ~[PC] You really burned innocent children alive, and broke down in battle?~
@11506 = ~[ARAN] I'd say it different. I'd say I followed th' orders to set th' village afire. I'd say I thought there might be some innocents there, an' mayhap th' enemy was shieldin' themselves. I'd say that when I saw th' sight an' heard th' screams, I ran to see if I could undo what had been done...~
@11507 = ~[ARAN] What I had done.~
@11508 = ~[ARAN] But when it be th' truth between my soul an' you, yes. I did.~
@11509 = ~[PC] Get. Away. From. Me.~
@11510 = ~[PC] You had no choice. An order is an order. You could not have been sure. It was not your place to make that choice.~
@11511 = ~[PC] Why have you not told me this before now?~
@11512 = ~[PC] I could say that everything that has happened to us is my fault. That would not be truth. It would be self-pity.~
@11513 = ~[ARAN] You could say that it be self pity. But there be a difference in my case. You didn't choose your blood or th' things what followed. Me, I could say I had no choices...~
@11514 = ~[ARAN] What do you mean?~
@11515 = ~[PC] You knew I would see this as an opportunity, a weakness in your character that I could exploit. You held it from me, even while showing me how much you care for me. That kind of inner strength, I can respect. Can you understand that?~
@11516 = ~[PC] You followed orders, even when you felt that they were wrong. You may have regretted doing so, but you followed. I know now that you will do anything for me, even if it goes against your very soul to do so. That is the kind of control I crave.  Can you understand that?~
@11517 = ~[PC] I do not see things the same way you do, Aran. I know you are hurting, and I hurt because you hurt... but in my eyes, you are blameless. War destroys all it touches, which is why we wield it very carefully. Can you understand that?~
@11518 = ~[PC] You knew even I have limits on what I am willing to do to further my own ends, and you sought to hide something I would never condone so that you could be with me. I don't like that, but I respect that.  Can you understand that?~
@11519 = ~[PC] You risked everything to tell me the truth. If that is not love, then I do not know what love really is.  Can you understand that?~
@11520 = ~[PC] You knew I would not be able to handle the burden of your feelings and my own guilt and frustration. You held this burden away from me. That takes strength.~
@11521 = ~[PC] You risked everything to tell me the truth. If that is not love, then I do not know what love really is. Do you understand what I am saying to you?~
@11522 = ~[PC] I try to do the right thing. But my hands are stained with innocent blood too; there can be no mortal way of stopping the consequences of violent action. But the pain you feel, the guilt, shows a strong conscience. I can love a man who takes responsibility for his actions.~
@11523 = ~[PC] You managed to lie to me every day that we have known each other. You know, I do not need your twisting and hiding the truth. You should leave.~
@11524 = ~[PC] There is no right or wrong in these things, Aran. The same hand that sweeps away a Tyrant kills innocents. Balance, chaos, order... all of those are a part of life on Faerun. We just have to make sense of this for ourselves, and remember we are just passengers on this plane of existence. Do you understand?~
@11525 = ~[PC] Strength of character. You decided when to tell me what you are capable of. I can love a man who shows that kind of restraint.~
@11526 = ~[ARAN] That be a lie. We all have choices, every second o' every day. An' when we make th' wrong ones, we with death in our hands an' blood in our hearts... we kill people. We make that choice.~
@11527 = ~[PC] Would you ever have told me?~
@11528 = ~[PC] Then I am making a choice right now. I think you should leave.~
@11529 = ~[PC] Then I make a choice every minute of every day. I choose to love you.~
@11530 = ~[PC] Aran... You and I know you are not the only person in my life. But I keep choosing to be with you. That should tell you that I can handle both the good and the bad in you. I love you.~
@11531 = ~[PC] I have done worse things than you could ever imagine. War claims all in its path as victims. As I see it, you have no more need of self-recrimination than I need apologize for being the child of a dead god. I can live with that. Can you?~
@11532 = ~[ARAN] I have told no one. Never. Until now.~
@11533 = ~[PC] And you say you love me. You really think I am that weak.~
@11534 = ~[PC] Thank you for telling me the truth. I understand... there are things in all of our pasts that we want buried forever. Do you love me?~
@11535 = ~[ARAN] Now, hold on, I was tryin' to keep th' guilt off of...~
@11536 = ~[PC] I can handle guilt. I can handle blood. I was born to it. What I can't handle is someone who claims to love me, but will hide things from me. You should leave. Now.~
@11537 = ~[PC] I... I understand. You did not think I was strong enough. I don't think you realize how strong a woman can be for the man she loves.~
@11538 = ~[PC] Don't you love me?~
@11539 = ~[PC] I have held things back from you, too. Did you know that I envied Imoen? That I hated Gorion for keeping me away from a life outside the library? That I have killed without remorse, tricked and lied my way through life, and that in spite of it all I can't stop loving a silly do-gooder who can't seem to see exactly how wrong I am for him? Love stinks, doesn't it.~
@11540 = ~[PC] No, you misunderstand me. I am that weak. I... I can see myself, and I hate that woman. I needed to think you were different. Perhaps it is time I grew up, and realized that we all carry burdens. I... I just need your help, sharing the weight between the two of us.~
@11541 = ~[ARAN] Told you wi' out all this? On th' truth an' respect I have for you... no. I would not.~
@11542 = ~[PC] You were wise. I can't have the blood and guilt you bring added to my burdens. You need to find your own path.~
@11543 = ~[ARAN] O' course I do.~
@11544 = ~[PC] Then trust me. No secrets. I am a Child of Murder. If I can handle that truth, then I can handle your truth.~
@11545 = ~[PC] Then say no more about this. What is past is past, and we have a future to plan. Don't let old blood drown a new life together.~
@11546 = ~[PC] Then... I need you to leave. I have the weight of my own guilt to carry. I can't handle both yours and mine.~
@11547 = ~[PC] Then kiss me, and forget the past. We have to focus on what is ahead of us, not what is behind us.~
@11548 = ~[ARAN] You want me to go.~
@11549 = ~[PC] (Turn your back to him, walking away silently.)~
@11550 = ~[PC] Leave.~
@11551 = ~[PC] No. Stay with the party. But stay away from me.~
@11552 = ~[PC] I need time to understand what you did. Just leave me alone for awhile, while I think.~
@11553 = ~[PC] No... I don't want you to go. I don't understand what you did. But I... I can't face the future without you at my side.~
@11554 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap you be right. I learn somethin' new about you almost every day.~
@11555 = ~[ARAN] I don't think I say this right strong enough, or often enough.~
@11556 = ~[ARAN] I love you.~
@11557 = ~[ARAN] Right. Check my gear, eh? It might just be that this ends up as th' mother o' all battles.~
@11558 = ~[PC] Oh, relax.~
@11559 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know how you dealt wi' th' feelin's about that bastard takin' that sister o' yours. It be one thing to have things pushed on you, but on family, that be a heavy burden to carry.~
@11560 = ~[PC] She... she isn't really my sister by blood. Or, she is, but not by mortal blood, you know.~
@11561 = ~[PC] Sisters, sisters... can't live with them, can't live without them. Don't worry, We set him straight. Or rather, we chopped him into little pieces. Why the deep sibling introspection?~
@11562 = ~[PC] Sometimes the greater good requires some sacrifices, but where Imoen is concerned, I think less about the big picture and more about making sure she is safe.~
@11563 = ~[PC] This is a bit too personal for me right now. Just move along, and cut the chatter, Aran.~
@11564 = ~[PC] Stop rehashing old history. Irenicus transgressed, I hit back with everything I had, and now I am here and he no longer has any power at all.~
@11565 = ~[PC] There is always more at play than it seems, Aran. I wanted Imoen back, but there was far more to be gained by hunting down Irenicus then simply rescuing my 'sister'.~
@11566 = ~[ARAN] Now, this be just plain silly. Why in Gond's Great Gears do we have to be blighted walkin' everywhere?~
@11567 = ~[PC] What does that have to do with my mission?~
@11568 = ~[PC] I know it is slow and sometimes painful, but I don't see any alternatives.~
@11569 = ~[PC] We walk because we have feet. Did you want to try sprouting wings?~
@11570 = ~[PC] Because you would get tired of carrying me on your back?~
@11571 = ~[PC] I agree. We should get some horses. Do you know where we can get a few?~
@11572 = ~[PC] If there is some way I could support you on this, please, let me know. I just don't see any good alternatives to using our feet.~
@11573 = ~[PC] Just shut up and let's keep moving.~
@11574 = ~[PC] Less complaining, or I will cut out your tongue and use it as fishbait.~
@11575 = ~[PC] Were you talking, or did you just break wind?~
@11576 = ~[ARAN] I be havin' a right hard time keepin' my mind off o' th' sisters. Yours an' mine, I mean.~
@11577 = ~[PC] Is there something wrong with me?~
@11578 = ~[PC] What are you thinking about now?~
@11579 = ~[PC] I think you have been thinking about the past too much.~
@11580 = ~[PC] Another letter? How do you get mail service around here?~
@11581 = ~[PC] You seem particularly fascinated with the whole 'sister' topic. Is there something I should be aware of?~
@11582 = ~[PC] Do I talk about my family as much as you do?~
@11583 = ~[PC] Are you hinting that your sister might be interested in me, romantically?~
@11584 = ~[PC] If this is a prelude to asking me about Imoen's relationship status so that you can flirt with her, don't bother. You are not truly suitable, you know. I think the phrase is "not husband material".~
@11585 = ~[PC] We should stay focused on our tasks, Aran. Do not let irrelevant matters cloud your mind.~
@11586 = ~[PC] I am having a hard time keeping up with your thoughts and whims. Have I told you lately about the power of dicipline and focus, and how order is the foundation of success?~
@11587 = ~[PC] I would rather you talk about something much more interesting, like me.~
@11588 = ~[PC] Imoen, Imoen, Imoen. She gets all the attention, but sits in the background while I do all the hard work. It was always this way. Even Winthrop liked her better than me.~
@11589 = ~[PC] I think you should concentrate on something more important.~
@11590 = ~[PC] Now, why are you talking about sisters again? I am a much more fascinating topic of conversation.~
@11591 = ~[PC] I understand sisters can be a distraction. I think you should concentrate on something more important.~
@11592 = ~[PC] Why are you pressing this? Do you have feelings for Imoen or something?~
@11593 = ~[PC] I thought I made it clear last time that I was not interested in discussing Imoen, or your sister Elena.~
@11594 = ~[PC] What are you so worried about?~
@11595 = ~[ARAN] Aye, now. I just had a thought.~
@11596 = ~[PC] I don't believe you! Aran? A thought?~
@11597 = ~[PC] So, what is it?~
@11598 = ~[PC] I have thoughts too. They usually don't get communicated that well without actually saying them out loud.~
@11599 = ~[PC] Tell me later. Right now, I don't need the distraction.~
@11600 = ~[PC] If it is about supplies, I already have the full list. Did you want to add something to it?~
@11601 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>... there be times when th' smile on your face makes me right glad to be alive. Your face when th' night just be fallin', your eyes when someone mentions that Irenicus were defeated, an' mayhap once in awhile when you be lookin' my direction. For a moment or two here or there, you look right happy.~
@11602 = ~[PC] There are times when I think things will work out the way I think best. Not often, but there are definitely such times.~
@11603 = ~[PC] I would think that the smile I have just after destroying a particularly fierce foe would be much more satisfying to see.~
@11604 = ~[PC] What about that perpetual good-natured grin you wear? Or does that have nothing to do with me? Let me guess. You are dreaming of wild, willing women.~
@11605 = ~[PC] Stop that. You know that makes me blush.~
@11606 = ~[PC] (Wrap your arms around his neck and pull his lips to yours.)~
@11607 = ~[PC] Dear gods, are you trying to get me into your bed?~
@11608 = ~[PC] Dear gods, are you trying to get me into your bed? Again?~
@11609 = ~[PC] Look, just shut up already. You talk too much.~
@11610 = ~[PC] Can a <PRO_BOYGIRL> get a little peace and quiet around here?~
@11611 = ~[PC] Stop yammering on, will you? Give it a rest.~
@11612 = ~[ARAN] Well, not completely. You done told me that was off limits, an' out o' bounds. But still...~
@11613 = ~[ARAN] Well, not completely. Just holdin' hands an' kissin' be right hard for me, but I can handle it. What I really be tryin' to say, though... well...~
@11614 = ~[ARAN] Do you be blamin' me for appreciatin' such fine beauty that way? I'd do a bit more in th' bed department if you'd let me, you know. But I was tryin' to say...~
@11615 = ~[ARAN] Aye. I would spend a good deal o' my life there wi' you, if you'd let me. But really, what I was tryin' to say...~
@11616 = ~[ARAN] O'course. But there be more important things to think about. I know, shockin', comin' from me, but...~
@11617 = ~[ARAN] Now that was right nice, it was. But hold on a moment. I got somethin' to say, an' it keeps trippin' up my tongue somethin' fierce.~
@11618 = ~[ARAN] I wish there would be more times to show happiness, that be for sure. I keep wonderin' when we will be able to just loosen our weapons an' gear an' enjoy each other's company.~
@11619 = ~[PC] Given our current situation, you should keep one hand on your weapon even when you are kissing me.~
@11620 = ~[PC] What are you... are you trying to say you are thinking about marriage? Settling down? Having children?~
@11621 = ~[PC] (Take his hand in yours.)~
@11622 = ~[PC] We will rest when the job is done.~
@11623 = ~[PC] I thought you always wanted a life of danger, exploration, and everything depending on a flip of Tymora's Coin?~
@11624 = ~[ARAN] (His roughened hands envelop yours, pulling you close.)~
@11625 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I certainly did want all o' that. But that were before I realized that there were an adventure more perilous, more dangerous, an' yet much more rewardin'.~
@11626 = ~[PC] What in Toril are you talking about?~
@11627 = ~[PC] Wait a minute. You are not about to tell me that you love me, are you?~
@11628 = ~[PC] All right. Tell me. What new adventure have you gotten us into, what does it involve, and how much more time are we going to spend wandering about in mortal danger?~
@11629 = ~[ARAN] That depends on th' definition o' willin'... but I certainly have had my share o' dreamin' this particular dream. An' you do figure in it prominently.~
@11630 = ~[PC] I what?~
@11631 = ~[PC] Aran, do you smile at me like that because you love me?~
@11632 = ~[PC] Look, Aran, before you say anything else... I think we should just be friends. I think you may be getting too emotionally involved.~
@11633 = ~[PC] That is very disturbing. You do know you are just a minor diversion, right? I have no grand plans for you and I to found a dynasty or anything.~
@11634 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I am havin' troubles just sayin' it. I mean to say, well.... I think I love you.~
@11635 = ~[PC] Why, I would never have guessed that you had such deep feelings for me. Is that why you constantly try to kiss me?~
@11636 = ~[PC] Why, I would never have guessed that you had such deep feelings for me. Is that why you constantly touch me and kiss me?~
@11637 = ~[PC] Why, I would never have guessed that you had such deep feelings for me. I mean, we have only explored almost everything we can together physically. Well, everything that doesn't make us worried about having children, that is.~
@11638 = ~[PC] Why, I would never have guessed that you had such deep feelings for me. Is that why you keep sharing my bed, and claiming me with such passion?~
@11639 = ~[PC] I love you too. Didn't you already know that?~
@11640 = ~[PC] You are so cute when you get all worked up and emotional. It is such a pity that I just don't feel the same way. I wish we could just keep things simple, and be friends with benefits.~
@11641 = ~[PC] I... look, Aran, I don't feel the same way you do.~
@11642 = ~[PC] I know you do. So what is stopping you?~
@11643 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be a trick, I think, you little minx. You blighted well know that a kiss wi' you drives all thoughts out o' my head. Or do you be talkin' metaphor here? In which case, I think you already have a hand on my weapon...~
@11644 = ~[PC] Well, it drives all thoughts from the head on your shoulders, anyways, but it certainly stirs other things...~
@11645 = ~[PC] You are not about to tell me that you love me or some such nonsense, are you?~
@11646 = ~[PC] I may have a hand on your... 'weapon'. But you have taken all of my heart. Now what is a girl supposed to do with that uneven a trade, may I ask?~
@11647 = ~[PC] I know how you feel about me, if that is what you are trying to say. So, what is stopping you?~
@11648 = ~[ARAN] Hells n... err...~
@11649 = ~[ARAN] Well, now. This be one for Volo's recordbooks.~
@11650 = ~[ARAN] Come to think about it, mayhap I am. Th' marriage, babies, settlin' down. I never did think that were for me. But wi' you, I could see myself makin' it work.~
@11651 = ~[PC] I have though about that, too. I think... I think we could make that work.~
@11652 = ~[PC] We will rest when the job is done. Until then, it is probably too much to be thinking beyond the next few hours or days.~
@11653 = ~[PC] Volo would die laughing rather than write that in one of his tomes. You? Me? Settling down and raising little Bhallspawnlings in a quiet cottage? HAH!~
@11654 = ~[ARAN] Now, which job? Wi' you, every new place you come to gives new quests, new challenges, an' new jobs. Some rewards, too. But in general, there seems naught in th' way o' your job endin' any time soon.~
@11655 = ~[PC] Somehow, the way you are looking at me, I get the feeling you are about to make some important declaration of your deep feelings for me, no matter how hard I try to delay you.~
@11656 = ~[PC] I think we should save such deep matters for another discussion, Aran. We should just be happy with what we have.~
@11657 = ~[PC] Well, if all of our tasks were over, what specifically would you be proposing?~
@11658 = ~[PC] If you are askinhg about my choice of companionship, you know that I am not tied down to any one person right now.~
@11659 = ~[PC] If we are talking about jobs, you do know that you have yet to clean my gear. And there are weapons that need attention. Oh, and you were going to write me some poetry. You seem to have quite a few tasks ahead of you before you get to sleep tonight.~
@11660 = ~[ARAN] Well, yes. But seein' as how you be phrasin' that, I am not so sure that would be a right good idea, eh?~
@11661 = ~[PC] It would be a good idea. Could be a good idea. Oh, I don't know...~
@11662 = ~[PC] Of course it would be a good idea!~
@11663 = ~[PC] You don't have to tell me. You have proven it with actions over and over.~
@11664 = ~[PC] I love you, too.~
@11665 = ~[ARAN] I don't have much in th' way o' balancin' things out, but I were thinkin' o' a simple trade. Your heart be mine, an' mine be yours, straight swap.~
@11666 = ~[PC] You are a scribe. Put it in writing. Wait... even better... pledge your love with a ring.~
@11667 = ~[PC] I love you, Aran... but I also have a very open interpretation. Does this mean you want a committed, monogamous relationship?~
@11668 = ~[PC] I love you too, Aran... but as a friend more than as a life partner. Can't you just be happy with flirting with me?~
@11669 = ~[PC] We are just friends. I know we have been very close friends, perhaps much more, but from now on, we are just friends.~
@11670 = ~[PC] What is stopping you?~
@11671 = ~[PC] Add the condition of absolute fealty to me under any and all circumstances, and I accept. Shall we seal the deal?~
@11672 = ~[ARAN] I hold naught in th' way o' hope that you will stay faithful to me. I can stay faithful, on account o' I can't rightly see myself wi' anyone else. But you... you have a might bit more on your platter than any other person I know. I... I can live wi' that, if it means you will stay wi' me. Rather, if you will let me stay wi' you.~
@11673 = ~[PC] What brought that on? Of course I will be faithful to you.~
@11674 = ~[PC] I... I have never been truly unfaithful to you in my heart. Physical needs are different from spiritual ones.~
@11675 = ~[PC] I cannot truly love you or anyone else completely, remaining faithful the way you are talking about. I am a daughter of Bhaal. Sometimes the feelings are so intense that I must act whether it hurts those who love me or not.~
@11676 = ~[PC] I expect you to challenge anyone with whom I have a romance, and prove your worth.~
@11677 = ~[PC] How can you say that? Wouldn't that hurt you?~
@11678 = ~[PC] Good. I love you, but I cannot have anything that constrains my decisionmaking... including romance.~
@11679 = ~[ARAN] Now, I thought I made myself quite clear on my feelin's long long ago, on account o' all that recreational activity... an I thought you did, too. But somethin' about th' way things have been goin', well, it made me take stock o' what we mean to each other.~
@11680 = ~[PC] Men are so silly. I love you, and I strongly suspect I may have to ask you to marry me some day.~
@11681 = ~[PC] You have made it very clear. In fact, I think you have been waiting a little too long to make our status more... permanent.~
@11682 = ~[PC] All of Toril is plunging into chaos and destruction. Being with you stabilized me and made me feel loved and wanted. But I think am ready now to be a part of something much bigger.~
@11683 = ~[PC] All of Toril is plunging into chaos and destruction. Having some physical comfort made me feel loved and wanted - but it did not really have anything to do with love. But I am happy with hearing you love me.~
@11684 = ~[PC] Physical attraction is not love. If you have that confused, perhaps you don't really love me.~
@11685 = ~[PC] Both you and I could die at any time. Why can't we just enjoy what happening between us, without asking too many questions?~
@11686 = ~[PC] So because I withhold being fully... physical... with our love, my feelings for you are in question?~
@11687 = ~[PC] So I am just another conquest. A minor diversion, to be bedded but not taken too seriously.~
@11688 = ~[ARAN] Sune's Smile, you can't rightly be serious.~
@11689 = ~[PC] If we are ever to be married, you are going to have to change some of your language. According to Hull, in a marriage the woman is always right. Even when she is wrong. Perhaps especially when she is wrong.~
@11690 = ~[PC] I love you, and want to be a part of your life forever. You love me. Why wouldn't I be serious?~
@11691 = ~[PC] I... Wait. I know it seems silly, but... I want you to ask me to marry you. I don't really want to be the one to ask. Officially, I mean.~
@11692 = ~[PC] Why are you looking at me like I just threatened you with torture and death?~
@11693 = ~[ARAN] Stoppin' me?~
@11694 = ~[PC] From kissing me right now?~
@11695 = ~[PC] From holding my hand as we walk together right now?~
@11696 = ~[PC] From tearing through my clothing like a madman, crushing me beneath you, and having your way with my body and soul?~
@11697 = ~[PC] From... from asking me to marry you?~
@11698 = ~[PC] From doing the right thing, and declaring fealty to me as a proper servant should?~
@11699 = ~[ARAN] I... Hells. I... You...~
@11700 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Blackened Bones. I can't rightly say what I need to say right now. I mean, I love you, but...~
@11701 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells.~
@11702 = ~[ARAN] Why, to tell th' truth, not one thing. Not one blighted thing at all.~
@11703 = ~[ARAN] There were a time when that would be enough. Mayhap all this death an' destruction be makin' me think on long term plans more. An' how close to not havin' a chance to start 'em we be just about every day an' night.~
@11704 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap all this death an' destruction be makin' me think on things too fast. You done gave me a thing or two to think about, there.~
@11705 = ~[ARAN] Not to put too fine a point on it, but I get all that *not* bein' married to you. I suspect a little matter o' a ring an' an oath will have naught in th' way o' avoidin' all that, now, will it?~
@11706 = ~[ARAN] That were short, to th' point, an' as painful to hear as a rusty dagger grindin' on my ribcage. But a truth be a truth. If you don't feel what I feel, then I'd rather hear it straight an' be done wi' it than limpin' along nursin' a broken heart.~
@11707 = ~[ARAN] You know, I do be downright lucky.~
@11708 = ~[PC] You have me, so that is true.~
@11709 = ~[PC] You have fallen in love with me.~
@11710 = ~[PC] Well, so far, your cooking has not actually killed anyone. Though that last curry was a little too hot.~
@11711 = ~[PC] I consider myself lucky, as well.~
@11712 = ~[PC] Why are you looking at me that way?~
@11713 = ~[ARAN] I done got word Kartuck be married now. He finally tied th' knot wi' that lass o' his.~
@11714 = ~[PC] So, don't you have something to ask me?~
@11715 = ~[PC] Who is Kartuck?~
@11716 = ~[PC] Were we invited to the wedding?~
@11717 = ~[PC] I like weddings. I like them a lot.~
@11718 = ~[PC] Why on earth would anyone want to get married?~
@11719 = ~[ARAN] Like what?~
@11720 = ~[PC] I thought you might want some kind of assurance. About our love. Something long term.~
@11721 = ~[PC] Oh, I don't know. Something.~
@11722 = ~[PC] Do I have to prompt you for everything?~
@11723 = ~[PC] Think carefully, Aran. And notice the distinct absence of a ring on my finger, symbolizing the eternal circle of love.~
@11724 = ~[PC] Like why we have not talked about getting married.~
@11725 = ~[ARAN] Oh, just an ol' friend from th' 'Fist. They knew better than to invite those o' us what be on th' campaign, since we might be pressed hard to make it back for th' ceremonies.~
@11726 = ~[ARAN] He an' his lady-love be a right fine pair, they do. They has a Helmite marriage, an' then shipped out to Maztica. Apparently, th' food were great, th' drink was strong, an' th' bachelorette party only had three what needed a healer.~
@11727 = ~[ARAN] No troubles wi' th' bachelor party, at least ones talked about, on account o' Hera, she be th' jealous type. But they will be happy enough carvin' out a Freehold in th' colony. His axework be strong, an' her swordwork be quick, an' between th' two there be little what can stop 'em.~
@11728 = ~[PC] They sound like they are well suited to each other. Kind of like you and I are.~
@11729 = ~[PC] So... is there anything you want to ask me?~
@11730 = ~[ARAN] So, if someone asked you to marry them, then you would...~
@11731 = ~[PC] ...tell them they are an idiot and that they are wasting their time. Life is to be experienced, not shackled.~
@11732 = ~[PC] It depends on who is asking.~
@11733 = ~[PC] ...tell them that my boyfriend Aran is going to be very upset if I say yes.~
@11734 = ~[PC] ...tell them that I will ask him to marry me when I am ready. I need to make up my own mind on my own terms.~
@11735 = ~[PC] ...ignore the question.~
@11736 = ~[ARAN] Do that be some kind o' hint?~
@11737 = ~[PC] No, of course not.~
@11738 = ~[PC] Not really. You probably have already realized that I think marriage is a bad idea.~
@11739 = ~[PC] Maybe it is, maybe it isn't.~
@11740 = ~[PC] If by hint, you mean an obvious blazing sign that says "I love you and want to marry you", then sure, I guess it is a hint.~
@11741 = ~[ARAN] I never thought you wanted anythin' like that.~
@11742 = ~[PC] Why not?~
@11743 = ~[PC] I don't. But you might.~
@11744 = ~[PC] Of course. I may not be a woman who wants a small cottage in a nice quiet village with lots of children running around, but that doesn't mean that I don't want love, marriage, and a life partner.~
@11745 = ~[PC] I have a dream that someday, just one little part of my life is normal. A small cottage, a loving husband, children...~
@11746 = ~[PC] I have not really thought about it. But I know I love you, and I know you love me. I think that when that happens, and the time is right, it makes sense that we should be married.~
@11747 = ~[PC] Oh, I am not opposed to the concept of marriage. I am only opposed to the two of us getting married.~
@11748 = ~[ARAN] Well, souls bondin' need souls, an' you were missing a fair part o' yours.  I'd be happy with half, but you... probably not.~
@11749 = ~[PC] I have my full soul now.~
@11750 = ~[PC] I don't mind, but I don't really think I am interested in getting married. But you might be.~
@11751 = ~[PC] I would be happy with anything we share.~
@11752 = ~[PC] I suppose you are right. Besides, I have decided I don't really ever want to get married.~
@11753 = ~[ARAN] Why would you want me?~
@11754 = ~[PC] You have to ask?~
@11755 = ~[PC] Scared?~
@11756 = ~[PC] I don't just want you, Aran. I need you.~
@11757 = ~[PC] I don't want you, don't need you, and I really don't like the whole marriage idea. But then you say something, or turn against the light, and my breath catches in my throat.~
@11758 = ~[PC] I wouldn't want you, or anybody else for that matter. I don't really want to get married.~
@11759 = ~[ARAN] You already know I'd follow you past death's door, an' right into any o' th' various versions o' hell.~
@11760 = ~[PC] A woman wants more.~
@11761 = ~[PC] But how do you know that I would do the same?~
@11762 = ~[PC] You know, I don't think this conversation is headed in the right direction. I am never, ever going to be interested in marrying you.~
@11763 = ~[PC] Sometimes you are just so... so... dense.~
@11764 = ~[ARAN] As for th' whole contract thing, well... I suspect if I were th' marryin' type, it would be you. But since you aren't, then that be a part o' life what I will just skip, on account o' there really never could be anyone else.~
@11765 = ~[ARAN] I were about to say some blighted romantic thing like you already knowin' I'd follow you past death's door, an' right into any o' th' various versions o' hell, but truth be told that last were a mite bit cold. Mayhap you were jokin'. But I was bein' right serious, I was.~
@11766 = ~[ARAN] One day, mayhap right soon, I am goin' to run up against th' gods. An' I am goin' to ask them each in turn why in th' nine hells they made me so's I can never understand women in any way, shape, or form.~
@11767 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I understand. But you grew up wi' her, and it seems like th' bond is more than many feel for their own true sisters.~
@11768 = ~[PC] I thought you had a sister for whom you cared deeply.~
@11769 = ~[PC] I care for Imoen as a close sister. Given that picture you showed me of your Elena, I think I might... I... oh, never mind.~
@11770 = ~[PC] I feel a bond. Usually it is her tying something around me. Why, do you want me to ask her to... oh, sorry. I should not be saying things like that.~
@11771 = ~[PC] I feel a bond. A bond, or a burden, or perhaps a small heavy rock in my shoe. But I shouldn't be talking this freely about such matters.~
@11772 = ~[PC] That is private. But yes, I think so. I mean, I think I have a close bond with Imoen.  Don't you feel close to your sister?~
@11773 = ~[PC] Sometimes I think about her. I mean, sometimes... look, she is pretty.~
@11774 = ~[PC] I... You don't think about your sister in a strange way, right? I don't. Most times.~
@11775 = ~[ARAN] I feel th' same way. I mean, I feel th' same way about my sister. I was goin' through some old letters o' Elena's sent on from th' Waterdeep Mage Academy. I guess I get worried I won't be around for to protect her, th' way you did your sister.~
@11776 = ~[PC] Are you close to your sister? If that isn't too personal, I mean.~
@11777 = ~[PC] Helping the greater good also helps your sister.~
@11778 = ~[PC] I know it is hard to decide which is more important... the people we care about or the common good.~
@11779 = ~[PC] I sympathize, but I need you to put aside your worries and concentrate on what we are doing.~
@11780 = ~[PC] Oh, no worries. After all, a sister's primary responsibility is to drive her older siblings crazy. Early on, it is "hide the books" or "tattletale". When they get older, it is "Help, help, I'm captured by an evil mage and spirited away to be tortured". But you still have to go help.~
@11781 = ~[ARAN] I know, I know. But Imoen reminds me somethin' o my sister Elena, apprenticed away in Waterdeep. An' I find it right hard to avoid thinkin' on how far away from her I am right now, an' how she could get into trouble an' not have her big brother around to protect her.~
@11782 = ~[PC] If your sister is strong, she does not need you. If she is weak, then it is better that she learn how to grow strong without you.~
@11783 = ~[PC] I suppose you are close to your sister. That seems like it would be inconvenient.~
@11784 = ~[PC] I need concentrated, strong forces to face what I am facing. Do you need to take some time and get your head on straight?~
@11785 = ~[PC] This is too personal for me. Just move along, and cut the chatter, Aran.~
@11786 = ~[PC] I need you more than she does.~
@11787 = ~[PC] Oh, great. Another delay or distraction. What is it now, a troublesome sister who has been captured and held for ransom?~
@11788 = ~[ARAN] I figured you might o' been playin' more than one angle there, on account o' you did wander around a bit, doin' all sorts o' things. But Imoen reminds me somethin' o my sister Elena, apprenticed away in Waterdeep. An' I find it right hard to avoid thinkin' on how far away from her I am right now, an' how she could get into trouble an' not have her big brother around to protect her.~
@11789 = ~[PC] It seems like a rather personal concern. I am not sure it is a good idea to share feelings that can be used against you.~
@11790 = ~[PC] It is not always in your best interests to be there for family. Sometimes they need to learn self reliance.~
@11791 = ~[PC] If you really care for her, let her toughen up and learn how to work things to her advantage using just her own skills.~
@11792 = ~[PC] What does your sister have to do with me?~
@11793 = ~[PC] If we are comparing sisters, perhaps we should get some clothing measurements, go out and chat over tea... wait a moment, did you just admit to having a feminine side?~
@11794 = ~[PC] Look, we need to move along. I understand you miss your sister. Let's talk about this later.~
@11795 = ~[ARAN] I be a right proud o' Elena, her wi' her Academy apprenticeship, an' all that mage study she writes about in her letters. True enough, I wish I could go see her. She could light up a room with her eyes literal, now, instead o' figuratively.~
@11796 = ~[PC] You might miss your sister, but do you... do you think is it more important than what we are doing right now?~
@11797 = ~[PC] It seems you are a fan. Not that I blame you, or anything. I think I would want to go see her, too, based on that picture. I would, I mean. Not you.~
@11798 = ~[PC] Should I be jealous of her? She is not the only one who might need some help. Don't you think... aren't I facing greater dangers than she is?~
@11799 = ~[PC] I could say something about you having a big effect on people, too, only with you it is emptying the area with your breath. But that might be rude.~
@11800 = ~[PC] I think I would be proud of her, too. I know Imoen is strong enough to stand on her own two feet, but perhaps it helps to have a big brother in the background, assisting where he can.~
@11801 = ~[PC] I think you should be proud of her. I know I am proud Imoen is strong enough to stand on her own two feet, and I would like to think I helped in some way.~
@11802 = ~[PC] So she spits fire from her eyes? I heard that things were strange in Waterdeep, but I... I never actually believed all the stories. Is she in more danger that we are?~
@11803 = ~[ARAN] I am not sure. I don't expect I have more to worry about than th' usual what happens at Academies. Young lads sniffin' round, stray spells makin' mischief, an' that sort o' thing.~
@11804 = ~[PC] Nothing is stopping you from visiting her.~
@11805 = ~[PC] I might be a lad. I mean, I am a lad. And your sister is very pretty. But I can't go anywhere. Perhaps you should go.~
@11806 = ~[PC] There might be a family connection. I mean, you are.. well, girls seem to like you. And your sister is very pretty. But I can't go anywhere. Perhaps you should go.~
@11807 = ~[PC] So you don't trust young lads around your sister, I bet... because you think they think like you do!~
@11808 = ~[PC] Perhaps you should go visit her, just to settle your mind. If you want to, that is. I have to keep moving forward, I think.~
@11809 = ~[PC] Stray spells and young lads sounds very fun. If I were able to, I might like to visit, and see what people there do. As an observer, you know. Do you want to go check on her?~
@11810 = ~[ARAN] I'll not lightly leave your side.~
@11811 = ~[PC] That is up to you. I'm not pushing you.~
@11812 = ~[PC] I am glad of that. Sometimes, I am not sure I know what I would do without you.~
@11813 = ~[PC] You will not go anywhere lightly, I think. I suspect you have, well... have put on several pounds from all that cooking you do.~
@11814 = ~[PC] I know. And I would go with you, if I could.~
@11815 = ~[PC] Oh, you might. I mean, you do seem to like looking at young ladies, and I bet the whole academy is full of temptations.~
@11816 = ~[ARAN] Why, sure, on account o' you bein' so girly, an' all. I said to myself th' other day, "self, <CHARNAME> would make a right fine little sister, on account o' th' way he always do be actin' all girly."~
@11817 = ~[PC] So you really want to be stripped and sent naked into a spider's lair, just so we can steal your gear and move on? I think you are asking for trouble, boyo.~
@11818 = ~[PC] We could get a song and dance team going, and title ourselves "Faerun's Fighting Females". Gods, did I just say that? What a horrible idea. And dangerous, too.~
@11819 = ~[PC] Girly, shmirly. I get the job done, in spite of the dangers we face. Liches, dragons, the occasional accidental injury caused by inattentive comrades...~
@11820 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be completely wrong, I don't rightly think o' you in that way at all.~
@11821 = ~[PC] I was teasing you, Aran. I don't think you have as much to worry about as I did, though.~
@11822 = ~[PC] What a pity. I would make such a good little sister for you. I would have you worrying about all sorts of interesting things, most of whom are poisonous, dangerous, undead, or all three combined.~
@11823 = ~[PC] That is a good thing, as I think some of the things we might feel about each other might be considered inappropriate. Wait, that was a poor choice of words...~
@11824 = ~[ARAN] Hey, that be unfair! That were an accident, by Helm's Fist. I just didn't see you there. I done apologized, too! But on th' dangers we face, compared to the usual, well...~
@11825 = ~[ARAN] No, not too personal. I think I am right close to her. I write to her often enough.~
@11826 = ~[PC] I don't mean to pry into your business. It is just... well, I have a had time balancing what is right, and what is right for Imoen.~
@11827 = ~[PC] It sounds like you have found a way to balance both being part of her life and following our cause.~
@11828 = ~[PC] It sounds like you have found some balance in your life. I am glad, as it helps you be a stronger companion when you have more vested interest in my cause.~
@11829 = ~[PC] I suppose that would work for some people. Me, I have a hard time being close to a person through a bunch of scratchy ink blots on some vellum.~
@11830 = ~[PC] Look, we need to move along. I understand - you miss your sister, and wish we were able to back her up the way I did Imoen. Let's talk about this later.~
@11831 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know if there be a good balance to be had. On th' one hand, protectin' you is protectin' her from some seriously nasty things happenin' to her as well as th' world. On th' other hand, she be my responsibility, directly.~
@11832 = ~[PC] Sometimes just being there is not the right decision. Sometimes... sometimes being there puts a sister in more danger.~
@11833 = ~[PC] I failed to protect Imoen. Irenicus took her and tortured her, and I will never be truly able to atone for that.~
@11834 = ~[PC] I guess feelings about protecting little sisters are the same everywhere, to some degree. We agree on that.~
@11835 = ~[PC] We both care about our 'family', whether bonded by the blood of  god, the blood of a normal parent, or just bonded because of our adopted companions.~
@11836 = ~[PC] If you call having to chase Imoen's captors across the face of Toril while scrounging for coin and resources in the process "protecting", then I don't think that word means what you think it means.~
@11837 = ~[ARAN] Do you give naught in th' way o' thinkin' about balancin' th' two sides?~
@11838 = ~[PC] I give it thought. But the common good always ends up being the course I try to take.~
@11839 = ~[PC] Not really. There is doing the right thing, and then after that if there is a way of taking personal feelings into account, I do that, too.~
@11840 = ~[PC] Think about it? Yes. Actually find a balance? Well, look at the last few months, and you have your answer.~
@11841 = ~[PC] Fortunately or unfortunately, Imoen is my weak spot. After she is safe, I start thinking about the rest of the world.~
@11842 = ~[PC] Balancing acts are for circuses. I don't have time to think farther than the next battle, the next challenge, and the next creature trying to rip the flesh from my bones or the spirit from my body.~
@11843 = ~[ARAN] I can say naught but support for that. I have been on th' receivin' end o' more than my own share o' teasin'. I give as good as I get, though. It be harder now that most o' th' time we speak only through letters.~
@11844 = ~[PC] So you communicate with her regularly, and that balances out not living closer to her?~
@11845 = ~[ARAN] Elena an' I have had plenty o' practice at that kind o' communication. I sent her back letters from every place I could get to, an' she has kept in touch wi' me th' same way. Sometimes it is a mite bit o' a delay from th' time we say somethin' to th' time it gets read. It is right hard to keep family ties goin' when everyone has so much physical distance between them.~
@11846 = ~[ARAN] On balance, I think th' kinds o' trouble I get into wi' you are th' kinds where if we don't take care o' it right away, Elena will feel th' effects for th' rest o' her life. Or do you be talkin' about Imoen?~
@11847 = ~[PC] Imoen.~
@11848 = ~[PC] I guess feelings about protecting little sisters are the same everywhere, to some degree.~
@11849 = ~[PC] Just how many sisters do you think I have? Wait a moment... OK, let me rephrase. I don't consider Bhaal wandering around sowing his seed all over creation as creating a family. Imoen, on the other hand, is the only real family I have left.~
@11850 = ~[ARAN] That we do. But there be times when they have to just take care o' themselves, I guess.~
@11851 = ~[PC] Sometimes the best way to help is... standing back and letting things happen.~
@11852 = ~[PC] I don't think standing in the background doing nothing is easy. Sometimes it is all we can do.~
@11853 = ~[PC] She is your sister. You can't just sit there and ignore your feelings. You have to do something.~
@11854 = ~[PC] You are worried about your sister. I am worried about the Prophecies currently bathing Faerun in a sea of blood.~
@11855 = ~[PC] At least the power-hungry arch-villain mage suitor scenario seems unlikely.~
@11856 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, by Corellon's Bow-hand, there were naught you could do. He captured you, too, by your account. Th' worry wi' Elena be much less than that kind o' situation. I be worried on account o' lads sniffin' 'round, not on account o' twisted power-mad villains draggin' her off.~
@11857 = ~[PC] I think there is always more that I could do. I just don't have the confidence to do it.~
@11858 = ~[PC] The power-hungry arch-villain mage suitor scenario seems unlikely.~
@11859 = ~[PC] Just because it is not a power-mad arch enemy does not mean your feelings are unimportant. But listen to what you just said - you are worried about her suitors, not her life being in danger.~
@11860 = ~[PC] Well, I suppose we could send a warning message to our enemies, letting them know that they should delay taking over all of creation while we check on who your sister is thinking of dating...~
@11861 = ~[ARAN] True enough. Do you ever tell her that?~
@11862 = ~[PC] Hells, no.~
@11863 = ~[PC] Hells, yes. Daily. Or whenever I can.~
@11864 = ~[PC] I... look, I have some difficulties expressing my feelings sometimes.~
@11865 = ~[PC] Do you tell your sister that you love her and feel like you need to protect her?~
@11866 = ~[PC] Imoen knows. I don't have to tell her.~
@11867 = ~[ARAN] Well, I do. Not Imoen, o' course. I mean I tell Elena.~
@11868 = ~[ARAN] I do, too. Not Imoen, o' course. I mean I tell Elena.~
@11869 = ~[ARAN] Well, I do. Not Imoen, o' course. I mean I tell Elena. Expressin' those feelin's be easier in a letter, though. Face to face, it just seems kind o' awkward.~
@11870 = ~[ARAN] Hells, yes. I do. Not Imoen, o' course. I mean I tell Elena, every single letter.~
@11871 = ~[ARAN] I suppose that might be true. But sisters be females, an' it seems to me that it don't hurt none to be right clear about th' whole feelin's thing right up front. She might punch your arm an' get all silly, but it be worth it to make sure she knows how you feel.~
@11872 = ~[ARAN] I guess I should not worry about Elena so much. I write to her as often as I be able, an' I tell her every time right specific that I value her. I keep right on it, on account o' Faerun be a hazardous place to make a life, an' backin' you increases th' odds that any one o' those letters might be th' last one. I don't want to be beggin' Tymora for a moment to set things clear wi' her.~
@11873 = ~[ARAN] I do think you have a point. I just worry, is all. A brother's prerogative, I guess.~
@11874 = ~[PC] I... I can't hold you here, you know. If you needed to go check on her...~
@11875 = ~[PC] You have the right to worry, the right to share that worry with friends, and even the right to go make sure everything is fine yourself.~
@11876 = ~[PC] Sometimes you have to just let a little sister grow up and handle her own business. You can't let worry harm your readiness.~
@11877 = ~[PC] I thought it was a brother's prerogative to try and intimidate any potential suitors, to call her childhood nicknames in public, and share embarrassing stories about her until she blushes and threatens violence.~
@11878 = ~[ARAN] I have confidence in you.~
@11879 = ~[PC] That is not enough.~
@11880 = ~[PC] You are a good friend to say so.~
@11881 = ~[PC] I don't think confidence has anything to do with how you feel about being away from your sister. I think that might be a matter of trust.~
@11882 = ~[PC] This isn't about me, or about you. It is about whether you think Elena is any real danger. I don't think she is.~
@11883 = ~[PC] Are you asking to go up to Waterdeep and see for yourself how she is doing?~
@11884 = ~[PC] I appreciate that.~
@11885 = ~[PC] The world needs people who are ready to put aside personal fears, however small, and just do the right thing. I am glad you are part of the team.~
@11886 = ~[PC] I need to prevail. There is too much harm that could be done to too many people if I fail. I am glad you are at my side, helping me finish this.~
@11887 = ~[PC] No, I suppose not... you have been eating way too much of your own cooking for you to do anything 'lightly', my friend!~
@11888 = ~[ARAN] Aye, that too. Just like it be her prerogative to try to fix you up wi' her friends, steal th' best part o' any meal you share, tell you your fashion sense be that o' a troll,  an' generally tease th' livin' hells out o' you at every opportunity.~
@11889 = ~[ARAN] That don't rightly track wi' what you did to protect Imoen, now, do it?~
@11890 = ~[PC] Imoen was a side issue. Irenicus should not have tried to challenge me in that way.~
@11891 = ~[PC] I can have the luxury of having family ties, especially as they are divine. You can't.~
@11892 = ~[PC] That is different. I think you could find much more advantage and protection for your sister if you support me and stay with me. I am a force to be reckoned with.~
@11893 = ~[PC] No, I don't suppose it does. But you are not a Bhaalspawn. You can't even begin to understand the powers fighting within me, and what I need to do to keep them under my control.~
@11894 = ~[PC] Look, I know you mean well, but you just don't see the world the way I do. Where you see support and emotion, I see lines of power and control. You have been a strong force at my side, and I need you there until I say otherwise, regardless of what I may choose or not choose to do.~
@11895 = ~[ARAN] There be naught in th' way o' need for that, I think. I have no word as to any real problems, only my own imagination.~
@11896 = ~[PC] You have a big imagination, it seems. I would think you would have cut ties with any family you had, given that you are supporting my cause now.~
@11897 = ~[PC] Look, we need to move along. I understand - you miss your sister, and wish we were able to back her up. Now shut up and get moving.~
@11898 = ~[PC] Then wouldn't it be in your best interests to curb that imagination, and get back to business?~
@11899 = ~[PC] Stop inventing problems that don't exist. We have enough to deal with. Unless you have some proof that something is wrong, let her fight out her own problems.~
@11900 = ~[PC] Given your imagination, you must think she is being pursued by a maddened curry, several kobold shaman, and a demon from the abyss. Of the three, the demon would make the most powerful choice of mate, I think.~
@11901 = ~[ARAN] No, you blighted well don't. I am what they call "expendable". But th' sentiment be nice to hear.~
@11902 = ~[PC] Look, we need to move along. I understand - now shut up and get moving.~
@11903 = ~[PC] Wouldn't it be in your best interests to curb that imagination, and get back to business? I didn't make you a part of my team so that you could indulge in overprotective sibling behavior.~
@11904 = ~[PC] I don't deal in sentiment, only raw power. I have invested heavily in you, knowing that you are a very useful tool. You do know that you are beholden to me, right?~
@11905 = ~[PC] Well, I have a soft spot for you. I can't seem to help myself. By the way, if you desert this party to go of on some family reunion weekend, I will hunt you down and kill you myself.~
@11906 = ~[ARAN] Now, no call to be so testy, eh? I have naught in th' way o' bad news. I just get a mite protective o' my sister, is all.~
@11907 = ~[PC] Why does everyone always seem to need to go rescue some family member from danger, just when things seem to be getting worse than could ever be imagined?~
@11908 = ~[PC] I understand - you miss your sister, and wish we were able to back her up. Now shut up and get moving.~
@11909 = ~[PC] By the way, if you desert this party to go off on some family reunion weekend, I will hunt you down and kill you myself.~
@11910 = ~[ARAN] Oh, blighted hells... I try to talk straight to you, an' all you can do is make fun o' me. Stick your left fist where th' sun don't shine. I'll just go blighted well check on th' gear.~
@11911 = ~[PC] Don't sulk too long. We have places to go and things to kill.~
@11912 = ~[PC] You will not get away with swearing at me without repercussions, sellsword. I settle up with those who show me disrespect.~
@11913 = ~[PC] You are so touchy today. Get some sleep tonight, and get a better attitude, or your time with me will come to a very short end.~
@11914 = ~[PC] I am in no mood for talking about family problems. I have enough of my own right now.~
@11915 = ~[PC] I am sorry you feel like you have been wronged. Now check that gear and get back to work. This is no time for sentimentality and deep discussion.~
@11916 = ~[PC] You follow me, but you don't really embrace the power and control I exert. I would think you would be against me, trying to stop my rise to power, to protect her from coming under my control.~
@11917 = ~[ARAN] Well, I suspect I have naught in th' way o' grand villains capturin' her an' runnin' off th' god's only knows where. Th' worst might be a lad what be a little too amorous for his own good.~
@11918 = ~[PC] Perhaps it might be advantageous to have some eyes and ears in Waterdeep, after all. I am going ahead with my plans, but you might take a quick trip north if you need to.~
@11919 = ~[PC] I am not going to travel all the way up to Waterdeep.~
@11920 = ~[PC] That is up to you. I'm not pushing you~
@11921 = ~[PC] You are damned right you won't. I don't take kindly to betrayal or wavering of any kind.~
@11922 = ~[PC] Sure, you go right along and visit your sister. I will just sit here and wait for you, delaying all my plans... you do know that I could never let that happen, right?~
@11923 = ~[PC] Look, I don't understand your position at all. But you have been useful to me, so if you have to go play nursemaid, I won't stop you or exact retribution. If you go, you had better make it a quick trip. Things look like I may need you soon.~
@11924 = ~[PC] Lightly is not an adjective I would use to describe anything about you, Aran. Too much curry lately? Your sword belt seems excessively tight...~
@11925 = ~[ARAN] You may not think th' way I do, but I cast my lot in wi' you. I can be a damned strong ally, an' that might protect Elena. Hells, look at it this way... th' way things be goin' on th' Sword Coast, I'd rather be backin' you an' seekin' your protection than followin' any o' th' bastards what be our opponents. You, I can talk to.~
@11926 = ~[PC] I don't need allies. I need servants.~
@11927 = ~[PC] Serve me well, and you have nothing to fear.~
@11928 = ~[PC] I appreciate and reward loyalty and trust, however misguided it is.~
@11929 = ~[PC] I don't know if it is a weakness or a strength, but at least I know I have one person I can trust to be predictable - you.~
@11930 = ~[PC] I will keep that in mind. I do have a reputation for doing whatever I want, though... something perhaps you should keep in mind.~
@11931 = ~[ARAN] Hey, I trust you, don't I? Well, to a point, anyways.~
@11932 = ~[PC] You are a fool to trust me. I never did understand that about you. You don't see things my way, yet you follow me. Are you that weak?~
@11933 = ~[PC] And I trust you. At least, I trust you more than I usually trust someone. I guess that counts as friendship. I can't afford to have many friends.~
@11934 = ~[PC] Trust is a silly idea, unless it is backed up with coercion or force to ensure that it can't be broken. I bet that is why you are worried about your sister. You don't trust her because you have no control over her.~
@11935 = ~[PC] I don't give trust lightly, and usually it ends when someone is out of my sight. I... I just have been harmed so many times.~
@11936 = ~[PC] At the very least, I am predictable. So are you. Perhaps that is why we work well together, in spite of your silly soft ideas.~
@11937 = ~[PC] Perhaps I have a weak spot for her. More likely, I could find advantage in the circumstances surrounding her abduction.~
@11938 = ~[PC] That is my concern, not yours. I am not sure it is a good idea for anyone to share feelings that can be used against them later.~
@11939 = ~[PC] It is in both our interests to keep family out of our discussions. Just be glad you don't have a god's blood running through your family veins, and shut the hells up about your sister already.~
@11940 = ~[ARAN] Th' world don't rightly revolve around you, do it?~
@11941 = ~[PC] Actually, it does.~
@11942 = ~[PC] It should, but it doesn't seem to. If you need to go make sure your sister is not in any danger, you could just go, I suppose.~
@11943 = ~[PC] There is no pressing need to deal with family issues while the entire face of Faerun descends into war.~
@11944 = ~[PC] You know, you follow me, but you don't really embrace the power and control I exert. I would think you would be against me, trying to stop my rise to power, to protect her from coming under my control.~
@11945 = ~[PC] Alas, my one weakness... modesty.~
@11946 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly admit naught in th' way o' such a thing. Besides, we be talkin' about our sisters, not discussin' teatime.~
@11947 = ~[PC] Actually, the only really important part of our discussion is how it impacts my plans.~
@11948 = ~[PC] Sisters and tea have little to do with my plans. If you feel strongly about how your sister is faring, you might visit her.~
@11949 = ~[PC] Imoen might be my one weakness. Well, either that, or putting up with you.~
@11950 = ~[ARAN] I don't think like you do, somehow. Not outside o' combat, I don't. I suspect that be part o' why I never could gather th' skills to hold a group together on my own leadership.~
@11951 = ~[PC] Look, if it bothers you, nothing is stopping you from visiting her.~
@11952 = ~[PC] Worrying about family is the first thing you need to forget if you are ever going to be a leader, Aran. You need to learn to make the tough decisions, and not let emotion cloud your better judgment.~
@11953 = ~[PC] To be fair, there are people who think like you do who are very effective leaders. I don't understand how they do it without coercion, fear, manipulation, or showing power, but they do. You just must not have it in you to lead.~
@11954 = ~[PC] You don't need to think like me. In fact, that is why I keep you around. I want someone who supports me, not someone who constantly challenges me. Perhaps that is one of my weaknesses.~
@11955 = ~[PC] Do you need time to get this out of your system, so that we can get on with my business?~
@11956 = ~[PC] You are damned right you won't. I don't take kindly to betrayal or wavering of any kind, and you know that leaving me at this point would be the worst kind of betrayal. I don't let many people in on my plans.~
@11957 = ~[PC] Look, sometimes I don't understand you at all. But you have been useful to me, so if you have to go play nursemaid, I won't stop you or exact retribution. If you go, you had better make it a quick trip, though. Things look like I may need you soon.~
@11958 = ~[ARAN] Do this be one o' them "do as I be sayin' not as I be doin'" things? On account o'you seemed to deal wi' Imoen in a completely different way from what you be describin'.~
@11959 = ~[PC] Do not discuss Imoen again, or I will show you exactly how much you have displeased me.~
@11960 = ~[PC] Yes, it is one of those things. If you don't like my advice, you can leave any time you think you need to... and suffer the consequences.~
@11961 = ~[PC] Let's just say that I needed to relearn that particular lesson myself. I am as close to perfect as a mortal can get, but even I can learn something from time to time.~
@11962 = ~[PC] I have a certain weakness for her. I am not proud of it, but I acknowledge it. And I take steps to ensure she can not be used against my interests again.~
@11963 = ~[ARAN] You don't have any blighted weaknesses. I don't like th' way you do things sometimes, but I can't say you haven't made defeats into victories an' kept us alive, mostly.~
@11964 = ~[PC] Flattery will not get you what you want, Aran, if what you want is for me to give you permission to go all the way up to Waterdeep so you can have a family reunion.~
@11965 = ~[PC] I have a huge weakness. I let you distract me with all this talk about family. Don't you know it really drives me crazy?~
@11966 = ~[PC] I may not seem to at times, but I have a huge weakness. I let my friends into my plans, and help them as well as I help myself. Some would call that a waste of time. I consider it good business.~
@11967 = ~[PC] A good acknowledgment of one's weaknesses makes one stronger. Perhaps you need some time to reflect on that.~
@11968 = ~[ARAN] I know.~
@11969 = ~[ARAN] Well, it does, a bit. We could move a might faster, you know.~
@11970 = ~[ARAN] I see a right fine set o' alternatives, I do...~
@11971 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells... keep your voice down, eh? I know Aerie has a mite bit more self confidence now, but th' whole wing thing most likely will bother her on some level for th' rest o' her life. No provokin' more waterworks, for all th' god's sake.~
@11972 = ~[ARAN] Now that would be a right fine joke, now, wouldn't it. I don't see where I'd be stuffin' a set o' wings in this here armor, that be for sure.~
@11973 = ~[ARAN] Do we be talkin' physically, or just metaphorically?~
@11974 = ~[PC] Watch it, sellsword. I am an easy woman to understand. I *always* mean physically.~
@11975 = ~[PC] I can just see it, the two of us, battling dragons, me riding your shoulders, cuddled up around your head...~
@11976 = ~[PC] Do you even know what 'metaphorically' means?~
@11977 = ~[PC] I could try to ride your front, if you want, instead... but somehow I think that would be a little distracting. Especially when I kiss you.~
@11978 = ~[PC] It would be more romantic if you carried me in your arms, instead.~
@11979 = ~[PC] Don't you want to feel my thighs clasped firmly around you, holding on tight?~
@11980 = ~[PC] Oh, come on, Aran... give me a piggy-back ride!~
@11981 = ~[ARAN] Look, we be one o' th' most powerful forces on th' face o' Toril, but do we ride horses around? Do we use one o' them flyin' Calimshan carpet contraptions? Do we summon levitation spells an' waft are way about, pretty as a feather? No. We blighted slog through th' crap like we was green recruits doin' basic trainin'.~
@11982 = ~[PC] I am doing just fine on my own two feet.~
@11983 = ~[PC] We would if we could. But we need to concentrate on basics. Feeding and protecting animals, securing magical items, all of that distracts from our mission. We can't expend magic on things that we can do with our own two feet.~
@11984 = ~[PC] Have you seen any horses to buy, or carpets to steal? Have you ever managed to cast a levitate spell that lasts for hours on end and doesn't subject us to the first strong wind blowing us into a ravine?~
@11985 = ~[PC] You are doing just fine on your own two feet. Think of it as muscle maintenance.~
@11986 = ~[PC] I may be one of the most powerful forces on the face of Toril. You are just the smelliest.~
@11987 = ~[PC] Now you are just whining. Shut up, or I will trade you in for something useful, like a smart-talking two-handed sword with delusions of grandeur.~
@11988 = ~[PC] Dear gods, you never shut up, do you?~
@11989 = ~[PC] All I hear is whine, whimper, cry. Are you really a sellsword, or do you just play one at the Ten Taverns Amateur Acting Night?~
@11990 = ~[PC] Oh, fine. You get on my back, and I will carry you.~
@11991 = ~[ARAN] Well, I might... but there be a big problem. I somehow think a horse might not last in that little plane o' th' hells you created. They might make th' trip, but keepin' 'em in their right mind might be dangerous.~
@11992 = ~[PC] I could make it calming for them, I think.~
@11993 = ~[PC] Good point. So basically, horses are a bad idea.~
@11994 = ~[PC] Well, what about some of those flying Calimshan carpets? Do you have any sources for those?~
@11995 = ~[PC] There is also that whole talk you gave me one night about how horses are force multipliers, but come with heavy costs... food, care, and the fact that you become a big shiny monster target...~
@11996 = ~[PC] I do remember something about how keeping close to the ground and reducing the potential angles of attack made better tactical sense. In fact, I think you have said that about two hundred times.~
@11997 = ~[PC] Watch it, sellsword. Joking with me is gambling with Fate. Not many have bet against her and lived.~
@11998 = ~[PC] Physically, of course. I can just see it, the two of us, battling dragons, me riding your shoulders like a child...~
@11999 = ~[PC] You carry your fair share of battles, Aran. I was only joking about with you.~
@12000 = ~[PC] I love a man with quick wit. When are you going to introduce me to one?~
@12001 = ~[PC] I love a man with quick wit. It lightens my day.~
@12002 = ~[ARAN] To be fair, this whole poppin' in an' out o' existence cuts down a fair bit on th' walkin'. I do remember traipsin' around a good deal more back when we didn't have no option like that.~
@12003 = ~[PC] So why were you complaining?~
@12004 = ~[PC] I think of it as my home away from home, complete with butler. Hey, I don't have to worry about you there! Nothing for you to break!~
@12005 = ~[PC] I am glad that having sections of my soul torn and ripping open the fabric of reality let you take it easy on your feet. Next time, it is your turn to be the primary target of a dead god and his minions.~
@12006 = ~[PC] Aran, there is an old Candlekeep saying... "Let not the reader complain of the words already inscribed, for they are the past. Let the knowledge in them carry the future forward".~
@12007 = ~[ARAN] Well, I might... but there be a big problem. I somehow think a group o' us flyin' off between areas on a raft o' them contraptions might give away our position, an' make it a bit tougher to be stealthy. Plus, Dragons. They fly. Though it might cut down on th' number o' undead we run across... wait, nope. Vampires fly too. Blighted hells.~
@12008 = ~[ARAN] I do guess we might bring up some problems wi' th' whole idea. I just don't like walkin' around. Everywhere. Constantly. Especially when there be wagons, carts, airships, magical equipment, boats... well, you get th' idea.~
@12009 = ~[PC] I wish there were a better way, Aran. But I think we are stuck with just using our feet. It has served well enough for a long time now.~
@12010 = ~[PC] Just think of how wonderful that footbath and massage will feel when you finally get a chance to indulge..~
@12011 = ~[ARAN] Right. I guess I be doin' too much grousin', on account o' you mostly do th' right thing by people. If you saw th' need, you would provide it.~
@12012 = ~[PC] I figure you are smart, dexterous, and tough. A little walking won't kill you. It will make you stronger and more able to pick those locks and dodge those traps.~
@12013 = ~[PC] You may be wielding some decent magic now, but I always think it is good to stick to basics, too. You wouldn't want to lose all that fighting muscle, now, would you?~
@12014 = ~[PC] The gods provide you with spells, but you have to be strong enough to carry the gear and protect yourself. There is no sense in taking the easy way out.~
@12015 = ~[PC] Just think of it as a necessary evil bound to the fighting profession. Besides, getting up on a horse makes you a much larger target, or so you have told me...~
@12016 = ~[PC] We need to concentrate on basics. Feeding and protecting animals, securing magical items, all of that distracts from our mission. We can't expend magic on things that we can do with our own two feet.~
@12017 = ~[PC] Plus, I tend to listen when a trusted military advisor says "no horses... too big, too hard to feed, to hard to heal, and too hard to keep quiet when a blighted great dragon comes swooping down on you. Wasn't it you who said "swooping is bad"? Or was it someone else?~
@12018 = ~[PC] It would be so much easier if you would just understand that I am right. Well, once I thought I was wrong, but it turns out I was mistaken, so I was actually right.~
@12019 = ~[ARAN] You know, sometimes it be more than about you, eh? You do right by most folks, I know. But this walkin' business, it don't seem like you are lookin out for th' party.~
@12020 = ~[PC] A little walking won't kill you. It will make you stronger and more able to pick those locks and dodge those traps. You don't have to sulk about it.~
@12021 = ~[PC] You may be wielding some decent magic now, but you wouldn't want to lose all that fighting muscle, now, would you?~
@12022 = ~[PC] The gods provide you with spells, but you have to be strong enough to carry the gear and protect yourself. If you don't like it, you could try praying for some support.~
@12023 = ~[PC] I thought you said getting up on a horse makes you a much larger target, and that flying opponents are much more vulnerable.~
@12024 = ~[PC] It sounds more like you are just grumbling about your feet, and not really thinking things through. I think I have proven that I look out for more than my own interests.~
@12025 = ~[PC] That isn't fair at all. I talk to you, and I take your ideas into consideration. This isn't about me, or my needs. If I could have found alternatives, I would have.~
@12026 = ~[ARAN] That would figure. Another way to torture me an' still make it be all about you.~
@12027 = ~[PC] Walking will make you stronger and more able to pick those locks and dodge those traps, doing my bidding. You don't have to sulk about it.~
@12028 = ~[PC] You may be wielding magic now, but I don't want to have you lose all that fighting muscle.~
@12029 = ~[PC] The gods provide you with spells, but you have to be strong enough to carry the gear and protect yourself. If you don't like it, take it up with them. Until then, stop crying about it.~
@12030 = ~[PC] Your words, your analysis... you said getting up on a horse makes you a much larger target, and that flying opponents are much more vulnerable.~
@12031 = ~[PC] I don't want to torture you, Aran. I want to make sure you are useful to my goals. If I make you suffer, it is for a reason.~
@12032 = ~[PC] If it were all about you, do you think I would be here?~
@12033 = ~[PC] True, all too true. After all, my usual day starts with squishing small squirrels, and wandering about thinking up ways to torture you and make your life miserable. Then I eat a hearty breakfast, and get to the job of making your life a living hell.~
@12034 = ~[ARAN] I done forgot again. Everythin' be about you.~
@12035 = ~[PC] Walking will make you stronger and more able to pick those locks and dodge those traps, doing my bidding. Think of it as job protection.~
@12036 = ~[PC] I won't have you lose all that fighting muscle. Spells will only take you so far, and I expect you to be both might and magic, if I am going to have a use for you here.~
@12037 = ~[PC] You said getting up on a horse makes you a much larger target, and that flying opponents are much more vulnerable. Don't cry when I actually take your advice... be thankful I acknowledge that you are useful to me, in a minor way.~
@12038 = ~[PC] Absolutely. And don't forget it again. A man who serves me well could accomplish many things. A man who annoys me could accomplish many things, but none of them would be the sort of thing they really want.~
@12039 = ~[PC] Don't make it be about you. There is only room for one leader.~
@12040 = ~[ARAN] Funny, funny, funny. Don't trouble yourself none... I will find somethin' to break even there, by Tymora's Bright Coin. But I still think we could do better than usin' our feet.~
@12041 = ~[ARAN] I suppose you be right. Most times, you are. But my feet get right sore, an' I don't have no other outlet than to complain, eh?~
@12042 = ~[PC] I think we are better served by complaining only about things we can actually do something about.~
@12043 = ~[PC] What is the use of complaining? The gods seem to have a strange sense of humor on that one. Complain too little, and they cause you mischief. Complain too much, and they give you more mischief.~
@12044 = ~[ARAN] I suppose you might look at it that way, you havin' a mean streak an' all. Though I suppose I should be thankful you don't come up wi' more insidious ways o' makin' my life hell.~
@12045 = ~[PC] Stop thinking. It makes it harder for me to control you, and therefore makes you less useful to my goals. I like you, Aran. I wouldn't want to have to get rid of you.~
@12046 = ~[PC] Actually, I thought about having you carry some rocks in your gear, just to toughen you up more, but I need you rested enough for combat. I may have my own interests at heart, but my interests do end up lining your pocket and making you more powerful, so it might be time to shut up and soldier, soldier.~
@12047 = ~[ARAN] Figures. Right, right, got it... strength an' control gives th' biggest rewards. I should look for ways o' turnin' th' walkin' into an advantage. None o' that soft goodie-two-shoes help th' other guy out... toughen up or get th' blighted hells out o' th' way.~
@12048 = ~[PC] Absolutely. You are learning. I have high hopes, for you, Aran. Either you will be a valuable asset, or a strong rival. I look forward to the day when you finally grow a spine, and I get to crush you back into submission.~
@12049 = ~[ARAN] You do have a good point there. I think I'd best be shuttin' up an' gettin' back to th' job at hand.~
@12050 = ~[ARAN] It be a real surprise you survived that place. I like a simpler way o' sayin' it... 'Don't bother complaining - just fix it, kill it, or ignore it, and move on'.~
@12051 = ~[ARAN] (mutter) Blighted hells... 'Let not th' Shar-kissed book-looker get <PRO_HISHER> panties in a twist, or <PRO_HESHE will blighted well use Cyric-Buggerin' fancy-pants phraseology an' bore th' livin' daylights out o' th' poor sod who just doesn't want his feet to hurt so bad...~
@12052 = ~[ARAN] Aye... it be all fun an' games, until th' wyrm strikes and we find ourselves a mite toasty main course! But on that walkin' thing...~
@12053 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a right fine thought. Makes this armor feel a mite constrainin', but it still be one blighted wonderful thought. But on that walkin' thing...~
@12054 = ~[ARAN] I could do that. Only I might have a mite bit o' trouble carryin' on, as I would want to stop every few paces an' kiss th' livin' daylights out o' you. But on that walkin' thing...~
@12055 = ~[ARAN] I'd be right happy to, but I have enough gear on right now that it would be a sorry sight, me staggerin' around. Tell you what, next time we see a nice meadow, we'll try it out. Mayhap somethin' else will happen, too. But on that walkin' thing...~
@12056 = ~[ARAN] N'Tel'Quessir n'iarelia vodi Tel'Quessir, amin arwin alcarinqua vanima roche.~
@12057 = ~[PC] You just blended three different Elven dialects, mispronounced 'horse', and I think in Waterdeep slang you may have just called me your gloriously beautiful sex toy. Perhaps you should quit while you still have a foot to put in your mouth.~
@12058 = ~[PC] No, non-elves do not usually ride elves. Something about weight, body size, and general politeness. But you wanted alternatives to walking...~
@12059 = ~[PC] The way you said that, it sounded like you want to escalate our relationship a bit, but are worried I might not say yes because you are a human, and I am an elf. Let me worry about both of those things, please.~
@12060 = ~[PC] Hmmmm. I think we have actually done that, if I recall... you were very, very happy.~
@12061 = ~[PC] True. Unless you work it around the other way, in which case I think we have done that... you were very, very happy.~
@12062 = ~[PC] You are so cute when you try to speak my language!~
@12063 = ~[PC] I don't mind, really. Hop on, and I will carry you.~
@12064 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, a lad don't usually go about ridin' his lady's back, an'... blighted hells, that came out all wrong, didn't it?~
@12065 = ~[PC] Why, Aran, you naughty boy. Did you just make a sly innuendo? Perhaps you should quit while you still have a foot to put in your mouth.~
@12066 = ~[PC] No, you probably would look a little silly. Something about weight, body size, and general politeness. But you wanted alternatives to walking...~
@12067 = ~[PC] The way you said that, it sounded like you want to escalate our relationship a bit, but are worried I might not say yes. There is no harm in asking, you know.~
@12068 = ~[PC] Never doubt the strength of a determined woman. Or stand between her and chocolate.~
@12069 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, a lad don't usually go about ridin' his lady's back, an' there be a mite bit o' a size difference... blighted hells, that came out all wrong, didn't it?~
