@12267 = ~[PC] I have no power. I don't even have the power to stop you pouring your whole heart out to me like this.~
@12268 = ~[PC] You have no concept of how much power you have over me. Your happiness is mine, and your sadness mine as well.~
@12269 = ~[PC] You give me too much power over you.~
@12270 = ~[PC] You know, I thought it would be nice to hear all of this, but it is a little sad. I think we should end anything outside of a professional relationship.~
@12271 = ~[ARAN] Dear gods, what to you be wantin' to hear? I could go on all blighted day sayin' all th' bits an' pieces o' you what make me want to spend th' rest o' my days wi' you. But it be th' whole package what does that, not any o' th' parts.~
@12272 = ~[PC] Well, why didn't you just say that in the first place?~
@12273 = ~[PC] You have known me and loved me long enough to know that words never sway me. Actions always speak louder. Shout, Aran. Right now.~
@12274 = ~[PC] That was nice to hear. But completely and utterly a waste of time. I am not in love with you.~
@12275 = ~[PC] If you are finally finished making a fool of yourself, then I am glad it is out in the open. I love you, too.~
@12276 = ~[PC] If you are finally finished making a fool of yourself, then I am glad it is out in the open. Now you can begin to deal with the reality that I don't love you.~
@12277 = ~[ARAN] Well, if I could, I would, but there be naught in th' way o' privacy right here an' now. Which brings up a point...~
@12278 = ~[ARAN] Then I be a right happy man.~
@12279 = ~[ARAN] I rightly remember th' last piece o' th' puzzle what drives me mad, an' completely puts me under your spell. You are th' most exasperatin' creature what ever walked th' Planes.~
@12280 = ~[ARAN] I... well, I guess you rightly know your own mind. I have naught in th' way o' power to make you love me, so I'd best not press this any more.~
@12281 = ~[ARAN] I do say, thought, that you be th' most exasperatin' creature what ever walked th' Planes.~
@12282 = ~Send Aran Whitehand home to Amn.~
@12283 = ~Bring Aran Whitehand back from Amn.~
@12284 = ~[ARAN] Do you be certain you want me to go?~
@12285 = ~[PC] Not right now. I might be back later, though. Stay right here and wait for me.~
@12286 = ~[PC] Why don't you find a good inn and wait for us there? Perhaps in Saradush?~
@12287 = ~[PC] Why don't you find a good inn and wait for us there? I hear there is an inn somewhere around Amkethran...~
@12288 = ~[PC] Actually, I've changed my mind. Stay with the party.~
@12289 = ~[PC] I'm sure.~
@12290 = ~[PC] Stay here, and don't gather any attention to yourself. That means no fighting, no drinking to excess, and no wenching.~
@12291 = ~[PC] I'm sure. Just wait right here, for now.~
