@12300 = ~[PC] You are gaining enough power as a sorcerer that you might actually be useful. Come on, I need you.~
@12301 = ~[PC] I need a healer, and you fit the bill. Gear up, boyo... we are heading out.~
@12302 = ~[PC] Quit whining, and toughen up. I will tell you when I need you.~
@12303 = ~[PC] Actually, wait here awhile longer, Aran. I need you close by.~
@12304 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I be listenin'. Do you want me along? There's naught to do here worth doin'.~
@12305 = ~[PC] Come on, Aran. We are off to have yet another battle.~
@12306 = ~[PC] I need your lore and inspiring oratory, Aran. Just please stop the whole 'try to teach yourself a stringed instrument by reading old manuscripts' thing. It sounds like cats being thrown in a shower.~
@12307 = ~[PC] Not right now, thanks.~
@12308 = ~[PC] Well, I came back to this oh-so-pleasant place, and I came over here to talk to you. Do you think it was because I wanted a status report on the massive amount of things going on around here?~
@12309 = ~[ARAN] I can keep myself a mite busy by drinkin', here, but I'd rather be fightin' alongside you. Take me along?~
@12310 = ~[PC] Of course. Join up, so we can go save the world.~
@12311 = ~[PC] Not right now. I might be back later, though.~
@12312 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. There you are. There's naught for me to do here, an' I'd rather be fightin' alongside you. Take me along?~ [c-aws133]
@12313 = ~[ARAN] Aye, that would be a nice trick, now wouldn't it. I'd oblige, if I could, but you know right well I can't leave here alone. Enough wi' th' jokes, eh?~
@12314 = ~[ARAN] My, a mite bit snarky today, are we? Don't tell me... yet another impossibly convoluted schemin' bastard decided to give you a pain in th' rear. Come on, let me get my gear, an' we'll both go jam Bane's Bones up his arse.~
@12315 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. I'll just wait. The barmaid looks pretty fetchin' anyways.~
@12316 = ~[ARAN] Right, then. I'll just wait. Didn't want to go on no Shar-kissed adventure, nohow. I'll go take a blighted nap an' be done wi' it.~
@12317 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I'll wait. Tyr's Eye, I left th' blighted rolls o' silk behind. I had in mind to live like a king this time. Guess th' old bedroll will just have to do.~
@12318 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I'll wait. Mask's Left hand, I left th' blighted cookin' spices behind. Oh well - there'll be some opportunity to restock sometime, I suppose.~
@12319 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I'll wait. By the way, I'm feelin' a bit nekkid, an' all, on account o' bein' swooped up here wi' naught for gear. Lend a lad a sword, please, eh?~
@12320 = ~[ARAN] Bane's Bones, I'd much rather fight a bit than sit around with a stick up my arse. But you call th' shots, <CHARNAME>. I'll be here when you need me.~
@12321 = ~[ARAN] Fine. I'll be waitin' at the pub in Saradush, when you need me. I think I can do some advance scoutin' ahead, or behind, or whatever.~
@12322 = ~[ARAN] Fine. I'll be waitin' at the pub in Amkethran, when you need me.~
@12323 = ~[ARAN] Now there be a neat trick. I go for a few drinks to figure out what th' nine hells I am supposed to be doin', on account o' you took off. I just get to thinkin', an' suddenly I be... where? Where in th' blighted...~
@12324 = ~[PC] I need your help, Aran. I need you to travel with me.~
@12325 = ~[PC] I told you I was heading out to investigate those old stone heads, but you just had to stay and try to flirt with those twins.~
@12326 = ~[PC] Focus. Battles ahead. Big battles. I need you. Are you in, or out?~
@12327 = ~[PC] I don't have much use for you, Aran, unless you can figure things out faster than that.~
@12328 = ~[PC] It is all a dream, your fevered imagination, and that extra round of Bitterblack Beer you ordered... I am just an odd bit of subconscious thought.~
@12329 = ~[PC] You don't need to know where. You need to know what I want to get accomplished, and what you have to kill in order to get it done.~
@12330 = ~[PC] Aran... after all I have been through, I think it is time for me to take action. I have some feelings for you. Do you think we could become more than just friends?~
@12331 = ~[PC] It is nice to have a good friend watching my back. Just not too closely, please... I said 'friends', not 'woman to be hit on'.~
@12332 = ~[PC] You seemed much more interested in those twins, and how little of their chests were covered up in that leather armor. Not that I mind - it was very funny to watch you try to act suave and sophisticated.~
@12333 = ~[ARAN] Now there be a neat trick. I go for a few drinks to figure out what th' nine hells I did wrong this time, an' you just up an' take off. I just get to thinkin', an' suddenly I be... where? Where in th' blighted...~
@12334 = ~[PC] I summoned you here because I need you, but I need to be clear about us, Aran. I am not interested in a romance with you any more.~
@12335 = ~[PC] I need you here with me, but I think we were headed down the wrong path, Aran. It was fun while it lasted, but it is over. Let's just be friends.~
@12336 = ~[PC] Look, I know we have had a rough patch... and I don't know who really started the fight. But I love you, and I need your help.~
@12337 = ~[PC] I need your help, but I also need you to keep a low profile. I said we could be together, if you were discreet. I have other lovers who are much less forgiving than you. Play by my rules, and we can keep our affair.~
@12338 = ~[PC] I had to clear my head, and to think. I did not expect to be ambushed and taken to this place. Can we talk about this later, and get back to the business at hand?~
@12339 = ~[PC] You didn't do anything wrong. I need you to focus. Look at me... we are still together. Just focus on getting your bearings and joining me.~
@12340 = ~[ARAN] You blighted Feywardens be all th' same. One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to Corellon knows where.~
@12341 = ~[PC] I am impressed. Swearing by Corellon? I didn't know you were hoping to be resurrected as Tel'Quessir. Should I mention in my prayers that you want to become one of the People?~
@12342 = ~[ARAN] Cyric-buggerin' Strifeleader. You should have done a bit more prayin'. Looks like ol' Bloody Bones has decided you need more random chaos an' murder in your life, an' now I get dragged along for th' ride.~
@12343 = ~[PC] I am impressed. Calling on Cyric, and insulting His name directly? Should I mention in my prayers that you have joined the fold?~
@12344 = ~[ARAN] You may be a blighted Painbearer, but I might want to actually enjoy life once or twice, an' not always be tryin' to outdo th' Cryin' God.~
@12345 = ~[PC] Ilmater has a plan, Aran. But it sounds as if you question my faith. Should I mention in my prayers that you think my faith is more about personal achievement and less about alleviating the suffering of others?~
@12346 = ~[ARAN] You blighted Lorekeepers be all th' same. One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to Oghma only knows where.~
@12347 = ~[PC] I am impressed. Swearing by Oghma? I didn't know you were coming to see the light. Should I mention in my prayers that you have joined the fold?~
@12348 = ~[ARAN] You blighted Firewalkers be all th' same, carin' for not much but th' burn. I was restin' up proper, an' here you have to go get all lighted up an' on fire again.~
@12349 = ~[PC] We come from the Fire, we go to the Fire. Why waste time questioning Kossuth's motives? Though you seem to have a good idea of what we believe. Should I mention in my prayers that you have joined the fold?~
@12350 = ~[ARAN] Silverstars may have th' Moonmaiden in their corner, but when I look around this place, it looks like we won't be seein' much o' Her face any time soon.~
@12351 = ~[PC] Selune will find us, even in this place.But I didn't know you were coming to see the light. Should I mention in my prayers that you have joined the fold?~
@12352 = ~[ARAN] I would o' thought a Holy Strategist wouldn't get caught wi' their trousers down an' all their parts exposed. You know, have some backup? One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to th' Red Lady only knows where.~
@12353 = ~[PC] The Red Fellowship has had some bad miscalculations before. I seem to have done the same. Perhaps I need more study and prayer.~
@12354 = ~[ARAN] I thought I was used to all your Nightcloak ways, but Shar's Caress... one hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to Shar only knows where.~
@12355 = ~[PC] Shar's secrets are not to be shared with outsiders. Unless... should I mention in my prayers that you wish to join the fold?~
@12356 = ~[ARAN] Lady Firehair will be pleased as punch one o' Her Heartwarders be disappeared down some hole in th' nine hells. One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to Sune only knows where.~
@12357 = ~[PC] We Heartwarders pursue beauty wherever we find it. We even find it in that thing you wear on your skull, and call a face. Shall we get you some help in that department?~
@12358 = ~[ARAN] You blighted Battleguards don't think beyond th' edge o' an axe or hammer, do you? One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to Tempus knows where.~
@12359 = ~[PC] Why waste time waiting for you when I could get things done? Do you question the way of Tempus? I believe the best way to question is to engage me in battle...~
@12360 = ~[ARAN] You blighted Authlim be all th' same. One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to Xvim knows where. You bloody well know I'm no competition on th' shares o' any find. I'm just th' hired help.~
@12361 = ~[PC] You of all people should realize that my motives are my own, and not for questioning. Do not mention Xvim unless you wish to serve him directly, and in that case, you would need to challenge me...~
@12362 = ~[ARAN] Morninglords may needs be shinin' th' Light into dark places, but by Lathander's Golden Poop, blighted well let a lad know where you be goin'. One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to His Suniness knows where.~
@12363 = ~[PC] Sunny-ness or Sune-i-ness, Aran? I never did get whom you venerate most. Did you want me to try to pray for some great spell to reverse time itself, and undo the past?~
@12364 = ~[ARAN] You blighted Watchers be all th' same. One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to Helm knows where. You bloody well know I'd be a help watchin' your back.~
@12365 = ~[PC] Helm watches all things. Unfortunately, His followers are not quite omnipotent or omniscient. Or are you saying you have never made a mistake?~
@12366 = ~[ARAN] You blighted well did it again. Look, I know you blighted Stormlords an' Stormladies all want to go around blastin' th' crap out o' th' universe, sewin' seeds o' chaos an' evil, but by Talos' Tempestuous Tresses, you should know by now that goin' wi' out backup is just stupid. Yet there you be. One hint o' some esoteric Tel'Qessirim ruin, an' you go an' investigate alone, an' get magically swept to gods knows where.~
@12367 = ~[PC] Why waste time waiting for you when I could get things done? Do you question the way of Talos? I believe the best way to question is to engage me in battle...~
@12368 = ~[PC] I need to be clear about this, Aran. I am not interested in a romance with you any more.~
@12369 = ~[PC] I think we were headed down the wrong path, Aran. It was fun while it lasted, but it is over. Let's just be friends.~
@12370 = ~[PC] I said we could be together, if you were discreet. I have other lovers who are much less forgiving than you. Play by my rules, and we can keep our affair.~
@12371 = ~[PC] I need you to focus. Look at me... we are still together. Just focus on getting your bearings and joining me.~
@12372 = ~[PC] Don't you love me any more? I think I want you back.~
@12373 = ~[PC] I know we have had ups and downs in the past, but the whole chaotic 'love me, love me not' thing is so exciting. Can we go back to that?~
@12374 = ~[PC] Oh, never mind all that. I am being silly, and rethinking our whole relationship. We should just leave things the way they are right now, and continue being friends.~
@12375 = ~[PC] Oh, never mind. I am being silly, and rethinking our whole relationship. We should just leave things the way they are right now, and continue being friends.~
@12376 = ~[ARAN] I didn't say I wanted none o' that. I just get a mite grumpy when I be unceremoniously whisked away from a perfectly good drink at your whim. Somethin' that wouldn't have happened if you had let me stay right close by, instead o' harin' off on your own.~
@12377 = ~[ARAN] Now that be right fine. I am sorry for whatever I did what made you go off alone, but we can talk about that later. What do you be needin' right now?~
@12378 = ~[PC] Come with me. I need your help.~
@12379 = ~[PC] You'll do what I say or you'll rot here, do you understand that?~
@12380 = ~[PC] Wait here for now.~
@12381 = ~[PC] Fine. We can talk later. That's good enough for me.~
@12382 = ~[PC] Get in line and don't bother me.~
@12383 = ~[PC] Stay here, my love. I will be back for you as soon as I can.~
@12384 = ~[ARAN] I... I guess I saw that comin', eh? There be little enough I can offer you, except mayhap some service. Fine. I can do that.~
@12385 = ~[PC] I... I thought you did not want me any more. If you do... well, we could try...~
@12386 = ~[PC] Hey, I pulled you here because I have some feelings for you, but you had no right to flirt with her like that. I expect you to try harder to be the man I need you to be.~
@12387 = ~[PC] You have many things to offer. I just needed to see how you would react. I am happy to have you as my lover again, if you behave yourself.~
@12388 = ~[PC] Good. I have someone else in my life right now, and I don't want this to distract from our work.~
@12389 = ~[PC] I am sorry to hurt you like this, but it is for the best. I need friends right now, not romance.~
@12390 = ~[PC] It was all in your mind, anyways. You should be glad that you can go about your drinking and womanizing without having to look over your shoulder every few seconds.~
@12391 = ~[ARAN] Now, you selfish little minx, I blighted well put up wi' your evil ways for all that time, an'...~
@12392 = ~[PC] I am sorry to hurt you like this, but it is for the best. I need your loyal service, not your love.~
@12393 = ~[PC] It was all in your mind, anyways. You should be glad that you can go about your drinking and womanizing without having to look over your shoulder every few seconds. Just be careful... if I get a little jealous, someone might end up dead.~
@12394 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know whether you be comin', goin' or just playin' wi' me. By th' gods, you blighted little...~
@12395 = ~[ARAN] Well, on second thought, I guess I should have seen that comin', eh? There be little enough I can offer you, except mayhap some service. Fine. I can do that.~
@12396 = ~[PC] Hey, I pulled you here because I have some feelings for you, but you don't seem to be able to handle our relationship the way I need you to. I expect you to try harder to be the man I need you to be.~
@12397 = ~[PC] You have many things to offer. I just needed to see how you would react. I am happy to have you as my lover again.~
@12398 = ~[ARAN] I am th' one left bloody well holdin' th' drinks, while you... you... oh, hells. I don't rightly know what I did wrong, but I know I can't blighted well live wi' out you in my life.~
@12399 = ~[ARAN] I want to be mad, I do... I am th' one left bloody well behind. But when you look at me like that, I am not rightly goin' to resist, eh? I can't blighted well live wi' out you in my life.~
@12400 = ~[ARAN] Well, that be a nice thing to say. Do I get a bonus,too, or do you want me to see if I can get into th' Whores' Guild while I be at it?~
@12401 = ~[PC] If you can't handle being friends, then I don't need you around sulking like a stupid little apprentice whining over his lost love. Are you in, or out?~
@12402 = ~[PC] I am sorry if I hurt your feelings, but this is the way it has to be. Are you in, or out?~
@12403 = ~[PC] So being friends is out. Fine. Can you serve me, or should I find someone else who can do the job instead?~
@12404 = ~[PC] Prostitute, sellsword... there is a difference? I was not aware of any, except the kind of sword they handle.~
@12405 = ~[ARAN] I fought for you, an' worked my hardest to be a right fine person. I expected you would be more than a few little games o' 'ruffle th' covers'.~
@12406 = ~[PC] I don't know what your fevered imagination dreamed up, but you have not ruffled any of my covers, and you won't be doing any of that now.~
@12407 = ~[PC] The ruffling was substandard, and I really am not that interested in you romantically any more.~
@12408 = ~[PC] I told you to be discreet. You were less than discreet. I can't take the chance of messing that relationship up, so it is over between you and I.~
@12409 = ~[PC] I have fallen in love with someone else. I can't keep flirting and teasing with you. It is over between us.~
@12410 = ~[PC] I know you tried, but I am not in love with you any more. I don't know what the future will bring, but for right now, it has to be this way. Can you handle this?~
@12411 = ~[PC] Grow a spine. You were never strong enough to be anything more than a fling. Now, get hold of yourself and make a decision. Battles ahead. Gold, magic, power, and my favor to those who serve well. Are you in, or out?~
@12412 = ~[ARAN] So why did you yank me out o' my life an' drag me here... just lookin' to screw wi' my life an' torture me before discardin' me on th' trash heap?~
@12413 = ~[PC] Don't be bitter. I need your help. Join me, and we can gain power and security together.~
@12414 = ~[PC] I need your help. Join me, and perhaps you could change my mind about the status of our relationship.~
@12415 = ~[PC] I know you are hurting, but we have heavier matters to address. I need your skills, so join me.~
@12416 = ~[PC] Stay here awhile longer, then. A little sulk might be good for you.~
@12417 = ~[ARAN] In.~
@12418 = ~[ARAN] Right. I can serve you. Just a little rattled, but I have taken worse in th' gut an' come out swingin'.~
@12419 = ~[ARAN] I have been waitin' to hear that. I have been well past that boundary for a good bit o' time now. I'd be right happy to be more than friends.~
@12420 = ~[ARAN] I would be right happy to try a bit harder, on my part. We could slow down a mite, an' see what happens.~
@12421 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, that be unfair, takin' advantage o' me when I was just drinkin' brandy. Or was it kissin' Brandy, an' drinkin' scotch? You can't blighted fool me, <CHARNAME>. You done spirited me away to some strange place.~
@12422 = ~[ARAN] TWINS. Blighted... <CHARNAME>, send me back, eh? Right now... There be a pair o' ladies what are goin' to be searchin' Faerun for revenge, if I don't get back there right quick!~
@12423 = ~[PC] Your lovelife is your own problem. We have some bigger challenges to face.~
@12424 = ~[PC] Oh, cry me a river. You have fun while I get sucked into a vortex, and not in a good way. Stay here awhile... a little sulk might be good for you.~
@12425 = ~[ARAN] I don't like th' tone o' that, seein' as there be no fury like a woman scorned, an' somehow I just done that to two, what be twin sisters, an' most likely Guild. An' I don't mean th' Baker's Guild, neither. But I have been in your service long enough to know that th' danger be high, th' fame large, an' th' goals... well, they don't rightly matter as long as I be on your side, eh?~
@12426 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know what to say. I thought we had a contract, but then I looked up, an' you had disappeared. But I guess we could pick right up where we left off. I had little enough time to figure out what I was doin'.~
@12427 = ~[ARAN] I seem to have lost some o' my gear, an' might need a bit o' remindin' what I do for you. Between th' drink an' bein' whisked in here, I need a mite bit o' time to figure myself straight.~
@12428 = ~[PC] Fair enough. Join me. I'll help you settle your gear, and then we can figure out what comes next.~
@12429 = ~[PC] What am I, your wet-nurse? Shake it off, settle your own gear, join up, and then we can figure out what comes next.~
@12430 = ~[PC] Don't drown me with your troubles. You don't know what I have had to deal with. Morality, causality, and a whole other family of '-ality's.~
@12431 = ~[PC] Just a reminder... You'll do what I say or you'll rot here.~
@12432 = ~[PC] It is great to have you with me again, Aran.~
@12433 = ~[PC] Stay here awhile longer. I will be back for you as soon as I can.~
@12434 = ~[ARAN] I wasn't threatenin' to drown you wi' my troubles, an' I be naught but a decent right arm for you. What in th' nine hells has gotten under your skin?  I don't give a rat's arse what cause you serve, on account o' my job be to make sure things on th' ground get done. You handle most o' th' morality, an' I look for things what be in the way, an' kill 'em.~
@12435 = ~[PC] Come with me, then.~
@12436 = ~[PC] You'll wait here for now.~
@12437 = ~[ARAN] I don't break a contract. Unless you be sellin' slaves, I am backin' you. I may not agree, but that be a conversation for another time.~
@12438 = ~[PC] Fine. That's good enough for me. Join me.~
@12439 = ~[PC] Damn straight. Get in line and don't bother me.~
@12440 = ~[PC] Stay here, then. I might be back. Or perhaps I won't.~
@12441 = ~[ARAN]Fine. But someone else better do th' blighted dishes. I'll fight, but none o' that camaraderie crap.~
@12442 = ~[ARAN] I feel th' same way.~
@12443 = ~[ARAN] Well, if th' fates have brought me around, it seems I don't rightly ought to argue wi' em. I have learned you do things your own way. But I do question stayin' here an' not accompanyin' you, on account o' th' nearest alcohol be a long, long ways off.~
@12444 = ~[ARAN] I should have known that rest an' recreation were somethin' only normal people have. Just help me look through my gear an' get straight, an' I will be good to travel.~
@12445 = ~[ARAN] You need my help, eh? I was thinkin' mayhap it was time for me to retire from things, an' settle down. You... you be right powerful, but some o' th' things you do don't sit so well wi' me. On th' other hand, I didn't get where I be without a fair amount o' backin' your play, so I should just shut up an' soldier, eh?~
