@12557 = ~[c-aranbio] When you ask him about his past, ARAN WHITEHAND grasps at a nearby twig to chew on. He explains that he grew up in a small independent family-run Coster plying the Trade Way and Coast Way from Waterdeep both north and south. Working as both Pen and Sword (scribe and fighting guard) made him attractive as an independent, since he could balance accounts, keep inventory, and still operate as a sellsword. A few campaigns with mercenary companies, a few battles, and lots of wandering about has brought him to Amn. He hastens to note that he is not the man to send in to negotiate anything, preferring to wield weapons rather than the spoken word - but if you want a trading contract written up, he's the right man for the job.~ [C-ABLANK]
@12558 = ~[ARAN] Well, th' wildlife has right perky breasts, long fangs, an' an unaccountable taste for a poor lad's blood. So far, I'd give it a nine out o' ten on th' 'stay the hells away' vacation list.~
@12559 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Grinnin' Teeth, you been waitin' to say that awhile, eh? Fine. Shuttin' up. Didn't want to talk to your sorry smelly arse anyways.~
@12560 = ~[ARAN] I got blighted tired o' losin'?~
@12561 = ~[ARAN] Hey, we fight. I think. Don't we? Mayhap we don't. I don't rightly remember. Whatever you say, it probably is right.~
@12562 = ~[ARAN] You leavin' me like that an' wanderin' off to a netherworld in a sub-dimension o' th' Nine Rings o' hell created out o' your subconscious kind o' put things into perspective. As in, if I want to be around her, I'd bloody well pick an' choose when to get a good discussion goin', an' when to say "yes dear".~
@12563 = ~[ARAN] We fight. Just not in front o' th' children. Wait... we don't have no children. Say, there be a right interestin' idea in there somewheres...~
@12564 = ~[ARAN] I don't remember us fightin'. Wait, hold on... oh, I remember. Th' sick feelin' in my gut, the angry looks, th' whole lack o' physical contact... nope. Don't miss that one bit.~
@12565 = ~[ARAN] That depends on what kind o' advice you be lookin' for, eh? I got some decent advice on decoratin', an mayhap some ideas on how to spruce th' place up a bit. Other than that, I am not sure I know what to say. I still am not even sure where 'here' be.~
@12566 = ~[ARAN] There be naught in th' way o' knowledge personal-like, on account o' I have not been here before. But I can tell you that th' best defense be a right solid offense, when it comes to sieges like this. It seems like you could stay tight behind th' wall, but anyone who has giants lobbin' great blighted boulders at us has th' resources to slag th' walls to mud through magic. Then where do you be?~
@12567 = ~[ARAN] Blighted bad place to be standin' around jawin'. Too many entrances an' lots o' soldiers to close by for some comfort. Let's get to a place we can defend, eh?~
@12568 = ~[ARAN] Up that staircase or down, don't seem to matter much. There be a hells o' a racket comin' from above, though. Should we go check it out?~
@12569 = ~[ARAN] Th' only advice I have right now is to make th' most important choice you can make at a time like this... ale, wine, or harder spirits.~
@12570 = ~[ARAN] I say we drop a coin or two as a nice little gesture. Never hurts to get th' word out, an' may make people think better o' us.~
@12571 = ~[ARAN] Bloody poor defenses, if you ask me. We can probably waltz through this place wi' out much pain. This bastard doesn't seem to believe in trainin' his followers so well.~
@12572 = ~[ARAN] I'd rather not leave none o' us separate, on account o' all these blighted cells. No tellin' what be hidin' where. Not that thrilled wi' bein' no snack for whatever keeps this place so deserted, eh?~
@12573 = ~[ARAN] Save everyone we can, an' watch everythin' right careful. There be more traps here than in some mad wizard's fantasy.~
@12574 = ~[ARAN] I don't trust that slippery arse. I say we loot th' whole blighted place. It might not be th' nicest thing to do, but somethin' tells me th' bastard has it comin'.~
@12575 = ~[ARAN] That bed be lookin' right invitin'. Pity there be such blighted noise none o' us could sleep.~
@12576 = ~[ARAN] Chauntea's Basket, that kitchen be right fine. A steady source o' clean water, some o' th' finest produce... I'd be right happy to spend a few hours in there, eh?~
@12577 = ~[ARAN] I say give me th' party purse, an' walk away. I bet there be some o' th' nicest scrolls an' supplies this side o' Neverwinter, an' wi' a little persuasion an' some coin we could get some right fine materials! look at th' quality o' th' scraps left behind. Think o' what his private stores must be like!~
@12578 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, it be a house. What do you expect me to say - move in an' take up residence? Hey, when are we goin' to get back to our real job, an' stop all this wanderin' into random stranger's homes?~
@12579 = ~[ARAN] We are traipsin' about in a sewer. A sewer. Bane's Blackened Bones, what do you think my advice is goin' to be? Don't drink th' water, don't breath in too deep, an' when you think you see somethin' movin', By Tymora's Coin let a lad know before he gets pulled down an' digested by somethin' that literally eats crap for dinner every night!~
@12580 = ~[ARAN] Never saw no cellar what didn't have a secret or two. Or good root vegetables hidden away. That reminds me... I'm gettin' a mite peckish. What say we wrap up this visit real quick, an' find us somethin' nice to eat?~
@12581 = ~[ARAN] I say we don't get too close to the recruiter, on account o' we might just end up havin' to man the walls instead o' bein' free to do as we please.~
@12582 = ~[ARAN] Well, I don't recommend hangin' around long in jails. Though this one is at least a bit cleaner than some I done seen the insides of. An' at least we haven't been thrown down here to rot. Kind o' nice bein' just a visitor.~
@12583 = ~[ARAN] I'd avoid fightin' with giants on general principle, myself. An' this place looks like it has had a few large footprints. Plus, some o' these boulders didn't levitate themselves randomly. So, I'm for makin' our way real quiet-like from now on, I think.~
@12584 = ~[ARAN] Find somethin' large to hide in, an' make sure you run like th' nine hells when someone starts singin' about grindin' our bones for their bread?~
@12585 = ~[ARAN] I say this place looks like a trap hidden inside an ambush an' wrapped in horsedung. What say we step off to a nice range an' throw Fireballs an' some huge area o' effect spells until nothin' moves, then come in an' bring a body or two to someone who can speak wi' the dead? Might save us a world o' hurt.~
@12586 = ~[ARAN] Defendin' a bridge be easy enough wi' ranged weapons an' magic. I say we pull back an' let th' bastards keep pilin' on. Th' only problem be when they decide to levitate across, or  there be so many bodies that they can walk across on top o' 'em. Gond's Bladder, I saw that once.~
@12587 = ~[ARAN] Shiny floor, skull decorations, braziers o' fire... I like what he did wi' th' place. Well, not really. Blighted hells, <CHARNAME>, don't ask me... we came here to kill this Bane Kissed bastard an' figure out what this all be about!~
@12588 = ~[ARAN] I say we stock up on water. An' I don't mean wine, or naught else but plain, clean, clear water. Just lookin' at this Cyric-blighted place makes a man thirsty.~
@12589 = ~[ARAN] Shades o' Calimport. This do take me back. Well, almost... there seem to be no real bath, an' th' servin' wenches wear a fair sight more than they did at some o' th' more interestin... err... well, that be another story. Look careful in your drink before drinkin', eh? These people have an interestin' idea what constitutes 'fit for consumption'.~
@12590 = ~[ARAN] Gond's Gears! That be th' most interestin' contraption I ever did see. Hells, lets get this shortaxe whatever it takes to get it workin' again. I just want to see it in action.~
@12591 = ~[ARAN] Waukeen's Wise Ways, it be right nice to see th' Lady o' Coin be not completely forgotten. I'd say we could stay here an' relax a mite, if it weren't for th' fact that th' place be as barren o' sleepin' places as your average dungeon or cave. Pretty, though.~
@12592 = ~[ARAN] I say we stay out o' th' whole thing. An' stay out o' here, as well. Gettin' between crazed monks, an army o' mercenaries, an' a well supplied an' organized smugglin' operation sound like just th' sort o' thing to get all three o' th' sides to band together against the interlopers. An' by interlopers, that be meanin' ours truly.~
@12593 = ~[ARAN] Stairs, stairs, an' more bloody stairs. An' steep ones at that. My advice be to get us some o' those levitatin' boots. Or just avoid fightin' in here, anyways, on account o' fightin' uphill be a serious pain in th' arse.~
@12594 = ~[ARAN] Shhh! Llira's Joy, can't you rightly see they both be sleepin'? Let's be gettin' out right quick, an' right quiet.~
@12595 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know. There be priorities, an' then there be priorities. I wish I had a right good answer for you, but I think I need to consult th' journal an' see what in th' nine hells we have finished up, an' what we have left undone.~
@12596 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap talk to everyone, an' figure out what to do from there? That broken chair over there don't rightly make for much o' a conversation starter, but beggars can't rightly be choosers.~
@12597 = ~[ARAN] Aye. When you find yourself in a bloody great bronzed chamber wi' all manner o' arcane carvin's, start lookin' for th' quickest way to GET TH' HELLS OUT.~
@12598 = ~[ARAN] Dragon carvin's everywhere. Dark. Smells worse than my feet after a nine day march. My advice? Stage a tactical withdrawal. I be thinkin' a good place to be regroupin' be this quaint little tavern, mayhap you have heard of... Th' Friendly Arms Inn?~
@12599 = ~[ARAN] There be somethin' odd about those pools. I say we take a closer look. Mayhap we can find somethin' to our advantage. Or mayhap we just end up as bits o' sausage in someone's soup, eh?~
@12600 = ~[ARAN] Kill anythin' that wiggles, an' remind me to get somethin' what cuts fish-oil smell off o' gear.~
@12601 = ~[ARAN] I say we poke about in every single corner o' this place. Selune's Silver Strands, there be a fortune in vellum an' ink to plunder, an' have you seen th' rare inks he has just lyin' out there for th' takin'? I be like to jump out o' my skin!~
@12602 = ~[ARAN] Brilliant. Just bloody brilliant. A whole room full o' pools, an' on top o' it, dragon poop. Why don't we just go for th' whole trifecta, an' get a vampiric lich wi' halitosis. My advice? We need to take a blighted break. Every time we start makin' our way forward, we seem to step right into another wonderful experience just like this one.~
@12603 = ~[ARAN] I'd say somethin' quotable, but given th' amount o' pain radiatin' from that blighted huge nastyy lookin' sword, I think I'll just shut my mouth an' keep a wary eye out.~
@12604 = ~[ARAN] Dive back through th' pool?~
@12605 = ~[ARAN] Looks like someone done a right good job o' buildin' a library o' spell components an' writin' materials. Mayhap I'll be seein' one o' my manuscripts lyin' around, on account o'this place be just scary enough to be a publisher's office, eh?~
@12606 = ~[ARAN] I might have some advice, but I think I just swallowed a minnow. That be just wrong, that be.~
@12607 = ~[ARAN] Somethin' don't seem quite as it should be. I don't rightly know why, but it feels like there be plenty o' eyes watchin' us right now.~
@12608 = ~[ARAN] We sure as Shar's Spit don't stand around jawin'. This place be crawlin wi' those blighted Drow bastards.~
@12609 = ~[ARAN] My advice be to shut th' hells up an' kill everythin' we can. I'd say do it slow an' make 'em suffer, but right now speed be th' smartest route, I think.~
@12610 = ~[ARAN] Get out quick. Flame everythin'.~
@12611 = ~[ARAN] Give a lad a moment, eh? I just looked over th' edge, an' somehow fallin' a mile or so down into whatever th' blighted hells be down there don't seem that appealin' to me.~
@12612 = ~[ARAN] Small area. Confined spaces. We should throw up some defenses, an' blast area o' effect spells any time somethin' moves.~
@12613 = ~[ARAN] What do you be askin' me for? We don't rightly have much choice. We go forward, we go back... either way, we are bound to run into trouble. Drow travel in packs, like seriously screwed up gibberlings.~
@12614 = ~[ARAN] We done come this far. No sense not to go one more step forward, eh? By th' way,. I done made out a last will an' testament, just in case. Probably a bit late for it, on account of if you be needin' to read it, we probably will have all taken th' great dirt nap, eh?~
@12615 = ~[ARAN] Nope. I got nothin'.~
@12616 = ~[ARAN] When I say th' only good drow be a dead drow, I wasn't sayin' I was volunteerin' to singlehandedly depopulate th' entire range o' Faerun's dark elves.~
@12617 = ~[ARAN] Every time we be seein' those funny tusk-like projections circlin' 'round some dias, it seems there be a whole load o' trouble headin' our way. I say we start lookin' in th' doors careful like, an' every time we see somethin' that looks like this, just walk away.~
@12618 = ~[ARAN] Smells funny. Odd food supplies. We'd best poke around a bit. But I think I'll be leavin' those mushrooms over there alone, on account o' I think they be right poisonous.~
@12619 = ~[ARAN] Kill anythin' that moves. Then kill it again. Mayhap dig it up an' kill it a third time, just to be sure. Gods don't rightly die quick, is my guess.~
@12620 = ~[ARAN] You know, short o' th' standard combat tactics, I really got nothin' here. Ever since we started poppin' in an' out o' that blighted section o' hell, my sense o' what be possible has had to have some readjustin'. I'm not rightly sure I have a good handle on what we can do. Right now, it looks like we can take on half o' Faerun in battle an' win. I'm just not sure that be th' best way to get your point across, eh? But one thing be for sure... we needs be gatherin' what we can o' that water.~
@12621 = ~[ARAN] Anyone for a nice swim? That water looks right peaceful an' happy, it does. Or not.~
@12622 = ~[ARAN] Ilmater's Sufferin', do you ask questions like 'are we there yet?' 'how long until th' next town?' 'why is th' grass green?' 'why is Aran about to make a blighted rude gesture in your general direction?' What do you be, <PRO_GIRLBOY>, a four year old?~
@12623 = ~[PC] (You decide not to flirt with Aran).~
@12624 = ~[ARAN] What do you be lookin' at, <CHARNAME>?~
@12625 = ~[PC] Oh, nothing much.~
@12626 = ~[PC] Forget it, Aran. I don't really need anything.~
@12627 = ~[PC] They say silence is golden. Pay yourself.~
@12628 = ~[PC] Oh, just shut up, will you?~
@12629 = ~[PC] Can a <PRO_GIRLBOY> get a little peace and quiet around here?~
@12630 = ~[PC] Forget it. And stop yammering on, will you? Give it a rest.~
@12631 = ~[PC] I was looking at you. Do you have a problem with that?~
@12632 = ~[PC] I was looking at you. Did you know that your bottom is really tight and muscular?~
@12633 = ~[PC] Just checking that everything is in order. You seem to be dripping blood everywhere, so I guess you need some serious healing.~
@12634 = ~[PC] Just checking that everything is in order. You don't look so good, so I guess you might need a little healing.~
@12635 = ~[PC] Just checking that everything is in order. You don't look so badly off, so I guess you don't need healing.~
@12636 = ~[ARAN] Got my attention, anyhow. Any particular reason you be lookin' my way?~
@12637 = ~[PC] Is there any way I could persuade you to just shut the hells up? Short of physical violence, I mean.~
@12638 = ~[PC] Just listening to you talk to yourself about nothing. You know we can hear you when you do that, right?~
@12639 = ~[PC] Oh, just trying to distract you enough that you stop muttering under your breath.~
@12640 = ~[PC] Did I ask you to talk to me? Because if I did, I really didn't mean to.~
@12641 = ~[PC] No particular reason. I don't really need anything.~
@12642 = ~[PC] I was trying to discover the source of that really sharp sulfurous odor.~
@12643 = ~[ARAN] Right back at you. Why do you be lookin' my way, anyways? Just enjoyin' th' view?~
@12644 = ~[PC] Forget it, Aran. Sorry I bothered you.~
@12645 = ~[PC] Yes, you are a sight for sore eyes. Well, close, anyways - the sight of you makes my eyes sore...~
@12646 = ~[PC] Just leave me alone, ok? I didn't mean to disturb your industrious scratching of various body parts. Go back to doing whatever it is you were doing.~
@12647 = ~[PC] Actually, you were blocking my view. Have you put on a few pounds?~
@12648 = ~[ARAN] Whoa... Cyric's balls, that were a right close thing. I might o' had to scrub my footgear for a week. Good eyes, for noticin'... or were you just starin' at me?~
@12649 = ~[PC] You know, you impress me. You write very well, considering you look as if you have trouble spelling your name without help.~
@12650 = ~[ARAN] I'd bloody well fix myself up, if it didn't hurt so much to breathe. Hey, lend a lad a hand, will you? Just get me one o' them nice potions or a spell or somethin'.~
@12651 = ~[ARAN] It's just a flesh wound. I figure if worst comes to worst, I can distract 'em wi' a mite bit o' blood. Mayhap even scare 'em wi' some of my bruises. But thanks for lookin' in on me, eh?~
@12652 = ~[ARAN] If that be some kind o' crack about hangin' back in combat, m'<PRO_GIRLBOY>, I go where you be tellin' me an' do what you be tellin' me, so more's th' fault wi' you!.~
@12653 = ~[ARAN] Laugh away, monkey<PRO-BOYGIRL>. I know where you sleep!~
@12654 = ~[ARAN] I keep askin' an' they keep tossin'. Problem is, it be vegetables, not skirts!~
@12655 = ~[ARAN] You let me know when you be volunteerin'!~
@12656 = ~[ARAN] Funny, funny - I handle my weapon quite well, m'<PRO_GIRLBOY>. I just like it better when some fair maiden handles it for me!~
@12657 = ~[ARAN] No, seriously. Somethin' there? Did I forget to wash some blood off? A spider? Cyric's Black Heart, <CHARNAME>, you are messin' with me!~
@12658 = ~[ARAN] Well, you found it. An' there be more where that came form, so I'd move upwind if I was you.~
@12659 = ~[ARAN] Now how in th' hells you know that when I be wearin' armor is a question for th' ages. Most armor makes my arse look as big as a barn door. But thank you right kindly. Now, I would start complimentin' your various body parts, but I think I will avoid th' slappin' that will accompany my discussion o' your various curves an' byways, eh?~
@12660 = ~[ARAN] No problem. Only I would have slicked my hair back a bit an' struck a pose if you had let me know, eh?~
@12661 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly know. By Tymora's Bright Eyes, there's more than enough adventure around here for this lad. I could use a good belt o' hard spirits. Th' drinkin' kind, I mean.~
@12662 = ~[ARAN] Never did get it done. Helm's Arse, if it hasn't broken free again.~
@12663 = ~[ARAN] Does a Suneite enjoy a great piece o' art? Hells, yes. Except I want to use my own dice this time. I still owe you three dragons an' a crescent from last time.~
@12664 = ~[ARAN] That's right fine wi' me. I have been preppin' for somethin' special. Always thought all this slaughter was goin' to waste, so I was figurin' on doin' a nice stew with our next adversary as th' main course. Exceptin' humans, that is. Or litches. Re-hydration might be a bitch. Or elementals. Too tough to cook. An' no spiders. A nice dragon curry, perhaps?~
@12665 = ~[ARAN] Well, now that you mention it, NO. But I did put more paddin' under my armor. That last combat, I got me a blighted bruise th' size o' two hands, on account o' my paddin' was a mite understrength. Serves me right for not checkin' on it.~
@12666 = ~[ARAN] Am I doin' that again? I don't now where I picked that up. Probably one o' them damned bards, I guess. Sorry.~
@12667 = ~[ARAN] Well, we got that, for sure. Tymora's Light Fingers, if I'd have been smart, I would have wished for a ton o' gold, instead. I just figured the gods weren't listenin', so I got all wise with my mouth. Serves me right.~
@12668 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Stinkin' Arse, I didn't expect them to take me serious. All I asked was for a little adventure, and here we get stuck wi' changin' the whole world!~
@12669 = ~[ARAN] You know, you scare th' crap out o' me when you say things like that. Somehow I suspect your next statement will be 'Demonic Dragons with Wraith Henchmen? Pfft. Aran, go take care of them, while I boil us up a nice pot of tea'.~
@12670 = ~[ARAN] Oh, watch that sharp wit o' yours. You could harm a lad that way, you know. That is, if I gave a rat's arse!~
@12671 = ~[ARAN] Lolth's Stinkin' Arse... oh, funny. Real funny. Did I ever tell you about th' time we got a little revenge on Kravich for his breakin' wind all th' time? It involved a bucket o' lukewarm water, a sleepin' roll, an' his left hand. Now I wonder if that might make a repeat performance...~
@12672 = ~[ARAN] I'll have you know I was right drunk at th' time. An' it weren't me, it had to be my evil twin brother, separated at birth. Now, that be my story, an' I am stickin' wi' it!~
@12673 = ~[ARAN] Heh. You're killin' me, here. Wi' friends like you, I think I might just see what th' other side has to offer!~
@12674 = ~[ARAN] Now, last time you buttered me up like that, it was on account o' you had some clever plan what involved me runnin' out on point an' seein' if there was anythin' interested in whackin' us...~
@12675 = ~[ARAN] Have I got somethin' on my face? I have a bit o' food somewhere, don't I.~
@12676 = ~[PC] Yep, that's it. Green, kinda slimy looking, and... oh, wait... that's your nose.~
@12677 = ~[PC] If you only swung your weaponry as fast as you move your mouth... well, it would be a good thing.~
@12678 = ~[PC] No, I was joking. Really, I was just wondering when you are going to smarten up and ask some lovely young thing to toss up her skirts for you.~
@12679 = ~[PC] No food, but I just keep wondering how someone so pretty can handle that weapon so well.~
@12680 = ~[PC] Oh, of course not.~
@12681 = ~[ARAN] Well, then, what do you want? You're not payin' attention to our surroundin's much.~
@12682 = ~[PC] Just checking in with you to see if you are doing well.~
@12683 = ~[PC] Did you ever get that pack stitched? It looks a little loose.~
@12684 = ~[PC] Are you in for a game of dice tonight?~
@12685 = ~[PC] Look, where I put my attention is my own damned business. Just shut up already.~
@12686 = ~[PC] Look, just shut up already. I don't want anything. You talk too much.~
@12687 = ~[PC] I was going to say something about the great ugly lump of fat that was attacking your head, but then I realized that was your face...~
@12688 = ~[PC] Thou art a paunchy boil-brained pigeon-egg. See, I study, too.~
@12689 = ~[PC] It's your turn to cook tonight.~
@12690 = ~[ARAN] Well, I'd advise we keep lookin' out for trouble, then, on account o' it sure knows where to find us.~
@12691 = ~[PC] It might not find it so fast if you would stop whistling through your teeth like that.~
@12692 = ~[PC] Hey, you wanted adventure, right?~
@12693 = ~[PC] Look, that wasn't funny. Just shut up already. You talk too much.~
@12694 = ~[PC] If I wanted an idiot's opinion... wait... yep, I would have asked you, all right.~
@12695 = ~[PC] You shouldn't have put that advertisement out, then.~
@12696 = ~[PC] Well, now the tables are turned. We are going looking for it.~
@12697 = ~[ARAN] I think when scholars write 'watch your compatriots' back', it's a figure o' speech, not literal.~
@12698 = ~[PC] Laugh all you want, monkey boy. I just like seeing a good friend doing the job right.~
@12699 = ~[PC] Well, you watch my back, I'll watch yours... sounded like a good idea. Especially as you have a pretty hairy insect crawling on your left shoulder...~
@12700 = ~[PC] If that was meant to be funny, then you should keep your day job. At least then you will be bad at one thing instead of two.~
@12701 = ~[PC] I'd watch your back, but your buttocks are so large I would need a Wizard's eye to see all of it.~
@12702 = ~[PC] "Literally". The bighted word is "literally". And while we are at it, when are you going to learn how to pronounce the ends of words?~
@12703 = ~[PC] For a man who can't say "g" at the end of a word, "compatriot' is a little high class, isn't it?~
@12704 = ~[PC] Funny. Hey, didn't I see you at the Blade and Stars, once? You were the starting act for those Singing Dwarves. Classic.~
@12705 = ~[PC] Pay attention, boyo. I don't want a repeat of the last five times we were ambushed while you were on watch...~
@12706 = ~[ARAN] Talos' Hideous Strength, I wasn't tryin' to butt in. Just wanted to talk, you know.~
@12707 = ~[ARAN] By Ilmater's Tears, that don't help th' feelin's this bastard be slappin' me with. For th' sake o' mercy, can we shut him th' blighted hells up?~
@12708 = ~[ARAN] What do you want, Sarevok?~
@12709 = ~[ARAN] I'd be right happy to lend you a dagger. You could slit your gods-blighted throat, an' make us all a great deal happier.~
@12710 = ~[ARAN] You have no ability to make children, right? On account o' I think Faerun has blighted well had enough wi' just one o' you.~
@12711 = ~[ARAN] I want nothin' out o' you but breathin'. Strike that... I meant to say, I want you to quit breathin'.~
@12712 = ~[ARAN] Why don't you die already, an' go take over some nice corner o' th' nine hells, like a good little bastard? Wait... done forgot. You tried that, an' failed.~
@12713 = ~[ARAN] You got yourself a strikin' face, there. Hold still, an' I'd be right happy to strike it. Mayhap I might even stop after a bit.~
@12714 = ~[ARAN] Look, you stinkin' power-hungry evil bastard, I only put up wi' you on account o' <CHARNAME>'s wishes. Don't sleep too sound, or I might forget what <PRO_HESHE> done said, an' rid us all o' your unnatural presence.~
@12715 = ~[SAREVOK] You would be more amusing, sellsword, if you were not so weak.~
@12716 = ~[SAREVOK] The barking of stray dogs does not bother me, sellsword.~
@12717 = ~[SAREVOK] Ah, the breaking of wind. The sellsword must be talking again.~
@12718 = ~[SAREVOK] If you wish to act in <CHARNAME>'s best interest, fall on your sword now. Take care not to place it near your head, though, as it might not do enough damage on so hard a rock as that.~
@12719 = ~[SAREVOK] Ah, the mewling of an infant who realizes he will never be a powerful force to be reckoned with.~
@12720 = ~[SAREVOK] I merely wished to see if you had become more inventive in your invective. Sadly, you have the wit of a dull dagger.~
@12721 = ~[PC] Just checking.~
@12722 = ~[ARAN] You haven't told me to bugger off permanent, though you do seem a trifle short wi' me from time to time. Then again, you done got a huge amount to think about lately. I think we be friends. Why do you be askin'?~
@12723 = ~[ARAN] You told me to not try to confuse things by bein' friends, so we be supposed to keep to th' professional side. You command, I follow. Then you pay me. Why do you be askin'?~
@12724 = ~[HGWRA01] What of the inevitable pain you must cause to the one you love? This man, the one whom you call @68.~
@12725 = ~[ARAN] What in Cyric's Blighted Breath do this windbag be talkin' about? You be in control o' th' bloodurges...~
@12726 = ~[C-ARWRTH] Aran? Aye, Whitehand, light a torch or somethin'. It is as dark as hells here...~ [C-ARW001]
@12727 = ~[ARAN] What in th' nine hells... you be dead an' buried. Someone get me some holy water right quick, eh? You were no good when you was alive, an' I don't rightly want to see you now you be dead.~
@12728 = ~[C-ARWRTH] You have come up in th' world. Who is th' wench?~
@12729 = ~[ARAN] Keep a guard on your tongue, bastard.~
@12730 = ~[C-ARWRTH] Oho, a new lover? Stedd sees all now, Whitehand. You sorry weakling, you actually think you can keep her? Does she know?~
@12731 = ~[ARAN] Shut your filthy mouth.~
@12732 = ~[C-ARWRTH] Hah! She doesn't know! You remember, don't you? Th' smell of flesh burnin', th' screams of th' children...~
@12733 = ~[ARAN] I did what you ordered. Bane Blight your soul, I didn't know.~
@12734 = ~[C-ARWRTH] You lie, you piece of dung. You acted so high an' mighty, and then you go blindly followin' without a care or thought in th' world. Th' blood's on your hands, and those screams will haunt you past death's door. Think you will keep her precious lips close to you now, mercenary?~
@12735 = ~[ARAN] Gods...~
@12736 = ~[C-ARWRTH] Murderers all, we happy few. And you with th' weak stomach cryin' like a baby, battin' at the flames while your comrades died. Twice murderous, bastard. Charred flesh was not about to rise, an' we died because you had no stomach for th' collateral damage. Are you cryin' now?~
@12737 = ~[PC] Don't say those things to Aran! He did what he had to!~
@12738 = ~[PC] I... I knew you had done some difficult things in your past, but you never told me about this, Aran.~
@12739 = ~[PC] Stop tormenting Aran, spirit! ~
@12740 = ~[PC] Gorion, stop this! I won't let this go any further!~
@12741 = ~[PC] Aran, this isn't real. Don't listen to it!~
@12742 = ~[ARAN] I was goin' through some old letters o' Elena... you know, my sister what be in th' Waterdeep Mage Academy? I guess I get worried I won't be around for to protect her, th' way you did your sister.~
@12743 = ~[KORGAN] You dinna tell me you had a sister.~
@12744 = ~[HAERDALIS] Writing, journaling, tender sibling communications drawing a web of gossamer conversation across the miles... missives flying back and forth, and yet you do not introduce me, or send my warmest regards.~
@12745 = ~[ARAN] Can you blighted well blame me, you lecherous shortaxe?~
@12746 = ~[ARAN] As for introducin' a smooth talkin' amorous bard, I have my own reasons for delayin' that eventuality.~
@12747 = ~[KORGAN] Aye. When a buxom wench finds me attractive, there is no stopping me.~
@12748 = ~[HAERDALIS] Alas, this poor sparrow finds truth in your words, my friend. But think of how much she could have learned, under my gentle protective wing...~
@12749 = ~[CERND] There are times to be protective of your family, and times when you are unable to be there when you are needed most. Nature is not always kind.~
@12750 = ~[JAN] None of my family writes to me. I think it has to do with the last set of letters I replied to being sent with my latest invention, a new form of self-erasing ink. It seems to have caught itself on fire. Perhaps when Uncle Harald's fingers are healed, he will write to me again.~
@12751 = ~[PC] I was not around for Imoen, and it turned out alright. I had to chase an insane mage across the entire Sword Coast and beyond just to find her, but we could do the same for yours, if necessary.~
@12752 = ~[PC] You seem to be protective of me, too. I wonder if you see me as a little sister. It would explain so much...~
@12753 = ~[PC] Well, I worry about that, too, with the number of times you seem to need to be healed. You could try actually dodging a blow or two, you know.~
@12754 = ~[PC] Families are strange that way. We try to be there when we can, and worry when we can't.~
@12755 = ~[PC] I have a great idea... we swing north, pick her up, and start a small theater troupe. We can call it "Whitehand's Weird World". Or do you think that might interfere with the whole Prophecy thing? I suppose it would.~
@12756 = ~[ARAN] True enough. Th' worry wi' Elena be more on account o' lads sniffin' 'round than overbearin' evil twisted villainous mages... wait a moment... that blighted Mage's Academy be probably chock full o' power-hungry lads wi' slippery morals...~
@12757 = ~[JAHEIRA] You have a very large imagination, Aran. Then again, you are probably thinking that her peers are as earthy as you are.~
@12758 = ~[AERIE] Oh, I am sure everything is fine. There are many ways a woman mage has to protect herself.~
@12759 = ~[VICONIA] Surfacers always say such amusing things. The least of our Houses would easily best a Surfacer academy. Your sister sounds weak.~
@12760 = ~[VALYGAR] Another child warped by the unnatural influence of magic. Perhaps you should forbid her attendance, and get her away from that corruption.~
@12761 = ~[PC] I don't think it is likely that they would become another Irenicus.~
@12762 = ~[PC] Just a little overprotective, aren't you? How cute. Has she seen twelve summers yet, or only nine?~
@12763 = ~[PC] I hadn't realized she was in need of such intense protectiveness. I should have realized that apples don't fall far from trees, and since you both fell from the same tree... come on, Aran. She is a grown woman.~
@12764 = ~[PC] I think the Academy is far safer a place for her than on the road with you, don't you? I understand your worry, but you would be far more distracted if you were trying to do your job and protect her at the same time.~
@12765 = ~[PC] If she is anything like you, I would be more worried about the virtues of the poor boys trying to court her.~
@12766 = ~[ARAN] You do have a point there. I just let my imagination get th' better o' me, is all.~
@12767 = ~[ANOMEN] Your lack of discipline and coarse breeding triumphs again.~
@12768 = ~[KELDORN] Imagination is a useful trait in a warrior, but it can lead you astray very quickly.~
@12769 = ~[MAZZY] I think we should go and check on how she is doing.~
@12770 = ~[PC] Having an imagination is a good thing. We could always set aside a little time, go north, and hang around the Academy for awhile, seeing the sights... but I probably should stay here.~
@12771 = ~[PC] No, no... you are probably right. You should get there, before she ends up... oh, the horrors... *kissing* some *boy*. Even worse, having fun! Go, flex that incredible Whitehand command of Common.~
@12772 = ~[PC] If you feel that she is in danger, you should go. Family is family.~
@12773 = ~[PC] You are a good person to have around, Aran. Then again, your sister is probably a lot smarter than you. Perhaps you could switch places with her. I think we can find a polymorph spell someplace...~
@12774 = ~[EDWIN] Go, go, by all means, go.~
@12775 = ~[MINSC] No, Aran, we are you and and me and Boo, Boo and you and me... we should go together!~
@12776 = ~[PC] I am very glad to have you on my side.~
@12777 = ~[PC] Awww... just what I always wanted. A pack mule with a sense of honor and camaraderie! For that, I will give you a carrot. But I do appreciate it, you know.~
@12778 = ~[PC] I am glad you are on my team, Aran. Even if it means more burning hot curry and that incessant whistling.~
@12779 = ~[PC] Just my side? I am pretty sure you wouldn't likely leave any part of me, judging by the amount of time your hands spend checking that all my body parts are still intact.~
@12780 = ~[PC] Lightly, heavily, modestly, boldly... you could just say "I won't leave you alone because I like you", you know.~
@12781 = ~[PC] Besides, we could all head up there together, and you could introduce me to your sister. Does she like pretty silk underthings? I am quite the ladies man, you know.~
@12782 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, that be a good line o' thought to pursue. Th' touchin', that is, not you bein' my little sister, or anythin'...~
@12783 = ~[JAHEIRA] Have I described to you the definition and usage of the word 'subtle' to you yet, Aran?~
@12784 = ~[AERIE] Why is Aran blushing?~
@12785 = ~[ARAN] Th' worry wi' Elena be more on account o' lads sniffin' 'round than overbearin' evil twisted villainous mages... wait a moment... that blighted Mage's Academy be probably chock full o' power-hungry lads wi' slippery morals...~
@12786 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, that be a good line o' thought to pursue. Th' touchin', that is, not you bein' my little sister, or anythin'... I think that kissin' you feels nothin' like kissin' a sister.~
@12787 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, we done pursued some o' that thought together already, eh? Th' touchin', that is, not you bein' my little sister, or anythin'...~
@12788 = ~[JAHEIRA] Have I described to you the definition and usage of the word 'subtle' to you yet, Aran? You are displaying early signs of mating rituals, and this is not the time or place for such behavior.~
@12789 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, that be a good line o' thought to pursue. If I do recollect, we have done our share o' explorin' that topic, too. Th' touchin', that is, not you bein' my little sister, or anythin'...~
@12790 = ~[JAHEIRA] Have I described to you the definition and usage of the word 'subtle' to you yet, Aran? There is little chance of keeping your privacy when you are constantly so bold.~
@12791 = ~[AERIE] I... I am not sure we should be hearing all of this.~
@12792 = ~[ARAN] No, no... this got all sidetracked already. Look, th' worry wi' Elena be more on account o' lads sniffin' 'round than overbearin' evil twisted villainous mages... wait a moment... that blighted Mage's Academy be probably chock full o' power-hungry lads wi' slippery morals...~
@12793 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, that came out right fine in my hearin'. I do seem to have some troubles wi' not constantly touchin' you whenever I can find a way to.~
@12794 = ~[ARAN] Hells, Ajantis be as bad as you. He has naught in th' way o' good juicy gossip, just tales o' honor an' such. I think he were a companion back on th' Trade Way, before you all headed southwest.~
@12795 = ~[ARAN] Imoen must have been a sight to see, an' a blighted tough one to keep up with, back on th' Sword Coast. I can imagine she kept everyone on their toes. Glory, conquest, an' pink accouterments for all, eh?~
@12796 = ~[ARAN] I think Viconia met up wi' you way back, but I'm not blighted likely to get no stories from her. Not that I'd believe them anyways, or listen, or even ask that spiderspawn bitch naught.~
@12797 = ~[ARAN] I done heard rumors what put Edwin an' <CHARNAME> together far back on th' Sword Coast. I don't rightly believe anythin' he claims fully, on account o' that overweanin' ego o' his, but I think he claims all th' glories o' old were his doin'.~
@12798 = ~[ARAN] Gavin be a right good lad, but I can't get much in th' way o' glory stories out o' him. I think he done met up wi' you early on, eh? That must o' been somethin', wanderin' into dangerous territory wi' a healer what might trip over his own two feet if th' wind blows th' wrong way.~
@12799 = ~[ARAN] You have to help a lad out, here. Xan just looks at me wi' that morose expression o' his an' shakes his head. A Moonblade wielder, a Harper, an' <CHARNAME>. Hells, that must o' spawned quite a few stories an' glories.~
@12800 = ~[ARAN] Kivan don't say much about those days. He just looks at those hands o' his, flexes them a mite bit, an' gets a far-off look in his eyes. A powerful one like that on your side, you all must o' made quite th' play for glory.~
@12801 = ~[ARAN] Whoa, there, Nalia... easy on th' fierce gestures! I'd prefer to keep my head all in one piece, not be missin' half my face on account o' you be pissed off a bit, eh?~
@12802 = ~[NALIA] I am not angry, just frustrated.~
@12803 = ~[ARAN] Anger, frustration, a little bit miffed, well... when I be on th' receivin' end o' any o' those, an' th' giver be an archmage what can wipe me out wi' a few words an' a quick gesture... it all seems th' same to me.~
@12804 = ~[NALIA] Oh, I was not frustrated with you. It just seems that no matter how powerful I become, the less I am able to make meaningful change.~
@12805 = ~[ARAN] I'd say disintegratin', wiltin' an' generally obliteratin' your opponents counts as makin' a blighted meanin'ful change, at least to them.~
@12806 = ~[NALIA] I mean changes that make more of a difference than a few enemies here and there. The Council of Six, The Cowled Wizards, my own lands... all of them cry out for change. Any one of them could take a lifetime of commitment to adjust the inequities.~
@12807 = ~[ARAN] Hells, you be talkin' about social change. That takes a mite bit more than a single lifetime, I'd say. Only one answer. Kill 'em all an' set yourself up in charge, an' change everythin' all at once.~
@12808 = ~[NALIA] Aran! How can you even think that!~
@12809 = ~[ARAN] I'm only jokin', m'girl. Ask that bastard Sarevok how that kind o' thinkin' works out. I bet you he'd tell you it takes a lifetime just to keep power when you rise that way. You don't have time to change things much, on account o' you are always fightin' just to stay in power.~
@12810 = ~[ARAN] Whenever some blighted fool gets th' idea that you can make long-term change that way, th' mercenary life gets a bit more lucrative. Violent an' bloody social revolution, it do be a great equalizer, though.~
@12811 = ~[NALIA] I do not see how. The cost in lives and resources, the constant cycle of destruction, none of that stops the pain of the common folk.~
@12812 = ~[ARAN] Aye. But noble, common, rich, poor, pretty, ugly... dead be dead. Can't rightly get more equal that that, eh?~
@12813 = ~[NALIA] Aran, I do think that you are beginning to grow up.~
@12814 = ~[ARAN] Now, what in Sune's Blessed Sweetness would cause you to say somethin' so mean?~
@12815 = ~[NALIA] You seem to have stopped trying to stare at my bottom when you think I am not looking.~
@12816 = ~[ARAN] That's not growin' up. That's just realizin' that you have spells what can disintegrate me. Call it 'enlightened self interest.'~
@12817 = ~[NALIA] Still, that is more thinking than the old Aran would do.~
@12818 = ~[ARAN] Fair enough. By th' way, you done got a little spot o' somethin' on th' left o' your derriere. I'd have said somethin', but that self-preservation thing made me a mite bit reticent, eh?~
@12819 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly trust you, you know.~
@12820 = ~[SAREVOK] Then you have studied better than I thought. All war is based on deception. Trust is a weakness.~
@12821 = ~[ARAN] So you do be plannin' to betray <PRO_HIMHER> when th' time be right.~
@12822 = ~[SAREVOK] No.~
@12823 = ~[ARAN] Why not? You have done far worse in th' past, an' you hold no contract sacred.~
@12824 = ~[SAREVOK] I cannot.~
@12825 = ~[ARAN] You  can't rightly betray <PRO_HIMHER>, or you choose not to?~
@12826 = ~[SAREVOK] Both.~
@12827 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly understand.~
@12828 = ~[SAREVOK] That is not my problem, sellsword. Come to me when you have tasted the glories of unadulterated strength, when you have fools who follow you to their destruction regardless of cost to themselves, when you have ultimate power just within your reach...~
@12829 = ~[SAREVOK] ...and it has been torn from your grasp and from your very soul. Only then will you understand. I will not betray my <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>. My time has passed. Now, <PRO_HISHER>s is rising.~
@12830 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells. No accountin' for taste, I suppose, but Sune herself must o' cursed me right proper.~
@12831 = ~[AERIE] Tell her.~
@12832 = ~[ARAN] What?~
@12833 = ~[AERIE] Tell her how you feel.~
@12834 = ~[ARAN] Now, what do you be goin' on about, Aerie? Never did hear you dole out advice so freely. Complaints, yes. Advice, no.~
@12835 = ~[AERIE] It is obvious you love her. And it hurts you to see her with him.~
@12836 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, keep your voice down! She might hear you!~
@12837 = ~[AERIE] Why don't you just tell her how much you care?~
@12838 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. I be no extra-planar bard wi' beautiful speech an' soft words. Hells, I can't even rightly say naught wi' out bringin one or more gods into th' conversation.~
@12839 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. I be no world-travellin' kara-turan wi' interestin' stories an' soft words. Hells, I can't even rightly say naught wi' out bringin one or more gods into th' conversation.~
@12840 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. He be power, hunger, an' strength, tied right proper to her soul. I have naught to compete against that.~
@12841 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. Th' boy loves her right proper, an' she seems happy enough. Soon enough she will be tellin' me to keep away an' 'just be friends'.~
@12842 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. Necromantic extra-planar elf versus th' poor sod what sells his sword an' can barely speak two blighted words wi' out bringin' a god or two into th' conversation.~
@12843 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. He may be a clumsy bastard, an' gods knows he comes wi' a bit o' baggage wi' Lanie an' all, but th' boy makes her right happy. An' he be a good friend.~
@12844 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. I don't rightly see what she sees in that pompous self-centered bastard, but he can offer her much more than I can. An' she seems to be willin' to let him be close.~
@12845 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. He may be a self-centered prissy evil bastard, but he be a Red Wizard. Power, refinement, sophistication. Everythin' I'm not.~
@12846 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. A blighted knight, versus a sellsword what has naught to offer. Hells, I can't even sit at th' same table as Ajantis. I'd be out wi' th' other common rabble, not sittin' in a Greathall.~
@12847 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. I know she sees more in him than in me. I look at him, an' I see naught but an enemy. She looks at him, an' she sees somethin' that lets him get close. Soon enough, she will tell me to 'just be friends'.~
@12848 = ~[ARAN] I see it in her eyes. Th' way she looks at him... Lost love or no, he has followed her since th' first. How can I compete wi' an elven archer what has bent centuries o' will to servin' her an' lovin' her?~
@12849 = ~[ARAN] Look at me. An' then look at him. We be worlds apart, yet she lets him be close. I'm not sayin' Valygar is th' worst she could do, but am I really any better?~
@12850 = ~[ARAN] I'll take whatever time she gives me, an' be glad enough for that.~
@12851 = ~[AERIE] You sound like me. Like I used to sound. I thought I was the one who wallowed in self-pity.~
@12852 = ~[ARAN] Not self-pity, just cold hard facts.~
@12853 = ~[AERIE] I thought you once told me that the exterior didn't matter, and my inner strength was what made me interesting.~
@12854 = ~[ARAN] If I did, I was bein' a poncy idiot what wanted to bed you.~
@12855 = ~[AERIE] I... I know you better than that, Aran. I think you are running away. Just tell her.~
@12856 = ~[JAHEIRA] Tell her.~
@12857 = ~[JAHEIRA] Tell her how you feel.~
@12858 = ~[ARAN] Here it comes. Mother Jaheira, First Prime o' th' Busybody an' Unwanted Meddlin' Guild. Paid your dues yet this year?~
@12859 = ~[JAHEIRA] It is obvious you love her. And it hurts you to see her with him.~
@12860 = ~[JAHEIRA] Why don't you just tell her how much you care?~
@12861 = ~[JAHEIRA] Khalid used to think that way about himself. He once said he never understood why I chose him.~
@12862 = ~[ARAN] Why did you?~
@12863 = ~[JAHEIRA] I almost didn't.~
@12864 = ~[ARAN] What sealed th' deal?~
@12865 = ~[JAHEIRA] He let me know he loved me.~
@12866 = ~[NALIA] Tell her.~
@12867 = ~[NALIA] Tell her how you feel.~
@12868 = ~[ARAN] Look, Nalia, you be a right fine lookin' woman. If things were a mite bit different, I'd be chasin' you right proper. But you be a mite bit naive in th' love department, all arranged-marriage an' such. No offense, but you don't blighted know naught.~
@12869 = ~[NALIA] It is obvious you love her. And it hurts you to see her with him.~
@12870 = ~[NALIA] Why don't you just tell her how much you care?~
@12871 = ~[NALIA] It is true that you are coarse, crude, dirty-minded, usually dirty-handed, and rude.~
@12872 = ~[ARAN] You could have thrown in ugly an' lowclass, you know. I think you missed a couple o' opportunities to kick me while I was down, there.~
@12873 = ~[NALIA] On the other hand, you love her.~
@12874 = ~[ARAN] What difference does that make?~
@12875 = ~[NALIA] It makes all the difference in the world. Trust me.~
@12876 = ~[MAZZY] Tell her.~
@12877 = ~[MAZZY] Tell her how you feel.~
@12878 = ~[ARAN] Look, Mazzy, you be a right fine friend. But you see things a bit black an' white, all or naught. This be more complicated than that.~
@12879 = ~[MAZZY] It is obvious you love her. And it hurts you to see her with him.~
@12880 = ~[MAZZY] Why don't you just tell her how much you care?~
@12881 = ~[MAZZY] I know that Avoreen does not always let us have exactly what we want. But She seeks to give us what we need.~
@12882 = ~[ARAN] An' you think I am a better fit for what be needed?~
@12883 = ~[MAZZY] I do not know. But I know that there are seldom second chances. If I had another chance, I would tell Patrick how I felt. I would tell him every day.~
@12884 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells. Sune herself must o' cursed me right proper.~
@12885 = ~[KELDORN] Tell her.~
@12886 = ~[KELDORN] Tell her how you feel.~
@12887 = ~[ARAN] I can't rightly do that.~
@12888 = ~[KELDORN] It is obvious you love her. And it hurts you to see her with him.~
@12889 = ~[ARAN] Blighted.. Keldorn, keep your voice down. She might hear you.~
@12890 = ~[KELDORN] You have the strength, and you have the power. You lack the will. Just tell her how much you care.~
@12891 = ~[KELDORN] I have never seen you flinch from a battle, or hide from a true challenge. If it is in your heart, then the way forward is to let her know your feelings.~
@12892 = ~[KELDORN] Would you subject me to the... to the pain I have already experienced?~
@12893 = ~[ARAN] Hells, Keldorn, no, I... Have I been disloyal? I done pledged you my sword, an' I'd follow you anywhere. But she... she is...~
@12894 = ~[KELDORN] I know. But do not underestimate her. And do not underestimate me. Honesty and truth is more important in this matter than any other. She deserves to know, and to make her choice. And on the bonds of our friendship, both you and I need the truth to be open and between us, as well.~
@12895 = ~[ARAN] I hear you. I don't rightly believe love be truly a war. Somehow, it seems much bloodier, an' a hells o' a lot more painful.~
@12896 = ~[KELDORN] I believe that is the truest thing I have ever heard you say.~
@12897 = ~[ARAN] So, have you decided what th' acceptable level o' corruption be, or do you just be waitin' until th' right moment to say you be wrong?~
@12898 = ~[VALYGAR] I am not wrong. Magic is a force that corrupts all who use it.~
@12899 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>, <PRO_HESHE> be a right powerful user o' magic.~
@12900 = ~[VALYGAR] An occurrence which troubles me greatly. I think <PRO_HESHE> should proceed carefully.~
@12901 = ~[ARAN] <CHARNAME>, <PRO_HESHE> an I both be right powerful users o' magic.~
@12902 = ~[VALYGAR] An occurrence which troubles me greatly. Both of you should proceed carefully.~
@12903 = ~[ARAN] I be a right powerful user o' magic.~
@12904 = ~[VALYGAR] An occurrence which troubles me greatly. You should proceed carefully.~
@12905 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly think we could get all th' way here without usin' some serious magic. I don't feel corrupted. Hells, I feel right fine, I do.~
@12906 = ~[VALYGAR] Do you think Bodhi felt that her vampiric nature and magical powers were a form of corruption?~
@12907 = ~[ARAN] Well, she were undead herself, eh? She looked a mite peaked an' whitish, I guess. Th' magic use were somethin' secondary to her nature, is all.~
@12908 = ~[VALYGAR] You do not seem to be getting my point.~
@12909 = ~[ARAN] Oh, I be gettin' it. I just don't find m'self in agreement, is all.~
@12910 = ~[HAERDALIS] My fierce hound, why so morose and destitute?~
@12911 = ~[ARAN] Who do you be callin' destitute? I have more than a few coin hidden about by now.~
@12912 = ~[HAERDALIS] Oh no, you misunderstand. I but alluded to your air of despondency, your troubled brow. It is at odds with our progress. Your part in our little drama seems a great success.~
@12913 = ~[ARAN] Aye. Th' thing is... well, to take a metaphor, mayhap this truly be like one o' your fancy plays.~
@12914 = ~[HAERDALIS] I shall listen, good hound, with much anticipation.~
@12915 = ~[ARAN] Well, th' long an' th' short o' it is, what happens when th' play be over?~
@12916 = ~[HAERDALIS] We take our bows, receive our acclaim, and enjoy the adoration of our many admirers for the brief span of time before the next performance.~
@12917 = ~[ARAN] You done played th' leadin' man too many times, boyo. For th' rest o' us bit parts, we don't follow along to th' next performance. We tend to get less o' glory an' challenge, an' more waitin' tables, muckin' out stalls, an' fadin' into th' woodwork. Metaphorically speakin', o' course.~
@12918 = ~[ARAN] Hey, Haer'Dalis, you be a right fine bard, eh?~
@12919 = ~[HAERDALIS] Would that all my audiences were as appreciative as you! Or perhaps you meant to ask this poor sparrow for an evaluation of his own talents?~
@12920 = ~[ARAN] Well, more o' th' first than th' second, I think. I was just wonderin'... would you do a lad a favor an' look this little story over for me?~
@12921 = ~[HAERDALIS] I see that you have talents of your own, my hound, for that 'little' story appears to be scribed on several parchments.~
@12922 = ~[ARAN] I done got carried away, a little.~
@12923 = ~[HAERDALIS] It would be my pleasure. Let me see this gentle foray into the wilds of authorship.~
@12924 = ~[ARAN] Well, what do you be thinkin'? On account o' you have a peculiar look on your face, even more'n usual.~
@12925 = ~[HAERDALIS] I must struggle to maintain my composure, my fierce hound. You have written perhaps the most... most amusing comedy! I had no idea you were so creative. This passage, for example; masterful overuse of purple prose. A parody -  nay, even a Burlesque!~
@12926 = ~[ARAN] Errr... it were supposed to be a bit risky, an' bedroomy, an' all. More get th' reader all hot an' bothered. Not really one o' those comedy things, eh?~
@12927 = ~[HAERDALIS] Ah. Yes. Well. To borrow a turn of phrase often heard in bardic lore... this is an intriguing concept. In the hands of a talented author, it might even be publishable. Alas, it is neither.~
@12928 = ~[ARAN] You look a mite pensive, Jaheira. What be draggin' you back down th' distant foggy paths o' memory?~
@12929 = ~[JAHEIRA] I am simply remembering how this all started. How young <CHARNAME> was, those few short years ago.~
@12930 = ~[ARAN] So, tell me a story, eh? You never do tell all th' ins an' outs o' what th' glorious days were like. You started out early enough to know <PRO_HIMHER> when a few kobolds were a right difficult challenge.~
@12931 = ~[JAHEIRA] I would not describe them as glorious. But they did have their charm.~
@12932 = ~[ARAN] I can see it now. <CHARNAME>, all wrapped up in swaddlin' clothes, wavin' <PRO_HISHER> arms wild-like an' bein' chased by a horde o' gibberlings.~
@12933 = ~[JAHEIRA] The waving of arms, perhaps. But no swaddling clothes.~
@12934 = ~[ARAN] Well, was there somethin' right special from th' first sight o' <PRO_HIMHER>, or did th' whole romance thing wi' you two spring up just when you be wanderin' around Amn fendin' off challenges to th' Balance?~
@12935 = ~[JAHEIRA] I was deeply in love with Khalid. I am still deeply in love with Khalid. After his death, it... it became complicated.~
@12936 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells... I done put my foot right in it. Look, I meant no harm. I was just askin' on account o' you an <PRO_HIMHER>, you seem to fit right together. Xvim's Spit, I just stuffed both feet right up my mouth.~
@12937 = ~[JAHEIRA] A habit which I find I must constantly remind you to curb.~
@12938 = ~[ARAN] I always wanted to know if was there somethin' right special from th' first, or did th' whole romance thing wi' those two spring up just when they be wanderin' around Amn smitin' evil an' generally doin' good?~
@12939 = ~[ARAN] Just wonderin', on account o' it seems they were a mite fast to get married.~
@12940 = ~[JAHEIRA] That is their story to tell, Aran. If Ajantis does not wish to tell you, and <CHARNAME> says nothing, then I certainly cannot.~
@12941 = ~[ARAN] Not to put too fine a point on it, but... well, I don't quite get what th' two o' them have as a relationship. On th' one hand, Imoen be like a sister to <PRO_HIMHER>. On th' other, I done seen how <CHARNAME> looks at Imoen, an' there be little o' sisterlyness, eh? It be hard to hide that they be right close together more'n most folks what be married. Did they always be this way?~
@12942 = ~[JAHEIRA] That is their story to tell, Aran. If Imoen does not wish to tell you, and <CHARNAME> says nothing, then I certainly cannot.~
@12943 = ~[ARAN] When did <CHARNAME> get all bent up over th' Shar-kissed drowess, anyways? I mean, were it just animal attraction at first, an' then some kind o' power struggle, or did she set right out to seduce <PRO_HIMHER> right away?~
@12944 = ~[JAHEIRA] That is their story to tell, Aran. Given your obvious hatred of Viconia, I would be discreet, and leave them alone.~
@12945 = ~[ARAN] Th' two o' them, Odesseiron an' <CHARNAME>... were they like to spark right from th' beginnin', or did they decide to become insufferable together later on?~
@12946 = ~[JAHEIRA] That is their story to tell, Aran. I do not doubt that Edwin will gladly boast of their relationship.~
@12947 = ~[ARAN] An' when did Gavin start gettin' so close to <CHARNAME>? Were it gradual, or instant-like? Love at first sight back by th' Temple he says he worked with back near Beregost, or did he have to batter at th' gates, so to speak?~
@12948 = ~[JAHEIRA] That is their story to tell, Aran. If Gavin does not wish to tell you, and <CHARNAME> says nothing, then I certainly cannot.~
@12949 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly see what <PRO_HESHE> seen in him, y'know. All that doom an' gloom an' angst. But they spark an' confer like they was attached at th' soul, or somethin'. When did <PRO_HESHE> fall for Xan, anyways?~
@12950 = ~[JAHEIRA] That is their story to tell, Aran. If Xan does not wish to tell you, and <CHARNAME> says nothing, then I certainly cannot.~
@12951 = ~[ARAN] Did <PRO_HESHE> fall for th' ohtar right away, or were it more gradual? It seems all a mite bit complicated, it do. Kwentra i'narn, mellonamin.~
@12952 = ~[JAHEIRA] That is their story to tell, Aran. If Kivan does not wish to tell you, and <CHARNAME> says nothing, then I certainly cannot. And 'ohtar' translates as 'warrior'. Kivan is far more than that.~
@12953 = ~[ARAN] Well, nothin' ventured, nothin' gained, I guess. Don't blame a lad for some simple curiosity.~
@12954 = ~[ARAN] I know it were not all teacups an' roses, but I'd give a blighted fortune to have seen th' whole Iron Throne thing from your perspective, instead o' from th' front lines fightin' Chill an' Blacktalons.~
@12955 = ~[JAHEIRA] I... I have many memories I would not repeat. But I am glad that I can think back on them, and see where we are now.~
@12956 = ~[JAHEIRA] I am simply remembering how this all started. How young <CHARNAME> seemed, those few short years ago.~
@12957 = ~[ARAN] Branwen was mutterin' somethin' similar just a bit ago. Judgin' by th' amount o' "Tempus this" an' "Tempus that", she weren't so sure things have gotten better.~
@12958 = ~[ARAN] You Tel'Quessir must be connected somehow. Coran were sayin' somethin' yesterday about th' wondrous Cloakwood, an' how th' more things change th' more things change. Didn't rightly make no sense to me.~
@12959 = ~[ARAN] You Tel'Quessir must be connected somehow.  Coran were sayin' somethin' yesterday about th' wondrous Cloakwood, an' how th' more things change th' more things change. Didn't rightly make no sense to me.~
@12960 = ~[ARAN] I don't rightly trust that Eldoth fellow to tell th' tales. For a bard, he be a mite bit on th' silent side. But I suppose he might have seen a fair bit.~
@12961 = ~[ARAN] My bet be Minsc has not changed much.~
@12962 = ~[ARAN] I'd ask Quayle about th' old days, but somehow I suspect I'd be listenin' to a blighted hells o' a long story. I just want some o' th' juicy bits.~
@12963 = ~[ARAN] Shar-Teel were around back then, I think, but she don't seem to like me much. Comes wi' havin' to wear a codpiece, I guess.~
@12964 = ~[ARAN] I'd ask Skie, on account o' she loves a good piece o' gossip, but then I'd have to get through all th' chatter about silks, an' that bastard Elfred, or Eddoth, or whatever th' bard what she moans about were named.~
@12965 = ~[ARAN] I'd ask Skie, on account o' she loves a good piece o' gossip, but then I'd have to get through all th' chatter about silks, an' that bastard Eldoth treated her right bad, but she just loves him anyways. Or hates him. Guess it depends on th' day.~
@12966 = ~[ARAN] Somehow I think th' conversation wi' Tiax would be about how he solved th' whole Iron Throne crisis in spite o' havin' all o' you along, eh?~
@12967 = ~[ARAN] Yeslick has one hells o' a hollow leg, but no matter how much he drinks he don't spill naught in th' way o' good stories.~
@12968 = ~[ARAN] Alora just looks at me an' giggles, so no help there.~
@12969 = ~[ARAN] An' you, you be th' worst o' all. You never do tell all th' ins an' outs. My boon companions, startin' out early enough to know <PRO_HIMHER> when a few kobolds were a right difficult challenge, an' you hold back on th' tales o' glory.~
@12970 = ~I heard you, I heard you.~
@12971 = ~No rush. Just letting you know I need more ale.~
@12972 = ~Orrin, whose orders are these?~
@12973 = ~I have no idea.~
@12974 = ~Oh.~
@12975 = ~You know, either someone just set this whole place shaking, or I have had too much to drink.~
@12976 = ~Orrin, the half orc back there says she wants real ale, not the watered down stuff.~
@12977 = ~Orrin, what does "coin-lass" mean?~
@12978 = ~It means you do what Gisele does to make a living.~
@12979 = ~In that case, make sure the next pint on table twelve makes them sick.~
@12980 = ~So let it be written, so let it be done.~
@12981 = ~I wonder if anyone has a game going in the center room.~
@12982 = ~You would think this place would have a good spittoon...~
@12983 = ~Oh. I'm drinking from it.~
