@13144 = ~The Broken Sword~
@13145 = ~The Broken Sword. Room and board. Mercenaries and sellswords only.~
@13146 = ~Aran Whitehand Joins

A sellsword named Aran has joined me. He seems to have had some experience, so perhaps he will be useful. I met him at an inn for mercenaries, The Broken Sword, on the Promenade.~
@13147 = ~The Broken Sword

The Broken Sword Inn turned out to be a productive visit. It looks like there are several sources of information there, and I picked up a mercenary named Aran Whitehand as well. He seems to have some ties with an innkeeper, a mercenary recruiter named Teldra, and the barmaid. I may investigate this place again.~
@13148 = ~[ARAN] Erudite Edwin? Egregious Edwin? Mayhap I'd better leave him out o' this, on account o' his sense o' humor runs more to th' pain side o' things, I expect..~
@13149 = ~[PC] Sorry, but I can't help myself sometimes. Ah, Aran, don't be mad but...perhaps you want this book back, too. And perhaps this comb...~
@13150 = ~[PC] Hey. Turnabout is fair play. Didn't I see you poking about in my pack a few days ago?~
@13151 = ~[PC] Fine. be that way. Go sulk.~
@13152 = ~[PC] I'm sorry, Aran. I won't do it again.~
@13153 = ~[ARAN] Once a sticky-fingered inquisitive little thief, always one, eh? Right. Only don't take naught in th' way o' my spices. Nor these letters, eh?~
@13154 = ~[ARAN] Right. Well, no harm done, but that be a mean thing to do to a lad, eh? My space, my things.~
@13155 = ~[ARAN] That were different. I were... I were... I were doin' th' laundry. Right. I were doin' th' laundry.~
@13156 = ~[ARAN] You know, I be a mite bit worried.~
@13157 = ~[PC] What are you worried about now?~
@13158 = ~[PC] You should be.~
@13159 = ~[PC] I am worried, too.~
@13160 = ~[PC] I would stuff your gear in your mouth to shut off the noise, but somehow I think you would still find a way to blather on about nothing.~
@13161 = ~[PC] Silence is golden. Pay yourself. Or perhaps I can pay you to SHUT THE HELLS UP.~
@13162 = ~[PC] Just leave me alone, ok? I wouldn't want to disturb your industrious scratching of various body parts. Go back to doing whatever it is you were doing.~
@13163 = ~[ARAN] Aye. That be another thing what worries me. Ever since I started workin' wi' you, I start thinkin' when I should be actin', an' actin' when I should be thinkin'.~
@13164 = ~[PC] So you have a little crush on me?~
@13165 = ~[PC] So you have a little crush on me? I thought you said you prefer women.~
@13166 = ~[PC] Oh, and here I thought you were worried that we keep running into all sorts of powerful adversaries, and understanding that it is only a matter of time before one of them rends us limb from limb.~
@13167 = ~[PC] There is nothing to worry about, Aran. We are a pretty good team.~
@13168 = ~[PC] You keep your eyes open and be ready for whatever comes next. Let me do the worrying.~
@13169 = ~[PC] I am trying to think up a random insult to hurl your way, but I'm fresh out of ideas.~
@13170 = ~[PC] I would insult you, but I have rules against taking advantage of idiots.~
@13171 = ~[PC] To quote a Rashemite insult, thou art a warped ill-nurtured gibberling.~
@13172 = ~[ARAN] Just about everythin', I think.~
@13173 = ~[PC] You really do think too much.~
@13174 = ~[PC] Why worry? What happens, happens. All we can do is be prepared to the worst.~
@13175 = ~[PC] I would insult you so that you would stop talking to me and leave me alone, but I have rules against taking advantage of idiots.~
@13176 = ~[ARAN] That be what bothers me th' most. So far, every time I think o' th' worst situation we could face, an' prepare myself, it turns out that things be far worse than I could ever o' imagined. I be startin' to get th' twitches, watchin' each little child what walks by just in case they be a demon or dragon or lich or some other gods-blighted creature o' myth an' legend.~
@13177 = ~[PC] Your biggest worry should be how to procure curry powder and store it without accidentally getting it into your smallclothes.~
@13178 = ~[PC] Hey, we are wandering about a huge trapped guarded stone fortress with unspeakably horrendous adversaries lurking at every turn. What could possibly go wrong?~
@13179 = ~[PC] I think we are safe here. There is less to worry about when you are tucked away in a planar pocket. Unless, of course, this is just a dream, and when I wake up the whole bubble just disappears with you inside it.~
@13180 = ~[PC] Perhaps we should talk about being worried when we are not in a city that has had Fire giants slamming huge rocks into it. I think some of the timers over there look a little worse for the wear...~
@13181 = ~[PC] I think you need a drink. If we are going to sit around in the Tankard Tree worrying about beams damaged by seigework, and the possibility of the roof falling in on us, we need to do it while drunk.~
@13182 = ~[PC] I think you need to order us drinks. If we are going to sit around and worry about who is spying on us right this very minute and plotting our slow death by unspeakable tortures, we need to do it while drunk.~
@13183 = ~[PC] Do not fret, Aran. Waukeen will protect Her temple. Unless she really is gone, and a new goddess is just messing about giving her worshipers powers...~
@13184 = ~[PC] It must be the prison surroundings making you all upset. Just think, you could have been imprisoned here ages ago, and I could be meeting you for the first time right now, and wondering why the sellsword in the corner cell has a beard that goes past his knees.~
@13185 = ~[PC] It must be the barracks. It must remind you of what your life would have been like if you had stayed in the Flaming Fist. Just think - you might have made it all the way up to Captain!~
@13186 = ~[PC] It must be the smell of these sewers. Or perhaps it is the thought of slimy little creatures dripping on the back of your neck...~
@13187 = ~[PC] Oh, come on. What are a few legion Drow, some minor hirelings, and a minor risk the eye of Lolth glances our way? Nothing to worry about at all.~
@13188 = ~[PC] Oh, come on. We are just wandering about in a crypt. Nothing bad ever happens in one of these places, right?~
@13189 = ~[PC] Oh, come on. We are just wandering about in a place guarded by Fire Giants. Nothing bad ever happens in one of these places, right?~
@13190 = ~[PC] Now you have me worried.~
@13191 = ~[ARAN] Well, you blighted well hide it well.~
@13192 = ~[PC] I am trying to think up a random insult to hurl your way, but I'm fresh out of ideas. Just stop talking, please.~
@13193 = ~[PC] I am not sure I hide it well at all. But so far, we have been able to prevail.~
@13194 = ~[ARAN] Hells, this has naught to do wi' any romance or such. It be more a matter o' skills. Or mayhap direction. Or, hells... ~
@13195 = ~[ARAN] ...well, mayhap it be a little about th' way you make me feel. But it be more about somethin'... ~
@13196 = ~[ARAN] Well, mayhap we be a good team, an' so far we have come out only a mite bit worse for th' wear. Mayhap you be right. You worry, I watch.~
@13197 = ~[PC] Absolutely. After all, there is nothing we can do. Our fate has been set into stone since the beginning of time. When our eventual doom befalls us, it is just the natural course of events.~
@13198 = ~[PC] Absolutely. Your biggest worry should be how to procure curry powder and store it without accidentally getting it into your smallclothes.~
@13199 = ~[PC] I am glad we have that all settled. Now, did I remember to tell you that we are almost out of ale?~
@13200 = ~[PC] I never worry. I just know you will step in front of whatever tries to harm me. No matter how many pieces it tears you into.~
@13201 = ~[ARAN] Kelemvor's Sharp Scythe... now, why did you go an' say that? Now I'll be havin' naught in th' way o' sleep, on account o' th' nightmares!~
@13202 = ~[ARAN] Bane's Bones, all this wanderin' gets to a lad. Come on, pass th' time wi' me, eh? What scares you most in all th' world?~
@13203 = ~[PC] Nothing. Nothing scares me.~
@13204 = ~[PC] The thought of having to continue this conversation with you scares the hells out of me.~
@13205 = ~[PC] Losing control of my actions or thoughts scares me.~
@13206 = ~[PC] Being powerless scares me most.~
@13207 = ~[PC] This may sound strange, but death scares me.~
@13208 = ~[PC] Bhaal regaining his Essence scares me.~
@13209 = ~[PC] Forgetting my friendships, and letting people I care about down scares me.~
@13210 = ~[PC] Forgetting which of my many lovers I am with, and crying out the wrong name in the heat of the moment scares me.~
@13211 = ~[PC] You know what scares me already. You tell me what scares you the most.~
@13212 = ~[ARAN] You done put up wi' my random blather long enough where I be knowin' you be jokin', eh?~
@13213 = ~[PC] Well, if you really want to talk about this, you should tell me what scares you.~
@13214 = ~[PC] Of course. Besides, you know absolutely nothing scares me.~
@13215 = ~[PC] I am not joking. I have had enough of you talking. Leave me alone, please.~
@13216 = ~[PC] I was not joking. And stop yammering on, will you? Give it a rest.~
@13217 = ~[ARAN] Now I rightly agree on that. Losin' control wi' out consent be a scary thing. Though sometimes, it almost seems like worryin' about that might you hesitate when it be more prudent to take th' risk.~
@13218 = ~[PC] Are you questioning my courage?~
@13219 = ~[PC] I think I have proven my courage often enough. I have never backed away from doing what needed to be done.~
@13220 = ~[PC] So, what really scares you?~
@13221 = ~[PC] You are so easy to fool. You should know by now that absolutely nothing scares me.~
@13222 = ~[ARAN] Now that be interestin'. Me, not so much on that point, on account o' I never will have quite th' power you do, so there will always be somethin' I will have naught in th' way o' control over. Some folks can almost take that whole power thing too far, though.~
@13223 = ~[PC] Are you saying I am seeking too much power? Are you questioning my courage, my ability to wield authority?~
@13224 = ~[PC] I think I have proven my courage and my ability often enough. I have never backed away from doing what needed to be done.~
@13225 = ~[ARAN] Now I agree on that. There be nothin' like wonderin' just before you go down if there will be a way to come back, or if this be th' end o' this part o' th' journey on th' Great Wheel. That rightly scares most creatures, I expect.~
@13226 = ~[PC] What does my being scared have to do with what we are facing? Are you questioning my courage?~
@13227 = ~[ARAN] Now I agree that be a dangerous thing, but you have been fightin' that prophecy for a long time now. An' so far, you have risen to meet th' challenge.~
@13228 = ~[PC] So far? Are you questioning my courage?~
@13229 = ~[ARAN] Which be why there be many who will follow you to th' ends o' th' Planes themselves. But sometime soon you may have to let one o' us be sacrificed to get th' job done, you know.~
@13230 = ~[ARAN] Now I will say, that be not as bad as I once thought. It done happened to me once or twice, an' it be survivable. O' course, when th' current lover be a cute little assassin, you got to watch your food an' drink for a few months, but usually there be a way to make it up to them.~
@13231 = ~[ARAN] Stop lookin' at me like that. It be a story for another day an' time. Besides, I almost think you be jokin' wi' me, anyways.~
@13232 = ~[PC] Almost? Of course I was. I thought you were joking, too. Were you actually questioning my courage?~
@13233 = ~[ARAN]  Now I almost believe that.~
@13234 = ~[PC] Almost? Are you questioning my courage?~
@13235 = ~[ARAN] Well, I am not sure I have an answer what will serve. There be a fair number o' things that scare me. What be th' context you want to know, eh?~
@13236 = ~[PC] What scares you about me?~
@13237 = ~[PC] What causes you nightmares when you go to sleep?~
@13238 = ~[PC] What monster are you scared to face in combat?~
@13239 = ~[PC] What scares you about <PLAYER2>?~
@13240 = ~[PC] What scares you about <PLAYER3>?~
@13241 = ~[PC] What scares you about <PLAYER4>?~
@13242 = ~[PC] What scares you about <PLAYER5>?~
@13243 = ~[PC] What scares you about <PLAYER6>?~
@13244 = ~[ARAN] Well, for starters, it be hard to breathe when you look at me. You be th' most dangerous, alluring creature I ever did see. But you can smash me like an eggshell if you choose. That won't stop me carin' for you, though.~
@13245 = ~[ARAN] You be th' most dangerous, alluring creature I ever did see. An' for whatever reason th' gods give, I would die for you in an instant. Be tortured, kill, destroy... anythin'. But you... I have a deep fear you wouldn't do th' same unless it helped you in some way. Yet I won't rightly be runnin from you any time soon.~
@13246 = ~[ARAN] You be th' most dangerous, alluring creature I ever did see. I wish things were more serious between th' two o' us, but I understand why they are not. But I live in fear o' th' day when you decide I am not needed. It don't rightly stop me, though.~
@13247 = ~[ARAN] Well, to tell th' whole truth o' it, you were born to lead, an' I were born to follow. Sometimes I start thinkin' I could do th' leadership job better than you, an' then we hit th' next challenge, an' I says to myself, "self, there be no way you could do what he does". Sometimes it be a little scary to see you take on what any other creature on Toril would run screamin' from. So I stay beside you, though I be a mite fearful at times.~
@13248 = ~[ARAN] Not much, as I been on campaign long enough to never, ever catch up on rest. Mayhap too much spicy food, where I end up tossin' an' turnin'. But usually th' time for my worryin' be when I be awake.~
@13249 = ~[ARAN] You blighted well know I hate th' Great Wyrms. Spiders, snakes, slime, insects, Drow... they be pains in th' arse, an' things to be wary around. But dragons...~
@13250 = ~[ARAN] Dragons be smarter, stronger, trickier, older, massively powerful, conniving, manipulative, an' most times just plain mean. They look at you wi' those eyes, an' the outcome usually be in their favor.~
@13251 = ~[PC] We have fought dragons and won. Doesn't that help salve your fears?~
@13252 = ~[PC] Overgrown snakes with attitude problems really bother you that much?~
@13253 = ~[PC] Not all dragons are evil, Aran. Do you fear even the good ones?~
@13254 = ~[PC] I have not seen you allow your fears to hold you back from fighting them.~
@13255 = ~[PC] Hey, I didn't mean to be so serious. Come on, lighten up. Play a game with me... courage is to fear as light is to...~
@13256 = ~[ARAN] Not much, I think. An' mayhap that be gettin' off th' subject I were talkin' about, anyways.~
@13257 = ~[ARAN] Hells, no. Courage an' fear, they be related, but I'll tell you this right true - no one what be fearless has ever been courageous.~
@13258 = ~[PC] That is ridiculous. Fearlessness *is* courage.~
@13259 = ~[PC] So you think you have to overcome your fear to become courageous?~
@13260 = ~[PC] You have got to be joking. Are you trying to make me angry? Are you implying I am not courageous?~
@13261 = ~[PC] Now there is a good game - courage is to fear as light is to...~
@13262 = ~[PC] I don't mind the discussion, Aran, but couldn't we talk about lighter topics, like the weather, or who thinks the Waterdeep dresses show too much cleavage?~
@13263 = ~[PC] I don't mind the discussion, Aran, but couldn't we talk about lighter topics, like the weather, or who thinks Boo is actually a Giant Space Hamster?~
@13264 = ~[ARAN] Flame?~
@13265 = ~[PC] Ooooh, good one. Try this one. Wind is to mouth as discussion is to...~
@13266 = ~[PC] I would have said "fire", but that is about right. What about pen is to ink as spell is to...~
@13267 = ~[ARAN] Now that one be a trick, eh? On account o' there be multiple answers. You could be sayin' "...as spell be to faith", or "...as spell be to component", or "...as spell be to th' Weave". How about this...~
@13268 = ~[ARAN] Salt be to Earth as...~
@13269 = ~[PC] ...spice is to meat?~
@13270 = ~[PC] ...Aran is to Toril?~
@13271 = ~[PC] I think I have had enough of playing this game. Besides, it is sidestepping your point; I think fearlessness is a requisite for courage.~
@13272 = ~[PC] I think I have had enough of playing this game. Besides, it is sidestepping your point; I think courage is only shown when one overcomes fear.~
@13273 = ~[PC] I like things with multiple answers. Life is not always definitive. So perhaps you should loosen your ideas about the relationship between fearlessness and courage.~
@13274 = ~[PC] Oh, forget it. This is a boring game. Couldn't we talk about lighter topics, like the weather, or who thinks the Waterdeep dresses show too much cleavage?~
@13275 = ~[PC] Oh, forget it. This is a boring game. Couldn't we talk about lighter topics, like the weather, or who thinks Boo is actually a Giant Space Hamster?~
@13276 = ~[ARAN] I disagree on that point, I do.~
@13277 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I do.~
@13278 = ~[ARAN] I knew a lad what were truly fearless once, back on the Moonsheas. He'd charge right in an' do what he felt were required, regardless o' cost. But th' true courage I found to be found in th' men an' women what followed him.~
@13279 = ~[ARAN] See, since he were fearless, he never rightly understood what he could lose. To him, death an' life, acceptable losses, collateral damage, all those were just words. They had no power over him, an' gave him no reason to evaluate his actions. But those who followed, they had to go into combat realizin' they were expendable pawns. They had to overcome their fears, an' fight when they knew an' felt exactly how much those "words" would mean to them in th' here an' now.~
@13280 = ~[PC] He sounds like a good war leader.~
@13281 = ~[PC] He sounds a little like me.~
@13282 = ~[PC] He sounds like a fool, if he never reevaluated his plans or looked at the true cost of his actions.~
@13283 = ~[PC] He sounds like he was doing what he had to do when faced with difficult decisions.~
@13284 = ~[PC] I would not want to serve under a man like that.~
@13285 = ~[PC] I would never want one of my companions to behave like that.~
@13286 = ~[ARAN] Well, mayhap yes, mayhap no... there be power in just actin', an' he certainly won his share o' battles. An' when he gave his life, it were a powerful thing he did, savin' men an' women he considered more important to th' long term objective than himself. Th' point is, he never had no chance to show true courage. For him, it were all percentages, all a calculation wi' no appreciation o' th' stakes he were playin'.~
@13287 = ~[ARAN] I think fear gives us a reason to appreciate th' costs o' what is to be done, an' courage is doin' what needs to be done even when you be deathly afraid.~
@13288 = ~[PC] I disagree.~
@13289 = ~[PC] Well, on that point, I think we can agree.~
@13290 = ~[PC] So, when did you start your lecture series on the nature of human existence?~
@13291 = ~[PC] For small talk, you sure use heavy subjects.~
@13292 = ~[ARAN] Now that be a right good answer. I will have to be goin' off an' thinkin' up more o' these!~
@13293 = ~[ARAN] An' blighted hells if I didn't clean forget what I were sayin' in th' first place. Well, it weren't naught o' importance anyways.~
@13294 = ~[ARAN] Why, surely! My apologies. Though we'd best stay wi' topics what could actually have a discussion. Everyone knows Boo is a Giant Space Hamster. Th' real question is, what the hells be Minsc?~
@13295 = ~[ARAN] Why, surely! My apologies. Though we'd best stay wi' topics what could actually have a discussion. Everyone knows there can never be too much cleavage.~
@13296 = ~[ARAN] Mystra's Mouth, I were just makin' conversation. I guess I do get a mite pedantic at times. Long forced marches make for plenty o' time to think deep philosophy. Even deeper, if you have had a few extra drinks on th' road!~
@13297 = ~[ARAN] Aye, true enough, at times. But I understood that up front. Like him, you have to do what you have to do. An' th' gods only know why, but I am relatively sure you won't waste my life needlessly. Usefully, I can deal wi', an' Tymora will be tickled I took th' gamble o' backin' you to th' death. It be nice to have a purposeful death, you know. Makes a lad feel like he made a difference.~
@13298 = ~[ARAN] What be scary about you? Well... have you ever seen somethin' so beautiful it actually hurts to look at? Or so important there be naught else what could be more pressin'?~
@13299 = ~[ARAN] There be so much ugliness in th' world. But you shine like a blighted star, from th' inside. An' when your light turns on, I feel like my heart be about to explode. That kind o' power, that kind o' pain... it be a pedestal what I put you on. An' it scares me. But I still won't rightly be scared off.~
@13300 = ~[NEERA] So. Aran. Hmmm. Is that your real name?~
@13301 = ~[NEERA] Do you like it?~
@13302 = ~[ARAN] I suppose I do. Never did give it much thought.~
@13303 = ~[NEERA] It seems so... ordinary.~
@13304 = ~[NEERA] Wouldn't you rather be named Alphonse Redhand?~
@13305 = ~[NEERA] What about Arnold of the Strong Hands?~
@13306 = ~[ARAN] No, that has naught in th' way o' interest for me, neither.~
@13307 = ~[NEERA] I would just think that 'Whitehand' is more like a girl's name. You know, 'Snowlips', 'Gentlehand'...~
@13308 = ~[ARAN] So, do you be thinkin' your name should be 'Slenderwaist'?~
@13309 = ~[NEERA] No.~
@13310 = ~[ARAN] How about 'Smallbreast'?~
@13311 = ~[NEERA] You do know I can kill you with a thought, right?~
@13312 = ~[ARAN] Now, most o' th' magic I see, it be a controlled, purposeful thing. Planned power, applied like a duellist or an assassin, prepared an' set into motion.~
@13313 = ~[NEERA] Not with me. Sure, I can plan, but then things just happen. Usually not what I was planning.~
@13314 = ~[ARAN] So, can it be interrupted? I mean, there be a small measure o' time where a mage can lose an entire spell, on account o' a small thing distractin' 'em.~
@13315 = ~[NEERA] If I get distracted, some... some very strange things can happen.~
@13316 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap somethin' distractin' like...~
@13317 = ~[NEERA] OH!~
@13318 = ~[ARAN] Hey, now, I were just playin' about... A little pinch between friends, eh?~
@13319 = ~[ARAN] Neera, now, your eyebrows be a mite bit more frownin', an'... that shimmerin' around your hands...~
@13320 = ~[ARAN] Gond's Gears! I were just havin' some harmless fun!~
@13321 = ~[ARAN] Now you look right pensive, you do.~
@13322 = ~[NEERA] Pensive? Oh. No, not really. I just keep having troubles with this one little thing.~
@13323 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap I can help, eh?~
@13324 = ~[NEERA] Well... I suppose you could. I mean, yes, you could.~
@13325 = ~[ARAN] So what needs be done?~
@13326 = ~[NEERA] If you just stand there, really, really still... no, quit moving. Stand there really still, and I will just try this ONE more time...~
@13327 = ~[ARAN] Awww hells. It be that damned 'Polymorph Other' spell you be tryin'. Last time, I done got turned into a potted plant.~
@13328 = ~[NEERA] So, why haven't you flirted with me lately?~
@13329 = ~[ARAN] I have been. You just seem right oblivious.~
@13330 = ~[NEERA] I don't think giving me extra helpings of curry is flirting.~
@13331 = ~[ARAN] An' why not?~
@13332 = ~[NEERA] For one thing, it leads to indigestion. There is nothing romantic about passing gas.~
@13333 = ~[ARAN] Serves me right for learnin' basic courtin' etiquette from a blighted half-orc.~
@13334 = ~[ARAN] Now why in Sune Firehair's name would I be flirtin' wi' you, when you an' <CHARNAME> are quite th' item?~
@13335 = ~[NEERA] Well... sometimes, it helps to have a little jealousy. Make <PRO_HIMHER> realize what <PRO_HESHE> has.~
@13336 = ~[ARAN] Neera... look at <PRO_HIMHER>. Now look at me. Do you think there be any profit in' stressin' exactly how little I have to offer in comparison, save loyalty?~
@13337 = ~[NEERA] That's the point. I don't want any actual jealousy. I just want <PRO_HIMHER> to remember. I mean, how could anyone see you as a SERIOUS romatic threat?~
@13338 = ~[ARAN] Way to make a lad feel two inches tall. Wi' friends like you, who needs enemies?~
@13339 = ~[ARAN] You know how I feel about <CHARNAME>.~
@13340 = ~[NEERA] Oh, I don't know. Sometimes loyal and faithful ends up being dull and boring. Perhaps you need to spice things up a bit.~
@13341 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap, mayhap not. But seein' as how one wild surge could wipe me off o' Toril, I think I'd be better off not leadin' you on, eh? I can be persuasive. Mayhap you fall head over cute little bottom for me, an' go weepin' an' pinin' away...~
@13342 = ~[NEERA] Sheesh. Like THAT is going to happen.~
@13343 = ~[NEERA] Do you think <PRO_HESHE> knows?~
@13344 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells, girl.. I don't rightly know what <PRO_HESHE> knows. I know <PRO_HESHE> seems right interested in both o' us, an' that be th' truth.~
@13345 = ~[NEERA] You don't suppose <PRO_HESHE>... <PRO_HESHE>... well, YOU know... both of us...~
@13346 = ~[ARAN] Well, all I know is if that particular combination o' personages were to happen, I'd be a right happy man, right up until your wild side chimed in an' blasted half o' Toril off o' th' map.~
@13347 = ~[ARAN] Keep ahead o' me, there.~
@13348 = ~[HEXXAT] I am not an object for your lusts, Aran.~
@13349 = ~[ARAN] Ahead o' me, it be less likely I will become an object o' yours.~
@13350 = ~[HEXXAT] You do not attract me.~
@13351 = ~[ARAN] That be what th' spider says to th' fly, right before she sucks th' carcass dry.~
@13352 = ~[HEXXAT] You seem worried by my presence.~
@13353 = ~[HEXXAT] What do you have to fear from me?~
@13354 = ~[ARAN] Plenty.~
@13355 = ~[HEXXAT] You do not usually say so little.~
@13356 = ~[ARAN] Just watchin' careful, on account o' if I happen to get distracted, I might become a meal.~
@13357 = ~[HEXXAT] You should relax. Your curry has enough of a stench to drive me away.~
@13358 = ~[ARAN] Good to know.~
@13359 = ~[ARAN] So you still be here.~
@13360 = ~[HEXXAT] And so are you.~
@13361 = ~[ARAN] True enough.~
@13362 = ~[HEXXAT] Have you learned to trust a little more?~
@13363 = ~[ARAN] Trust, aye. You, no.~
@13364 = ~[HEXXAT] At some point you have to deal with your irrational fears and accept me.~
@13365 = ~[ARAN] Th' hells I do.~
@13366 = ~[HEXXAT] Could you move a little farther away?~
@13367 = ~[ARAN] Aye. Why?~
@13368 = ~[HEXXAT] You stink.~
@13369 = ~[ARAN] Must be th' garlic an' such I used in that last curry.~
@13370 = ~[HEXXAT] It could also be that you need a bath.~
@13371 = ~[ARAN] Why, now, that be an idea. I have some holy water around here, an' I think that be just th' ticket for a right fine bath. Hold this wooden stake for me a mite bit while I search for it, eh?~
@13372 = ~[ARAN] Calimport, eh? I spent some right pleasurable time in th' baths there, I did. Th' heatin' system were a wonder o' modern architecture an' magic combined.~
@13373 = ~[RASAAD] Calimport is a city of wonders, but it was not all enjoyable, I assure you of that.~
@13374 = ~[ARAN] You have a right fine gift for understatement. In some parts, it be a miracle to survive even one day. You must be a right sharp lad.~
@13375 = ~[RASAAD] My brother and I were... Yes. We were fortunate. In spite of what has now happened to us.~
@13376 = ~[ARAN] Now if you be talkin' about th' whole sun philosophy, an' moon goddess, an' fallin' from grace, or whatnot, well, hells... more'n once I have been on th' wrong side o' an employer. Sometimes doin' th' job right means doin' somethin' not quite in the rulebook, eh?~
@13377 = ~[RASAAD] Perhaps that is a comforting thought. But I was talking about the loss of my brother.~
@13378 = ~[ARAN] See, there you go again, thinkin' too much. That be an easy fix. We find th' bastard what did him in, an' then we do to him what been done to your brother. Simple problem, simple solution, an' all's well what ends well, eh?~
@13379 = ~[RASAAD] You seem to have reduced all of my seeking of vengeance to a short catch-phrase.~
@13380 = ~[ARAN] That be me. Aran Whitehand, sword an' scribe. Trade contracts written, caravans defended, an' complex things reduced to over-simplified generalizations. Some say it be a gift, but I say it be just second nature.~
@13381 = ~[ARAN] Help a lad out, eh? I have seen you do some right interestin' moves. Can I learn 'em?~
@13382 = ~[RASAAD] That depends on your abilty to focus. To concentrate.~
@13383 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I can do that. What be first?~
@13384 = ~[RASAAD] First, take a deep breath, and calm your mind.~
@13385 = ~[ARAN] Aye. Done.~
@13386 = ~[RASAAD] Not if you are speaking. Take a deep breath, hold it... now gently exhale.~
@13387 = ~[ARAN] .... ~
@13388 = ~[ARAN] Done.~
@13389 = ~[RASAAD] You broke concentration too early. Try again. Take a deep breath, hold it... now gently exhale...~
@13390 = ~[ARAN] I think you just wanted to shut me up.~
@13391 = ~[RASAAD] Your path to enlightenment has already begun.~
@13392 = ~[RASAAD] How are your concentration studies progressing?~
@13393 = ~[ARAN] Not well, to tell th' whole truth.~
@13394 = ~[RASAAD] That would tend to break your concentration.~
@13395 = ~[ARAN] Hells, no. It locks me on target right quick. Th' problem is, th' more I concentrate, th' less clothes she has on in my mind. Blighted hard on th' codpiece, that be. Makes it a mite bit difficult to stay focused.~
@13396 = ~[RASAAD] What is the challenge you face?~
@13397 = ~[ARAN] I get as far as exhalin', start to concentrate... an' a picture o' that last barmaid's form as she walks away from me just pops into my head.~
@13398 = ~[ARAN] I get as far as exhalin', start to concentrate... an' a picture o' <PLAYER1>'s form as she walks away from me just pops into my head.~
@13399 = ~[ARAN] I get as far as exhalin', start to concentrate... an' a picture o' <PLAYER2>'s form as she walks away from me just pops into my head.~
@13400 = ~[ARAN] I get as far as exhalin', start to concentrate... an' a picture o' <PLAYER3>'s form as she walks away from me just pops into my head.~
@13401 = ~[ARAN] I get as far as exhalin', start to concentrate... an' a picture o' <PLAYER4>'s form as she walks away from me just pops into my head.~
@13402 = ~[ARAN] I get as far as exhalin', start to concentrate... an' a picture o' <PLAYER5>'s form as she walks away from me just pops into my head.~
@13403 = ~[ARAN] I get as far as exhalin', start to concentrate... an' a picture o' <PLAYER6>'s form as she walks away from me just pops into my head.~
@13404 = ~[ARAN] I have been studyin' that whole concentratin' idea you use. You know, th' take a breath in, an' let it out slowly, thinkin' on centerin' down.~
@13405 = ~[RASAAD] How do you feel about your progress?~
@13406 = ~[ARAN] Sometimes it works right fine. But lately... I just fall asleep.~
@13407 = ~[RASAAD] Relaxation is only part of the process. You have to be mentally awake while your body remains still.~
@13408 = ~[ARAN] I get th' basic idea, I do. I just get all centered an' calm, an' then th' snores wake me up.~
@13409 = ~[RASAAD] It takes years of detailed study and practice to achieve mastery over both body and mind. Keep working on it.~
@13410 = ~[ARAN] I suppose you be right. Mayhap I'd do better apprenticin' somewhere instead o' tryin' to pick it up on th' trail. Though I do say th' naps be refreshin'.~
@13411 = ~[RASAAD] They are indeed.~
@13412 = ~[ARAN] Hey, Rasaad, this whole poverty an' wealth thing. What be bad about havin' coin, an' spendin' it?~
@13413 = ~[RASAAD] Having wealth is a state through which one passes. Wanting wealth is a distraction. Needing wealth is corruption.~
@13414 = ~[ARAN] But if I have wealth, an' I use it to help friends out, how do it be corruption?~
@13415 = ~[RASAAD] Transferring wealth is not bad or good. It just happens. Needing to do it, though, is just purchasing friendship.~
@13416 = ~[ARAN] Right... so wealth has naught in th' way o' good or bad, and what you do wi' it can be good or bad. So why do so many different orders o' monks all take vows against material gain?~
@13417 = ~[RASAAD] The real question to ask is 'Am I still true to myself when I am poor, when I am rich, when I am neither, and when I am both?'~
@13418 = ~[ARAN] You know, for a vengeance-obsessed livin' weapon, you sure think things through right proper, you do.~
@13419 = ~[DORN] You are weak.~
@13420 = ~[ARAN] I'm blighted not. I can carry my fair share, an' then some.~
@13421 = ~[DORN] But you are divided.~
@13422 = ~[ARAN] What in th' hells do you be talkin' about?~
@13423 = ~[DORN] You fly between the gods like a frightened child, mouthing their names.~
@13424 = ~[ARAN] Apparently, you have naught in th' way o' understandin' th' relationship between catharsis an' swearin'.~
@13425 = ~[DORN] I do not. But I understand the power a single purpose can serve.~
@13426 = ~[ARAN] Dividin' some time betwixt an' between th' gods gives everyone a little taste, is all. But mayhap you be right. Mayhap it weakens when I be callin' on one in particular.~
@13427 = ~[DORN] When I find a being who is not strong enough to withstand my will... I divide them.~
@13428 = ~[ARAN] You are one bloodthirsty bastard, eh?~
@13429 = ~[DORN] Yes.~
@13430 = ~[ARAN] There be times when smashin' everythin' in sight means some collateral damage, you know.~
@13431 = ~[DORN] Mercy is weakness. Hesitation is death.~
@13432 = ~[ARAN] You have said that before. An' I still think you be wrong. Allies get built by showin' you can work together, an' that means waitin' to see if they be useful or not.~
@13433 = ~[DORN] If they are strong enough to stay alive, then they may be worthy allies.~
@13434 = ~[ARAN] An' if you give them naught in th' way o' a chance?~
@13435 = ~[DORN] Then they would not be allies. They would be dead weight.~
@13436 = ~[ARAN] That be th' right word choice, I guess.~
@13437 = ~[DORN] My patron hears you.~
@13438 = ~[ARAN] What in Bane's...~
@13439 = ~[DORN] Your mewling cries to the gods. Azothet could provide... direction.~
@13440 = ~[DORN] Your mewling cries to the gods. Ur-Gothoz could provide... direction.~
@13441 = ~[ARAN] Tell that patron o' yours to bugger off.~
@13442 = ~[DORN] You are too weak to stand without a patron. You have some power. You could be useful.~
@13443 = ~[ARAN] It seems to me that if I were to submit to that sort o' arrangement, I'd be more like a puppet than a man, eh?~
@13444 = ~[DORN] You are a fool. You do not understand.~
@13445 = ~[ARAN] Blighted straight. I think I be my own man, not a puppet, an that be th' gods' truth.~
@13446 = ~[DORN] That is what you do not understand.~
@13447 = ~[ARAN] So, no more patron.~
@13448 = ~[DORN] I have no need of one.~
@13449 = ~[ARAN] An' what does that change, eh?~
@13450 = ~[DORN] It means I can revel in the glory, and share none of it.~
@13451 = ~[ARAN] Do you be meanin' glory, or gore?~
@13452 = ~[DORN] What is the difference?~
@13453 = ~[ARAN] So, when will you be makin' your move?~
@13454 = ~[DORN] I am moving now.~
@13455 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Black Heart, Dorn. You know what I be meanin'.~
@13456 = ~[DORN] Enlighten me.~
@13457 = ~[ARAN] You believe in bein' th' strongest, th' most powerful, mayhap th' most bloodiest bastard in all creation.~
@13458 = ~[DORN] You are correct.~
@13459 = ~[ARAN] So there will come a time when th' only bigger an' more powerful creature left unconquered will be th' Bhaalspawn.~
@13460 = ~[DORN] That is likely.~
@13461 = ~[ARAN] So when will you be makin' your move?~
@13462 = ~[DORN] Someday, perhaps. But not today.~
