@13466 = ~[PC] Branwen seems to be handling this better than you are.~
@13467 = ~[EDWINA] Keep your lecherous gaze to yourself, sellsword. (The moron thinks I do not see his covetous glances.)~
@13468 = ~[ARAN] Now, Edwin, how's a lad supposed to feel, when all those robes be concealin' such art? I just have to look at th' legs.~
@13469 = ~[EDWINA] You will have trouble with your eyes, I think. Perhaps turning them to stone will keep your lusts in check.~
@13470 = ~[ARAN] Oh, no worries on my account. Your form may be right fine to look at, but you still be an evil, over-educated, stone-hearted, backstabbin', manipulative Red Wizard, wi' all th' trappin's that entails.~
@13471 = ~[EDWINA] Flattery will get you nowhere. (The moronic baboon. Though his points do have merit. I am still a magnificent specimen.)~
@13472 = ~[ARAN] Now, I be listenin'...~
@13473 = ~[ARAN] Well, no Sheri tonight, it seems. An' that be a pity, too. She sings th' kind o' songs I like.~
@13474 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap if we drop by again an' she be here, you do th' talkin', eh? On account o' I think I might have ticked her off proper last time I tried to get friendly wi' her.~
@13475 = ~[PC] Let me guess. You made a clumsy pass at her and ended up insulting her.~
@13476 = ~[PC] Just when was this "last time"?~
@13477 = ~[PC] That is fine with me.~
@13478 = ~[PC] What kind of songs do you like?~
@13479 = ~[PC] I... I do not usually wander up to strangers and talk to them. Even bards and storytellers.~
@13480 = ~[PC] I do not usually wander up to strangers and talk to them. Even other bards and storytellers. I usually listen without interacting with them.~
@13481 = ~[ARAN] Aye, she be in right fine form tonight. An any night, for that matter.~
@13482 = ~[ARAN] But mayhap you should do th' talkin'. I did not do so well on th' communication front last time we spoke. In fact, I mayhap be better off standin' a ways back an' just listenin'.~
@13483 = ~[PC] The bard over there in the corner? Is she special?~
@13484 = ~[PC] I do not usually waste my time talking to insignificant people.~
@13485 = ~[PC] I will take that under consideration. Perhaps I will go listen to her.~
@13486 = ~[ARAN] Aye, guilty as charged.~
@13487 = ~[PC] Is she special?~
@13488 = ~[PC] Fine. If we do go  listen to her, you stay back.~
@13489 = ~[PC] This habit of offending women you meet... you are working on fixing that, right?~
@13490 = ~[PC] So, to cut a long story short, you think she is worth hearing, but you should avoid her, right?~
@13491 = ~[ARAN] There be no accountin' on whether she be better than you nor I on th' vocal front, as to some th' sopranos run, some th' tenors, an' baritones or bass be solid for all sorts o' songs. But she be a far sight better trained than either o' us blighted bastards.~
@13492 = ~[PC] A coloratura. Wait... she just... that high a range with little or no effort. A Spinto?~
@13493 = ~[PC] So... you really like her voice. ~
@13494 = ~[PC] You have no idea how insulting you just were, do you. I have extensive training.~
@13495 = ~[PC] Do not compare my skills to yours. You can barely speak, let alone sing.~
@13496 = ~[PC] I would rather not spend my time listening to the competition.~
@13497 = ~[ARAN] Well, just listen. Notes into th' upper octave as clear as a bell. Diction clean without heavy handed plosives. Th' way she just controlled her dynamics on that last line to throw th' pathos... musical line...~
@13498 = ~[ARAN] Hells. you did th' trainin' same as I. You *know* how blighted rare it be for a true acuto sfogato soprano t' be playin' bit places an' bars. She should be in Waterdeep, at th' Masked Court.~
@13499 = ~[PC] I disagree. That upper range is too dark and covered to be a true sfogato. But I can see that you truly love her voice.~
@13500 = ~[PC] Sopranos get all the attention. We have to work twice as hard to get noticed. I take it she did not want a singing partner...~
@13501 = ~[PC] Fine. You stay back. Perhaps I will go see what she can sing.~
@13502 = ~[ARAN] You be th' judge, on account o' you have th' right trainin', eh? But to my untrained ear, she sounds like a blighted Avatar o' Sune made flesh an' blood.~
@13503 = ~[ARAN] Well, she be a fully trained vocalist, an' her upper register be absolutely clear, wi' no forced notes or improper placement in th' headvoice.... ah, there I go, talkin' shop. Yes. She is blighted good.~
@13504 = ~[PC] Right now, I need a drink. Perhaps later.~
@13505 = ~[PC] Is she a better vocalist than I am?~
@13506 = ~[PC] She... I can hear it. She has a better voice than I do.~
@13507 = ~[PC] I disagree. That last passage, she clipped two notes, and her breath support is... lacking. If she bends or scoops one more note, I shall have to throw something at her.~
@13508 = ~[PC] Well, perhaps I should evaluate her. I can always use a careful analysis to better my own craft.~
@13509 = ~[PC] So... you really like her voice.~
@13510 = ~[ARAN] Well, just listen to her, an' mayhap a trained bardess like you can explain to me why she can turn a tune t' make a man weep or laugh as easy as I can flick a blade from left to right. She certainly do catch my ear.~
@13511 = ~[PC] I do not know... That last passage, she clipped two notes, and her breath support is lacking. If she bends or scoops one more note, I shall have to throw something at her.~
@13512 = ~[PC] Well, perhaps we should evaluate her. I can always use a careful analysis to better my own craft.~
@13513 = ~[ARAN] Well, I defer to your better judgement, on account o' I hold your opinion in high regard, I do.~
@13514 = ~[ARAN] Now, that be a bad idea. There be strengths an' weaknesses in any what follow th' craft. You know full well what you are capable of. She may be rare, but you be just as strong.~
@13515 = ~[ARAN] Aye, somethin' seriously special, an' rare. She be a true acuto sfogato soprano, wi' a range higher than most o' th' coloratura sopranos... err... there I go, talkin' shop. Yes. She is blighted good.~
@13516 = ~[ARAN] Aye. No interest in me, more be th' pity. Mayhap she be frightened off by th' brilliance o' my manly charms. Either that, or she has been talkin' to Erika at Th' Broken Sword.~
@13517 = ~[PC] So... you and Erika...~
@13518 = ~[PC] You have that bad a reputation?~
@13519 = ~[PC] You seem to have a very high opinion of yourself.~
@13520 = ~[ARAN] I love th' sound o' her voice, an' that be for sure.~
@13521 = ~[PC] Is that all you love?~
@13522 = ~[PC] Anything she can do, I can do better.~
@13523 = ~[PC] Anything she can sing, I can sing higher.~
@13524 = ~[PC] You know, I think I should see this... singer.~
@13525 = ~[ARAN] Hells, no! Th' way her eyes sparkle, it be right nice to see. An' when she takes in a right solid breath...~
@13526 = ~[ARAN] Err...~
@13527 = ~[ARAN] Yes. That be all I love about her. That be my story, an' naught can shake me from it. But it don't matter for naught either way. She didn't find my sparkin' to her taste.~
@13528 = ~[ARAN] Aye. That voice... it caught me right away. But then I had to go an' be a jackass, an' try to spark a bit wi' her. It were before I met you.~
@13529 = ~[ARAN] There be no deal between us at all. I am not likely to be makin' serious passes at Erika. She has a great sense o' humor, an' I needs be keepin' in good graces wi' Orrin an' Teldra as well. Fun teasin' her, is all.~
@13530 = ~[ARAN] Well, I mayhap be a bit forward wi' th' ladies. But most o' th' time it be just talk. No harm in that.~
@13531 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap you be right. But I think that calls for a bit o' a contest later on to decide, eh?~
@13532 = ~[ARAN] I be right confident in my abilities, to be sure. But I know my limits. Sheri, she be as far out o' my reach as th' nearest star.~
@13533 = ~[PC] Perhaps she will find me interesting.~
@13534 = ~[PC] Well, perhaps I should pay her a visit.~
@13535 = ~[PC] This is a distraction. Go make yourself useful. Go fix the gear, or sharpen something.~
@13536 = ~[ARAN] I like all sorts o' songs. But when it be Sheri, some sets she sings be on th' bawdy side.~
@13537 = ~[PC] Does she do more than... sing that kind of song?~
@13538 = ~[ARAN] About a tenday before I met up wi' you, if I rightly recall.~
@13539 = ~[ARAN] Busy day, that one. I had to dodge my way out right quick. Great voice, an' a sight better aim wi' crockery than I'd have guessed. But I deserved th' cuts an' bruises she dealt, I did, every last one.~
@13540 = ~[ARAN] Aye, mayhap. So far, wi' anyone I done seen talk to her, she seems friendly enough. Which kind o' fits wi' th' whole "relatin' to people" thing bards an' bardesses seem to be right good at.~
@13541 = ~[ARAN] I think you would enjoy th' time spent. Her voice... it be an experience.~
@13541 = ~A SELLSWORD stands before the arena! Will this would-be SCRIBE show that the QUILL is mightier than the SWORD?~
@13542 = ~[ARAN] Now, this be naught in th' way o' my business. But I have to ask... are you an' Saerileth gettin' serious?~
@13543 = ~[PC] Of course not. That is a ridiculous suggestion.~
@13544 = ~[PC] What do you think?~
@13545 = ~[PC] Are we holding hands and kissing occasionally? Yes, I think we are. Are we getting serious? I am not sure.~
@13546 = ~[PC] Do I ask you about your dalliances with half of Faerun?~
@13547 = ~[PC] Speak of this to me again, and you will be looking for a new line of work. And perhaps searching for your missing head.~
@13548 = ~[ARAN] You must be blighted blind, then. Th' lass looks at you wi' th' intensity o' first love, an' th' passions o' a full grown woman. You'd best be careful around her, on account o' she might get th' wrong idea - or worse, th' right one.~
@13549 = ~[PC] I don't really need to be careful. I think I am falling for her.~
@13550 = ~[ARAN] Look, <CHARNAME>, I love th' way women move, th' way they speak, th' way they smell, th' way they smile... hells, I just love women. But me an' someone what wears th' flower be a mite different than what you are talkin' about. First off, we all have th' age o' consent. Second off, if I tick off th' lady in question, she may box my ears, kick me, get me thrown into th' street, or mayhap carve me up a little, as be her choice. With Saerileth...~
@13551 = ~[ARAN] Do you be kiddin' wi' me? A lass what has seen less than sixteen winters? Give her a year to come o' age a' make her own choices, an' mayhap I wouldn't kick her out o' my b... err...  well, she is pretty an' all, I guess. But she don't know squat about livin', let alone havin' a serious relationship. Tyr's Blasted Buttocks, don't send a child to do adult's work, <CHARNAME>. Love isn't just for play.~
@13552 = ~[PC] Take one look into her eyes, and tell me that she does not love me.~
@13553 = ~[PC] She is the Chosen of Tyr. She is strong enough, wise enough, and driven enough to know her own mind. Do you really think we would be together if she was not set on having it that way?~
@13554 = ~[PC] What, are you jealous? I did not know you were in love with her too.~
@13555 = ~[PC] It is a passing crush, and I intend to have as much fun with her as her religious views will allow.~
@13556 = ~[PC] So now you are an expert on serious relationships? That is a laugh. You don't even remember the barmaid's name the next morning.~
@13557 = ~[ARAN] Aye, she does. That be even more dangerous.~
@13558 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap you are right. Mayhap she be older than her years, an' wiser than a sage; mayhap she be mature enough to understand that relationships be work as well as fun. But all that wisdom an' such be packed into a body what be still growin' an' changin'.~
@13559 = ~[ARAN] Jealous? No possibility o' that, boyo. She scares me half to death.~
@13560 = ~[ARAN] Look, <CHARNAME>, I love th' way women move, th' way they speak, th' way they smell, th' way they smile... hells, I just love women. But me an' someone what wears th' flower be a mite different than what you are talkin' about. First off, we all have th' age o' consent, meanin' we can make our own choices. Second off, if I tick off th' lady in question, she may box my ears, kick me, get me thrown into th' street, or mayhap carve me up a little, as be her choice. With Saerileth...~
@13561 = ~[ARAN] You know how 'hell hath no fury like a woman scorned'? Well, take one look at her an' all you see is slim little hips, curves to die for, an' lips beggin' to be kissed - not one bit o' th' hells about her. Take a look in her eyes, though, an' you see an intensity an' a devotion that be downright scary. Now picture her if you hurt her. There won't be any place on any o' th' Planes where you could hide from her wrath. She'll rip you in half wi' her bare hands, then heal you up just so she can do it again.~
@13562 = ~[PC] You are taking this too seriously. I am much more powerful than she is. She will never be able to defeat me.~
@13563 = ~[PC] I don't intend to hurt her. I think she may be my soulmate.~
@13564 = ~[PC] She's a bunny rabbit. What's she going to do, nibble my bum?~
@13565 = ~[PC] This is my business, not yours. Keep out of it.~
@13566 = ~[ARAN] None o' my business, anyways. You think you can handle it. But I have been on th' receivin' end o' a regular woman what feels she has been wronged, an' it were a mite painful. Breakin' th' heart o' someone with th' feelin's o' adolescent first love who just happens to be an accomplished fighter an' th Chosen o' Tyr... that's bloody suicide.~
@13567 = ~[ARAN] Heh. Apparently, I have been wanderin' wi' you so long that I have followers o' my own now.~
@13568 = ~[ARAN] I do be guessin' that when a lad gets to a certain point, folks think he be worth backin' up. Just never thought I'd have that happen.~
@13569 = ~[PC] Congratulations! How did this all happen?~
@13570 = ~[PC] This is a distraction. We  need assistance here and now, not some long term plan.~
@13571 = ~[PC] Aran Whitehand. Adventurer, Raconteur..... Landlord.~
@13572 = ~[PC] Could any of them be useful to us right now?~
@13573 = ~[PC] So you are leaving and starting your own project.~
@13574 = ~[PC] I hope it works out for you. Now stop talking and move along.~
@13575 = ~[ARAN] Well, a few of th' lads an' lasses from some o' th' past guild work I were doin' heard what we were about, an' it seems they wanted to chip in an' help.~
@13576 = ~[ARAN] I done told 'em that I weren't goin' to be around much, on account o' we be adventurin', but they would take naught but yes for an answer.~
@13577 = ~[PC] Where are they settling?~
@13578 = ~[PC] This is a very bad idea. You should not be sponsoring followers.~
@13579 = ~[PC] Let me guess... they are all walking around trying to imitate your speech patterns, and swearing up a storm.~
@13580 = ~[PC] It sounds as if they really look up to you.~
@13581 = ~[PC] You fell for that hook, line, and sinker. Now they get to adventure on your coin and have no real oversight.~
@13582 = ~[ARAN] Look, they have naught in th' way o' half th' experience we have. They would not survive th' first battle. They be a fair sight stronger than th' average mercenary, but nowhere near what we can do.~
@13583 = ~[PC] So they are not useful to us now, and they will take your coin and distract you from helping me.~
@13584 = ~[PC] Some days I am not sure what we can do. And most days, I really don't know what YOU can do!~
@13585 = ~[PC] It sounds like you are getting an independent reputation as someone who can get things done.~
@13586 = ~[PC] How can you trust that they are really your followers, and not just taking your coin and having a great time at the local inn?~
@13587 = ~[ARAN] Me. A landlord. An' in charge o' other people. It boggles th' mind, it do.~
@13588 = ~[PC] Wait, back up... someone actually sees you as a... a... leader? Gods, they really do not know with whom they are dealing!~
@13589 = ~[ARAN] I am not rightly sure. They have a bit more experience than th' average soldier, but most o' them are just lookin' to stop wanderin' around old ruins an' attemptin' to avoid a hideous death over a few coppers an a tradebar's worth o' figurines.~
@13590 = ~[ARAN] Tyr's Eye, how could you be thinkin' that? They be perfectly self sufficient, except for some coin an' some basic directions. No call for me to go sit an' supervise.~
@13591 = ~[PC] You have no independent experience. You are not there in person. You have a habit of getting distracted. These are not positive indicators for this kind of venture.~
@13592 = ~[PC] WWait, back up... someone actually sees you as a... a... leader? Gods, they really do not know with whom they are dealing!~
@13593 = ~[PC] Where did you find them? Or did they just hear about you on the road, and decide to seek you out?~
@13594 = ~[ARAN] Well, I have a little bit o' land my father traded for, up on th' Sword Coast. I figured wi' th' coin from adventurin', I'd set up a small tower an' tradin' port right on th' coast.~
@13595 = ~[PC] A lighthouse? Or some sort of library tower? A shipbuilding operation might be very handy in that location.~
@13596 = ~[PC] That is a dangerous area, and this project is most likely to end up like so many have in the past - yet another abandoned ruined tower cluttering the coastline.~
@13597 = ~[PC] Trading wits? Words? Wait... you could capture the entire wolf pelt bounty. I think I have two people you will want to meet. Hmmm... what were those names... ~
@13598 = ~[PC] I travelled the southern part of that area while dealing with the Iron Throne. It is a very dangerous area. Sirenes, pirates, hobgoblin tribes, orcs, gibberling hordes... but the opportunity is hard to pass up.~
@13599 = ~[PC] If it were me, I would stick to the Trade Way and rebuild some of the destroyed travel towers. Perhaps even set up tolls. Perhaps you could expand the operation.~
@13600 = ~[ARAN] Blighted hells. A lad gets somethin' special happenin' to him, gets a little piece o' the' glory like you get, an' you have to go all down on it.~
@13601 = ~[PC] I am just worried that you do not realize how much work you may have set yourself up for. Perhaps I was hasty in my judgement. If someone can succeed at this, it is probably you.~
@13602 = ~[PC] You have been my follower. Your will is not in question, but your ability to lead is definitely my concern. I just do not see you becoming their leader.~
@13603 = ~[PC] Sure. Glory. That's what they call it these days. Look, I just think that you are setting yourself up for disappointment. You are a long way from them. It is hard to lead in those circumstances.~
@13604 = ~[PC] I am sorry... I am proud to hear that you are getting some recognition. Perhaps this is the start of bigger things for you.~
@13605 = ~[PC] Alright. If you do this, you should think about how to make the most of it. Set up tolls on the local roads, build some alliances with the nearest freeholds, that sort of thing.~
@13606 = ~[PC] Fine. I hope it works out for you. Now stop talking and move along.~
@13607 = ~[ARAN] Now, don't you be teasin' 'em on account o' their bad taste in sponsors, eh? There be a scribe or two, a cleric o' Sune, an' a handful o' fighters.~
@13608 = ~[ARAN] They just want an opportunity to get together, a place to call home, an' mayhap to feel a mite bit useful. I can understand that right plain.~
@13609 = ~[PC] That sounds like a useful group of followers to have.~
@13610 = ~[PC] They must not have enough experience to be useful, or they would be out on their own finding their own followers.~
@13611 = ~[PC] Just as long as you aren't starting the Sword Coast Inn, Writer's Theater, and Brothel. Sometimes these things just spiral out of control, you know.~
@13612 = ~[PC] If you trust them and they have proven themselves to you, then I support your decision. If you need more coin, just ask.~
@13613 = ~[PC] Just do not expect me to help you throw good coin after bad. This is entirely on you. I doubt it will work.~
@13614 = ~[ARAN] I did a few favors an' helped out a mite bit before I met you, an' that be th' truth o' it. I guess you have naught in th' way o' knowin' when a good deed gets rewarded.~
@13615 = ~[PC] So, they get a few new adventures and a base of operations, and you gain access to the resources of a group of experienced assistance.~
@13616 = ~[PC] It sounds more like they know who to turn to when they need steady income. They must know you are too trusting.~
@13617 = ~[PC] I wonder how long it is before one of them decides to start imitating your speech patterns and telling pointless stories...~
@13618 = ~[PC] Perhaps someday they will pay a solid dividend. Having a private freehold could be useful. Having experienced adventurers to give missions to could help you, too.~
@13619 = ~[PC] We have enough to deal with here and now without you chasing some wild dream of becoming the next Lord of the Coast.~
@13620 = ~[ARAN] These be lads an' lasses what I trust. They have been on th' Shield Wall wi' me. An' mayhap I can make my own judgements on what to do wi' my coin, eh?~
@13621 = ~[PC] That sounds much better. You are taking charge, and not backing down. You  might be able to give them some good leadership after all.~
@13622 = ~[PC] It is your coin. I just think it is a waste of your resources and a distraction.~
@13623 = ~[PC] Whoa, so serious! Relax! It is a better idea than the last venture you were thinking about spending coin to support.~
@13624 = ~[ARAN] Well, we will see, I guess. Right now, th' lads an' lasses be right happy enough settin' up an encampment an' spendin' my coin right quick to clear out th' unwanted elements. Good to know I have some kind o' investment in th' future.~
@13625 = ~[ARAN] Well, now, that be a bit o' a problem I never had before. Those followers o' mine want some advice.~
@13626 = ~[PC] What sort of advice?~
@13627 = ~[PC] They may need to learn things the way we have... the hard way.~
@13628 = ~[PC] I think you can handle giving them a little guidance. We have certainly survived through enough to have some confidence.~
@13629 = ~[PC] Never get in a drinking match with two dwarves and a fire giant? ~
@13630 = ~[PC] We do not have time for this, Aran. We should press on. ~
@13631 = ~[ARAN] It seems like they have found themselves a cave or some sort o' cavern under a bluff right along th' coast, an' they think it might be worth an expedition.~
@13632 = ~[PC] Ah, memories... I found one of those, once, right along the coast by Candlekeep. It was guarded by sirenes, filled with monsters, and even had treasure.~
@13633 = ~[PC] Well, give them some basic advice on supplies and preparation, and then let them do their job.~
@13634 = ~[PC] Great. A cave. We have plenty of experience with those. Usually they involve screaming, and running, and things being set on fire. And spiders.~
@13635 = ~[PC] You are not asking to go all the way back to the Sword Coast to investigate a cave, are you?~
@13636 = ~[ARAN] Now, we do get more than our fair share o' folks who want to give us advice. Whether we be takin' it or not, they still offer it.~
@13637 = ~[ARAN] Well, that be true enough. An' th' thing they be interested in be somethin' we can relate to.~
@13638 = ~[PC] Tell them that clearing a perimeter, setting up a solid defense, and planning out the site takes precedence over random sink holes that may spell inevitable death.~
@13639 = ~[ARAN] Funny, funny... an' probably advice I should have had told to me long ago.~
@13640 = ~[PC] Look, telling someone what to do on their first big adventure spoils all the fun.~
@13641 = ~[PC] I think you should give them a list of local dry goods suppliers, a map to the nearest healing shrines and temples, and let them figure the rest out.~
@13642 = ~[PC] So, what are you going to advise them to do?~
@13643 = ~[ARAN] I think it be worth a look.~
@13644 = ~[PC] You are an incurable optimist, aren't you.~
@13645 = ~[PC] Do you have any specific advice you can give them?~
@13646 = ~[ARAN] So, healin' advice, check. Supplies, includin' some decent rope an' mayhap a sack o' four or two, check.~
@13647 = ~[PC] Tell them to prepare for giant spiders, wandering vampiric mists, flesh golems, and random but inevitable death.~
@13648 = ~[PC] I hope they know the difference between a wet mossy rock and a grey ooze.~
@13649 = ~[PC] Burial shrouds. Lots of burial shrouds. Something to haul their broken bodies home.~
@13650 = ~[PC] That sounds appropriate. Having good supplies can make the difference between success and failure.~
@13651 = ~[ARAN] Now, it will be naught in th' way o' bein' so bad, eh? We done survived worse things than most could imagine. Mayhap they will find a nice little cave wi' a good challenge an' a bit o' treasure.~
@13652 = ~[PC] You can always send a second expedition to bring back their dead bodies. If there are any bodies left.~
@13653 = ~[PC] You are right. They have to have better luck than we do...~
@13654 = ~[PC] They are not us.~
@13655 = ~[ARAN] I have some small ideas, but I have made naught in th' way o' a clear decision. Clear a site an' set up for a settlement, or explore somethin' nearby that can wait for a bit. That be a difficult call.~
@13656 = ~[PC] Setting up a camp and a detailed perimeter sounds like a smart idea. Then when they have more of a settlement, they will have a place to retreat to if things go wrong.~
@13657 = ~[PC] Clearing the cave should probably take priority. Is it just a cave, or is it a passage to Underdark? That would make settling there a bit of a challenge.~
@13658 = ~[PC] I think they should find a new site father away from caves and caverns.~
@13659 = ~[PC] They are the ones with the most immediate knowledge. Let them make the decision.~
@13660 = ~[ARAN] Oh, hells no. But they can do it, an' mayhap it will prove to be a new source o' income. Or mayhap a good mine, a good resource for buildin' that tower. It could be anythin'. An old-fashioned adventure.~
@13661 = ~[PC] You sound very excited for them.~
@13662 = ~[PC] I wish them well. I miss those days. Well, except for the running away from packs of wolves and gibberlings. I do not miss that.~
@13663 = ~[PC] It is none of my business. Tell them whatever you want.~
@13664 = ~[PC] Make sure they have an effective cleric or a pile of healing potions. Caves can be tricky.~
@13665 = ~[PC] If it were me, I would tell them to stay at the camp and take up farming. This adventuring business has brought me a great deal of pain.~
@13666 = ~[ARAN] Aye, sure enough. Though... well, I'd best make my own mind up an' send along a message. No point in bein' in charge o' somethin' if I do naught in th' way o' leadin', even if from a fair distance.~
@13667 = ~[ARAN] Cyric's Bleached Bones, all that blighted work for naught.~
@13668 = ~[PC] Your curry was not that bad this time, Aran. In fact, it was pretty good.~
@13669 = ~[PC] You are holding that letter like it was a living thing that you are attempting to strangle.~
@13670 = ~[PC] What is wrong?~
@13671 = ~[PC] Yes. You are still swearing, and your accent is still very strong. All my careful re-training work on you has vanished.~
@13672 = ~[PC] Whatever it is, Aran, we do not have time to deal with it right now.~
@13673 = ~[ARAN] That band o' adventurers what attached themselves to me went ahead into th' cave. An' they found....~
@13674 = ~[ARAN] Naught.~
@13675 = ~[ARAN] Great piles o' grand stinkin' heapin' blighted NOTHIN'.~
@13676 = ~[PC] Well, that was always a possibility. Sometimes a cave is just a cave.~
@13677 = ~[PC] I bet that if it were me, there would have been a band of Orcs. Or a massive inter-planar being with horrible breath and magical weapons.~
@13678 = ~[PC] That is a little disappointing.~
@13679 = ~[PC] They survived!~
@13680 = ~[PC] I am serious. We do not have time to deal with it right now. We need to drop this and move on.~
@13681 = ~[ARAN] WE wander about tryin' to get from here to there an' back all intact, an' are swarmed wi' monsters o' myth an' legend. THEY set out to find adventure, an' find th' start o' a great root cellar.~
@13682 = ~[PC] Aran... have you ever really looked at how different we are from.... ordinary?~
@13683 = ~[PC] Wait a minute. This is good news. No Underdark exits, no tribe of goblins to fight off, and they can excavate the stone to build fortifications and buildings!~
@13684 = ~[PC] I blame the leadership. Particularly your lack of leadership.~
@13685 = ~[PC] This is a distraction. You need to tell them to stick to the business of planning the settlement, and leave the adventuring to us.~
@13686 = ~[PC] Well, that grand "follower" experiment is over, I assume.~
@13687 = ~[ARAN] Serves me blighted right. I have gotten so used to us openin' every door an' bein' attacked that I assume every place is inhabited, filled wi' treasure, an' there for th' discoverin'.~
@13688 = ~[PC] You are travelling with me. They are not.~
@13689 = ~[PC] Aran, how are you getting and sending all these letters and messages? We are not exactly in touch with a reliable network of couriers.~
@13690 = ~[ARAN] Yes, they survived. Gond's Great Gears, they barely broke sweat on a blighted buttock!~
@13691 = ~[ARAN] I spend hours an' days sendin' messages, usin' what precious few sorcerered stones to send supply lists, plans, local mercenary contacts, and authorizin' th' use o' coin to fund th' expedition, and there be naught there but dust, a little spring pool, an' some blighted moss.~
@13692 = ~[PC] "Sorcerered stones"...~
@13693 = ~[PC] Perhaps it is time to let them know that they should stick to building a simple settlement.~
@13694 = ~[ARAN] Aye, I get that th' Prophecies, an' th' Bhaalspawn thing, an' all that mean we are havin' more adventure every day than most would in their entire lives. I just...~
@13695 = ~[PC] ...wanted them to have a successful first adventure?~
@13696 = ~[PC] ...wanted the cave to be filled with ferocious monsters that they could win glory by defeating?~
@13697 = ~[PC] ...wanted to find an abandoned gold mine that could fund a full settlement and set you up for retirement?~
@13698 = ~[PC] ...wanted them to be useful, instead of a large waste of money and time?~
@13699 = ~[PC] ...wasted my time telling me about a bunch of idiots who chose to follow you about playing at being adventurers.~
@13700 = ~[ARAN] Aye, mayhap you have a point there. It could be a right fine storage annex, or mayhap even a vault. An' savin' supplies from th' wear an' tear o' th' weather be a good outcome, I expect.~
@13701 = ~[ARAN] But I were hopin' for more in th' way o' a morale boost for them. It be blighted hard to say 'you done found a wonderful empty hole. Congratulations'.~
@13702 = ~[PC] You might surprise yourself. Even a small success is a great morale booster, if you handle it right. You just need to avoid showing how much you do not like that outcome.~
@13703 = ~[PC] I think you should have them move the settlement site closer to that cavern, and use it.~
@13704 = ~[PC] Not every adventure results on fine gems and expensive magical weapons. I think morale is about what is next, not what is now.~
@13705 = ~[ARAN] An' what be my failure?~
@13706 = ~[PC] Getting upset at a setback. This is not the first time an expedition has ended in failure. Get yourself together.~
@13707 = ~[PC] Not leading from the front. You should have gone there and made sure the job was done right. Of course, you couldn't do that...~
@13708 = ~[PC] Having followers. They tend to disappoint the one they claim to be following.~
@13709 = ~[PC] Lack of decent scouting. Someone should have watched that cave for several weeks before entering. Perhaps even before asking to mount an expedition.~
@13710 = ~[PC] Oh, let me count the many, many ways...~
@13711 = ~[ARAN]  Now, that be right harsh. Not every adventure be a great haul o' lewels an' items. Sometimes just findin' a new safer route, or mayhap some usable rock be a step forward.~
@13712 = ~[ARAN] I got me some pebbles what can be called an' swapped between large spaces. Blighted expensive to use, on account o' the time spent on th' other end by th' mage or sorceror callin' th' stone, but it can bring along a sheet o' vellum all wrapped up tight an' sealed. Naught in th' way o' more, but it works passably to get th' stones to swap places.~
@13713 = ~[ARAN] From there, th' courier network takes it on right fine. How in th' hells else would I be able to get an' receive messages in some o' th' places we have been?~
@13714 = ~[PC] I.... had never though about that.~
@13715 = ~[PC] Perhaps it is time to let your followers know that they should stick to building a simple settlement.~
@13716 = ~[PC] Transferring messages via magical displacement of pebbles, followed by a courier system. Oh, let me count the many, many ways that could go wrong...~
@13717 = ~[PC] Well, I am sorry that your first big independent expedition ended in failure.~
@13718 = ~[PC] Well, I am sorry that you do not see how much they have accomplished on your behalf.~
@13719 = ~[ARAN] Hells. I just be disappointed, is all. But I did see somethin' in one o' those sets o' notes I picked up a ways back... hmmm...~
@13720 = ~[ARAN] Swordcoastswordcoastswordcoast... err, no, that be naught.... lookin' for th' coastal region, not inland... ~
@13721 = ~[ARAN] Mayhap... yes. There be an abandoned tower only two days travel up th' coast. Right here. Mayhap they will have better luck there. Now, to send off some sort o' plan...~
